Tuti Indra Malaon ( 1 December 1939 -- 20 September 1989 ) , born Pudjiastuti Suratno , was an Indonesian actress , dancer , and lecturer .
Karl Wilhelm Ohnesorge ( 8 June 1872 -- 1 February 1962 ) was a German politician in the Third Reich who sat in Hitler 's cabinet .
Reino Ala - Kulju ( 25 April 1898 , Kuortane - 5 August 1983 ) was a Finnish Lutheran clergyman , secondary school teacher and politician .
Gradinja ( fl . 1125 - -1146 ) was the King of Duklja , from either 1131 to 1142 or 1135 to 1146 .
Bernard Henry McGinn ( c. 1957 -- body discovered 21 December 2013 ) was a Provisional Irish Republican Army ( PIRA ) member , specialising in explosives , who was sentenced to a total of 490 years imprisonment in 1999 .
Richard de Prebenda ( died 1210 ) was an early 13th - century bishop of Dunkeld .
Ingierd Gunnarsdotter ( 1601 - -1686 ) was a Swedish peasant wife and ballad singer from Lyrestad parish in Västergötland .
Ronald Walter Mackelworth ( 7 April 1930 -- 15 January 2000 ) was an English insurance salesman and science fiction author active as a writer in the late 1960s and early 1970s , who wrote as R. W. Mackelworth , an abbreviated form of his name .
Charles Hylton Stewart ( 21 March 1884 - -14 November 1932 ) was an English cathedral organist , who served in Rochester Cathedral and St. George 's Chapel , Windsor Castle .
Arthur Louis ( 21 June 1945 -- 24 December 2014 ) was a rock , blues and reggae cross - over musician .
Isidor Seiss died by his own hand in Cologne in 1905 , having suffered increasing blindness that had forced him to retire from his teaching position .
Marmaduke Gwynne ( 1691 - -1769 ) was a descendant of the Gwynne family of Glanbrân near Llandovery and an early and influential Methodist convert .
Joseph Frans Lescrauwaet , M.S.C. ( 19 June 1923 -- 19 November 2013 ) was a Dutch prelate of the Roman Catholic Church .
Major - General Christoph August von Wangenheim ( 23 March 1741 in Hanover -- 23 June 1830 in Hanover ) was a German Hanoverian army officer and court official .
Duncan Brown Cooper ( 1844 - 1922 ) was an American journalist , publisher and Democratic politician .
Jane Brotherton Walker ( 1925 - 2009 ) was a leading 20th century expert in the field of tick taxonomy , particularly in Africa .
Bartley Fahey ( 15 October 1836 -- 9 August 1920 ) was member of the Queensland Legislative Council .
Paul Sciacca ( pronounced `` SHAH - kah '' ) ( June 15 , 1909 -- August 1986 ) was a New York City mobster who became boss of the Bonanno crime family .
Tadashi Yanada ( 梁田貞 ; 1883 - -1959 ) was a Japanese composer .
Regin Prenter ( 6 November 1907 Frederikssund -- 15 December 1990 ) was a Danish Lutheran priest and theologian .
Tyrone Gilks ( 11 December 1993 -- 21 March 2013 ) was an Australian motorbike personality , known for his world record distance jumping and freestyle motorcross riding .
Liang Xiang ( Chinese : 梁湘 ; pinyin : Liáng Xiāng ; 1919 -- 13 December 1998 ) was a politician of the People 's Republic of China .
Ostasio III da Polenta ( died 1447 ) was the last lord of Ravenna of the da Polenta family .
William Broadbent Luddington ( March 1843 - -November 1888 ) was a Primitive Methodist missionary who went to the island of Fernando Po ( today Bioko in Equatorial Guinea ) in about 1880 .
The Reverend Pierre Jacques Smit ( 1863 - -1960 ) , who often signed his works Peter Smit , Peter J. Smit , or P.J. Smit , was a natural history illustrator of the Victorian era in England .
Ralph Winterton ( 1600 - -1636 ) was an English physician , academic and humanist .
Friedrich Wilhelm Sander ( August 25 , 1885 , Glatz ( Kłodzko ) -- September 15 , 1938 ) was a German pyrotechnics engineer and manufacturer remembered for his contributions to rocket - powered flight .
Arthur Crowther ( 1 August 1878 -- 4 June 1946 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played one match for Yorkshire County Cricket Club in 1905 , against Warwickshire at Dewsbury .
Mário Lemos Pires ( 30 June 1930 -- 22 May 2009 ) was a Major - general of the Portuguese Army and the last colonial governor of Portuguese Timor .
Lawrence Bogorad ( 1921 - - 28 December 2003 ) was an American botanist , pioneer of photosynthesis research and President of the American Association for the Advancement of Science .
Léon - Paul Classe ( 28 June 1874 -- 31 January 1945 ) was a Catholic priest who was Vicar Apostolic of the Apostolic Vicariate of Ruanda , in what is now Rwanda , from 1922 until his death in 1945 .
George Kingsmill ( 1808 - -1852 ) was the High Constable of Toronto in 1835 and from 1837 to 1846 .
P. R. Ramaiya ( 1894 - -1970 ) was the founder of Tainadu , the premier Kannada Newspaper of the Indian state of Mysore during the freedom movement .
Andrea Pininfarina ( 26 June 1957 -- 7 August 2008 ) was an Italian engineer and manager , former CEO of the Italian coachbuilder Pininfarina , founded by his grandfather Battista `` Pinin '' Farina in 1930 and still controlled by the family .
Vasili Postnov ( Russian : Василий Постнов ; 24 March 1962 -- 4 March 2009 ) was a Tajikistani professional footballer .
Matthew Noble ( 23 March 1817 -- 23 June 1876 ) was a leading British portrait sculptor .
Robert Darcy , 4th Earl of Holderness PC ( 17 May 1718 -- 16 May 1778 ) , known before 1721 as Lord Darcy and Conyers , was a British diplomat and politician .
Albert Étienne Jean Baptiste Terrien de Lacouperie ( 23 November 1844 , Ingouville , Le Havre-11 October 1894 , London ) was a French orientalist , specialising in comparative philology .
Ågot Gjems Selmer , also Ågot Gjems - Selmer , ( 1858 - -1926 ) was a Norwegian actress , writer , and lecturer .
Félix Morisseau - Leroy ( 13 March 1912 -- 5 September 1998 ) , was a Haitian writer who wrote in Haitian Creole for poetry and plays , the first significant writer to do so .
Qahtaba ibn Shabib al - Ta'i ( died 27 August 749 ) was a follower of the Abbasids from Khurasan who played a leading role in the Abbasid Revolution against the Ummayad Caliphate .
Reginald Grey , 5th Earl of Kent ( before 1541 -- 17 March 1573 ) was an English peer .
Riccardo Ajmone - Marsan ( 1889 - 1958 ) was an Italian footballer who played for Juventus .
Gordon Benjamin Isnor ( 10 May 1885 -- 17 March 1973 ) was a Canadian merchant and parliamentarian .
Per Eberhard Cogell ( b. 1734 Stockholm - d. 21 January 1812 in Lyon ) was a Swedish artist who is one of these Swedish artists who were attracted by France throughout the eighteenth century .
Charles - Paul Marin de la Malgue , ( 1633 -- 14 April 1713 ) , was an officer in the colonial regular troops .
John Longland ( died 1547 ) was the English Dean of Salisbury from 1514 to 1521 and bishop of Lincoln from 1521 to his death in 1547 .
Christian III , Count Palatine of Zweibrücken - Birkenfeld ( Strassburg , 7 November 1674 -- Zweibrücken , 3 February 1735 ) was a German nobleman .
Toma Ciorbă ( January 15 , 1864 - -December 30 , 1936 ) was a Bessarabian - born Romanian physician and hospital director .
Christopher James Hardman ( 26 August 1990 -- 23 March 2015 ) , known by the stage name Lil ' Chris , was an English singer - songwriter , actor , and television personality .
Ernest Vincent ( 28 October 1910 -- 2 June 1978 ) was an English footballer .
Jens Henrik Nordlie ( 18 January 1910 -- 2 April 1996 ) was a Norwegian military officer , resistance fighter from World War II and businessperson .
Lt - Col . Samuel Hall - Thompson ( 1885 -- 26 October 1954 ) was a Unionist politician from Northern Ireland .
Melbourne Inman ( 15 July 1878 - 11 August 1951 ) was the World Billiards Champion in 1908 , 1909 , 1912 , 1913 , 1914 and 1919 .
Mansfield Parkyns ( 16 February 1823 -- 12 January 1894 ) was a British traveller , known for his travel book Life in Abyssinia : being notes collected during three years ' residence and travels in that country ( 1853 ) .
John M. Feehan ( 8 September 1916 -- 25 May 1991 ) was an Irish author and publisher .
Major Harold Berridge CIE OBE ( 1872 -- 17 June 1949 ) was a British civil engineer and mechanical engineer .
The Honourable ( Ralph ) Edward Gathorne - Hardy ( 4 June 1901 -- 18 June 1978 ) was a British Bohemian socialite .
Manuel Francisco dos Santos ( 28 October 1933 -- 20 January 1983 ) , known by the nickname Garrincha ( Portuguese pronunciation : ( ɡaˈʁĩʃɐ ) , `` little bird '' ) , was a Brazilian footballer who played right winger and forward .
José Eusebio de Llano Zapata ( 1721 - -1780 ) was a Peruvian scholar , writer and scientist .
Muslim Mulliqi ( 1934 -- 13 January 1998 ) was an impressionist and expressionist painter of Kosovo .
William Shainline Middleton , M.D. , M.A.C.P. ( 7 January 1890 - 9 September 1975 ) was a prestigious American internist and military physician .
William Petre , 4th Baron Petre ( 1626 -- 5 January 1684 ) was an English peer , a victim of the Popish Plot .
André Gorz ( 9 February 1923 -- 22 September 2007 ) , pen name of Gérard Horst , born Gerhart Hirsch , also known by his pen name Michel Bosquet , was a social philosopher .
Tarjei Rygnestad ( 26 July 1954 -- 2 February 2013 ) was a Norwegian physician .
Brad Newman ( born Charles Melvyn Thomas in Wakefield , West Yorkshire , England , 6 December 1938 , died in Spain on 18 January 1999 ) was an English singer - songwriter and pianist who , in 1962 , reached number 47 in the UK Singles Chart with the song `` Somebody to Love '' .
Nina Fishman ( 26 May 1946 -- 5 December 2009 ) was an American - born English labour movement historian and political activist .
Ralph the Staller ( or Radulf stalre ) ( c. 1011 - -1068 ) was a landowner in both Anglo - Saxon and post - Conquest England .
Alberto Prosdocimi ( September 9 , 1852 - 1925 ) was an Italian painter and manuscript illuminator .
Johnnie Lee Wills ( September 2 , 1912 - -October 25 , 1984 ) was an American Western swing fiddler popular in the 1930s and 1940s .
Georges Beuchat ( 1910 - -1992 ) was a French inventor , diver , businessman and emblematic pioneer of underwater activities and founder of Beuchat .
Il Sodoma ( 1477 -- February 14 , 1549 ) was the name given to the Italian Renaissance painter Giovanni Antonio Bazzi .
Mufarrij ibn Daghfal ibn al - Jarrah al - Tayyi ( fl . ca . 977 - -1013 ) , in some sources erroneously called Daghfal ibn Mufarrij , was an emir of the Jarrahid family and leader of the Tayy tribe .
Peter Magaddino ( February 25 , 1917 - August 1976 ) was a mobster in the Magaddino crime family of Buffalo , New York .
Filippos Margaritis ( 1810 - -1892 ) is generally acknowledged to have been the first Greek photographer , whose earliest daguerreotypes , of the Acropolis of Athens , date from 1847 .
Daphney Hlomuka ( 1949 -- 1 October 2008 ) was a South African television , film , radio and stage actress .
Ephraim Snow or Old Snow ( fl . 1850 - 1865 ) was an American criminal fence and underworld figure on New York City during the early - to mid-19th century .
Vadims Ulbergs ( 17 July 1921 -- 11 July 2008 ) was a Latvian football player and manager , one of the most respected veterans of Latvian football .
Louis Tracy ( 1863 - 1928 ) was a British journalist , and prolific writer of fiction .
Valdemar Rudolph von Raasløff ( 6 November 1815 in Altona -- 14 February 1883 in Paris ) was a Danish politician , military officer and diplomat .
William Culbertson III ( November 18 , 1905 -- November 16 , 1971 ) was as an American pastor , bishop of the Reformed Episcopal Church , and the fifth president of the Moody Bible Institute , in Chicago , Illinois .
Henry Ronald Godfrey ( 1887 - -1968 ) , was an early English motor car design engineer .
Victor Hugo Green ( November 9 , 1892 - 1960 ) was an African American postal employee from Harlem , New York City , best known for developing and writing what became known as The Green Book , a travel guide for African Americans in the United States .
John East ( died 1856 ) was a 19th - century Anglican clergyman and writer .
Japie Laubscher ( 1919 - -1981 ) was a concertina player for Boeremusiek in South Africa .
Werner Stark ( 2 December 1909 -- 4 October 1985 ) was a sociologist and economist , who made important contributions to the sociology of knowledge , the sociology of religion , and the history of economic thought .
Louis Charbonnier ( 9 October 1754 -- 2 June 1833 ) was a general of mediocre talent who commanded a French army for several months during the French Revolutionary Wars .
David Kirkaldy ( 1820 - -1897 ) was a Scottish engineer who pioneered the testing of materials as a service to engineers during the Victorian period .
John Lauchlan Farris , Q.C. , ( 1911 - -1986 ) was a Canadian lawyer and judge .
Domingo Vandewalle ( also Domingo Van de Walle de Cervellón , Don Domingo Vandeval ) ( 1720 Santa Cruz de La Palma - 1776 , Santa Cruz ) was a Spanish explorer and military commander of Las Palmas in the Canary Islands .
Lef Nosi was brought to trial in February 1946 , led by general prosecutor Misto Treska .
On January 22 , 1554 Henry Isley attended a meeting of thirty key conspirators at Wyatt 's Allington Castle .
Bhalchandra Pandharinath Bahirat ( Marathi : भालचंद़ पंढरीनाथ बहिरट , 5 September 1904 -- 14 October 1998 ) was a philosopher and educationist who studied the Marathi literature of Jñāneśvar and other sants of Maharashtra .
Heinrich Isaac ( c. 1450 -- 26 March 1517 ) was a Netherlandish Renaissance composer of south Netherlandish origin .
Arnold Buntine ( 27 December 1898 -- 26 February 1975 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Dame Alice Wedega , DBE ( 20 August 1905 in Ahioma , Milne Bay , Papua New Guinea -- 3 December 1987 ) was a Papuan politician , educator , peacemaker and conscientious objector .
Malcolm Ross Bow ( 13 July 1887 -- 5 July 1982 ) was a Canadian medical doctor and public health officer .
Dong Zhuo ( died 22 May 192 ) , courtesy name Zhongying , was a politician and warlord who lived in the late Eastern Han Dynasty .
Richard Caddick ( 1740 - -1819 ) was an English Hebraist .
Blessed Robert Grissold ( died 1604 ) was an accomplice of John Sugar , Roman Catholic priest co - martyred at Warwick in 1604 .
Giovanni Battista Fiammeri ( c. 1530 -- 1606 ) was an Italian painter and Jesuit priest , active in Florence .
Jevto Dedijer ( Serbian Cyrillic : Јевто Дедијер ; 15 August 1880 - 24 December 1918 ) was a Bosnian Serb writer and geographer from the Maleševci clan who was influential in the formation of the Serb Academy .
Dušan Mitević ( Serbian Cyrillic : Душан Митевић ; 3 February 1938,Pljevlja , Kingdom of Yugoslavia -- 31 May 2003 , Belgrade , Serbia and Montenegro ) was a Serbian journalist .
Golding Bird ( 9 December 1814 -- 27 October 1854 ) was a British medical doctor and a Fellow of the Royal College of Physicians .
Carola Richards ( 1916 - -2004 ) was an English artist and member of the Eastbourne Group .
Simon Ardé ( also Simon Ardi , Symon van Antwerpen and nickname Tovenaer ) ( probably Antwerp , 1594 - Rome , 1638 ) was a Flemish Baroque painter who was active in Italy for most part of his life .
Ardgal mac Conaill ( died 520 ) was a King of Uisnech in Mide of the Ui Neill dynasty .
Augusts Vilis Abakuks ( December 12 , 1914 -- February 13 , 1994 ) was a Latvian government official and émigré activist .
Dorothy Ann Collins , known as Dolly Collins ( 6 March 1933 -- 22 September 1995 ) , was an English folk musician , arranger and composer .
Moses Ashley Curtis ( 11 May 1808 -- 10 April 1872 ) was a noted American botanist .
Egnech ( died 915 ) was an Abbot of Aran .
Savelii Yakovlevich Mitelman ( Russian : Савелий Яковлевич Мительман ) ; ( 3 January 1940 -- 21 December 2004 ) was a Russian painter .
Max Wall ( 12 March 1908 -- 21 May 1990 ) , was an English comedian and actor , whose performing career covered music hall , theatre , films and television .
Jacques Loeillet ( 1685 - -1748 ) was a Baroque - era composer and oboist .
Gwen Nelson ( 30 June 1901 -- 15 October 1990 ) was an English actress who was a member of the Royal Shakespeare Company and the Royal Court Theatre Company .
Johann Bernhard Logier ( 9 February 1777 -- 13 February 1846 ) was a German composer , teacher , inventor , and publisher resident in Ireland for most of his life .
William Maynard , 1st Baron Maynard ( c. 1589 - -1640 ) was an English politician .
Charles Georges Javet ( 1802 , Winterthur , Kanton Zürich -- 25 May 1882 , Passy , Paris ) was a Swiss - born French insect dealer and entomologist .
Zeng Jiongzhi ( Chinese : 曾炯之 ; pinyin : Zēng Jiǒngzhī ; Wade -- Giles : Tseng Chiung - chih , April 2 , 1898 -- November 1940 ) , also rendered as Chiungtze C. Tsen in English , was a Chinese mathematician born in Nanchang , Jiangxi , who proved Tsen 's theorem .
Karl - Erik Hult ( 1936 -- 11 May 2010 ) was a Swedish football player and manager .
Alexander Fussell or Fussel ( b. circa 1814 , Warwickshire ; d. 1881 ) was an English artist and illustrator .
James Abree ( 1691?--1768 ) was an 18th - century Canterbury printer , publisher , and bookseller .
Jean - André Cuoq ( 1821 - -1898 ) was a Roman Catholic priest and a philologist in the Algonquin and Mohawk languages .
Shangguan Yi ( Chinese : 上官儀 ; 608 -- 4 January 665 ) , courtesy name Youshao ( 游韶 ) , formally Duke of Chu ( 楚公 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as chancellor during the reign of Emperor Gaozong .
Kurt Gustav Wilckens ( 1886 - 1923 ) was a militant German anarchist , known in Argentina for having avenged the massacre of hundreds of workers on strike in the repression unleashed by the Argentine government in response to the prolonged labor uprising later known as Patagonia rebelde - the Patagonia uprising .
Edward Moore , 5th Earl of Drogheda PC ( I ) ( 1701 - 28 October 1758 ) was an Anglo - Irish peer and politician .
József Schweidel ( 18 May 1796 , Zombor ( Serbian : Sombor ) - 6 October 1849 , Arad ) was a honvéd general in the Hungarian Army .
Blessed Robert Ludlam ( c. 1551 -- 24 July 1588 ) was an English priest , martyred in the reign of Queen Elizabeth I. He was born around 1551 , in Derbyshire .
Justo Boneo y Morales was a soldier and knight of the Order of Santiago who served as governor of Texas between 1743 - -1744 .
Nicolas Josef Eugene Holl ( 10 December 1855 , Provins - c. 1919 ) was a French entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera .
Emperor Ming of Northern Zhou ( ( 北)周明帝 ) ( 534 - -560 ) , personal name Yuwen Yu ( 宇文毓 ) , nickname Tongwantu ( 統萬突 ) , was an emperor of the Xianbei dynasty Northern Zhou , although at the start of his reign he used the alternative title `` Heavenly Prince '' ( Tian Wang ) .
Sir Alexander Boswell , 1st Baronet FRSE FSA ( 9 October 1775 -- 27 March 1822 ) was a Scottish poet , antiquary and song writer .
Glyn Worsnip ( 2 September 1938 -- 7 June 1996 ) was a British radio and television presenter .
George Hogarth ( 6 September 1783 -- 12 February 1870 ) eldest son of Robert Hogarth , a farmer , and his wife , Mary Scott , was a Scottish newspaper editor , music critic , and musicologist .
Leonard Humphrey Razzall , known as Humphrey Razzall ( 13 November 1912 -- 26 October 1999 ) , was a British Liberal Party politician and solicitor .
Cyril Snipe ( 1888 - 1944 ) was a British motor racing driver who won the 1912 Targa Florio in Sicily driving an Italian SCAT motor car .
John Stockwood ( died 1610 ) was an English clergyman , preacher , translator of Protestant texts and school - master .
Gilbert Dennison Harris , Ph . B. ( 1864 - -1952 ) was an American geologist .
David Caradoc Evans ( 31 December 1878 -- 11 January 1945 ) , was a Welsh story writer , novelist and playwright .
Daniel Costigan ( 1911 - -1979 ) was Commissioner of the Garda Síochána from July 1952 until February 1965 .
Anna Synodinou ( Greek : Άννα Συνοδινού ; 21 November 1927 -- 7 January 2016 ) was a Greek actress and politician .
Whitney Halstead ( 1926 - 1979 ) was an American art historian , and artist .
Elisabeth Freund ( 1898 - -1982 ) was a German - Jewish immigrant who left Germany in the 1930s , finally immigrating to the US in 1941 .
Frederick William Bissett ( 1902 - 1978 ) was a Justice of the Supreme Court of Nova Scotia , Canada and is known for having previously represented Viola Desmond during his career as a lawyer .
Motiram Lahane ( 1922 - 11 March 2005 ) was a member of Rajya Sabha from Maharashtra state during the term 14 December 1978 to 2 April 1980 as Janata Party candidate .
Joe Seliga ( 11 April 1911 -- 18 December 2005 ) was a master builder of wood - and - canvas canoes in Ely , Minnesota .
Néstor Martín - Fernández de la Torre , generally known simply as Néstor ( 4 May 1887 , Las Palmas - 6 February 1938 , Las Palmas ) was a Canarian painter and theatrical designer who worked in the Symbolist and Art Deco styles .
The Reverend Henry Hawkins Tremayne ( 1741 -- 1829 ) was a member of a landed family in the English county of Cornwall , and owner of the Heligan estate near Mevagissey , with significant interests in the Cornish tin mining industry .
Adam August Müller ( 1811 - -1844 ) , a Danish history painter , was one of Eckersberg 's favourite students .
George Champagne MA ( ca 1751 - 26 October 1828 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1802 - 1828
Lieutenant - General Sir John Bruce Hope , 7th Baronet ( c. 1684 -- 5 June 1766 ) was a Scottish soldier and politician .
Gernot Reinstadler ( 1 January 1970 -- 19 January 1991 ) was an Austrian ski racer .
Israel Mauduit ( 1708 -- 14 June 1787 ) was a British merchant , writer and colonial agent .
Charles March - Phillipps ( 28 May 1779 -- 24 April 1862 ) was a British Whig politician from Garendon Park in Leicestershire .
Noel Ellis ( 9 July 1921 -- 6 July 1942 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League .
Tilly Fleischmann ( 2 April 1882 -- 17 October 1967 ) was an Irish pianist , organist , pedagogue and writer of German descent .
William Mylne ( 1734 - -1790 ) was a Scottish architect and engineer .
Jan Siberechts ( 1627 - -1703 ) was a Flemish landscape painter who after a successful career in Antwerp , emigrated in the latter part of his life to England where his topographical views stand at the beginning of the English landscape tradition .
Meir Max Bineth ( Max Bennett ) ( 27 June 1917 -- 21 December 1954 ) was a Lieutenant Colonel in the Israeli Intelligence .
Marvin Koner ( 1921 - 1983 ) was an American photographer who became known for his photographs of Johnny Cash and Miles Davis which he published in Pageant and other magazines .
Thomas Roger Smith ( 1830 - -1903 ) was an English architect and academic .
Guillaume Vandive ( 1680 - -1706 ) , Printer and ordinary bookseller of Monseigneur the Dauphin .
Richard Morrell Staigg ( 7 September 1817 Leeds , England - 11 October 1881 Newport , Rhode Island ) or R.M. Staigg was a portrait painter in Boston , Massachusetts , in the 19th century .
Jonathan Couch ( 15 March 1789 -- 13 April 1870 ) was a British naturalist , the only child of Richard and Philippa Couch , of a family long resident at Polperro , a small fishing village between Looe and Fowey , on the south coast of Cornwall .
Al - Zuhri was able to use the writings of the geographers of the reign of Caliph Al - Ma'mun of Baghdad ( d. 456/1068 ) Al - Zuhri died between 1154 and 1161 .
Richard Northalis ( died 20 July 1397 ) was an Irish cleric and judge who held the offices of Bishop of Ossory , Archbishop of Dublin and Lord Chancellor of Ireland ; for the last decade of his life he was one of the English Crown 's most trusted advisers .
Sisebut ( Latin : Sisebutus , Spanish : Sisebuto ; also Sisebuth , Sisebur , Sisebod or Sigebut ) ( c. 565 -- February 621 ) was King of the Visigoths and ruler of Hispania , Septimania and Galicia from 612 until his death .
Indrechtach mac Lethlobair ( died 741 ) was a Dal nAraide king of the Cruithne in Ulaid ( Ulster ) .
Rolf Semb - Thorstvedt ( 3 April 1898 -- 15 October 1972 ) was a Norwegian football player for the club SK Frigg .
Bevil Skelton ( 1641 - -1696 ) was a British foreign envoy and diplomat .
Eliezer Smoli ( Hebrew : אליעזר שמאלי ) ( born 1901 ; died 1985 ) was an Israeli writer , famous for his children 's books .
Odd Strand ( 21 August 1925 -- 18 May 2008 ) was a Norwegian civil servant .
Dr Ralph Tatham ( bap . 1778 - -1857 ) was an English academic and churchman .
Saint Dorothea of Alexandria ( died c. 320 ) is venerated as a virgin martyr .
Herschel Lynn Greer ( 1906 - -March 19 , 1976 ) was a prominent businessman and the first president of Vols , Inc. , an ownership group organized in 1959 for the purpose of keeping the Nashville Vols minor league baseball franchise in Nashville , Tennessee .
Manuel Mendes ( or Manoel Mendes ; c. 1547 -- 24 September 1605 ) was a Portuguese composer and teacher of the Renaissance .
Lauri Soininen was born : 1 April 1875 in Pielavesi and died in Helsinki on 2 September 1919 .
Amelia Griffiths ( 1768 - -1858 ) , often referred to in contemporary works as Mrs Griffiths of Torquay , was a beachcomber and amateur phycologist who made many important collections of algae specimens .
Kevin Wilkinson ( 11 June 1958 -- 17 July 1999 ) was an English drummer , who was based in Swindon , Wiltshire , England .
Mathias Hagerup ( 1765 - -1822 ) was a Norwegian director general in Stockholm 1814 - -1822 , and acting state secretary to the Council of State Division in Stockholm and acting councillor of state in 1822 .
Walter Froucester ( died 1412 ) , was abbot of St. Peter 's , Gloucester .
George Canning , 1st Baron Garvagh FRS ( 15 November 1778 -- 20 August 1840 ) was an Anglo - Irish Member of Parliament .
Colonel Hoshiar Singh Dahiya , PVC ( 5 May 1937 -- 6 December 1998 ) was born in a Hindu Jat family in Sisana village , Sonipat district , Haryana to Choudhary Hira Singh .
John Honyman ( 1613 -- April 1636 ) , also Honeyman , Honiman , Honnyman , or other variants , was an English actor of the Caroline era .
Hemendra Mohan Bose ( Bengali : হেমেন্দ্রমোহন বসু ) ( 1864 -- 28 August 1916 ) was an Indian entrepreneur , manufacturer of Kuntalin hair oil and Delkhosh brand of perfume .
Lawrence Fernandes ( 1932 - 14 November 2005 ) was a socialist political leader from India .
Syed Nausher Ali ( 1891 - -1972 ) was a prominent left - leaning politician in West and East Bengal ( now India and Bangladesh ) during the British rule .
Sir ( William ) Keith Hancock KBE ( 26 June 1898 -- 13 August 1988 ) was Australia 's `` most distinguished historian '' .
Martin Joyce ( 24 January 1900 -- q1 1960 ) was an English footballer who made 181 appearances in the Football League playing for Darlington and Durham City .
Frederick Leigh Gardner ( 1857 - -1930 ) was a British occultist and member of various initiatory orders , among them the Hermetic Order of the Golden Dawn .
Mark Lundberg ( 25 March 1958 -- 15 August 2008 ) was an American opera singer who had an active international career from the 1980s up until his sudden death in 2008 .
Helen Adelia Rowe Metcalf ( 1830 - 1895 ) was a founder and director of the Rhode Island School of Design ( RISD ) in Providence , Rhode Island .
Pundit Ganga Prasad Upadhyaya ( 1871 - 1968 ) was an Arya Samaji writer .
Lieutenant - Colonel William Boynton ( 14 July 1641 -- 17 August 1689 ) was an English Member of Parliament .
Count Pyotr Aleksandrovich Tolstoy ( Russian : Пётр Александрович Толстой ) ( 1769 -- 28 September 1844 ) was a Russian general and statesman .
Edmund P. Murray ( July 1930 -- October 2007 ) is an American novelist and journalist .
Siva Prasad Barooah ( Assamese : শিৱ প্ৰসাদ বৰুৱা ) ( 1880 - -1938 ) was a renowned planter , philanthropist , politician , and humanist from Assam .
Luagalau Levaula Kamu ( died 16 July 1999 ) was a lawyer and Minister of Public Works in Samoa , whose assassination shocked the Samoan and Pacific Islands community .
Benjamin Hall Kennedy ( 6 November 1804 -- 6 April 1889 ) was an English scholar and schoolmaster , known for his work in the teaching of the Latin language .
Manuel Victoria ( ☩ 1833 ) was governor of the Mexican - ruled territory of Alta California from January 1831 to December 6 , 1831 .
Božena ( Křesinová ) ( died after 1052 ) was the second wife ( and probably earlier the mistress ) of Duke Oldřich of Bohemia and mother of Bretislaus I of Bohemia .
Katharina Pepijn or Catharina Pepijn ( baptized on 13 February 1619 , Antwerp - 12 November 1688 , Antwerp ) was a Flemish painter who was known for her history and portrait paintings .
Mohammad Taghi Rouhani Moghaddam ( Persian : ‌تقی روحانی‎‎ , 26 July 1920 -- 25 June 2013 ) commonly known as Taghi Rouhani was an Iranian radio news anchor .
Otto Moritz Walter Model ( German pronunciation : ( ˈmoːdəl ) ; 24 January 1891 -- 21 April 1945 ) was a German field marshal during World War II . He is noted for his defensive battles in the latter half of the war , mostly on the Eastern Front but also in the west .
Thomas Emlyn ( 1663 - -1741 ) was an English nonconformist divine .
Vlado Dijak ( 1925 in Brezovo Polje , Brčko District , Kingdom of Yugoslavia -- 1988 in Sarajevo , Bosnia and Herzegovina , SFR Yugoslavia ) was known a former Yugoslav poet and songwriter .
Steve Whitaker ( 26 June 1955 -- 22 February 2008 ) was a British artist best known as the colourist on the reprint of V for Vendetta .
Charles L. Frink ( February 16 , 1849 -- January 1937 ) was an American politician who served as the eighth Mayor of North Adams , Massachusetts .
Mary Rozet Smith ( 1868 - 1934 ) was a Chicago - born US philanthropist who was one of the trustees and benefactors of Hull House .
Liu Heita ( 劉黑闥 ) ( died 623 ) was an agrarian rebel leader during China 's transition period from Sui Dynasty to Tang Dynasty , who initially successively served under Hao Xiaode ( 郝孝德 ) , Li Mi , and Wang Shichong .
Emily D. West ( c.1815 - -1891 ) , also known as Emily Morgan , is a folk heroine whose legendary activities during the Texas Revolution have come to be identified with the song `` The Yellow Rose of Texas '' .
Frederick Atwood Greeley ( 26 November 1896 in Pelham , New Hampshire -- 19 March 1980 in Laguna Hills , California ) was an American astronomer who worked on the solar constant program of the Smithsonian Astrophysical Observatory ( SAO ) , which had been started by Samuel Pierpont Langley .
Steinar Schjøtt ( 13 November 1844 -- 11 January 1920 ) was a Norwegian educator , philologist and lexicographer .
Reginald Spofforth ( 1769 ( baptised 12 September ) - 8 September 1827 ) was an English musician .
Edmund Trzcinski ( 2 January 1921 -- 3 June 1996 ) was an American playwright who was born in The Bronx , New York City , New York and died in Manhattan .
Giani Gurmukh Singh Musafir ( 15 January 1899 -- 18 January 1976 ) was an Indian politician and Punjabi writer .
Yakup Kulmiy ( Russian : Якуб Кулмый ; Bashkir : Яҡуп Ҡолмой ; 7 September 1918 , village of Kanakbaevo , Bashkortostan -- 11 October 1994 , village of Kanakaevo ) was a Bashkir poet working under the pen name of Yakup Khairullovich Kulmukhametov .
Vishuddhananda Paramahansa ( Bengali : : Bishuddhananda Pôromôhongśo ) ( 14 March 1853 -- 14 July 1937 ) popularly known as Gandha Baba ( The perfume saint ) was an Indian yogi .
Romée de Villeneuve ( c. 1170 - c. 1250 ) was a Constable and Seneschal of Provence .
Edgar A. Wedgewood ( 2 May 1856 -- 31 January 1920 ) was a General in the United States army during World War I. Wedgewood joined the United States military at the outbreak of the Spanish American War .
Milovan `` Minimaks '' Ilić ( Serbian : Милован Илић Минимакс ; 5 November 1938 -- 9 February 2005 ) was a Serbian radio and television host .
Svetislav Glišović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Светислав Глишовић ; 17 September 1913 -- 10 March 1988 ) , was a Serbian international football player and manager .
Richard Smirke ( 1778 - -1815 ) was an English antiquarian draughtsman .
Gordon Klatt , M.D. ( 1942 - 2014 ) was a practicing surgeon in Tacoma , Washington , and the founder of the American Cancer Society 's Relay For Life .
Norman Arthur Wakefield ( 28 November 1918 -- 23 September 1972 ) was an Australian teacher , naturalist , paleontologist and botanist , notable as an expert on ferns .
Joachim Rouault ( died 1478 ) , French soldier , was a member of an old family of Poitou .
Maria Charlotta Cedercreutz , married surname Wrangel ( 1736 - -1815 ) , was a Swedish artist , lady - in - waiting and baroness .
Christopher Billopp ( c.1738 -- March 29 , 1827 ) was a British loyalist during the American Revolution who commanded a Tory detachment during the war , earning him the sobriquet , `` Tory Colonel '' .
Kathleen Basford ( 6 September 1916 -- 20 December 1998 ) was a British botanist , with a special interest in genetics .
Edgar Lubbock LLB ( 22 February 1847 -- 9 September 1907 ) was an English amateur footballer who twice won the FA Cup , and later became a partner in the Whitbread Brewery , a Director and Deputy Governor of the Bank of England and the Master of the Blankney Foxhounds .
William Luscombe Searelle ( 1853 -- 18 December 1907 ) was a musical composer and impresario .
Duan Dechang ( Chinese : 段德昌 ; August 19 , 1904 -- May 1 , 1933 ) was a member of the Chinese Workers ' and Peasants ' Red Army .
Liu Bingzhong ( Chinese : 劉秉忠 ; 1216 - -1274 ) , or Liu Kan ( Chinese : 劉侃 ) was a Yuan dynasty court adviser and architect .
Astrid Njalsdotter ( or Ástríðr Njálsdóttir ) of Skjalgaätten ( also Aestrith ) ( died 1060 ) , according to an unsubstantiated legend in the Hervarar saga ok Heiðreks , may have been a Norwegian - born Swedish queen .
Jim Howe ( 7 November 1895 -- 28 December 1958 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Brooke Evans ( 1797 - -1862 ) , was well known as an English nickel refiner , weapons manufacturer and geologist .
Jacquetta Hawkes ( 5 August 1910 -- 18 March 1996 ) was a British archaeologist and writer .
Standish Backus , Jr. ( 1910 - -1989 ) was a United States military artist .
Grand Duke Michael Mikhailovich of Russia ( Russian : Михаил Михайлович ; 16 October 1861 -- 26 April 1929 ) was a son of Grand Duke Michael Nicolaievich of Russia and a grandson of Tsar Nicholas I of Russia .
Shanta Apte ( 1916 - 1964 ) was an Indian singer - actress who worked in Marathi and Hindi cinema .
James B. Hume ( January 23 , 1827 - -May 18 , 1904 ) was one of the American West 's premier lawmen .
Wallace Groves ( c. 1902 - -30 January 1988 ) was a prominent financier , who , after his release from federal prison in 1944 , moved to the Bahamas and there founded and operated the free trade zone , resort , and casino development Freeport on Grand Bahama Island .
Georg Friedrich Wreede or Georgius Fredericius Wreede ( died on 29 February 1672 ) was governor of Dutch Mauritius from 1665 to 1672 , with a break between 1668 - 1669 .
Bartolomeo Cesi ( Italian : ( bartoloˈmeːo ˈtʃeːzi ) ; 16 August 1556 -- 11 July 1629 ) was a painter of the Baroque era of the Bolognese School .
Francis Carolus Eeles ( 1876 -- 17 August 1954 , Dunster ) , OBE , was an English liturgical scholar and church historian .
Michael Davitt ( Irish : Mícheál Mac Dáibhéid ; 25 March 1846 -- 30 May 1906 ) was an Irish republican and agrarian agitator who founded the Irish National Land League .
Dr. William Rickman ( c.1731 - -1783 ) was a prominent figure in the American Revolution , known best as the first Director of Hospitals of the Continental Army in Virginia during the war .
Dzhuma Durdy Karayev ( 1910 - 4 May 1960 ) was a Turkmen politician who served as General Secretary of the Communist Party of Turkmenistan .
Li Huaixian ( 李懷仙 ) ( died July 8 , 768 ) was a general of the Chinese rebel state Yan , who later submitted to and became a general of Tang Dynasty , from which Yan had rebelled .
Jens Nygaard ( 26 Oct 1931 - 24 Sep 2001 ) was an American orchestra conductor .
John Barrie ( 6 May 1917 -- 24 March 1980 ) was a British actor who appeared in a number of television shows and films , but became best known for his roles on the police series Sergeant Cork and Z - Cars in the 1960s .
William de Lode ( died 12 May 1403 ) , also known as William Gilbert , was the Prior of Spinney Abbey in Cambridgeshire from 1390 to 1403 .
Leslie Alcock FRSE ( 24 April 1925 -- 6 June 2006 ) was Professor of Archaeology at the University of Glasgow , and one of the leading archaeologists of Early Mediaeval Britain .
Harry Revel ( 21 December 1905 -- 3 November 1958 ) was an English composer of musical theatre .
John White Alexander ( 7 October 1856 -- 31 May 1915 ) was an American portrait , figure , and decorative painter and illustrator .
Siva Simha Malla ( Nepali : शिवसिंह मल्ल ) ( died 1619 ) , also known as Shiva Simha , was a Malla Dynasty King from Kathmandu .
Charles Wyatt ( 1758 -- 13 March 1819 ) was an English architect and Member of Parliament for Sudbury , Suffolk .
Sir Patrick Vanse ( also spelt Vans ) ( c. 1655 -- 27 January 1733 ) was a Scottish MP in the British Parliament .
Stephen Cartwright ( 28 December 1947 -- 12 February 2004 ) was a British children 's book illustrator who illustrated more than 150 books which sold millions of copies worldwide .
Sir Robert de Ashton , also called `` Robert Assheton '' or `` Robert de Assheton '' ( died 1385 ) , was a civil , military , and naval officer under Edward III of England who achieved distinction alike in court and camp , by land and by sea .
Edith Vane - Tempest - Stewart , Marchioness of Londonderry DBE ( born Edith Helen Chaplin ; 3 December 1878 -- 23 April 1959 ) was a noted and influential society hostess in the United Kingdom between World War I and World War II .
Ottar Egil Toreng ( 5 December 1922 -- 8 January 2015 ) was a Norwegian newspaper editor and politician .
John Cunningham Geikie ( Edinburgh , 26 October 1824 -- 1 April 1906 ) was a Scottish - born minister and author , primarily active first in Toronto , Canada , and then in England .
Kamel Hana Gegeo ( died 18 October 1988 ) was a personal bodyguard of the former president of Iraq , Saddam Hussein , and served as his valet and food taster .
Dame Elizabeth Leah Manning DBE ( née Perrett ; 14 April 1886 -- 15 September 1977 ) was a British educationalist , social reformer , and Labour Member of Parliament ( MP ) in the 1930s and 1940s .
Lionel Grigson ( 12 February 1942 -- 14 June 1994 ) was a British jazz pianist , cornettist , trumpeter , composer , writer and teacher , who in the 1980s started the jazz course at the Guildhall School of Music .
Robert Latou Dickinson ( 1861 - 1950 ) was an American obstetrician and gynecologist , surgeon , maternal health educator , artist , sculptor and medical illustrator , and research scientist .
Agnes Keith , Countess of Moray ( c. 1540 -- 16 July 1588 ) was a Scottish noblewoman having been the eldest daughter of William Keith , 4th Earl Marischal and Margaret Keith .
Lieutenant General Charles O'Hara , 1st Baron Tyrawley ( died 9 June 1724 ) was Commander - in - Chief , Ireland .
Sir Adam Mytton ( born before 1498 -- 1561 ) was an English Member of Parliament and county sheriff .
George Henry Vansittart ( 16 July 1768 -- 4 February 1824 ) was an English army general during the Napoleonic Wars .
William Edward Frank Britten , or W. E. F. Britten ( 1848 or 1857 -- 1916 ) was a British painter and illustrator .
Josephine Leavell Allensworth ( 1855 - -1938 ) was an African - American musician , music teacher , and activist .
Frederika Louisa of Hesse - Darmstadt ( Friederike Luise ; 16 October 1751 -- 25 February 1805 ) was Queen consort of Prussia as the second wife of King Frederick William II .
William John Townsend ( 20 January 1835 -- 7 March 1915 ) was a British minister of the Methodist New Connection .
Robert Stephenson FRS ( 16 October 1803 -- 12 October 1859 ) was an early railway engineer .
A Marxist scholar of the history of political thought , Neal Wood ( 10 September 1922 -- 17 September 2003 ) located political ideas within social relations , property forms , and popular struggles , writing on topics as variant as the British Communist Party , John Locke , Aristotle , Edmund Burke , and St. Augustine .
Rose Ethel Janet White - Haney ( 11 March 1877 -- 21 October 1952 ) , known as Jean White - Haney , was an Australian botanist who was officer - in - charge of the Queensland Board of Advice on Prickly Pear Destruction and held develop biological control methods for managing the invasive cactus .
Sir John Stenhouse Goldie - Taubman JP ( January 1838 -- 9 November 1898 ) followed his father , John Taubman Goldie - Taubman , both into the House of Keys and also as Speaker .
Rodulf Haraldsson ( died June 873 ) , sometimes Rudolf , from Old Norse Hróðulfr , was a Viking leader who raided the British Isles , West Francia , Frisia , and Lotharingia in the 860s and 870s .
Phineas Ryrie , JP ( 16 July 1829 -- 22 February 1892 ) was a Scottish tea merchant in Hong Kong .
William McLaren Bristol ( 1860 - -1935 ) was one of the two co - founders ( along with John Ripley Myers ) of Bristol - Myers Squibb .
Michał Wiśniowiecki ( died 1616 ) was a Polish--
Klaas Sybrandi ( Haarlem , 18 November 1807 - Haarlem , 4 September 1872 ) , also spelled as Sijbrandi , was a Dutch Mennonite minister , author , translator and involved with several societies and foundations .
Oswald Burton ( 21 August 1874 -- 4 July 1944 ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket for Derbyshire in 1901 and 1905 .
William Mayne , 1st Baron Newhaven PC ( 1722 -- 28 May 1794 ) , known as Sir William Mayne , Bt , between 1763 and 1776 , was a British politician .
Edward Walter Solly ( 7 May 1882 - 12 February 1966 ) was an English cricketer who played eight first - class games for Worcestershire as a professional between 1903 and 1907 .
Cecil Roderick Fry ( 1890 - -1952 ) was a member of the Fry family who ran the J. S. Fry & Sons confectionery business after World War I. He was chairman of J. S. Fry & Sons for 28 years , from the retirement of his father in 1924 to his own death in 1952 .
Muhammadu Junaidu ( 1906 -- 9 January 1997 ) was a Nigerian historian , writer and one of the foremost scholars on Fulani history and the Sokoto Caliphate .
John Williams , 1st Baron Williams of Thame ( c.1500 -- 14 October 1559 ) was Treasurer of the King 's Jewels , Lord Chamberlain of England ( 1553 - -1557 ) and Lord President of the Council of the Welsh Marches .
Solomon David Sassoon ( 1915 - -1985 ) was an educator , Rabbi , philanthropist , fundraiser , and collector of Jewish manuscripts .
Robert Hausmann ( 13 August 1852 -- 18 January 1909 ) was a notable 19th - century German cellist who premiered important works by Johannes Brahms ( including the Double Concerto ) and Max Bruch ( including Kol Nidrei ) .
François Coulon de Villiers ( 1712 -- 22 May 1794 ) was a French military officer from an influential military family in the French and Indian War and then an influential officer in the New Spain community of New Orleans .
Whitworth Wallis ( 23 June 1855 -- 16 January 1927 ) was the first director of Birmingham Museum & Art Gallery ( opened in 1883 ) .
Henry Swinden ( 1716 - -1772 ) was an English antiquary , known for his history of Great Yarmouth , Norfolk .
Sándor Garbai ( 27 March 1879 -- 7 November 1947 ) was a Hungarian socialist politician .
Saint Juan Grande Román ( 6 March 1546 -- 3 June 1600 ) was a Spanish Roman Catholic who was a professed religious of the Hospitallers of Saint John of God .
Jakob Eriksson ( 30 September 1848 - 26 April 1931 ) was a Swedish plant pathologist , mycologist and a taxonomist .
William Walter Murray Yeatts ( died 4 August 1948 ) was Census Commissioner for the 1941 census of India , which was the last such exercise prior to the country 's independence from the British Raj .
William Tayler ( 1808 - -1892 ) was a civil servant of the East India Company who lived in India from 1829 until 1867 .
John Tuchet , 6th Baron Audley , 3rd Baron Tuchet ( 1423 -- 26 September 1490 ) was an English politician .
Milbourne Christopher ( 23 March 1914 -- 17 June 1984 ) was a prominent American illusionist , magic historian , and author .
Pacifico Buzio ( 1843 - -1902 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of portraits , but also of illuminated manuscripts .
Edward Dutkiewicz ( 1 April 1961 -- 9 December 2007 ) was a British visual artist known for his use of bright colours and abstract forms , reminiscent of Calder and Matisse .
Arne Sejr ( 31 January 1922 -- July 1998 ) was a Danish World War II resistance member who became involved in anti - communist activities after the War .
James Lawrence died of his wounds on 4 June 1813 , while his captors directed Chesapeake to Halifax , Nova Scotia .
Bonaventura Peeters ( I ) or Bonaventura Peeters the Elder ( 23 July 1614 -- 25 July 1652 ) was a Flemish painter , draughtsman and etcher and one of the leading marine artists in the Low Countries in the first half of the 17th century .
Erasmus Saunders ( 1670 -- 1 June 1724 ) was a Welsh priest and writer .
Dr Boonsong Lekagul ( 15 December 1907 -- 9 February 1992 ) was a Thai medical doctor , biologist , ornithologist , herpetologist , and conservationist .
Lt . General Aftab Ahmad Khan died of a sudden Heart Attack on 12 July 2011 at the age of 88 , and was laid to rest with Pakistan Army 's traditional Military Honors for retired commanders .
Matija Majar , also spelled Majer ( 7 February 1809 - 31 July 1892 ) , pseudonym Ziljski , was a Carinthian Slovene Roman Catholic priest and political activist , best known as the creator of the idea of a United Slovenia .
Rodney Robert Porter , CH , FRS ( 8 October 1917 -- 6 September 1985 ) was an English biochemist and Nobel laureate .
Sir William Pooley ( died 5 August 1629 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1621 and 1629 .
Emil Kvanlid ( 4 July 1911 , Målselv -- 1 June 1998 ) was a Norwegian nordic combined skier who won the Nordic combined event at the Holmenkollen ski festival in both 1938 and 1940 .
Group Captain Cecil Chaudhry ( 27 August 1941 -- 13 April 2012 ) was a Pakistani academic , human rights activist , and veteran fighter pilot .
Gaynor Rowlands ( 3 April 1883 - 18 July 1906 ) , was an English actress , singer , and dancer , born in London , of Welsh parents .
Henricus Grammateus ( also known as Henricus Scriptor , Heinrich Schreyber or Heinrich Schreiber ; 1495 -- 1525 or 1526 ) was a German mathematician .
Sir George William Lefevre M.D. ( 1798 - -1846 ) was an English physician and travel writer .
Harry Hiams ( 1886 - 10 April 1954 ) was a Welsh international forward who played club rugby for Swansea and Llanelli .
Balappa Hukkeri ( Kannada : ಬಾಳಪ್ಪ ಹುಕ್ಕೇರಿ ) ( 1911 - -1992 ) was a singer of folk songs and Bhavageetes in Kannada language and a freedom fighter in his early years .
Bojo Jinul ( Hangul : 보조지눌 ; hanja : 普照知訥 , 1158 - -1210 ) , often called Jinul or Chinul for short , was a Korean monk of the Goryeo period , who is considered to be the most influential figure in the formation of Korean Seon ( Zen ) Buddhism .
Sir Leonard Redshaw ( 15 April 1911 -- 29 April 1989 ) was a shipbuilder from Barrow - in - Furness , Cumbria , England .
Jørgen Plaetner ( 1930 - 2002 ) was a Danish electronic composer .
Bernie Baxter ( 15 June 1929 -- 27 December 2012 ) was a former Australian rules footballer in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Walter Robert Smith ( 7 May 1872 -- 25 February 1942 ) was a Labour Member of Parliament ( MP ) who represented Wellingborough and Norwich .
Emmanuel Fisher ( September 25 , 1921-July 22 , 2001 ) was a British composer and conductor who was best known for leading the London Jewish Male Choir for 21 years .
Edward Seymour , Lord Beauchamp of Hatch ( 21 September 1561 -- 21 July 1612 ) had a theoretical strong claim to the throne of England , but in reality , he was a cipher whose legitimacy was questioned .
Andrew Kerins ( Irish : Aindreas Ó Céirín ; 18 May 1840 -- 17 April 1915 ) , known by his religious name Brother Walfrid , was an Irish Marist Brother and the founder of Celtic Football Club .
Dan Rolyat , born Herbert Taylor ( 11 November 1872 -- 10 December 1927 ) , was an English actor and singer .
Anne Marie de Bourbon ( Anne Marie Victoire ; 11 August 1675 -- 23 October 1700 . ) was the daughter of the Prince of Condé and of a Bavarian princess .
Philip Antony Corri ( also Arthur Clifton ) ( 1784 - 1832 ) was a composer , born in Edinburgh and later working in London and Baltimore , Maryland .
Torjus Værland ( 1868 - 1954 ) was the Norwegian Minister of Social Affairs 1928 - 1931 .
Wigmund was consecrated in 837 and died in 854 .
Enrico Piaggio ( 22 February 1905 - 16 October 1965 ) was an Italian industrialist .

Adrian Willaert ( c. 1490 -- 7 December 1562 ) was a Netherlandish composer of the Renaissance and founder of the Venetian School .

Major Abhey Singh , ( 14 August 1922 -- June 1981 ) was a cavalry officer in the Indian Army .

Francis Peter O'Hare , best known as Frank P. O'Hare ( 1877 - 1960 ) , was an American socialist political activist , journalist , and newspaper editor .

George Simonds Boulger ( 1853 - -1922 ) , F.L.S. , F.G.S. , F.R.H.S. , was an English botanist .

Jakub Kagan ( 7 February 1896 -- 1942 ) was a popular Polish - Jewish composer , pianist , jazz musician and arranger .
Robert Tooth ( 28 May 1821 in Cranbrook , Kent , England -- 19 September 1893 in Bedford , USA ) was one of three brothers of Sydney 's Tooth brewery family .
Christine Hargreaves ( 22 March 1939 -- 12 August 1984 ) was an English actress who was best known for appearing as the character Christine Hardman in the soap opera Coronation Street between 1960 - 1963 .

Graham Gilmour ( 1885 - -1912 ) was a British pioneer aviator , known for his impromptu public displays of flying .

William Wailes , ( 1808 - -1881 ) , was the proprietor of one of England 's largest and most prolific stained glass workshops .
Momčilo Gavrić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Момчило Гаврић ; 1 May 1906 -- 28 April 1993 ) was the youngest soldier in the First World War .
Joseph R. Walker ( December 13 , 1798 -- October 27 , 1876 ) was a mountain man and experienced scout .
Richard Birdsall ( 1799 -- 21 January 1852 ) was an English - born immigrant to Upper Canada who became a surveyor in Canada .
Nazaret Daghavarian ( in Armenian Նազարեթ Տաղավարյան , in Western Armenian Նազարէթ Տաղաւարեան , in Turkish Nazaret Dağavaryan , 1862 in Sebastia , Ottoman Empire -- 1915 ) was an Armenian doctor , agronomist and public activist , and one of the founders of the Armenian General Benevolent Union ( AGBU ) .
James Fordyce , DD ( 1720 - -1 October 1796 ) , was a Scottish Presbyterian minister and poet .
Heinrich Bünting ( 1545 -- 1606 ) was a Protestant pastor and theologian .
Labib Hussein Abu Rokan ( Arabic : لبيب حسين أبو ركن‎ , Hebrew : לביב חוסיין אבו - רוכן ; born 1911 , died 20 November 1989 ) was a Druze Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Cooperation and Brotherhood between 1959 and 1961 .
Bertie Maurice van Thal ( 1904 - -1983 ) , known as Herbert van Thal , was a British bookseller , publisher , agent , biographer , and anthologist .
Per Karl Hjalmar Dusén ( 1855 - -1926 ) was a Swedish civil engineer , botanist and explorer .
Jane Squire ( bap . 1686 - 1743 ) was an English scientific writer who was the only known woman to have participated openly in the 18th - century debates and discussions over the solution to finding longitude at sea .
Grete Nordrå ( 22 November 1924 -- 13 March 2012 ) was a Norwegian actress who appeared on screen from the 1950s onwards .
Sackville Hamilton PC ( Ire ) ( 14 March 1732 -- 29 January 1818 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician .
Horst Schumann ( 1 May 1906 -- 5 May 1983 ) , SS - Sturmbannführer ( major ) and medical doctor , conducted sterilization and castration experiments at Auschwitz and was particularly interested in the mass sterilization of Jews by means of X - rays .
Major - General Thomas de Courcy Hamilton VC ( 20 July 1825 -- 3 March 1908 ) was a Scottish recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Bitino or Bittino da Faenza ( 1357 -- 1427 ) was an Italian painter , active in Rimini during the late 14th and early 15th - century .
Ma Chao ( 176 - -222 ) , courtesy name Mengqi , was a military general and warlord who lived in the late Eastern Han dynasty and early Three Kingdoms period .
Eyvind Kelve ( c. 965 -- May 6 , 995 ) was a Norwegian pagan martyr , killed on orders of King Olav Tryggvason for refusing to give up his pagan beliefs .
Gopal Baratham ( 9 September 1935 - 23 April 2002 ) was a Singaporean author and neurosurgeon .
Ryszard Torzecki ( 20 March 1925 in Łódź - 20 August 2003 in Konstancin ) was a Polish historian , specializing in the Polish - Ukrainian relations .
Dove Gregory ( real name Gregory Dove ; 9 February 1837 -- 21 May 1873 ) was an English cricketer who played for Derbyshire in 1871 and 1872 .
Ratu Epeli Kanakana ( died 2010 ) was a Fijian chief .
Norman Kirkman ( 6 June 1920 -- 17 November 1995 ) was an English footballer who played as a full - back for various clubs in the Football League in the 1940s and 1950s , before a brief career as a manager .
John Lumley - Savile , 7th Earl of Scarbrough ( 1761 -- 21 February 1835 ) was a British peer , styled Hon . John Lumley until 1807 , and Lumley - Savile from 1807 until 1832 .
Cui Cha ( 崔詧 ) ( died 689 ) was briefly a chancellor of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , during the first reign of Emperor Ruizong .
Mirsiad Mirshakar ' or Mirsaid Mirshakarov ( born 6 May 1912 - died 1993 ) was a Soviet administrator , author , playwright and poet .
' Adi ibn Artah al - Fazari ( Arabic : عدي بن أرطاة الفزاري‎ ) ( died 720 ) was a governor of al - Basrah for the Umayyad dynasty , serving during the caliphate of ' Umar ibn ' Abd al-'Aziz .
Saint Simeon of Jerusalem , son of Clopas , was a Jewish Christian leader and according to most Christian traditions the second Bishop of Jerusalem ( 62 or 70 - -107 ) .
Pelham Aldrich CVO ( 8 December 1844 -- 12 November 1930 ) was a Royal Navy officer and explorer , who became Admiral Superintendent of Portsmouth Docks .
Roger Michael Kelly , known by the stage name Sam Kelly ; ( 19 December 1943 -- 14 June 2014 ) was an English actor who appeared in film , television , radio and theatre .
K. Amarnath ( 1 Dec 1914 -- 14 May 1983 ) was an Indian film producer and director whose career spanned over four decades in the film industry .
Paul Bost ( 16 May 1905 Lincolnton , North Carolina -- 4 September 1974 Lincolnton , North Carolina ) ) was an American racecar driver .
John Collas ( usually known as J. P. Collas ) ( 1911 -- 13 August 1984 ) was Professor of French at Queen Mary College , London from 1953 to 1976 .
Wilhelmus Simon Petrus Fortuijn , known as Pim Fortuyn ( Dutch : ( ˈpɪm fɔrˈtœyn ) ; 19 February 1948 -- 6 May 2002 ) was a Dutch politician , civil servant , sociologist , author and professor who formed his own party , Pim Fortuyn List ( Lijst Pim Fortuyn or LPF ) in 2002 .
Pakubuwono VI ( Surakarta , Central Java , 26 April 1807 -- Ambon , Moluccas , 2 June 1849 ) ( also transliterated Pakubuwana VI ) was the sixth Susuhunan ( ruler ) of Surakarta from 1823 to 1830 when he was deposed by the Dutch and exiled .
Marshall Ayres , Jr. ( 1839 - -1906 ) was an industrial financier .
Louis George Alexander ( 15 February 1932 -- 17 June 2002 ) was a teacher and writer , the author of New Concept English and the Direct English Syllabus and Course Structure .
Edmund Jenkins ( April 9 , 1894 -- 1926 ) was an African American composer during the Harlem Renaissance .
Daniel Ivancho ( March 30 , 1908 - -August 2 , 1972 ) was the third bishop of the Byzantine Catholic Metropolitan Church of Pittsburgh , the American branch of the Ruthenian Catholic Church .
Elma Tryphosa Dangerfield CBE ( 11 October 1907 - 22 January 2006 ) was a British journalist , writer , campaigner and Liberal Party politician .
Procopius of Gaza ( c. 465 - 528 AD ) was a Christian sophist and rhetorician , one of the most important representatives of the famous school of his native place .
Robert Rollock ( c. 1555 -- 8 February 1599 ) was the first regent and first principal of the University of Edinburgh .
Helmut Käser ( 14 November 1912 -- 11 May 1994 ) served as the General Secretary of international governing body of association football FIFA , from April 1960 to June 1981 .
Sir Arnold Thornely ( 7 October 1870 -- 1 October 1953 ) was an English architect who practised in Liverpool .
Henry John Pettypiece ( November 11 , 1855 -- 1942 ) was an Ontario journalist , businessman and political figure .
Gordon Sanderson ( 1886 - 1915 ) was an officer with the Archaeological Survey of India ( ASI ) and held the position of the Superintendent , Mahomedan and British Monuments , Northern Circle .
James Coody Johnson ( 1864 -- February 1927 ) was an African - Creek entrepreneur , interpreter , lawyer and politician .
Otto Julius Zobel ( October 20 , 1887 -- January 1970 ) was an electrical engineer who worked for the American Telephone & Telegraph Company ( AT&T ) in the early part of the 20th century .
Archie McNeel ( 20 January 1882 -- 22 February 1926 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sergiu Luca ( 5 April 1943 , in Bucharest -- 6 December 2010 , in Houston ) was a Romanian - born American violinist , renowned as an early music pioneer ; during his career he performed and recorded on both baroque and modern violins .
Charitina of Lithuania ( died 1281 ) is a saint in the Eastern Orthodox Church .
Arthur Everett Pitcher ( known as `` Everett Pitcher '' ; 18 July 1912 , Hanover , New Hampshire -- 4 December 2006 ) was an American mathematician , known for early pioneering work on exact sequences and applying Morse theory to homotopy theory .
William Guise ( Guilelmus Guisius ) ( c.1653 - -1683 ) , was an English orientalist .
Elis Ragnar Furuhjelm ( 12 October 1879 , Oulu - 15 November 1944 ) was a Finnish astronomer and politician .
Saint Himelin ( Hymelin , Himelinus ) ( died Vissenaken , c. 750 AD ) was an Irish or Scottish priest who , returning from a pilgrimage to Rome , fell ill when passing through Vissenaken ( in present - day part of the municipality Tienen in Belgium ) .
Frederick Metz ( 1832 - -1901 ) founded and owned the Metz Brewery in Omaha , Nebraska , for forty years .
Rösli Streiff ( 1901 -- 7 February 1997 ) is a Swiss alpine skier and world champion .
Osmo Antero Wiio ( 4 February 1928 -- 20 February 2013 ) was a Finnish academic , journalist , author and former Member of the Finnish Parliament .
Archdeacon Archibald Shaw ( 8 June 1879 -- 1956 ) was a pioneer missionary amongst the Dinka people with the Gordon Memorial Sudan Mission of the Church Missionary Society ( CMS ) in southern Sudan in the first half of the 20th century .
Bob Crossley ( 30 August 1912 - -19 September 2010 ) was an abstract artist who lived in Cornwall , England from 1959 .
Martin Knutzen ( 14 December 1713 -- 29 January 1751 ) was a German philosopher , a disciple of Christian Wolff and teacher of Immanuel Kant , to whom he introduced the physics of Newton .
Gregory Bicskei ( died 7 September 1303 ) was a prelate in the Kingdom of Hungary at the turn of the 13th and 14th centuries .
Sir Ralph Vane , also known as Ralph Fane ( died 26 February 1552 ) was a supporter of Edward Seymour , 1st Duke of Somerset , and hanged on Tower Hill as a result of factional strife .
Mohit Sen ( Bengali : মোহিত সেন ) born on 24 March 1929 , in Calcutta , and died in Hyderabad on 3 May 2003 was a well - known communist intellectual .
Charles Mertens de Wilmars ( Leuven , 21 November 1921 -- 1994 ) was a Belgian psychiatrist .
Adam Burski or Bursius ( ca . 1560 - -1611 ) was a Polish philosopher of the Renaissance period .
Amanda Christina Elizabeth Aldridge , also known as Amanda Ira Aldridge ( 10 March 1866 -- 9 March 1956 ) , was a British opera singer , teacher and composer , under the pseudonym of Montague Ring .
Konstantinos Petimezas ( Greek : Κωνσταντίνος Πετιμεζάς ) ( 1764 - -1824 ) was a Greek revolutionary leader during the Greek War of Independence and a soldier .
Bjørn Egge CBE ( 19 August 1918 -- 25 July 2007 ) was a Major General of the Norwegian Army and President of the Norwegian Red Cross ( 1981 - -1987 ) .
Walter Alfred Don Munday ( 1890 -- 1950 ) was a Canadian explorer , naturalist and mountaineer famous for his explorations of the Coast Mountains with his wife Phyllis , and especially for the exploration of the Waddington Range .
Richard Leveson - Gower ( 30 April 1726 -- 19 October 1753 ) was the fourth son of John Leveson - Gower , 1st Earl Gower and a member of the Leveson - Gower family .
Frank Pearson ( 1837 - -22 December 1899 ) was an Australian bushranger , operating under the pseudonym Captain Starlight .
Paul Rotha ( 3 June 1907 -- 7 March 1984 ) was a British documentary film - maker , film historian and critic .
Sir Robert Kennaway Douglas ( born Larkbeare House , Talaton , Devon ; 23 August 1838 - 20 May 1913 ) was vice president of the Royal Asiatic Society , and the first Keeper of the British Museum 's new Department of Oriental Printed Books and Manuscripts when it was created in 1892 .
Henry Doetsch ( 31 January 1839 - 25 May 1894 ) was a German born industrialist who lived in London .
Mallika Sengupta ( Bengali : মল্লিকা সেনগুপ্ত,1960 - -2011 ) was a Bengali poet , feminist , and reader of Sociology from Kolkata , known for her `` unapologetically political poetry '' .
Eddie Connolly ( 29 October 1985 -- 17 September 2015 ) was an Irish hurler .
Vladimír Hagara ( 7 November 1943 -- 24 May 2015 ) was a former Slovak football player .
Irving Lowens ( 19 August 1916 -- 14 November 1983 ) was an American musicologist , critic , and librarian in the Washington , D.C. area .
Johann Jakob Greber ( ? -- buried 5 July 1731 ) was a German Baroque composer and musician .
Nirupama Devi ( Bengali : নিরুপমা দেবী)(7 May 1883 -- 7 January 1951 ) was a fiction writer from Berhampore in Murshidabad district .
Don McIntyre ( 5 March 1915 -- 16 July 2013 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the VFL .
Francisca Herrera Garrido ( 1869 -- 4 November 1950 ) was a Galician writer of poems and novels .
Admiral Sir William James Hope - Johnstone KCB ( 28 July 1798 -- 11 July 1878 ) was a Royal Navy officer who became Commander - in - Chief , The Nore .
Little is known about Nugent Barker ( 1888 - -1955 ) , who is remembered for the evocative ghost story ' Whessoe ' , and the grimly humorous ' Curious Adventure of Mr Bond ' .
Edward Aspinwall , D.D. ( died 1732 ) , was an English polemical divine .
Patrick MacGill ( 24 December 1889 -- 22 November 1963 ) was an Irish journalist , poet and novelist , known as `` The Navvy Poet '' because he had worked as a navvy before he began writing .
Lauri Kettunen ( 12 February 1905 -- 15 August 1941 ) was a Finnish fencer and modern pentathlete .
Thomas Phillips RA ( 18 October 1770 -- 20 April 1845 ) was a leading English portrait and subject painter .
Devi Das Thakur ( 9 December 1929 - 3 February 2007 ) was a former Governor of Assam .
Gilbert Berkeley ( 1501 - -1581 ) was an English churchman , a Marian exile and then bishop of Bath and Wells .
Sir Edward Atkyns SL ( 1587 - -1669 ) was an English judge , a baron of the exchequer of the Commonwealth period .
Bastian Vasquez ( 9 April 1990 -- early 2015 ? ) , also known as Abu Safiyyah , was a Norwegian jihadist who made prominent appearances in propaganda videos for the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant ( ISIL ) .
Henry Radclyffe , 4th Earl of Sussex , KG ( 10 April or 14 December c. 1530 -- 19 January 1593 ) was an English peer .
Ed Dorn ( April 2 , 1929 -- December 10 , 1999 ) was an American poet and teacher often associated with the Black Mountain poets .
Benjamin Thomas Williams ( 19 November 1832 -- 21 March 1890 ) was a Welsh barrister and Liberal Party politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1878 to 1882 .
Mario Scaccia ( 26 December 1919 -- 26 January 2011 ) was an Italian actor and author .
Maria Elizabeth Budden , ( née Halsey , c. 1780 - -1832 ) was a novelist , translator and writer of didactic children 's books , who frequently signed her work `` M. E. B. '' or `` a mother '' .
Conall Cremthainne ( died 480 ) , also called Conall Err Breg , was an Irish king .
Fitz James O'Brien ( also spelled Fitz - James ; 31 December 1828 -- 6 April 1862 ) was an Irish - American writer and poet often cited as an early writer of science fiction ..
Edward John Dent died on 8 March 1853 , at the age of 62 and his adopted son completed the Great Clock .
Rosemary Pratt , Marchioness Camden ( 9 May 1921 -- 27 February 2004 ) , born Cecil Rosemary Pawle , was a British socialite and artist , best known as the first wife of Group Captain Peter Townsend , who later became romantically involved with Princess Margaret of the United Kingdom .
Inge Wischnewski , née Kabisch , ( 2 March 1930 -- 11 July 2010 ) was a German figure skater and figure skating coach .
Harrison Kerr ( b. Cleveland , Ohio , October 13 , 1897 ; d. Norman , Oklahoma , August 1978 ) was an American composer of contemporary classical music , editor , administrator , and educator .
Hubert Ney ( 12 October 1892 -- 3 February 1984 ) was a German politician ( Zentrum , CVP , CDU ) and Minister - President of Saarland ( 1956 - 1957 ) .
Shaikh Ahmad Khatib al - Minangkabawi ( 1860 -- 1916 ) was a Minangkabau Indonesian Islamic teacher .
Maud Marshal , Countess of Norfolk , Countess of Surrey ( 1192 -- 27 March 1248 ) was an Anglo - Norman noblewoman and a wealthy co - heiress of her father William Marshal , 1st Earl of Pembroke , and her mother Isabel de Clare suo jure 4th Countess of Pembroke .
Sir James Davidson Stuart Cameron FRSE CBE TD ( 1900 -- 1969 ) was a Scottish physician of note .
Hobart Upjohn ( 1876 - -1949 ) was an American architect , best known for designing a number of ecclesiastical and educational structures in New York and in North Carolina .
Anthony II , Count of Ligny ( d. 8 February 1557 ) was a son of Count Charles I and his wife Charlotte of Estouteville .
Yosef Weitz ( 1890 - -1972 ) was the director of the Land and Afforestation Department of the Jewish National Fund ( JNF ) .
Sir James Frank Colyer KBE FRCS FDSRCS Eng ( 25 September 1866 -- 30 March 1954 ) was a British dental surgeon and dental historian .
Ahmed Asmat Abdel - Meguid ( Arabic : أحمد عصمت عبد المجيد‎‎ ; 1 March 1924 -- 21 December 2013 ) was an Egyptian diplomat .
Lillebil Ibsen ( née Sofie Parelius Monrad Krohn ) ( 6 August 1899 -- 12 August 1989 ) was a Norwegian dancer and actress .
Margaret Mannion ( 5 November 1883 -- 15 May 1970 ) was a survivor of the RMS Titanic .
Sir Thomas Denys ( c.1477 - 1561 ) of Holcombe Burnell , near Exeter , Devon , was a prominent lawyer who served as Sheriff of Devon nine times between 1507/8 to 1553/4 and as MP for Devon .
Stanley Hicks ( 1911 - -1989 ) was a nationally recognized American historic folk artist from Watauga County , North Carolina .
Matthias Döring ( in the 1390s -- 24 July 1469 ) was a German Franciscan historian and theologian .
John Henry Weber ( 1779 - -1859 ) was an American fur trader and explorer .
Robert Davol Budlong ( 1902 - -1955 ) was an American industrial designer from Denver , Colorado .
Hélène Brion ( 27 January 1882 -- 31 August 1962 ) was a French teacher , feminist , socialist and communist .
Richard FitzWilliam , 7th Viscount FitzWilliam ( 1 August 1745 -- 4 February 1816 ) was an Irish Viscount in the FitzWilliam family who was a benefactor and musical antiquarian .
William Brazier ( 1755 at Cudham , Kent -- 7 October 1829 at Cudham ) was a noted English cricketer of the late 18th century who played mostly for Kent .
Grand Duke Peter Nikolaevich of Russia ( 10 January 1864 -- 17 January 1931 ) was a Russian Grand Duke and a member of the Russian Imperial Family .
Margaret of Foix ( French : Marguerite de Foix ) ( c. 1449 -- 15 May 1486 ) was , by marriage , Duchess of Brittany from 1474 to 1486 .
Hercules von Oberberg ( 1517 - -1602 ) was a Dutch - Danish Renaissance architect .
Edouard Espinosa ( 1871 - -1950 ) was co - founder and Principal Examiner of the Association of Operatic Dancing .
Guy Rolfe ( 27 December 1911 -- 19 October 2003 ) was an English actor who specialised in playing villains .
Bill Copson ( 27 April 1908 -- 14 September 1971 ) was an English cricketer who played for Derbyshire between 1932 and 1950 , and for England between 1939 and 1947 .
Hans Hendrik van Paesschen ( c. 1510 - 1582 ) was a Flemish architect , based in Antwerp , who designed high - style classical buildings in many countries of northern Europe .
Ghiyath ad - Din Mas'ud ( c. 1108 -- September 13 , 1152 ) was the Seljuq Sultan of Iraq and western Persia in 1133 - -1152 .
Charles Gildon ( c. 1665 -- 1 January 1724 ) , was an English hack writer who was , by turns , a translator , biographer , essayist , playwright , poet , author of fictional letters , fabulist , short story author , and critic .
Odón Alonso ( 28 February 1925 -- 21 February 2011 ) was a Spanish conductor and composer , best known for his film scores .
Jela Spiridonović - Savić ( 1891 - -1974 ) , poet , was the wife of Vladislav Savić , the Consul general of Yugoslavia .
Sir Edward Robert Peacock , GCVO ( 1871 - -1962 ) was a Canadian merchant banker , born in St. Elmo , Glengarry County , Ontario .
Jackie Hamilton ( born Johnny Kearns , 1937 -- died 12 August 2003 ) was a stand - up comedian , nicknamed the `` Pele of Comedy '' .
Ambrose Heath ( born Francis Geoffrey Miller on 7 February 1891 in London , England ; died 31 May 1969 in Wotton , Surrey ) was a journalist and food writer who wrote for newspapers including The Times and The Manchester Guardian , before becoming the food writer for The Morning Post .
Herman van Ham ( 16 April 1931 - 2 August 2012 ) was a Dutch head chef .
George Wade Robinson ( 1838 -- 18 January 1877 ) was a poet and hymnist from Cork , Ireland .
John Somerville , 4th Lord Somerville , ( c.1484 - 1523 ) , was a Lord of the Parliament of Scotland .
Christiana Hely - Hutchinson , 1st Baroness Donoughmore ( née Nickson ) ( d. 24 June 1788 ) was a suo jure hereditary peer ; as a lady , however , she was unable to sit in the Irish House of Lords .
Lady Margaret Erskine ( died 5 May 1572 ) was a mistress of King James V of Scotland .
Vincent La Chapelle ( 1690 or 1703 -- 1745 ) was a French master cook to Phillip Dormer Stanhope , fourth Earl of Chesterfield , to William IV , Prince of Orange , to John V of Portugal then to Madame de Pompadour , the mistress of Louis XV of France .
John L'Archers , or L'Archer ( died 1349 ) was an English born cleric and judge who had a distinguished career in Ireland , holding the office of Lord Chancellor of Ireland ; he died during the first outbreak of the Black Death , and was probably a victim of it .
Joseph F. Fitzpatrick , Jr. ( 1932 -- 11 July 2002 in Mobile , Alabama ) was an American carcinologist .
Pearson Thompson ( 14 April 1794 -- 22 November 1872 ) was an English solicitor and property developer who was responsible for the layout of a great part of Cheltenham , and of the Ladbroke Estate in London .
Roger Orton ( c. 1799 -- 1851 ) was an early Mormon leader and non - functioning member of the First Seven Presidents of the Seventy of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter - day Saints .
Eugenio Cavallini ( 16 June 1806 -- 11 April 1881 ) was an Italian conductor , composer , violinist , and violist .
B. S. Lokanath ( c. 1937 -- 2011 ) was an Indian cinematographer who worked in Tamil , Telugu , Kannada and Hindi films .
( James J. ) Séamus Dwyer ( c.1882 -- 20 December 1922 ) was an Irish politician .
John Edward McCarthy ( 1911 - -1977 ) was a radio actor and announcer .
Pesah Grupper ( Hebrew : פסח גרופר‎ , b 21 August 1924 -- 29 April 2013 ) was an Israeli politician who served as Minister of Agriculture between October 1983 and September 1984 .
Aimerico Manrique de Lara ( c. 1152 -- 1177 ) was the co - Viscount of Narbonne from 1167 and Duke of Narbonne from 1172 .
Edward Divers FRS ( 27 November 1837 -- 8 April 1912 ) was a British experimental chemist who rose to prominence despite being visually impaired from young age .
Johann Ludwig Bach ( 14 February ( O.S. 4 February ) 1677 -- 1 May 1731 ) was a composer and violinist .
James Paul Moody ( 21 August 1887 -- 15 April 1912 ) was the Sixth Officer of the RMS Titanic and the only junior officer of the ship to die in the disaster .
Maia de Carvalho Najla Jabor ( born 25 September 1915 , d. 9 Mar 2001 ) was a Brazilian conductor and composer .
John Thomas Blair ( 1885 - -1976 ) , most commonly known as John T. Blair , was an architect and builder in Tulsa , Oklahoma .
Joseph Torrey ( 1797 - -1867 ) was an American professor of philosophy at the University of Vermont and acting president of that university for five years .
Francis Napier , 6th Lord Napier ( 1702 - -1773 ) was a Scottish peer .
Fiannamail mac Máele Tuile ( died 680 ) was a King of Leinster from the Uí Máil branch of the Laigin .
Paolo Virchi ( also known as Targhetta ; 1551 -- 2 May 1610 ) was an Italian composer and instrumentalist .
James Arthur Prescott , CBE , FRS , ( 7 October 1890 -- 6 February 1987 ) was an agricultural scientist .
Đuro Basariček ( Croatian pronunciation : ( d͡ʑǔːro basarǐt͡ʃek ) ; Zagreb , 13 March 1884 - Belgrade , 20 June 1928 ) was a Croatian politician , lawyer and social activist .
Sir William Fergus Montgomery ( 25 November 1927 -- 19 March 2013 ) was a British Conservative member of Parliament for three separate periods , each time representing a different constituency .
Earl Cunningham ( 1893 - -1977 ) was a twentieth - century American Folk artist .
Dr Emily Bovell ( 1840 - -1885 ) was a physician and credited as one of the original members of the Edinburgh Seven .
Satyen Kappu ( 1931 -- 27 October 2007 ) , also credited as Satyendra Kapoor , was an Indian character actor in Bollywood films .
Sir Patrick Hume of Polwarth and Redbraes ( c.1550 - -1609 ) was a Scottish courtier and makar ( court poet ) , the eldest son of Patrick and Agnes Hume , a major Scottish Borders family with landholdings in The Merse .
Georges Vincey ( died February 1960 aged approximately 60 ) was a French metal worker and militant anarchist .
Johnnie S. Aikens ( September 11 , 1914 - January 1986 ) was a Democrat politician who served in the Missouri House of Representatives .
Riccardo Fainardi ( 1865 - -1959 ) was an Italian painter and interior designer , noted for his contributions to buildings .
Al C. Kalmbach ( 1910 - -1981 ) was the founder of Kalmbach Publishing , a publisher of magazines and books geared towards enthusiasts of several different hobbies .
Major General Mamman Jiya Vatsa OFR ( 3 December 1940 -- 5 March 1986 ) was a senior Nigerian Army officer and writer who was executed by the government of Major General Ibrahim Babangida on 5 March 1986 following a military tribunal conviction for treason associated with an abortive coup .
Charles John Gabriel ( 28 May 1879 -- 19 June 1963 ) was an Australian pharmacist and amateur conchologist .
Jessie Wicker Bell or Lady Sheba ( Knott County , July 18 , 1920 - March 20 , 2002 ) was a writer of the U.S. Wiccan Celtic Tradition and founder of the American and American Order of the Brotherhood of the Wicca with the aim to unite all practitioners of Wicca ( covens , groups , traditions ) .
Ubaldo I Visconti ( died 1230 ) was the de jure overlord of the Giudicato of Cagliari from 1217 .
Dorothea Austin Banner ( 1921 -- 25 June 2011 ) was an Austrian - born American pianist and composer who specialized in electronic and computer generated music .
Ed Garlick ( 26 September 1883 -- 23 September 1935 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Mother Mary Odilia Berger , S.S.M. , ( 30 April 1823 -- 17 October 1880 ) was a German - born Religious Sister who founded the Sisters of St. Mary in 1872 in St. Louis , Missouri , which established and still runs hospitals throughout the Midwestern United States .
Rita Sangalli ( 20 August 1849 - 3 November 1909 ) was an Italian ballet dancer .
Leon Zaleski ( c. 1810 in Poland -- February 1841 in Lwów ) was a Polish patriotic activist .
Beverley Robinson ( 11 January 1721 -- 9 April 1792 ) , a wealthy colonist from New York , was a son of the Hon . John Robinson of Virginia , who was the President of that colony .
Niels Kjærbølling ( 11 October 1806 -- 2 January 1871 ) was a Danish ornithological writer and lithographer .
Sir John Barrington , 3rd Baronet ( 1605 -- 24 March 1683 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1645 and 1679 .
Rolf Widerøe ( 11 July 1902 -- 11 October 1996 ) , was a Norwegian accelerator physicist who was the originator of many particle acceleration concepts , including the resonance accelerator and the betatron accelerator .
Edmund Meisel ( 14 August 1894 -- 14 November 1930 ) was an Austrian - born composer .
Kharshedji Rustomji Cama ( 1831 - -1909 ) , often known as K. R. Cama , was a Parsi scholar and reformer from Bombay .
Juan Schwanner , János Schwanner ( 5 February 1921 -- 8 May 2015 ) was a Hungarian--
Ernest Howard Crosby ( 1856 - -1907 ) was an American reformer and author , born in New York City , the son of Presbyterian minister Howard Crosby , and a relative of prolific hymnwriter and rescue mission worker Fanny Crosby .
Jean - Baptiste Mimiague ( 3 February 1871 -- 6 August 1929 ) was a French fencer who competed in the early 20th century .
Yosef Fischer ( Hebrew : יוסף פישר‎ , born 11 February 1920 , died 14 December 1992 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Mapai and its successors between 1959 and 1969 .
Galéas de Saint - Séverin ( in Italian Galeazzo da Sanseverino ' , d. 24 February 1525 ) was an Italian - French condottiere and grand écuyer de France ( `` Grand Squire '' , the courtier responsible for the royal stables ) .
Tony Cummins ( 6 September 1906 -- 20 January 2010 ) was an Irish priest and centenarian .
Asle Sjåstad ( 6 January 1930 -- 22 May 2009 ) was a Norwegian alpine skier .
Sir Samuel Pennant ( died May 1750 ) was a Lord Mayor of London .
Hans Heyting ( 13 August 1918 -- 9 June 1992 ) , born Johannes Heijting was a Dutch poet , playwright , radio personality , children 's book writer and painter .
James Wimshurst ( 13 April 1832 -- 3 January 1903 ) was an English inventor , engineer and shipwright .
Guido Meregalli ( 1894 -- 1959 ) was an Italian racecar driver , known from several GP victories between 1920 and 1926 .
Peter Michal Bohúň ( 29 September 1822 , Veličná - 20 May 1879 , Bielsko - Biała ) was a Slovakian painter , primarily of portraits , although he also did landscapes and altarpieces .
