Willy Rizzo ( 22 October 1928 -- 25 February 2013 ) was an Italian photographer and designer .
Kathleen Winters ( 1949 - -2010 ) was an American author and aviator .
Gulielmus Peregrinus ( fl . c. 1190 -- 1207 ) , also known as Gulielmus de Canno or William the Pilgrim , was an English epic poet and versificator regis ( `` king 's poet '' ) to Kings Richard I and John .
David Patrick Moran ( 22 March 1869 -- 31 January 1936 ) , better known as simply D. P. Moran , was an Irish journalist , activist and cultural - political theorist , known as the principal advocate of a specifically Gaelic Catholic Irish nationalism during the early 20th century .
Varodaya Cinkaiariyan ( Tamil : வரோதய சிங்கையாரியன் ) ( died 1325 ) was the first of the Aryacakravarti kings of Jaffna Kingdom to take over the lucrative pearl fisheries that were in the hands of the Pandyan Empire .
Andrés Chabrillón ( anglicised as Andres Chabrillon , 20 September 1887 - -1968 ) was an Argentine poet , writer , lecturer and literature professor of French descent .
Boamponsem ( died 1694 ) was a Denkyirahene , or ruler of the Denkyira people , from the 1650s until his death .
Sir Francis Throckmorton , 2nd Baronet ( 1641 - 1680 ) , of Coughton Court , Warwickshire and Weston Underwood , Buckinghamshire , was a member of a prominent English family of Roman Catholic dissenters .
Kazimierz Lux ( 1780 - -1846 ) was an officer of the Polish Legions and a pirate in the Caribbean Sea during the early 19th century .
Sir Derek Birley ( 31 May 1926 -- 14 May 2002 ) was a distinguished English educationalist and a prize - winning writer on the social history of sport , particularly , cricket .
Koichi Kawana ( Japanese : 川名孝一 , born March 16 , 1930 in Hokkaido -- 1990 ) was a native garden designer , college professor , and architect .
Stanley McNail ( 1918 ? -- 1995 ) was an American poet .
Joseph Hornblower ( 1696 ? -- 1762 ) was an English engineer , a pioneer of steam power .
Finian Monahan ( 1 January 1924 -- 5 June 2010 ) was an Irish Roman Catholic priest .
William Henry Blaauw ( 1793 - -1870 ) was an English antiquarian and historian , particularly active in Sussex .
Alexander Legge ( 1866 - -1933 ) was a prominent American business executive , serving as president of International Harvester from 1922 - 1933 .
M. Penn Phillips , born Marion Phillips , ( 13 June 1887 , Parsons , Kansas -- 24 May 1979 , Sierra Madre , California ) was an American entrepreneur and prominent real estate developer .
Henry Bickersteth , 1st Baron Langdale KC , PC ( 18 June 1783 -- 18 April 1851 ) was an English law reformer and Master of the Rolls .
Reid Bryson ( 7 June 1920 -- 11 June 2008 ) was an American atmospheric scientist , geologist and meteorologist .
Yoshimasa Hirata ( 平田 義正 Hirata Yoshimasa , 1915 -- 5 March 2000 ) was a Japanese organic chemist .
Reginold of Eichstätt ( died 4 April 991 in Eichstätt ) was Bishop of Eichstätt from 966 to 991 , much ' admired as a poet , musician , scholar and orator ' and indeed ' the leading musician of his age ' .
William Nicholson Jennings ( 1860 - -1946 ) was a photographer active in Philadelphia from the 1890s .
John Killefer ( May 24 , 1833 - July 1926 ) was a businessman and inventor .
Sion Record Bostick ( 7 December 1819 -- 15 October 1902 ) was a soldier for the Texas Army during the Texas Revolution , and later fought for the Confederate States Army during the American Civil War .
John Grout ( c.1643 -- 25 July 1697 ) was an American colonial military figure and selectman for Sudbury , Massachusetts for thirty years .
Gustavus Conyngham ( about 1747 -- 27 November 1819 ) was an Irish - born American merchant sea captain , an officer in the Continental Navy and a privateer .
Alan Leonard Hunt ( 7 February 1943 -- 14 March 2007 ) was a British actor , known as Gareth Hunt , best remembered for playing the footman Frederick Norton in Upstairs , Downstairs and Mike Gambit in The New Avengers .
Kornelis ter Laan ( Gronings : Knelis ter Loan ) ( 8 July 1871 - 6 March 1963 ) , also referred to as Kees ter Laan and Klaas ter Laan , was a Dutch politician and liguist .
John Scudamore , 2nd Viscount Scudamore DL ( c. 1650 -- July 1697 ) , was an English landowner and politician .
Andrew Fairfoul ( c 1606 - 1663 ) was the first post - Restoration Archbishop of Glasgow , from 1661 until his death in November 1663 .
Leonard John Brass ( 17 May 1900 -- 29 August 1971 ) was an Australian and American botanist , botanical collector and explorer .
Ulick Fionn Burke , 6th lord of Clanricarde ( died 1509 ) was an Irish warlord .
Count Berengar II of Sulzbach ( c. 1080 - 83 - 3 December 1125 ) , sometimes known as Berengar I of Sulzbach , was Count of Sulzbach in Bavaria .
Maulana Naeem Siddiqui ( 1916 - 25 September 2002 ) was a Pakistani Islamic scholar , writer and politician .
Hermann Winkelmann ( 8 March 1849 -- 18 January 1912 ) was a German Heldentenor , notable for creating the title role in Richard Wagner 's Parsifal in 1882 .
Ernest Malcolm Fewtrell ( 28 September 1909 -- 28 November 2005 ) was a Detective Chief Superintendent in the Buckinghamshire Constabulary and head of Buckinghamshire CID .
Josh Gifford ( 3 August 1941 -- 9 February 2012 ) was a jockey and trainer in National Hunt racing .
Silvestro de Buoni ( died 1484 ) was an Italian painter of the early - Renaissance period , specifically the Quattrocento in Naples .
Robert Pakington ( c. 1489 -- 13 November 1536 ) was a London merchant and Member of Parliament .
Henry Hetherington ( 17 June 1792 -- 23 August 1849 ) was a leading British Chartist .
Charles Mathieu Schols ( 28 March 1849 , Maastricht -- 17 March 1897 , Delft ) was a Dutch surveyor , mathematician and pioneer of geodesy .
Martino Rota , also Martin Rota and Martin Rota Kolunić ( c. 1520 - -1583 ) was an artist , now mainly known for his printmaking , from Dalmatia .
Khan Abdul Ali Khan ( 20 August 1922 -- 19 February 1997 ) was a Pakistani educationist , former Principal of Islamia College Peshawar , The FazleHaq College Mardan , Aitchison College , former Vice Chancellor of Peshawar University , Gomal University and former Education Secretary of NWFP .
Victor Vicas ( 25 March 1918 -- 9 December 1985 ) was a Russian - born French film director and screenwriter .
Marcus Aurelius Mausaeus Valerius Carausius ( died 293 ) was a military commander of the Roman Empire in the 3rd century .
Ivan Matteo Lombardo ( 22 May 1902 -- 6 February 1980 ) was an Italian socialist politician .
Gösta Leandersson ( 22 April 1918 -- 1995 ) was a Swedish marathon runner .
Dr. Dámaso Centeno ( Rosario , 10 March 1850 - 11 October 1892 , Cosquín ) was an Argentine lawyer , politician and philanthropist .
Margareta of Opole ( Polish : Małgorzata opolska ; c. 1412/14 -- 15 January 1454 ) , was a Polish princess .
Tommy Breckons ( 1928 - -2009 ) lived all his life on his family 's Foundry Farm , Bellingham , central Northumberland .
Domnall Ó Cellaigh , King of Uí Maine and Chief of the Name , died 1295 .
Ferenc Mérei ( 24 November 1909 -- 23 February 1986 ) was a Hungarian psychologist and educator .
Richard Oliver Postgate ( 12 April 1925 -- 8 December 2008 ) was an English animator , puppeteer and writer .
Major General John Hay Beith , CBE ( 17 April 1876 -- 22 September 1952 ) , was a British schoolmaster and soldier , but he is best remembered as a novelist , playwright , essayist and historian who wrote under the pen name Ian Hay .
Ivar Mortensson - Egnund ( originally Ivar Julius Mortensen and also referred to as Ivar Matlaus ) ( 24 July 1857 -- 16 February 1934 ) was a Norwegian author , journalist , theologian , researcher , translator , writer , philosopher and advocate of nynorsk ( the new Norwegian language ) .
Thomas Bullaker ( also John Baptist ) ( born at Chichester about the year 1604 ; executed at Tyburn , 12 October 1642 ) was an English Franciscan Catholic priest .
Elizabeth Balneaves ( 24 September 1911 -- 7 November 2006 ) was a Scottish author , painter and filmmaker .
Frank Kofsky ( 1935 - -1997 ) was an American Marxist historian , author , and Professor of History at California State University , Sacramento , from 1969 until his death .
Leonard Keith Lawson ( 1927 -- 29 November 2003 ) , better known as Len Lawson or Lennie Lawson , was a bestselling Australian comic book creator , successful commercial artist and photographer .
Kamini Roy ( Bengali : কামিনী রায় ) ( 12 October 1864 - 27 September 1933 ) was a leading Bengali poet , social worker and feminist in British India .
William Reginald Morse ( 30 August 1874 -- 11 November 1939 ) was a Canadian author , medical doctor , and medical missionary in China .
Robert Michaelis von Olshausen ( 3 July 1835 -- 1 February 1915 ) was a German obstetrician and gynecologist .
Alex Vallauri ( born Alessandro Vallauri ; Asmara , Ethiopia,9 October 1949-São Paulo , 27 March 1987 ) was a Brazilian artist of Italian origin .
Guillermo Vargas Aignasse ( born in 1943 , disappeared 1976 ) was an Argentine Peronist politician , serving as a provincial Senator in Tucumán Province from 1973 until his disappearance in 1976 .
Ivo Brnčić or Brnčič ( 13 March 1912 -- May 1943 ) was a Yugoslav author , essayist and literary critic of Croat origin , particularly notable for his assessment of the midwar Slovene literature .
Andrew Boorde ( or Borde ) ( c. 1490 -- April 1549 ) was an English traveller , physician and writer .
Julio Victorio De Rissio ( 10 November 1916 -- 26 December 2013 ) , better known by the stage name of Dr. Tangalanga , was a popular Argentine comedian known for his humorous prank phone calls to unsuspecting recipients .
Professor Inga - Stina Ewbank SBS ( 13 June 1932 -- 7 June 2004 ) was a Swedish - born academic and educator in Great Britain , Munich , Hong Kong and the United States , as well as an author and translator .
Cecile Hulse Matschat ( 1895 - 1976 ) was an American geographer and botanist , known best as the author of books on gardens , gardening and the Okefenokee Swamp .
Carl Albert von Lespilliez ( also known as Karl Albert von Lespilliez ) ( 1723 - 1796 ) was a German draftsman , architect and printmaker .
William Bullein ( c.1515 - -1576 ) was an English physician and cleric .
Theodore Vejtehi ( Hungarian : Vejtehi Tivadar , Romanian : Teodor Voitici ; died 1327 ) , also Theodore Csanád , was an influential lord in the Kingdom of Hungary at the turn of the 13th and 14th centuries , who ruled the Banate of Severin ( Hungarian : Szörénység ) de facto independently of the central royal power .
Alec Kellaway ( 1894 - -1973 ) was a South African - born actor best known for his work in Australian theatre and film , notably playing a number of character roles for director Ken G. Hall .
Nanquan Puyuan ( Chinese : 南泉普願 ; Wade - Giles : Nan - ch’üan P’u - yüan ; Pinyin : Nánquán Pǔyuàn ; Japanese : Nansen Fugan ) ( c. 749 -- c. 835 ) was a Chán ( Zen ) Buddhist master in China during the Tang Dynasty .
Nicholas Loftus , 1st Viscount Loftus PC ( I ) ( c.1687 - 31 December 1763 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician and peer .
Carlo Zoccoli ( 1718 - -1771 ) was an Italian architect , engineer , and scientific writer , active mainly in Southern Italy .
Walley Barnes ( 16 January 1920 -- 4 September 1975 ) was a Welsh footballer and broadcaster .
Sir Thomas Meautys ( 1592 - -1649 ) was an English civil servant and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1621 and 1640 .
Les Husband ( 12 July 1898 -- 11 March 1970 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Agasalim Atakishiyev ( Azerbaijani : Agasəlim Atakişiyev , born 1900 - died 1970 ) was an Azerbaijani politician .
Alexander Lindsay , 6th Earl of Balcarres and de jure 23rd Earl of Crawford ( 18 January 1752 -- 27 March 1825 ) was the son of James Lindsay , 5th Earl of Balcarres .
Guy Morel ( 1933 in Seychelles - 9 November 2006 ) was a Seychellois accountant , economist and businessman .
Nicholas Kalliakis ( Greek : Νικόλαος Καλλιάκης , Nikolaos Kalliakis ; Latin : Nicolaus Calliachius ; Italian : Niccolò Calliachi ; c. 1645 - May 8 , 1707 ) was a Cretan scholar and philosopher who flourished in Italy in the 17th century .
Henri Pouctal ( 1856 - 3 February 1922 ) was an early French silent film director and actor best known for his silent films of the 1910s and his directorship of the Count of Monte Cristo serials in 1918 .
Jean - Baptiste Raymond de Lacrosse ( Meilhan , 6 September 1760 -- Meilhan , 10 September 1829 ) was a French sailor and admiral , hero of the French Revolutionary Wars .
Sylvester O'Halloran ( 31 December 1728 -- 11 August 1807 ) was an Irish surgeon with an abiding interest in Gaelic poetry and history .
Liam Ó Murchú ( 10 February 1929 -- 28 June 2015 ) was an Irish television broadcaster , who worked with the national station Radio Telefís Éireann ( RTÉ ) .
Isabella Motadinyane ( 1963 - -2003 ) was a South African poet , performance poet and actor .
James Ogilvie - Grant , 11th Earl of Seafield DL ( 18 April 1876 -- 12 November 1915 ) , briefly known as Viscount Reidhaven in 1888 , was a Scottish nobleman .
Edwin J. Vandenberg ( September 13 , 1918 -- 2005 ) was a chemist at Hercules Inc. and a researcher at Arizona State University .
Jonathan Odell ( 25 September 1737 -- 25 November 1818 ) was a Loyalist poet who lived during the American Revolution .
William Henry Chetwynd ( 17 September 1811 - 5 July 1890 ) was a son of Sir George Chetwynd , 2nd Baronet who was involved in a sensational divorce case in 1865 .
Vladimir Haensel ( 1 September 1914 -- 15 December 2002 ) was an American chemical engineer who invented the platforming process - a platinum catalytic process for reforming petroleum hydrocarbons into gasoline .
Otto Regenbogen ( 14 February 1891 -- 8 November 1966 ) was a German linguist and scholar .
Louis Luyt ( 18 June 1932 -- 1 February 2013 ) was a South African business tycoon and politician , and one - time rugby administrator .
Dimitrie Ghica - Comănești ( also Demeter Ghica , Ghica Comăneșteanu , Prince Ghica de Roumanie ; December 31 , 1839 -- 1923 ) was a Romanian nobleman , explorer , famous hunter , adventurer and politician .
Edmond Herbert Grove - Hills CMG CBE FRS ( 1 August 1864 -- 2 October 1922 ) was a British soldier and astronomer .
Nora Burglon ( born April 28 , 1896 in Minnesota , died 1976 ) was an American author of children 's literature .
Henry Walpole ( 1558 -- 7 April 1595 ) was an English Jesuit martyr .
Ileana Sararoiu ( Romanian : Ileana Sărăroiu ) ( 25 September 1936 -- 12 May 1979 ) was a renowned Romanian singer of traditional and popular folk music .
Laxman Shrawan Bhatkar ( b 1901 Thugaon Amravati district - d 1970 ) was a politician and social worker from Central Provinces and Berar of British India .
Zvi Raphaeli ( b. Egypt 1924 , d. 2005 ) was an Israeli impressionist painter .
Otakar Krámský ( 1 July 1959 -- 25 April 2015 ) was a Czech hillclimbing racecar driver .
Robert Samuel ( died 31 August 1555 ) was an English priest of East Bergholt in Suffolk , England who was imprisoned , tortured and burnt to death as a judicial execution under the Marian persecutions , and is commemorated as one of the Ipswich Martyrs .
Edgar Charles Polomé ( 31 July 1920 -- 11 March 2000 ) was a Belgian Indo - Europeanist , and professor of comparative religions and languages at the University of Texas .
David Gee ( Coventry , 1793 -- 1872 ) was an English oil painter who took his inspiration from the local area .
Henry Pendleton ( born in Manchester ; died in London , September , 1557 ) was an English churchman , a theologian and controversialist .
Willie Doonan ( 1920 -- August 1976 ) is a former Gaelic footballer for Cavan .
On 15 June 1915 Paramaz with 19 other his comrades were hanged in the central square of Constantinople .
Ram Gabale ( died 9 January 2009 ) was an Indian filmmaker .
Frederick Walter Robinson ( nickname Doc Robbie ) ( 1888 - -1971 ) was an Australian academic at the University of Queensland .
Sir Richard William Allen ( 1867 -- 17 July 1955 ) was an English mechanical engineer .
Peter Garlake ( 11 January 1934 - 2 December 2011 ) was a Zimbabwean archaeologist and art historian , who made influential contributions to the study of Great Zimbabwe and Ife , Nigeria .
Amelia Cary , Viscountess Falkland ( 21 March 1807 -- 2 July 1858 ) was a British noblewoman .
Ramiz Sadiku ( 19 January 1915 -- 10 April 1943 ) was an Albanian law student and one of the organizers of the anti - fascist uprising in Kosovo .
Flaochad ( or Flaochat ) was the mayor of the palace of Burgundy from 639 to 642 .
Joseph - Alexandre Crevier ( 1824 - -1889 ) was a French - Canadian doctor who discovered the microbial transmission of cholera as well as a powerful remedy .
Thomas Kipling ( 1745 or 1746 -- 28 January 1822 ) was a British churchman and academic .
Sir Robert Howson Pickard FRS ( 27 September 1874 -- 18 October 1949 ) was a chemist who did pioneering work in stereochemistry and also for the cotton industry in Lancashire .
Audrey Cruddas ( 1912 - -1979 ) was an English costume and scene designer , painter and potter .
Thomas Rotherham ( 24 August 1423 -- 29 May 1500 ) , also known as Thomas ( Scot ) de Rotherham , was an English cleric and statesman .
Liu Yao ( Chinese : 劉曜 ; died 329 ) , courtesy name Yongming ( 永明 ) , was the final emperor of the Xiongnu state Han Zhao .
Colgate Hoyt ( 1849 - -1922 ) was an American businessman active in the late nineteenth century .
James Douglas , 2nd Duke of Queensberry and 1st Duke of Dover ( 18 December 1662 -- 6 July 1711 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Maria Kraus - Boelté ( 1836 - -1918 ) was a pioneer of Fröbel education in the United States , and helped promote kindergarten training as suitable for study at university level .
Binyamin Arditi ( Hebrew : בנימין ארדיטי‎ , 1 July 1897 -- 20 May 1981 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Herut and Gahal between 1955 and 1965 .
William Melmoth ( sometimes `` William Melmoth the Elder '' ) ( 1665/66 - -1743 ) was an English devotional writer and lawyer , whose major work , The Great Importance of a Religious Life Consider'd ( 1711 ) , proved to be one of the most popular pieces of religious writing of the 18th century .
Lars Pinnerud ( 18 August 1700 -- 1762 ) was a Norwegian farmer and woodcarver .
Sir Edward John Gambier ( 1794 - -1879 ) was a colonial jurist and law officer , who served as a judge in British India , Chief Justice of Madras and Recorder of Penang , Singapore , Malacca .
George André Robertson ( 8 September 1929 , St Jean - de - Luz , France -- 22 February 2007 , Redhill , Surrey ) , was a British educator , headmaster and sportsman .
Shivaji Sawant ( Marathi : शिवाजी सावंत ; 31 August 1940 -- 18 September 2002 ) was a renowned novelist in Marathi .
Lorenz van Steenwinckel ( 1585 - -1619 ) was a Flemish - Danish architect and sculptor , son of Hans van Steenwinckel the Elder and brother of Hans van Steenwinckel the Younger .
George Vere Irving ( 1815 - -1869 ) was a Scottish lawyer and antiquary .
Count Ferenc Gyulay de Marosnémethi et Nádaska ( 1 September 1799 -- 1 September 1868 ) , also known as Ferencz Gyulai , Ferencz Gyulaj , or Franz Gyulai , was a Hungarian nobleman who served as Austrian Governor of Lombardy - Venetia and commanded the losing Austrian army at the Battle of Magenta .
Eglantyne Louisa Jebb ( 1845 - 1925 ) was an Irish social reformer .
His son , also named James Rogers Armstrong , took over the family business in 1856 , when his father retired to Whitby .
Jean Weidt is the name generally used by and in respect of Hans Weidt ( 7 October 1904 - 29 August 1988 ) who was a dancer and choreographer .
Admiral Sir John Kingcome , KCB ( died 1871 ) was a Royal Navy officer who went on to be Commander - in - Chief , Pacific Station .
Antong ( or Hantum ) ( Chinese : 安童 ) ( 1248 - -1293 ) was a prominent official of Kublai Khan , founder of the Yuan dynasty and the Great Khan of the Mongols .
William Graham , 3rd Earl of Menteith ( c. 1500 -- c. 1543 ) was a Scottish magnate and third Earl of Menteith .
Samuel Thorp , or Thorpe , ( c. 1765 - 1838 ) was born in Madeley , Shropshire .
Richard Niccols ( 1584 - -1616 ) was an English poet and editor .
Nissim Elias Benjamin Ezra ( 1883 - -1936 ) , commonly known as N.E.B. Ezra , was a Baghdadi Jewish publisher and Zionist based in Shanghai .
Robert Eadon Leader ( 2 January 1839 -- 18 April 1922 ) was a journalist , Liberal activist , and historian .
Edward Hastings , 1st Baron Hastings of Loughborough , KG ( c. 1521 in Loughborough , Leicestershire-1571 ) was an English peer , the fourth son of George Hastings , 1st Earl of Huntingdon .
Ivy Duke ( 9 June 1896 , Kensington , London -- 8 November 1937 , London ) was a British actress .
Saint Meletius of Antioch ( Μελέτιος ) ( died 381 ) was a Christian bishop , or Patriarch of Antioch , from 360 until his death .
Thomas Rice Edward Holmes ( 24 May 1855 -- 4 August 1933 ) , who usually published as T. Rice Holmes or T.R.E. Holmes , was a scholar best known for his extensive and `` fundamental '' work on Julius Caesar and his Gallic War commentaries .
Sir Richard Wingfield KG of Kimbolton Castle ( c. 1456 -- 22 July 1525 ) was an influential courtier and diplomat in the early years of the Tudor dynasty of England .
James Duckett ( died 1601 ) was an English Catholic layman and martyr .
Charles Etienne Boniface ( 2 February 1787 -- 10 December 1853 ) was an early nineteenth century music teacher , playwright , journalist and polyglot who was born in France , but who spent his adult life in Southern Africa .
Shabtai Sheftel Horowitz ( 1565 - -1619 ) was a Kabbalistic author , who flourished in Prague in the sixteenth and seventeenth centuries .
Heinrich von Louffenburg ( 1391 - -1460 ) was a Swabian priest born at Louffenburg on the Rhein , Germany .
Edward Proger ( 16 June 1621 or 16181 -- 31 December 1713 ) was a Member of Parliament for Brecknockshire / Breconshire , Page of Honour to King Charles I , Groom of the Bedchamber for King Charles II and Lord of the Manor of West Stow .
Alfonso Fernández el Niño ( c. 1243 - -1281 ) was a Spanish nobleman , the illegitimate son of King Alfonso X of Castile and Elvira Rodríguez de Villada .
Matilda Ellen Bishop ( 12 April 1842 , Tichborne , Hampshire -- 1 July 1913 , Camberwell , London ) was the first Principal of Royal Holloway College , University of London .
Jayanti Prasad Tiwari ( 1925 - -28 March 1983 ) was a social activist from Uttar Pradesh .
Marta Ljungberg ( 1656 - -1741 ) , was a Swedish innkeeper .
Claude Raguet Hirst ( born Claudine , 1855 - -1942 ) was an American painter of still lifes .
Louis Perrin PC ( 15 February 1782 -- 7 December 1864 ) was an Irish barrister , politician and judge .
Emil Fischbacher 巴醫生 ( 9 August 1903 - 27 May 1933 ) was a Scottish Protestant Christian missionary to Xinjiang .
Joseph Royal ( 7 May 1837 -- 23 August 1902 ) was a Canadian journalist , lawyer , politician , businessman , and Lieutenant Governor of the Northwest Territories .
François Fiedler ( Košice , 1921 - Saint - Germain - Laval , Seine - et - Marne , 2001 ) was a Hungarian - born naturalized French painter .
Mark Lovell ( 27 March 1960 -- 12 July 2003 ) was a British rally driver .
Evelyn Rose MBE ( 2 December 1925 -- 18 May 2003 ) was an Anglo - Jewish cookery writer .
Constance Smith ( 22 January 1928 -- 30 June 2003 ) was an Irish film actress , and contract player of 20th Century Fox in the 1950s .
Fred Yates ( 25 July 1922 -- 7 July 2008 ) , born Frederick Joseph Yates , was an English artist .
Chu Guangxi ( Chinese : 儲光羲 ) ( 707 - -760 ) was a Tang Dynasty poet .
Edward Howard , 8th Earl of Suffolk ( 1672 - 22 Jun 1731 ) was an English peer .
Colonel Richard Grace ( c.1612 - -1691 ) was an Irish Royalist soldier who fought for Charles I , Charles II and James II .
Bernt Moe ( 1 June 1814 -- 5 June 1850 ) was a Norwegian encyclopedist .
Count Friedrich Wilhelm Rembert von Berg ( Russian : Фёдор Фёдорович Берг Graf Fyodor Fyodorovich Berg ; 15 May 1794 -- 6 January 1874 ) was a Russian Field Marshal , and the Governor - General of Finland from 1855 to 1861 .
Leslie Sands ( 19 May 1921 -- 9 May 2001 ) was a British actor and writer of TV and film .
Roger Belbéoch ( 26 July 1921 -- 5 November 2010 ) was a French communist militant , member of the French Resistance during World War II ( 1939 - -45 ) , a policeman and deputy mayor of Joinville - le - Pont .
Jean - Bosco Barayagwiza ( 1950 , Mutura - 25 April 2010 ) was a Rwandan diplomat and the chairman of the executive committee for the Rwandan radio station Radio Télévision Libre des Mille Collines from 1993 and during the 1994 Rwandan Genocide .
John Xantus de Vesey a.k.a . de Csíktaplócza ( Hungarian : Csíktaplóczai ( Vese ) Xántus János , 5 October 1825 -- 13 December 1894 ) was a Hungarian exile and zoologist .
Thomas Charles Williams ( 28 August 1868 -- 29 September 1927 ) was a Welsh Calvinistic Methodist minister , who served as Moderator of the denomination 's General Assembly .
Renzo Pasolini ( 18 July 1938 -- 20 May 1973 ) , nicknamed `` Paso '' , was a popular Italian Grand Prix motorcycle road racer in the 1960s and early 1970s .
Lieutenant Colonel Herbert St Maur Carter D.S.O. , M.D. ( 7 May 1878 -- 10 February 1957 ) was an Irish - born British military officer , doctor and surgeon , who served with the Royal Army Medical Corps and the British Red Cross .
Ma Yueliang or Ma Yueh - liang ( 1 August 1901 -- 13 March 1998 ) was a famous Manchu teacher of taijiquan .
Phraya Songsuradej ( 1891 - -1944 , common name Deva Bandhumasena ) was a Thai military officer .
Dr Girish Bihari ( 5 March 1938 - 29 April 2009 ) was an Indian educationist and Indian Police Service ( IPS ) officer .
Marie Hartley ( 29 September 1905 -- 10 May 2006 ) was the author or co - author and illustrator of some 40 books on the social history of the Yorkshire Dales .
Wee Chong Jin ( Chinese : 黄宗仁 ; pinyin : Huáng Zōng Rén ; 28 September 1917 -- 5 June 2005 ) was a Singaporean judge and the first Chief Justice of the country .
Carl Christian Brenner ( August 1 ( or 10 ) , 1838 -- July 22 , 1888 ) was a German - born American artist .
Grand Duchess Maria Kirillovna of Russia , ( 2 February 1907 -- 25 October 1951 ) was the eldest daughter of Grand Duke Kirill Vladimirovich of Russia and Grand Duchess Victoria Feodorovna .
Dúngal mac Amalgado ( or Dúngal Cnogba ) ( died 759 ) was a King of Brega from the Uí Chonaing sept of Cnogba ( Knowth ) of the Síl nÁedo Sláine branch of the southern Ui Neill .
William Penkethman ( died 1725 ) was an English comic actor and theatre manager .
Saints Eulampius and Eulampia ( died 310 AD ) are venerated as 3rd century Christian martyrs .
Kate Cocks ( born Fanny Kate Boadicea Cocks on 5 May 1875 , died 20 August 1954 ) was welfare worker and the state 's first policewoman in South Australia .
Blessed Angelo Paoli ( 1 September 1642 - 17 January 1720 ) was an Italian Carmelite , known as `` the father of the poor '' .
Laurel Trivelpiece ( 1926 Nebraska -- 1998 ) was an American poet and novelist .
Dame Katharine Furse , GBE , RRC ( née Symonds ; 23 November 1875 , Bristol -- 25 November 1952 , London ) , founder of the English Voluntary Aid Detachment ( VAD ) force , was the daughter of the poet and critic John Addington Symonds and Janet Catherine North .
Arthur Broadbent ( 7 June 1879 -- 19 July 1958 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played six games for Yorkshire and Scotland from 1907 to 1912 .
Edward How ( c. 1702 -- 1750 ) was a British officer , diplomat and member of the Nova Scotia Council .
Ahmad ibn Muzahim ibn Khaqan ( Arabic : أحمد بن مزاحم بن خاقان‎ ) was the military governor ( wālī al - jaysh ) of Egypt for the Abbasid dynasty for a part of 868 .
Arthur Robert Hogg ( 25 November 1903 -- 31 March 1966 ) was an Australian physicist and astronomer .
John Pine ( 1690 - -1756 ) was an English designer , engraver , and cartographer notable for his artistic contribution to the Augustan style and Newtonian scientific paradigm that flourished during the British Enlightenment .
George Gordon , 3rd Earl of Aberdeen ( 19 June 1722 -- 13 August 1801 ) , styled Lord Haddo until 1745 , was a Scottish peer .
Karl Purgold ( 28 December 1850 , Gotha -- 1939 , Gotha ) was a German classical archaeologist and museum director .
Ferdinand Pecora ( January 6 , 1882 -- December 7 , 1971 ) was an American lawyer and judge who became famous in the 1930s as Chief Counsel to the United States Senate Committee on Banking and Currency during its investigation of Wall Street banking and stock brokerage practices .
Pjetër Gjoka ( 3 August 1912 -- 12 May 1982 ) was an Albanian movies and theater actor of the 20th century .
Jules Ferrette ( 22 April 1828 -- 10 October 1904 ) was a Bishop of Iona and founder of the Catholic Apostolic Church of the West ( later known as the British Orthodox Church ) .
Tetsuo Ochikubo ( 1923 - -1975 ) , also known as Bob Ochikubo , was a Japanese - American painter , sculpture , and printmaker who was born in Waipahu , Hawaii , Honolulu county , Hawaii .
Chic Chocolate ( 1916 -- May 1967 ) born Antonio Xavier Vaz , was a Goan trumpeter who led a Jazz band at the Taj Mahal Hotel in Bombay and was one of Bombay 's best known jazz musicians .
Surendra Pratap Singh , also referred to as S.P. Singh , ( 4 December 1948 -- 27 June 1997 ) was a leader among Hindi - language journalists .
Sir George Lisle Ryder , KCB ( 1838 - 30 June 1905 ) was a British civil servant in the Treasury and Chairman of the Board of Customs .
Anagarika Dharmapala ( Sinhalese : අනගාරික ධර්මපාල ; 17 September 1864 -- 29 April 1933 ) was a Sri Lankan Buddhist revivalist and writer .
Natu Gopal Narhar ( 1911 - -1991 ) was a Marathi poet , often referred to as Poet Manmohan .
Sir Ilay Campbell , Lord Succoth LLD FRSE ( 1734 - -1823 ) was a Scottish advocate , judge and politician .
Karl Ernst Rahtgens ( 27 August 1908 -- 30 August 1944 ) was a German officer in the Wehrmacht during World War II , and an active resistance fighter against the Nazi régime .
Lady Maria Bell ( née Hamilton ; 26 December 1755 -- 9 March 1825 ) was an English amateur painter .
Koçi Bey ( died 1650 ) was a high - ranking Ottoman bureaucrat who lived in the first half of the 17th century .
William Gilmour Leburn ( 30 July 1913 -- 15 August 1963 ) was a British company director and Conservative Member of Parliament for Kinross and West Perthshire from 1955 until 1963 .
Baron Johan August Gripenstedt ( 11 August 1813 -- 13 July 1874 ) was a Swedish businessman and politician .
William Inwood ( c.1771 -- 16 March 1843 ) was an English architect and surveyor , whose most important works including St Pancras New Church and Westminster Hospital were done in collaboration with his sons .
Rafael Artzy ( 1912 - -2006 ) was an Israeli mathematician specializing in geometry .
Mary Anne Barker , Lady Barker ( 29 January 1831 -- 6 March 1911 ) , later Mary Anne Broome , Lady Broome , was an author .
Thomas Walton Mellor ( 1814 - - 17 February 1902 ) was a British cotton manufacturer and Conservative politician .
Jeannette Genius McKean ( 1909 - -1989 ) was a painter , interior decorator , Louis Comfort Tiffany art glass collector , Morse Museum founder and benefactor of Rollins College .
Govert Bidloo or Govard Bidloo ( 12 March 1649 -- 30 March 1713 ) was a Dutch Golden Age physician , anatomist , poet and playwright .
Karl Paul Kristian Gylche ( 30 January 1890 -- 15 November 1944 ) was a detective of the Danish police force who died in the Buchenwald concentration camp following the deportation of the Danish police .
William Alexander Anthony `` Bunny Rugs '' Clarke ( 6 February 1948 -- 2 February 2014 ) , also known as Bunny Scott , was the lead singer of Jamaican reggae band Third World as well as recording as a solo artist .
José María de Echeandía ( ☩ 1871 ) was twice Mexican governor of Alta California from 1825 to 1831 and again from 1832 to 1833 .
Agostino Agostini ( died 1569 ) was a Renaissance era singer , composer and priest of Ferrara mostly active in the 1540s .
Richard Caton ( 1842 , Bradford -- 1926 ) , of Liverpool , England , was a scientist who was crucial in discovering the electrical nature of the brain and laid the groundwork for Hans Berger to discover Alpha wave activity in the human brain .
Christopher Villiers , 1st Earl of Anglesey ( c. 1593 -- 3 April 1630 ) , known at court as Kit Villiers , was an English courtier , Gentleman of the Bedchamber and later Master of the Robes to King James I. In 1623 he was ennobled as Earl of Anglesey and Baron Villiers of Daventry .
John Wenlock , 1st Baron Wenlock KG ( c.1400 - 04 - 1471 ) was an English diplomat , soldier , courtier and politician .
Mona Moore ( 20 March 1917- 20 September 2000 ) , also known as Mona Bentin and later as Deborah Bentin , was a British painter and illustrator , best known for her work during World War Two for both the Recording Britain project and for the War Artists ' Advisory Committee .
William Gager ( 1555 - -1622 ) was an English jurist , now known for his Latin dramas .
David McKee Wright ( 6 August 1869 -- 5 February 1928 ) was an Irish - born poet and journalist , active in New Zealand and Australia .
Joseph Makinson ( born 25 August 1836 at Higher Broughton , Salford , Lancashire ; died 14 March 1914 at Sale , Cheshire ) was an English amateur cricketer who played first - class cricket from 1856 to 1873 .
Andrew Bloxam ( 22 September 1801 -- 2 February 1878 ) was an English clergyman and naturalist ; in his later life he had a particular interest in botany .
Radbot , Count of Habsburg ( c. 985 -- 1045 ) , also known as Radbot of Klettgau , was Graf of the county of Klettgau on the High Rhine in Swabia .
Edward Micklethwaite Curr ( 25 December 1820 -- 3 August 1889 ) was an Australian pastoralist and squatter .
Heinz - Josef Große was a 34-year - old East German ( GDR ) construction worker who was shot and killed on 29 March 1982 by GDR border guards on the Inner German border at Schifflersgrund , near Bad Sooden - Allendorf .
Major Arthur Patrick Bateman - Champain ( 17 October 1866 -- 7 October 1907 ) was an Indian Army officer who served in the 2nd Battalion , 3rd Gurkha Rifles , and was in charge of the King 's Indian Orderly Officers .
Giorgio Panto ( 1 October 1941 -- 26 November 2006 ) was an Italian Venetist entrepreneur and politician .
Sheikh Abdul Munem Abu Zant ( 1954 -- 26 July 2015 ) was a Jordanian Muslim scholar and politician .
Richard de Ayreminne , or Ayermin , ( died 1340 ? ) , was the chancellor of the dioceses of Norwich and Salisbury .
John Edward Pigot ( 1822 - -1871 ) was an Irish music collector and lawyer , who played a key role in the foundation of the National Gallery of Ireland .
Mira Rani Devi ( 16 November 1929 -- 25 June 2009 ) , an Indian author and reformer , was born in Madaripur and raised later on in Faridpur district town .
Roger d'Ivry or d'Ivri or Rog'ive or Roger Perceval ( died 1079 ) was an 11th - century nobleman from Ivry - la - Bataille in Normandy .
Tadeusz Dominik ( 14 January 1928 -- 20 May 2014 ) was a Polish painter , draftsman and art professor .
John Marsden Beaumont Jones ( 20 December 1920 -- 11 June 1992 ) , known as Marsden Jones , was an emeritus professor and the founder and first director of the Center for Arabic Studies at the American University in Cairo .
Per Alfred Petersson ( as a parliamentarian referred to as Alfred Petersson i Påboda , i.e. `` in Påboda '' , after his home farm , and often just `` Påboda '' ) ( 25 June 1860 - -11 October 1920 ) was a Swedish politician and minister for agriculture in several cabinets .
Thakur Deshraj ( 1903 - -1970 ) was a social worker , journalist , nationalist , freedom fighter and author of many books .
Sister Mary Xavier Molony , P.B.V.M. ( August 1781 - October 1865 ) was an Irish Presentation Sister who was the first nun to establish Catholic schools in Newfoundland .
Ernst Heinrich Karlen , C.M.M. ( 1 February 1922 -- 28 October 2012 ) was a Swiss Prelate of the Roman Catholic Church .
Mary Devens ( 17 May 1857 - 13 March 1920 ) was an American photographer who was considered one of the ten most prominent pictorial photographers of the early 20th century .
Jovan Hadži - Vasiljević ( Serbian Cyrillic : Јован Хаџи-Васиљевић , 18 October 1866 -- 29 March 1948 ) was a Serbian historian , ethnographer , journalist and writer .
Charlotte E. Maguire ( 1918 - -2014 ) was the first woman doctor in Orlando , Florida and opened the first pediatric practice run by a woman in Orlando in 1946 .
Johann Peter Kellner ( variants : Keller , Kelner ) ( 28 September 1705 -- 19 April 1772 ) was a German organist and composer .
Henry Alexander Davidson , M.D. ( 1905 - 1973 ) was an American physician , a psychiatric administrator , and a proponent of forensic psychiatry .
Philippe de Carteret I , 2nd Seigneur of Sark ( 1552 - -1594 ) was the Seigneur of Sark from 1578 to 1594 .
Thomas Thornton ( c.1541 - 1629 ) D.D. was an English Church of England clergyman and academic administrator .
Arthur Maskell ( 28 March 1894 -- 16 June 1970 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Boris Fedtschenko died on 29 September 1947 in Leningrad ( now called St Petersburg ) .
Ali Naci Karacan ( 1896 -- 7 July 1955 ) was a Turkish journalist and publisher .
Joseph Wheless ( Montgomery County , Tennessee 1868 - 1950 ) was an American lawyer who wrote promoting the Jesus myth theory during the early years of the 20th Century .
Henry Harding Bingley ( 1887 - -1972 ) was a painter in washed oils and watercolour during the early 20th Century .
Dušan Vukotić ( 7 February 1927 -- 8 July 1998 ) was a Yugoslav and Croatian cartoonist , author and director of animated films of Montenegrin descent .
Uriel Fernandes ( 12 November 1913 -- 22 July 2000 ) , commonly known as Teleco , was a Brazilian footballer who played as a striker .
Catherina Boevey ( 1669 - -1726 ) ( or Bovey , nee Riches ) ( pronounced `` Boovey '' ) , was a philanthropist .
The Hon . Charles Hope - Weir ( or Hope - Vere ) ( 8 May 1710 -- 30 December 1791 ) was a Scottish politician .
Morris Abrams ( 1908 - 1981 ) was the founder of Arrow Fastener Co. , Inc. , a manufacturer of fastening tools that since 1999 has been a subsidiary of Masco Corporation .
Mahamahopadhyaya Dr. Nookala Chinna Satyanarayana ( 4 August 1923 -- 11 July 2013 ) was a Carnatic musician , a classical vocalist , musicologist , author and teacher , a great administrator and motivator .
John Canne ( d. 1667 ? ) was an English Independent minister and printer .
Harriet Howard , born Elizabeth Ann Haryett ( 1823 - -1865 ) was a mistress and financial backer of Louis Napoleon , later Napoleon III of France .
Frank Hince ( 13 January 1882 -- 4 May 1945 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy and Carlton .
Robert Furze Brettingham ( 1750 - -1806 ) was an English architect , the nephew of Matthew Brettingham the Elder , who practised in London .
Sir Bernard Katz , FRS ( 26 March 1911 -- 20 April 2003 ) was a German - born biophysicist , noted for his work on nerve biochemistry .
Bernhard Studer - Steinhäuslin ( 23 May 1847 -- 28 March 1910 ) was a Swiss pharmacist and naturalist .
Leopold Engleitner ( 23 July 1905 -- 21 April 2013 ) was an Austrian conscientious objector and Holocaust survivor who spoke publicly and with students about his experiences .
Piara Singh Gill ( 28 October 1911 -- 23 March 2002 ) was an Indian nuclear physicist who was a pioneer in cosmic ray nuclear physics and worked on the American Manhattan project .
Peter Turnerelli ( c.1772 - -1839 ) was a successful Irish - born sculptor of Italian descent working in Britain in the early 19th century .
Prince Alexander Bekovich - Cherkassky ( Russian : Алекса́ндр Беко́вич-Черка́сский ) , born Devlet - Girei - murza ( Russian : Девлет-Гирей-мурза ) ( died 1717 ) , was a Russian officer of Circassian origin who led the first Russian military expedition into Central Asia .
Coleman Sellers II ( 1827 - -1907 ) was a prominent American engineer and inventor .
Brigadier General Edward Fowell Martin CB , CMG , DSO ( 22 August 1875 -- 22 September 1950 ) was an Australian Army Brigadier General who served in World War I.
The Reverend Revett Sheppard ( 1778 , in Campsey Ash - 1830 , in Wrabness ) was an English malacologist .
Egbert of Lindisfarne ( or Ecgberht ) was Bishop of Lindisfarne from his consecration on 11 June 802 until his death in 821 .
Lyman Ray Patterson ( 18 February 1929 -- 5 November 2003 ) was an American law professor and an influential copyright scholar and historian .
Lord Mikołaj Oleśnicki the elder ( d. 1556 ) was a Polish Calvinist nobleman who established the first Protestant academy in Poland .
Charles Hunter Corregan ( December 11 , 1860 Oswego , New York - June 1946 ) was an American printer and politician .
Nikolai Nissen Paus ( born 4 June 1877 in Christiania , died 23 December 1956 in Tønsberg ) was a Norwegian surgeon , hospital director and humanitarian .
Captain John Evered ( ca.1611 - -1668 ) , also known as Webb , was one of the first Europeans to settle what is now known as the Merrimack Valley in Massachusetts , specifically the town of Dracut , which Evered named .
Saint Edmund Gennings ( 1567 -- 10 December 1591 ) was an English martyr , who was executed during the English Reformation for being a Catholic priest .
Joseph Sturge ( 1793 -- 14 May 1859 ) was an English Quaker , abolitionist and activist .
Pietro Generali ( born Mercandetti Generali ) ( 23 October 1773 -- 3 November 1832 ) was an Italian composer primarily of operas and vocal music .
George Haworth ( 17 October 1864 -- 5 January 1943 ) was an English footballer , who helped Blackburn Rovers win the FA Cup in 1885 .
Richard Davy ( c. 1465 - -1507 ) was a Renaissance composer , organist and choirmaster , one of the most represented in the Eton Choirbook .
Ralph Scotoni ( 1901 - 1955 ) was a Swiss businessman notable for his involvement in the German film industry .
SS - Obersturmführer Irmfried Eberl ( 8 September 1910 -- 16 February 1948 ) was an Austrian psychiatrist and medical director of the euthanasia institutes in Brandenburg and Bernburg , who helped set up and was the first commandant of the Treblinka extermination camp where he worked from 11 July 1942 until his dismissal on 26 August 1942 .
Virgilia D'Andrea ( 11 February 1888 -- 12 May 1933 ) was an Italian anarchist poet and political activist .
Pierre de Molins or Molaines ( fl . 1190 - -1220 ) was an early trouvère .
Edward Wesson ( April 29 , 1910 -- 1983 ) was an English watercolour artist .
Malcolm Charles Salaman ( 6 September 1855 -- 22 January 1940 ) was an English author , journalist and critic .
Sir Geoffrey Cory - Wright , 3rd Baronet ( 26 August 1892 -- 23 March 1969 ) was the 3rd Baronet Cory - Wright .
John Cadman , 1st Baron Cadman GCMG FRS ( 7 September 1877 -- 31 May 1941 ) was a British mining engineer , petroleum technologist and public servant .
Alexander Brodie Spark ( 9 August 1792 -- 21 October 1856 ) , influential merchant , businessman and free settler of Australia , was born on 9 August 1792 at Elgin , Scotland .
Ian Niall ( November 7 , 1916 -- June 24 , 2002 ) , born John Kincaid McNeillie , was a writer from Galloway in Scotland .
Andreas Andersen Feldborg , ( 9 September 1782 - 4 August 1838 ) was an author .
Andrei Nikolaevich Mironov ( Russian : Андре́й Никола́евич Миро́нов , 31 March 1954 , Irkutsk -- 24 May 2014 , Slovyansk ) , one of the last soviet political prisoners , was a human rights activist , reporter , fixer , interpreter .
Gideon Jacques Denny ( 1830 - -1886 ) was a marine artist who was born in Wilmington , Delaware on July 15 , 1830 .
Brynjólfur Pétursson ( 15 April 1810 -- 18 October 1851 ) was an Icelandic lawyer and government official .
Solomon Gai ( 1600 -- August , 1638 ) was an Italian scholar and hebraist .
Cyriel Paul Coupé ( 28 June 1918 -- 15 June 1998 ) was a Belgian writer and poet , also known by the pseudonym Anton van Wilderode .
Leon J. Davis ( November 21 , 1905 or 1906 -- September 14 , 1992 ) was a Polish - born U.S. labor leader .
James Schouler ( March 20 , 1839 - 1920 ) , American lawyer and historian , was best known for his historical work History of the United States under the Constitution , 1789 - 1865 .
Mario Da Vinci , stage name of Alfonso Sorrentino ( 14 March 1942 -- 10 May 2015 ) was an Italian Canzone Napoletana singer and actor .
Khalida Riyasat ( 1 January 1953 -- 26 August 1996 ) was a veteran Pakistani television actress .
Raymond Blaise Des Bergères de Rigauville ( 1655 -- 21 July 1711 ) was a French soldier who became a part of the history of New France .
Alekos Sofianidis ( Greek : Αλέκος Σοφιανίδης ; 3 August 1933 , Istanbul -- 6 July 2010 , Athens ) was a Greek football player and manager .
Hadi Sabzavari ( Persian : ملا هادی سبزواری‎‎ ) or Hajj Molla Hadi Sabzavari ( 1797 - -1873 ) was a famous Iranian philosopher , mystic theologian and poet .
Cornelio Malvasia , Marquis di Bismantova ( 1603 - 1664 ) was an Italian aristocrat , patron of astronomy and military leader .
Bruce Lannes Smith ( 11 December 1909 in Webster Groves , Missouri - 1987 ) was an American political scientist and communication theorist , and also a Propaganda specialist .
John Tuchet , 8th Baron Audley , 5th Baron Tuchet ( ca . 1483 - ca . 1557 ) was an English peer .
Hans Motz ( 1 October 1909 -- 6 August 1987 ) is known for his pioneering work at Stanford University on undulators which led to the development of the wiggler and the free - electron laser .
Private Hiram T. Smith is a legendary casualty of the bloodless Maine Aroostook War , having died in 1839 .
Edwin Ardener ( 1927 - -1987 ) was a British social anthropologist and academic .
Jean - Michel - d'Astorg Aubarède ( 1639 -- 4 August 1692 ) was a canon regular and Vicar Capitular of the diocese of Pamiers .
Kevin Ayers ( 16 August 1944 -- 18 February 2013 ) was an English singer - songwriter and a major influential force in the English psychedelic movement .
Charles Marie Bonaventure du Breil , Marquis de Rays ( 2 January 1832 -- 29 July 1893 ) was a French nobleman who had ambitions of starting a great French colony in the South Pacific .
David Haworth Hill ( Manchester , 1851 -- 30 May 1926 ) was an Australian civil servant and philatelist who was appointed to the Roll of Distinguished Philatelists in 1921 .
Sir Abraham Hume , 2nd Baronet ( 29 February 1749 -- 24 March 1838 , in London ) was a British floriculturist and Tory politician .
Gustavus Hamilton , 2nd Viscount Boyne PC ( Ire ) ( 1710 -- 18 April 1746 ) was an Irish peer and politician .
Helmut Ringelmann ( 4 September 1926 -- 20 February 2011 ) was a German film and television producer .
Refuse To Bend ( 17 March 2000 -- 10 February 2012 ) was Thoroughbred racehorse and sire .
Joseph Rumshinsky ( 1881 - -1956 ) , Jewish composer born near Vilna in Lithuania ( then part of Russian Poland ) .
Sir William Uvedale ( ca . 1581 -- 1652 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1614 and 1645 .
Henry Potts ( 1810 -- 22 March 1884 ) was an English cricketer with amateur status who was active in 1831 .
Gregorio Jiménez de la Cruz ( 1972-February 2014 ) was a Mexican journalist and photographer .
George Dean ( 14 November 1867 -- 7 May 1933 ) was a ferry boat master in Sydney , Australia , who was charged with attempting to poison his wife .
Stephen Birchington ( ? - 1407 ) was a British monk and writer in the 14th Century .
Elbert Allen Drummond ( a.k.a . E.A. Drummond or Larry Drummond ) ( 1943 - 2012 ) was an American heir , businessman and philanthropist from Alabama .
Li Hongzao ( Chinese : 李鴻藻 ; 1820－1897 ) , styled Lansun ( 蘭孫 ) , pseudonym Shisun ( 石孫 ) , was a high government official towards the end of the Qing dynasty .
Eve Adler ( 29 April 1945 -- 4 September 2004 ) was an American classicist who taught at Middlebury College for 25 years until her death in 2004 .
Ernst Gustav Zaddach ( 7 June 1817 , Danzig -- 5 June 1881 , Königsberg ) was a German geologist and zoologist , who made contributions in the fields of carcinology and entomology .
Sheikh Azizur Rahman ( 2 January 1916 -- 14 May 1998 ; known as Shawkat Osman ) was a Bangladeshi novelist and short story writer .
Sidonie of Bavaria ( 1 May 1488 -- 29 March 1505 ) was a member of the House of Wittelsbach .
Alexander Berry ( 30 November 1781 -- 30 November 1873 ) was a Scottish - born surgeon , merchant and explorer who in 1822 was given a land grant of 10,000 acres ( 40 km2 ) and 100 convicts to establish the first European settlement on the south coast of New South Wales , Australia .
James VI and I ( 19 June 1566 -- 27 March 1625 ) was King of Scotland as James VI from 24 July 1567 and King of England and Ireland as James I from the union of the Scottish and English crowns on 24 March 1603 until his death .
Kishi Joō ( 929 - -985 , 徽子女王 , also Yoshiko Joō 承香殿女御 Jokyōden Joō or 斎宮女御 Saigū no Nyōgo ) was a Japanese Waka poet of the middle Heian period .
Damiano Damiani ( 23 July 1922 -- 7 March 2013 ) was an Italian screenwriter , film director , actor and writer .
Ward Edwards ( 1927 - -2005 ) was an American psychologist , prominent for work on decision theory and on the formulation and revision of beliefs .
Edward Kemys ( c.1693 - -1736 ) , of Pertholey , Monmouthshire , was a politician .
Grigory Kosykh ( Russian : Григорий Георгиевич Косых ; 9 February 1934 -- 23 February 2012 ) was a Soviet sports shooter and Olympic medalist .
Abhiyaza ( Burmese : အဘိရာဇာ ( ʔəbi̯jəzà ) ; d. 825 BCE ) was the legendary founder of the Kingdom of Tagaung , and that of Burmese monarchy , according to the 19th century chronicle Hmannan Yazawin .
Janet Ray Michie , Baroness Michie of Gallanach ( née Bannerman ; 4 February 1934 -- 6 May 2008 ) was a British speech therapist and Liberal Democrat politician .
Giacomo Tachis ( 4 November 1933 -- 6 February 2016 ) was an Italian oenologist .
Sali Verdha ( 10 January 1918 -- 31 May 2009 ) was a distinguished World War 2 veteran who joined the ranks of the anti - fascist movement `` Çeta e Pezës '' and later led the 12th Shock Brigade which fought for the liberation of Pukë and Shkodër .
Henry Wharton ( 9 November 1664 -- 5 March 1695 ) was an English writer and librarian .
Michelle Urry ( 28 December 1939 - -15 October 2006 , born Michelle Dorothy Kaplan ) was the cartoon editor of Playboy magazine for over 30 years .
John Trotter Brockett ( 1788 - 1842 ) , was a British attorney , antiquarian , numismatist , and philologist .
Guido da Vigevano or Guido da Pavia ( born c. 1280 ; died c. 1349 ) was an Italian physician and inventor .
Vilko Gecan ( 16 June 1894 -- 25 June 1973 ) was a Croatian painter , influential in the Zagreb modern art scene of the 1920s and 30s .
Barnabas Zhang ( 張巴拿巴 Pinyin : Zhāng Bānábā , 11 February 1882 - 1961 ) , was an early preacher for the True Jesus Church , an indigenous Chinese church .
Vern Daniel ( 30 May 1887 -- 27 January 1969 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Marius Mercator ( born probably in Northern Africa about 390 ; died shortly after 451 ) was a Catholic ecclesiastical writer .
Hugh Heinrick ( 1831 - 1877 ) was a journalist and teacher and a campaigner for Home Rule in Ireland .
Ada Constance Duncan ( 26 October 1896 -- 13 September 1970 ) was an Australian welfare activist .
Henry Kučera ( 15 February 1925 -- 20 February 2010 ) , born Jindřich Kučera , was a Czech linguist who pioneered corpus linguistics , linguistic software , was a major contributor to the American Heritage Dictionary , and a pioneer in the development of spell checking computer software .
Dudley Blair Menzies ( /ˈmɛnziːz/ ; January 2 , 1906 - 1995 ) was a Canadian engineer and politician .
Hugh of Evesham ( died 1287 ) was a 13th - century English churchman , physician and alchemist .
Gökhan Budak ( 1968 -- 26 January 2013 ) was a Turkish professor of quantum physics .
Bertrada of Laon ( born between 710 and 727 -- 12 July 783 ) , also known as Bertrada the Younger or Bertha Broadfoot ( cf . Latin : Regina pede aucae i.e. the queen with the goose - foot ) , was a Frankish queen .
Sarah Osborne ( also variously spelled Osbourne , Osburne , or Osborn ; née Warren , formerly Prince , born ca . 1643 -- died May 10 , 1692 ) was one of the first women to be accused of witchcraft in the Salem witch trials of 1692 .
Johanna Müller - Hermann ( 15 January 1878 -- 19 April 1941 ) was an Austrian composer and pedagogue .
Robert Casadesus ( 7 April 1899 -- 19 September 1972 ) was a renowned 20th - century French pianist and composer .
Ibrahim Tunggul Wulung ( 1800 - -1885 ) was an indigenous evangelist working in East Java , Central Java , West Java and Banten , Indonesia .
Johann Condné ( 9 January 1919 -- 26 October 2001 ) was a highly decorated Hauptmann in the Wehrmacht during World War II and a Brigadegeneral in the Bundeswehr .
Charles Cowles - Voysey was born in London , England on 24 June 1889 and died there on 10 April 1981 .
Prof . Walter Lyon Blease ( 1884 - 12 April 1963 ) , was a British Liberal Party politician , barrister and academic .
John Wallis Titt ( 1841 - -1910 ) was a late nineteenth - century mechanical engineer and builder of a particular design of large wind engine .
Doris Totten Chase ( 29 April 1923 -- 13 December 2008 ) was an American painter , teacher , and sculptor , but is best remembered for pioneering in the production of key works in the history of video art . She was a member of the Northwest School .
Fred Sleeman ( 25 March 1885 -- 13 November 1953 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Octavius Beale ( 23 February 1850 -- 16 December 1930 ) was an Irish - born Australian piano manufacturer and a philanthropist .
Kanō Einō ( 狩野 永納 , 1631 - -1697 ) was a Japanese painter of the Kyō - ganō sub - school of the Kanō school of painting .
Alty George Nunes III ( 14 July 1986 -- 7 February 2011 ) , better known by his stage name J.O.E. , and previously as Lil Joe , was a Jamaican reggae singer .
William Henry Walsh FBA FRSE ( /wɒlʃ/ ; 10 December 1913 -- 7 April 1986 ) , usually cited as W. H. Walsh , was a British philosopher .
Mateo Albéniz , also known as Mateo Antonio Pérez de Albéniz ( 1755 -- 23 June 1831 ) was a Spanish composer and priest .
Sidney Nowell Rostron ( 10 August 1883 -- 17 March 1948 ) was a Church of England priest , theologian , and academic .
Leonard Lieberman ( October 25 , 1925 -- February 6 , 2007 ) was an American anthropology professor at the Central Michigan University for forty years .
They had one son , Charles Lanham Crouch , Jr. Charles Crouch died in San Francisco on December 11 , 1957 .
Air Marshal Sir Brian Edmund Baker KBE , CB , DSO , MC , AFC ( 31 August 1896 -- 8 October 1979 ) was an officer of the Royal Air Force who served in both World Wars .
Bolko IV of Opole ( Polish : Bolko IV Opolski ; 1363/67 -- 6 May 1437 ) , was a Duke of Strzelce and Niemodlin during 1382 - -1400 ( with his brothers as co - rulers ) , Duke of Opole from 1396 ( until 1400 with his brother as co - ruler , except Olesno ) .
Charles Seymour , 2nd Baron Seymour of Trowbridge ( c. 1621 -- 25 August 1665 ) was the son of Francis Seymour , 1st Baron Seymour of Trowbridge , whom he succeeded in the barony in 1664 .
James Fischer ( December 27 , 1927 -- July 3 , 2004 ) was an American engineer , who developed high - purity silicon technology for Texas Instruments .
Sir Clive Bourne ( 27 September 1942 , Stoke Newington , London - 10 January 2007 , Nevis , West Indies ) was a British businessman and philanthropist , particularly known for his work on city academies .
Francisco Luís Gomes ( Konkani : फ़्रान्सिस्को लूईस गोमॆस ) ( Goa , Portuguese India , 31 May 1829 -- Atlantic Ocean , 30 September 1869 ) was a Portuguese physician , writer , historian , economist , political scientist and MP in the Portuguese parliament .
George Hamilton Green , Jr. ( May 23 , 1893 -- 1970 ) was a xylophonist , composer , and cartoonist born in Omaha , Nebraska .
James Kitson , 1st Baron Airedale PC , DSc ( 22 September 1835 -- 16 March 1911 ) was a British politician of the Liberal Party , first a Member of Parliament and then a peer .
Gerry Marshall ( 16 November 1941 -- 21 April 2005 ) was a British saloon car racing driver , and , according to a 2002 magazine poll , one of the best drivers of all time .
Oscar Werner Tiegs FRS FAA ( 12 March 1897 -- 5 November 1956 ) was an Australian zoologist whose career spanned the first half of the 20th century .
Matt Price ( 15 October 1961 -- 25 November 2007 ) was a Western Australian journalist and newspaper columnist .
Gino Cervi ( Italian pronunciation : ( ˈdʒino ˈtʃɛrvi ) ; 3 May 1901 -- 3 January 1974 ) was an Italian actor .
Frutolf of Michelsberg ( died 17 January 1103 ) was a monk in Michelsberg Abbey in Bamberg , Germany , of which he became prior .
Frederick William Collard ( baptised 1772 , died 1860 ) was a British piano manufacturer .
André Marcel Desoutter ( 31 January 1894 - -13 April 1952 ) was an English aviator , who lost a leg in an early flying accident , but went on to a successful career in the aviation industry .
Þórbergur Þórðarson ( Thorbergur Thordarson ) ( Hali í Suðursveit , 12 March 1888/1889 -- Reykjavík , 12 November 1974 ) was an Icelandic author and Esperantist .
Francis John Savile Foljambe ( 9 April 1830 -- 5 February 1917 ) was a British Liberal member of parliament .
Galceran de Requesens y Santa Coloma ( before 1426 - 1465 ) , a Catalan nobleman , was an enemy of the Barcelona city council ( an oligarchic power group then known as La Biga , comprising the nobility and major merchants of the city ) , and was Governor of Mallorca .
Fulco Luigi Ruffo - Scilla ( 6 April 1840 -- 29 May 1895 ) was a Cardinal of the Holy Roman Church .
Nicolas Chauvin de Lafreniere ( died 26 October 1769 ) was Attorneys General of Louisiana .
Salah al - Din al - Sabbagh ( Arabic : صلاح الدين الصباغ ; l889 - 1945 ) was an Iraqi Army officer and Arab nationalist that led the Golden Square group which had opposed the government at the time and had highly influenced politics between the years of 1939 to 1941 .
Angiola Teresa Moratori Scanabecchi ( 1662 -- 19 April 1708 ) was an Italian composer and painter .
Colonel Stephen Terrell OBE TD DL QC ( 15 June 1916 -- 16 August 2004 ) , was a British barrister and Liberal Party politician .
Dolsi - naa Alhaji Abubakari Lunna ( died in 2009 ) was a Ghanaian music teacher , drum - maker , and performer of Dagbon music and dance .
Ingebjørg Øisang , née Guldahl ( 5 May 1892 - 2 May 1956 ) was a Norwegian politician for the Labour Party .
Herman Nicolas Ventje Sumual ( 11 June 1923 -- 28 March 2010 ) was a military officer involved in the Indonesian National Revolution .
Edoardo Monteforte or Eduardo Monteforte ( Polla , Province of Salerno 1849 -- Naples , 1933 ) was an Italian painter .
Remigius de Fécamp ( sometimes Remigius ; died 7 May 1092 ) was a Benedictine monk who was a supporter of William the Conqueror .
Benjamin Lett ( 14 November 1813 - -9 December 1858 ) was an Anglo - Irish - Canadian filibusterer who was a disciple of William Lyon Mackenzie .
Francisco Javier de Viana ( 1764 - -1820 ) , Argentine sailor and soldier , actively participated in the politics of his country as an ally of general Carlos María de Alvear .
Aben Kandel ( 15 August 1897 - 28 January 1993 ) was an American screenwriter , novelist , and ( earlier in life ) boxer .
Michael Dahl died in London on 20 October 1743 and was buried a week later in St James 's Church , Piccadilly .
Most Reverend Sir Peter Kurongku , KBE ( 1930 -- 11 June 1996 ) was Roman Catholic Archbishop of Port Moresby , Papua New Guinea .
Thomas Henry Fitzgerald ( 1 December 1824 -- 10 November 1888 ) was a pioneer in sugar cane farming in the early days of the colony of Queensland , Australia .
Adolf Ulrik Wertmüller ( February 18 , 1751 -- October 5 , 1811 ) was a Swedish painter whose notable works include Danaë receiving Jupiter in a Shower of Gold .
Wing - Commander John Scott - Taggart OBE , MC ( 1897 -- 1979 ) was a British radio engineer who served with distinction in both World Wars , applying his technical expertise firstly in radio , and then in radar , to the war efforts .
Federico Aldrovandi ( 17 July 1987 , Ferrara - 25 September 2005 , Ferrara ) was an Italian student , who died from injuries received during an arrest by four policemen .
Peter Pelham ( ca . 1695 -- December 1751 ) , American limner and engraver , was born in England , a son of a man named `` gentleman '' in his will .
James Stroudley , A.R.C.A ( 1906 - -1985 ) was an English painter and printmaker .
Verna Erikson ( 1893 - -1918 ) is a Finnish woman whose picture , taken when she was a weapon smuggler ( shown on the right ) was an icon of White Finland .
Raul Loya ( born Raul Bejarano Loya ; 30 June 1938 - 1 April 2015 ) was a Mexican - American workers ' rights activist , known for his association with Cesar Chavez and the National Farm Workers Association .
Shitao ( simplified Chinese : 石涛 ; traditional Chinese : 石濤 ; pinyin : Shí Tāo ; Wade -- Giles : Shih T'ao ) ; ( 1642 - -1707 ) , born Zhu Ruoji ( 朱若極 ) was a Chinese landscape painter and poet during the early part of the Qing Dynasty ( 1644 - -1911 ) .
Henry Power FRS ( 1623 - -1668 ) was an English physician and experimenter , one of the first elected Fellows of the Royal Society .
Elisabeth Dmitrieff ( real name : Elizabeta Luknichna Tomanovskaya ( née Kusheleva ) ; Russian : Елизавета Лукинична Томановская ( née Кушелева ) ; 1 November 1850 , Volok , now in Toropetsky District , Tver Oblast -- 1910 or 1918 ) was a Russian - born feminist and actress of the 1871 Paris Commune .
Oreste Vaccari ( 1886 - 1980 ) was an Italian Orientalist and linguist .
António Júlio da Costa Pereira de Eça GCIC ( Lisbon , 31 March , 1852 -- 6 November 1917 ) - commonly known as Pereira d'Eça - was a general of the Portuguese Army , a colonial administrator colonial and minister of War ( 1914 - 1915 ) .
James Goldwell ( died 15 February 1499 ) was a medieval Dean of Salisbury and Bishop of Norwich .
Alfred Perceval Graves ( 22 July 1846 -- 27 December 1931 ) , was an Anglo - Irish poet , songwriter and folklorist .
Samuel Sutton Rawlinson ( 1809 - 18 July 1880 ) was an architect and engineer based in Nottingham .
Ibrahim Sultan ibn Shahrukh ( Persian : ابراهيم سلطان بن شاهرخ‎‎ ) was a Timurid prince who governed a region around modern Fars from 1415 to 1435 under his father Shahrukh .
Langford Peel ( 1831 - -1867 ) , also known as Farmer Peel was a gunman in the American Old West .
Aniruddha Mahathera ( Devanagari : अनिरुद्ध महाथेरा ) ( born Gaja Ratna Tuladhar ) ( 15 December 1915 -- 17 February 2003 ) was a Nepalese Buddhist monk and the Sangha Nayak ( Patriarch ) of Nepal from 1998 until his death in 2003 .
Ludwig Lore ( June 26 , 1875 -- July 8 , 1942 ) was an American socialist magazine editor , newspaper writer , lecturer , and politician , best remembered for his tenure as editor of the socialist New Yorker Volkszeitung and role as a factional leader in the early American communist movement .
Michael Mellinger ( 30 May 1929 -- 17 March 2004 ) was a German actor who appeared mainly in British films and television shows .
Tunku Kurshiah binti Almarhum Tunku Besar Burhanuddin ( 16 May 1911 -- 2 February 1999 ) was the former Tunku Ampuan Besar or Queen of Negeri Sembilan .
Sir Richard Gresham ( c.1485 -- 21 February 1549 ) was an English mercer , Merchant Adventurer , Lord Mayor of London , and Member of Parliament .
Reverend Dr. H. Dale Jackson ( 7 December 1930 -- 15 February 2003 ) was a Baptist minister , denominational leader and ethicist .
Pavol Adami ( Slovak ) , Adámi Pál ( Hungarian ) , Paul Adami ( German ) ( 9 July 1739 in Beluša -- 21 September 1795 ) was a Slovak scientist and scholar , considered one of the world 's first veterinarians .
Richard Ryve ( also Reve ) ( d. 1594 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1560 to 1594 .
Hans Jørgen Uldall ( 1907 Silkeborg , Denmark -- 1957 Ibadan , Nigeria ) was a Danish linguist known for developing the linguistic theory of glossematics with Louis Hjelmslev .
Gilberto Rincón Gallardo y Meltis ( 15 May 1939 -- 30 August 2008 ) was a Mexican politician , activist and former presidential candidate .
Jovita González ( January 18 , 1904 -- 1983 ) was a Mexican American folklorist , educator , and writer , best known for writing Caballero :
Howard Fowler ( 20 October 1857 -- 6 May 1934 ) was an English sportsman who played international rugby union for England and first - class cricket .
Major General George Alan Vasey CB , CBE , DSO & Bar ( 29 March 1895 -- 5 March 1945 ) was an Australian Army officer .
Selden Connor Gile ( 20 March 1877 -- 8 June 1947 ) was an American painter who was mainly active in northern California between the early-1910s and the mid-1930s .
Johan Herbert Magnus Härenstam ( 19 June 1941 -- 13 June 2015 ) was a Swedish television host , actor and comedian .
Odd Roar Lofterød ( born 8 April 1947 , died 14 September 2012 ) is a Norwegian sailor .
John II of Legnica ( Polish : Jan II Legnicki ) ( 1477 -- 6 March 1495 ) was a Duke of Legnica since 1488 until his death ( with his brothers as co - ruler ) .
Reza Hosseini ( 8 May 1960 -- 19 August 2003 ) was a relief worker who was killed in the Canal Hotel bombing in Iraq .
José Palma y Velasquez ( 3 June 1876 -- 12 February 1903 ) was a Filipino poet and soldier .
Robert Nuttall ( 1 May 1908 -- 10 January 1983 ) was an English footballer who played as a wing half or as a centre forward .
William Henley Pearson - Jervis ( 1813 - -1883 ) was an English cleric and ecclesiastical historian of France .
Joshua Routledge ( 1773 - -1829 ) was an engineer and inventor during the late 18th and early 19th centuries when the Industrial Revolution was in full swing .
Aqif Pasha Elbasani ( 1860 or 1861 -- 1926 ) , also referred as Aqif Pashë Elbasani , Aqif Pashë Biçaku , Aqif Pashë Biçakçiu , was an Albanian political figure .
Albert Henry Payne ( 14 December 1812 in London -- 7 May 1902 in Leipzig ) was a steel engraver , painter and illustrator .
Danilo Stojković ( Serbian Cyrillic : Данило Стојковић ; 11 August 1934 -- 16 March 2002 ) , commonly nicknamed Bata ( Бата ) , was a Serbian theatre , television and film actor .
Isidor Grunfeld ( 1900 - -1975 ) , also known by his Hebrew name Yishai ha - Kohen Grunfeld , was a dayan ( rabbinical judge ) and author who was associated with the London Beth Din ( rabbinical court ) .
Paul Luty ( 4 May 1932 -- 12 January 1985 ) was an English wrestler who later became a film and television actor .
Ignacio Ponseti ( 3 June 1914 -- 18 October 2009 ) was a Spanish physician , specializing in orthopedics .
William Oswald Whitridge ( 14 August 1853 -- 12 February 1919 ) was an Australian Test Cricket umpire .
Gottfried VIII , Count of Ziegenhain ( after 1350 -- 1394 ) was a German nobleman .
Alberto Migré , pseudonime of `` Felipe Alberto Milletari Miagro '' ( 12 September 1931 , Buenos Aires -- 10 March 2006 ) was an Argentine TV screenwriter and producer , specialized on telenovelas .
Georges Mora ( 1913 - -1992 ) was a German - born Australian entrepreneur , art dealer , patron , connoisseur and restaurateur .
Marie - Aurore - Lucienne Gagnon , simply known as Aurore Gagnon ( 31 May 1909 -- 12 February 1920 ) , was a Canadian girl who was a victim of child abuse .
Ronald Cass ( 21 April 1923 -- 2 June 2006 ) was a British screenwriter and a composer .
Howard Kendall ( 22 May 1946 -- 17 October 2015 ) was an English footballer and manager .
Lieutenant General Sir Leicester Smyth ( formerly Curzon - Howe ) KCB KCMG ( 25 October 1829 -- 27 January 1891 ) was Governor of Gibraltar .
Harry Clifford Fassett ( 1870 - -1953 ) worked for the United States Fish Commission and later the United States Bureau of Fisheries .
Mehmet Arif Bey ( 1882 -- 13 July 1926 ) , also known as `` Ayıcı '' Arif ( `` The Bear - leader '' ) , was an officer of the Ottoman Army and the Turkish Army .
Herbert Clarence Randle ( 31 July 1906 -- 7 August 1976 ) , known as Harry Randle , was an English footballer who played professionally for clubs including Southend United , Accrington Stanley and Gillingham , for whom he made 110 Football League appearances .
Jessie Broughton ( 29 March 1885 -- 1938 ) was an English contralto and actress .
Major - General Francis John Fowler CB DSO died on the 5 June 1939 .
Thorunn Ormsdottir ( Þórunn Ormsdóttir ) ( died 1431 ) was the abbess of the Benedictine convent Reynistaðarklaustur in Iceland 1402 - -1431 .
Garci Lasso de la Vega I , also known as `` el Viejo '' ( d. 1326 , Soria ) was a Spanish noble in the service of King Alfonso XI of Castile .
Hieronymus Albrecht Hass ( variants Haas , Hasse , Hase , Hasch ) ( 1 December 1689 - 19 June 1752 ) ( dates of baptism and burial ) was a German harpsichord and clavichord maker .
Joyce Allan ( 8 April 1896 -- 31 August 1966 ) was an Australian conchologist , museum curator at the Australian Museum and a scientific illustrator .
Gavriil Marinakis ( Greek : Γαβριήλ Μαρινάκης , c. 1826 - 1866 ) was the hegumenos of Arkadi Monastery and a fighter of the Cretan Revolution of 1866 .
Saint Gerlach ( Gerlache , Gerlac , Gerlachus van Houthem , Gerlac of Valkenberg ) ( d. c. 1170 AD ) was a 12th - century Dutch hermit .
Georg Hermann Alexander Ochs ( 11 July 1887 -- 27 September 1971 ) was a German entomologist , specialising in Coleoptera and in particular the Gyrinidae .
Theresa Ducharme ( 1945 -- June 7 , 2004 ) was a Canadian disability rights activist and a perennial candidate for public office .
James Moncreiff , 1st Baron Moncreiff FRSE ( 29 November 1811 -- 27 April 1895 ) was a Scottish lawyer and politician .
Tom Gilson ( New York City , New York ; January 6 , 1934-Van Nuys , California ; October 6 , 1962 ) was an American actor in TV and occasional films from the 1950s , who was shot dead by his wife , model and actress Sandra Edwards , on October 6 , 1962 .
Mr. Pieter Philip van Bosse ( 16 December 1809 -- 21 February 1879 ) was a Dutch liberal politician .
Mary Katherine Herbert ( also known as Maureen ) ( 1 October 1903 , Ireland -- 23 January 1983 ) was a member of the Special Operations Executive ( SOE ) during World War II and worked as a courier for the French Section .
James Harmer ( 1777 - -1853 ) was an English solicitor , involved in the investigation of miscarriages of justice , radical politics , and local government in London , where he served as an alderman .
Thomas Robinson , 2nd Baron Grantham PC ( 30 November 1738 -- 20 July 1786 ) was a British politician and statesman .
Admiral Sir Richard Goodwin Keats ( 16 January 1757 -- 5 April 1834 ) was a British naval officer who fought throughout the American Revolution , French Revolutionary War and Napoleonic War .
Ruaidrí Ó Gadhra , was an Irish king of Sliabh Lugha and Chief of the Name , died 1256 .
Leutnant zur See Otto Wolfgang Zenker ( 1898 -- 5 November 1918 ) was a German officer killed during World War I. He was an officer on the battleship SMS König and was murdered by rebel sailors during the Wilhelmshaven mutiny together with Bruno Heinemann .
Alrutheus Ambush Taylor ( 1893 - -1955 ) was an African - American historian from Washington D.C ..
Elsa - Marianne von Rosen ( 21 April 1924 -- 7 September 2014 ) was a Swedish ballet dancer , choreographer and actress .
Samuel Prescott ( August 19 , 1751 -- c. 1777 ) was a Massachusetts Patriot during the American Revolutionary War .
Joseph Fennell ( 16 March 1835 at Cobourg , Upper Canada -- February 1919 ) was an Anglican priest .
Stig Ossian Ericson ( 7 September 1923 - 30 July 2012 ) was a Swedish actor , director , and screenwriter .
Joseph Dupuis ( 1789 - -1874 ) was appointed as Consul and Vice - Consul for the British Government between 1811 and 1842 , with various postings to Africa during that period , including one as Vice - Consul in Mogador .
Arturo Licata ( 2 May 1902 -- 24 April 2014 ) was an Italian supercentenarian , who lived until the age of 111 years , 357 days .
Munif al - Razzaz ( 1919 - 1984 ) was a Syrian political figure who was the second , and last , Secretary General of the National Command of the Arab Socialist Ba'ath Party , having been elected to the post at the 8th National Congress held in April 1965 .
Agop Jack Hacikyan ( 25 November 1931 -- 3 July 2015 ) was a Canadian university Emeritus Professor of Literary Studies , historian , academic and writer .
Pietro Sambi ( 27 June 1938 -- 27 July 2011 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic prelate who served in the Vatican 's Secretariat of State .
Janko Bobetko ( 10 January 1919 -- 29 April 2003 ) was a Croatian Army general and Chief of the General Staff during the Croatian War of Independence from 1992 until his retirement in 1995 .
Peter Woodthorpe ( 25 September 1931 -- 12 August 2004 ) was an English film , television and voice actor who supplied the voice of Gollum in the 1978 Bakshi version of The Lord of the Rings and BBC 's 1981 radio serial .
Ernest Read ( 22 February 1879 -- 9 October 1965 ) was an English conductor , organist , and music educator .
Francisco Diaz de Cabrera y Córdoba ( 1534-July 5 , 1606 ) was a Roman Catholic prelate who served as the Bishop of La Plata o Charcas ( 1605 - 1606 ) and the Bishop of Quito ( 1592 - 1605 ) .
Mychajlo Dmytrenko ( 1908 - -March 8 , 1997 ) was a Ukrainian - American painter of world recognition .
Sir Charles Cornwallis Lloyd , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1706 -- 25 February 1729 ) was a British aristocrat .
Sir Claude Hotchin OBE ( 7 March 1898 -- 3 June 1977 ) was a businessman and art dealer , patron and benefactor in Western Australia .
Ruth Bedford ( 2 August 1882 -- 24 July 1963 ) was an Australian poet , playwright and fiction writer .
Wilhelm August Thams ( June 22 , 1812-July 4 , 1884 ) was a Norwegian merchant and mill owner .
John Heminges ( sometimes spelled Heming or Heminge ) ( bapt . 25 November 1556 -- 10 October 1630 ) was an actor in the King 's Men , the playing company for which William Shakespeare wrote .
Alonso Muñoz de Gadea ( 1630s-1708 ) was a Spanish noblemen , Contador , Procurador , Mayordomo and Administrador general of the Church of Buenos Aires during the viceroyalty of Peru .
Damian Sawczak ( 1847 - -1912 ) was a Ukrainian judge in Halychyna ( Zalishchyky , Khodoriv , Husiatyn ) .
Jaime Ovalle or Jayme Ovalle ( Belem do Pará , 1894 - -1955 ) was a Brazilian composer and poet .
Austin Diamond ( 10 July 1874 -- 5 August 1966 ) was a cricketer who played for New South Wales in first - class cricket .
Šaban Bajramović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Шабан Бајрамовић , Serbian pronunciation : ( ʃǎban bajrǎːmɔʋitɕ ) , Romani : Shaban Bajramovičh ; 16 April 1936 -- 8 June 2008 ) , nicknamed Šabi ( Шаби ) , was a Serbian - Romani musician , known popularly as the `` King of Romani music '' .
William Henry Lansing ( 7 March 1914 -- 11 June 1942 ) born in Amsterdam , New York , enlisted in the United States Naval Reserve on 14 February 1933 .
Gordon Muortat Mayen Maborjok ( 1922 - -2008 ) was a South Sudanese veteran politician and a struggler for the rights and freedom of the South Sudanese people .
Oswald Rantucci ( 1907 - -1988 ) was a highly respected Classical Guitar teacher at The State University of New York at Buffalo , for whom the Rantucci International Guitar Festival & Competition is named .
Edward Ashe ( ca . 1609 -- 31 October 1656 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1652 .
Rabbi Moses Berlin ( 1852 - 1927 ) was a prominent British Reform Jewish rabbi .
Raymond Francis ( 6 October 1915 -- 24 October 1987 ) was an English actor best known for his role as Detective Chief Superintendent Tom Lockhart in the Associated - Rediffusion detective series Murder Bag , Crime Sheet and No Hiding Place .
Anthony Tailboyes ( died 1584 ) , of Skirmington , County Durham , was an English politician .
Pius Sack ( 3 December 1865 -- 5 February 1946 ) was a German entomologist who specialised in Diptera His collection of World Diptera is conserved in Naturmuseum Senckenberg .
Simon Ramsay , 16th Earl of Dalhousie KT GCVO GBE MC DL ( 17 October 1914 -- 15 July 1999 ) , styled The Honourable Simon Ramsay between 1928 and 1950 , was a British land owner , Conservative politician and colonial governor .
Sir Charles Richard Vaughan , GCH , PC , ( 20 December 1774 -- 15 June 1849 ) was a British diplomat .
Brebis Bleaney CBE FRS ( 6 June 1915 -- 4 November 2006 ) was a British physicist .
Eivind Astrup ( 17 September 1871 -- 27 December 1895 ) was a Norwegian explorer and writer .
Jaime Sáenz Guzmán ( 29 October 1921 -- 16 August 1986 ) was a Bolivian poet , novelist , and short story writer .
Dr William Smoult Playfair LLD ( 1835 - -1903 ) was a Scottish obstetric physician .
Herbert Kilpin ( 24 January 1870 -- 22 October 1916 ) was an English football pioneer , player and manager .
Robert Menli Lyon ( 1789 - -1874 ) was a pioneering Western Australian settler who became one of the earliest outspoken advocates for Indigenous Australian rights and welfare in the colony .
Albert Heber Longman ( 24 June 1880 -- 16 February 1954 ) , also often referred to as Heber Longman or Heber Albert Longman , was an Australian newspaper publisher and museum director of British origin .
Sayf al - Din al - Amidi ( also known as Muhammad al - Amidi ) ( died 1233 ) was an influential jurist of the Shafi`i school who worked to combine kalam ( theology ) with existing methods of jurisprudence .
George Opperman ( 1935 - -1985 ) was a graphic artist at Atari who created the original Atari logo and created the art for Atari 's coin - op cabinets and backglass artwork for Atari pinball games , such as Airborne Avenger and Superman .
Edward Bramwell Clarke ( 31 January 1874 -- 28 April 1934 ) was an educator in Meiji period Japan , who is credited with introducing the sport of rugby to Japan .
Robert Marsham ( 27 January 1708 -- 4 September 1797 ) was an English naturalist considered to be the founding father of phenology , the study of the effects of the seasons on plants and animals .
George Leeke ( died 30 March 1939 ) was an Irish nationalist politician .
André Boillot ( 8 August 1891 -- 5 June 1932 ) was a French auto racing driver .
Wyndham Meredith Manning ( 1890 - -1967 ) was a South Carolina politician and the scion of a political dynasty in that U.S. state .
Ahmet Anzavur ( 1885 - 15 April 1921 ) was a gendarme officer in the Ottoman Empire .
Hong Rengan ( Chinese : 洪仁玕 ; pinyin : Hóng Réngān ; Wade -- Giles : Hung Jen - kan ; 1822 -- 23 November 1864 ) was an important leader of the Taiping Rebellion .
Robert M. Holley ( 1913 - 1977 ) was a well - known U.S. cartoonist , commercial artist , and advertising executive .
Sébastien Le Balp ( born 1639 , Kergloff , died 1675 ) was a Breton politician .
