Gonzalo Aguirre Beltrán ( January 20 , 1908 , Tlacotalpan , Veracruz--1996 , Xalapa , Veracruz ) was a Mexican anthropologist known for his studies of marginal populations .
Bahij al - Khatib ( Arabic : بهيج الخطيب‎ ) ( 1895 - -1981 ) was a French - appointed Syrian Head of State from July 10 , 1939 to September 16 , 1941 .
Philip Walsted was a 24-year - old gay man in who was robbed and beaten in downtown Tucson , Arizona , on June 12 , 2002 .
Lewis Henry Haney ( March 30 , 1882 - -July 1 , 1969 ) was a conservative American economist , professor , and economic columnist .
Sir John Douglas , 3rd Baronet of Kelhead ( circa 1708 -- 13 November 1778 ) was Member of Parliament for Dumfriesshire between 1741 and 1747 .
José de Almeida de Ávila ( Horta , 28 October 1844 -- Lisbon , 30 October 1902 ) was an official in the Portuguese Marines , obtaining the post of Captain , colonial administrator , Governor of Quelimane and Lourenço Marques , as well as the Civil Governor of the district of Horta ( between 1894 and 1895 ) .
Card Mondor ( 1922 - 2001 ) was an Australian magician and stage performer .
Gao Zhizhou ( 高智周 ) ( 602 - -683 ) was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as chancellor during the reign of Emperor Gaozong .
Alexa Wilding ( born Alice Wilding , c. 1845 - -48 -- 25 April 1884 ) was one of the favourite models of the Pre - Raphaelite artist Dante Gabriel Rossetti , featuring in some of his finest paintings of the later 1860s and early 1870s .
Antonio Barbalonga or Barbalunga ( 1600 -- 2 November 1649 ) , also called Antonio Alberti , was an Italian painter of the Baroque period .
John Freemantle ( 1758 , probably at Bishop Sutton , Hampshire -- 3 August 1831 at Alresford , Hampshire ) was an English cricketer who played for the legendary Hambledon Club .
André Prokovsky ( 13 January 1939 -- 15 August 2009 ) was a Franco - Russian ballet dancer , choreographer , and company director .
Eliza Bridell Fox , née Eliza Florance Fox ( 1824 -- 1903 ) , was a British painter .
David Branson ( February 1963 -- 11 December 2001 ) was an Australian theatre director , actor , and writer .
Mihovil Pavlek Miškina ( 1887 , Đelekovec , Kingdom of Croatia - Slavonia -- 1942 ) was a Croatian poet , short story writer and politician .
James Charles Fahey ( 1903 - -1974 ) was an American author best remembered as the original compiler and publisher of the popular American reference The Ships and Aircraft of the United States Fleet .
Patrick Horsbrugh ( 21 June 1920 -- 12 January 2014 ) was a British architecture professor .
John Berwick Harwood ( 1828 -- 15 February 1899 ) was an English writer , best known for his ghost stories .
Alfonsas Dargis ( 1909 May 12 Reivyčiai , Mažeikiai parish -- 1996 January 13 Friedrichshafen , Baden - Wurttemberg land , buried in Friedrichshafen cemetery ) was a Lithuanian painter , graphic artist , set designer and poet .
Gustaf Vilhelm Carlberg ( 5 April 1880 -- 1 October 1970 ) was a Swedish Army officer and sports shooter .
Wequash Cooke ( also known as : Wequash Cook or Weekwash or Weekwosh or Wequashcuk ) ( died 1642 ) was allegedly one of the earliest Native American converts to Protestant Christianity , and as a sagamore he played an important role in the 1637 Pequot War in New England .
Danby Palmer Fry ( 1818 - -1903 ) was an English official and barrister , known as a legal writer .
Norah Lindsay ( née Bourke ) ( 26 April 1873 -- 20 June 1948 ) was a socialite garden designer who between the World wars became a major influence on garden design and planting in the United Kingdom and on the Continent .
Ted Blake ( 19 October 1921 -- 6 March 1998 ) was an early British trampoline pioneer .
Jorge Pepe ( 1939 - -2006 ) was an Argentine plastic artist and painter .
Phil McCumisky ( 28 May 1897 - 2 August 1970 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Richard Marpole ( 1850 in Wales -- 8 June 1920 , in Vancouver , Canada ) was General Superintendent with the Canadian Pacific Railway Pacific Division in Vancouver .
C. N. S. Iyengar ( - died 1972 ) was an Indian professor of mathematics and the founder head of the department of mathematics , Karnatak University , Dharwar .
Carl Wilhelm Kahlo Kauffmann ( 26 October 1871 -- 14 April 1941 ) , commonly known as Guillermo Kahlo , was a German - Mexican photographer .
Dame Phyllis Friend , DBE , FRCN ( 28 September 1922 -- 24 June 2013 ) was a British nursing officer .
Said Seyam ( Arabic : سعيد صيام‎‎ ; 22 July 1959 -- 15 January 2009 ) , first name also spelled Saeed and Sayed and last name also spelled Siam , was the interior minister of the Palestinian government of March 2006 .
Thomas Chettle ( died c 1640 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1614 .
Johann Gottlieb Stephanie the Younger ( 19 February 1741 -- 23 January 1800 ) was an Austrian playwright , director and librettist , most famously to Mozart .
Sally Douglas ( 30 November 1941 -- September 2001 ) was a glamorous British supporting actress of the 1960s and 1970s .
Amram Blau ( 1894 - -1974 ) was a Haredi rabbi from the Hungarian community of Jerusalem .
Anacarsis Lanús ( Concepción del Uruguay , Entre Ríos , Nov 14 1820 -- Oct 14 1888 ) was an Argentine entrepreneur .
Craig Sellar Lang ( 13 May 1891 -- 24 Nov 1971 ) was a New Zealand - born British organist , composer and music teacher .
Ivey Foreman Lewis ( August 31 , 1882 -- March 16 , 1964 ) was an American botanist and geneticist who served for two decades as dean of the University of Virginia and was a founder of the Virginia Academy of Science .
Vice - Admiral Lambert Jackson Woodburne DVR SD SM SAN ( 13 July 1939 -- 5 July 2013 ) was Chief of the South African Navy from 1 July 1990 to 31 August 1992 .
Thomas Foley , 2nd Baron Foley FRS ( 1703 -- 8 January 1766 ) was the eldest son of Thomas Foley , 1st Baron Foley and inherited the vast Great Witley estate on his father 's death in 1733 , including ironworks at Wilden and Shelsley Walsh .
Devarakonda Balagangadhara Tilak ( 21 August 1921 -- 1 July 1966 ) was an influential Telugu poet , novelist and short story writer .
Michael Aldred ( 6 July 1945 - 15 April 1995 ) was a British record producer and music journalist .
Denise Moore ( sometimes reported as Deniz Moore ) , was the pseudonym of E. Jane - Wright ( 1876 -- 21 July 1911 ) .
Nicolas Vignier ( 1530 - -1596 ) was a French lawyer , historian and theologian .
Louis Leloir ( 1911 - 1992 ) , originating from Namur , Belgium was a Benedictine professed at the Abbey of Clervaux , Luxemburg .
Emil Lindenfeld ( 1905 -- 1986 ) was a Hungarian - American oil - painter .
Nathan Cooper Branwhite ( c. 1775 -- 18 March 1857 ) was an English miniature portrait painter , watercolourist and engraver who was a member of the Bristol School of artists .
Max Elitcher ( 1918 - -2010 ) was a prosecution witness in the Julius and Ethel Rosenberg trial in 1951 .
Robert Hornmede ( died 1409 ) , of Guildford , Surrey , was an English politician .
George Hastings , 1st Earl of Huntingdon ( 1488 -- 24 March 1544 ) was an English nobleman .
Sybold van Ravesteyn ( born Sijbold van Ravesteijn , 18 February 1889 , Rotterdam -- 23 November 1983 , Laren ) ) was a Dutch architect .
Isidro Sánchez García - Figueras ( 17 December 1936 -- 2 September 2013 ) , known simply as Isidro , was a Spanish footballer who played as a right back .
Rev. Richard Lynch Cotton ( 14 August 1794 -- 8 December 1880 ) was a British vicar and academic administrator at the University of Oxford .
Arnaldo Mecozzi ( 1876 in Frascati , Italy - Santos , Brazil 1932 ) was an Italian decorator and painter .
Margaret Hoard ( ca . 1880 - 1944 ) American sculptor and painter born in Washington , Iowa .
Ulrich of Hardegg ( German : Ulrich von Hardegg or Ulrich von Hardeck or Ulrich zu Hardegg auf Glatz und i m Marchlande ; after 1483 -- 1535 ) was an Austrian nobleman from the Prüschenk family of Count of Hardegg .
William Wesley Cornell ( 1823 - -1870 ) was an industrialist and philanthropist from New York and the namesake of Cornell College in Iowa .
William Bannerman ( born November 5 , 1841 , in Kildonan , Sutherland , Scotland -- 1914 ) was a Scottish - born Canadian politician .
Mipham Chokyi Lodro ( 27 October 1952 - 11 June 2014 ) , also known as Kunzig Shamar Rinpoche , was the 14th Shamarpa of the Karma Kagyu school of Tibetan Buddhism .
Major General Sir George Kenneth Scott - Moncrieff KCB KCMG CIE ( 1855 - 1924 ) was a Scottish soldier and engineer .
James Stanley , 10th Earl of Derby PC ( 3 July 1664 -- 1 February 1736 ) , styled The Honourable until 1702 , was a British peer and politician .
Tivadar Filótás ( 1903 -- 2 August 1945 ) was a Hungarian modern pentathlete .
George Edmundson ( 4 February 1848 -- 3 July 1930 ) was a clergyman of the Church of England and academic historian of the University of Oxford .
Lionel Giles ( 29 December 1875 -- 22 January 1958 ) was a British scholar and translator .
Captain Joshua Allen , 5th Viscount Allen ( 26 April 1728 -- 1 February 1816 ) was an Irish peer .
Tacfarinas ( Latinised form of Berber Tiqfarin , died AD 24 ) was a Numidian deserter from the Roman army who led his own Musulamii tribe and a loose and changing coalition of other Ancient Libyan tribes in a war against the Romans in North Africa during the rule of emperor Tiberius ( AD 14 - 37 ) .
Jacques Delarüe - Caron de Beaumarchais ( 1913 - 1979 ) was French Ambassador to the United Kingdom from 1972 until 1977 .
Heriberto Lazcano Lazcano ( 25 December 1974 -- 7 October 2012 ) , commonly referred to by his aliases Z-3 and El Lazca , was a Mexican drug lord and the leader of Los Zetas drug cartel .
Scilla Sclanizza ( 1926 - 2006 ) was an Italian screen and stage actress , who later dedicated her life to educational theatre and puppeteering .
Anton Elschnig ( August 22 , 1863 -- 1939 ) was an ophthalmologist born in Leibnitz , Austria .
Jeremiah Hess Barr ( 1876 - 1955 ) , of Pennsylvania , was a stamp collector who was active in collecting and writing on philately .
Malcolm Hughes ( 22 July 1920 -- 19 September 1997 ) was a British constructive artist .
Stepan Pobodailo ( Ukrainian : Степан Пободайло ; died 1654 ) was a Ukrainian Cossack leader .
George Bradford Brainerd ( 1845 - 1887 ) was a civil engineer , an amateur photographer , and an amateur natural historian .
Michael Hamburger OBE ( 22 March 1924 -- 7 June 2007 ) was a noted British translator , poet , critic , memoirist and academic .
Layal Najib , also Romanized Nagib , Nejib or Najeeb , ( died 23 July 2006 ) was a Lebanese photojournalist for Al Jaras ( Translated : The Bell ) and the first journalist killed during the 2006 Lebanon War .
Ulrich Ochsenbein ( 24 November 1811 , Unterlangenegg - 3 November 1890 ) was a Swiss politician and member of the Swiss Federal Council ( 1848 - 1854 ) .
Sir George Barne II was the Sheriff of London between 1545 - -1546 , Lord Mayor of London in 1552 , Alderman of the London wards Portsoken between 1542 - -1546 and Coleman Street between 1546 - -1558 , a chief proponent of trade with Russia , and son of George Barne , a citizen of London and alderman .
Maurice Owen ( 4 July 1924 -- 8 July 2000 ) was an English former professional footballer who scored 150 goals in 555 appearances in the Football League playing for Swindon Town .
Alasdair Caimbeul or Alexander Campbell of Carco ( died February 1608 ) was a Scottish noble and prelate .
Thomas Taplin Cooke ( 1782 - -1866 ) was an eminent English showman , born in Warwick , who toured in America as well as his own country .
Gu Yanlang ( 顧彥朗 ) ( d. 891 ) was a warlord late in the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty who controlled Dongchuan Circuit ( 東川 , headquartered in modern Mianyang , Sichuan ) from 887 to his death in 891 as its military governor ( Jiedushi ) .
Saint John of Egypt ( ? - 394 ) , also known as John the Hermit or John the Anchorite ( Latin : Iohannes anchorita ) , was one of the hermits of the Nitrean desert .
Georges Merle ( 1851 - -1886 ) was a French painter known for his outstanding command of the female form .
Sir Edward Hussey , 3rd Baronet ( ca . 1662 - 1725 ) , of Caythorpe , Lincolnshire , was an English politician .
Kavignar Meenavan ( Tamil : கவிஞர் மீனவன் , 9 January 1933 -- 22 August 2012 ) , born R.K. Narayanasamy , was a Tamil poet , writer and activist .
Jean Pierre Ginnett ( died 1861 ) founded the Ginnett circus dynasty .
Sylvain Dupuis ( 9 October 1856 -- 28 September 1931 ) was a Belgian conductor , composer , oboist , and music educator .
Henry Hemphill ( 1830 - -1914 ) was an American malacologist , a biologist who studies mollusks .
Ya'akov Meridor ( Hebrew : יעקב מרידור‎ , born Yaakov Viniarsky on 29 September 1913 , died 30 June 1995 ) was an Israeli politician , Irgun commander , and businessman .
Alena Kish ( Belarusian : Алена Андрэеўна Кіш , 1889 or 1896 -- 1949 ) was a Belarusian primitivist painter from the surroundings of Slutsk .
Bishop Emanuel Galea continued his pastoral activities to the last days of his life ; he passed peacefully away on 21 August 1974 after a short illness at the venerable age of 83 years .
Simon bar Giora ( alternatively known as Simeon bar Giora or Simon ben Giora or Shimon bar Giora ; died 70 CE ) was the leader of a rebel faction during the First Jewish - Roman War in 1st - century Judea .
Hughie Mulligan ( died 1973 ) was a New York mobster and bookmaker who headed criminal activities of the `` Irish Mob '' in Hell 's Kitchen during the 1950s .
Dr. Sebastian Poulter , who died in 1998 , was a distinguished legal scholar , and an advocate of ethnic diversity and its recognition and warning against discrimination and islamophobia .
Samuel Philip Sadtler , Ph.D. , LL.D. ( July 18 , 1847 - -December 20 , 1923 ) was an American chemist , and the first President of the American Institute of Chemical Engineers in 1908 .
V. S. Malimath ( 12 June 1929 -- 22 December 2015 ) was a Chief Justice of Kerala and Karnataka .
Charles Francis Keary ( 1848 - -1917 ) was born in Stoke - on - Trent , England , and he became a scholar and historian .
Huilgol Narayana Rao ( Kannada : ಹುಯಿಲಗೋಳ ನಾರಾಯಣರಾಯ ) ( October 4 , 1884 - July 1971 ) was a popular playwright in the modern Kannada literature and a freedom fighter .
Jackson Burke ( San Francisco , California 1908 - 1975 ) was an American type and book designer .
George Mathison ( 24 November 1909 -- 19 April 1989 ) was an English footballer who made 140 appearances in the Football League playing for Newcastle United , Lincoln City and Gateshead .
Jacob Panken ( January 13 , 1879 -- February 4 , 1968 ) was an American socialist politician , best remembered for his tenure as a New York municipal judge and frequent candidacies for high elected office on the ticket of the Socialist Party of America .
Francesco Flarer ( 27 November 1791 -- 22 December 1859 ) was an Italian ophthalmologist born near Merano , South Tyrol .
Thomas Willement ( 18 July 1786 - -10 March 1871 ) was an English stained glass artist , called `` the Father of Victorian Stained Glass '' , active from 1811 to 1865 .
The elder , Eugène Louis Gabriel Ferry de Bellemare ( November 1809 Grenoble - 3 January 1852 ) , wrote adventure novels .
Lydia Lopokova , Baroness Keynes ( born Lidia Vasilyevna Lopukhova ) ( Russian : Ли́дия Васи́льевна Лопухо́ва ; 21 October 1892 -- 8 June 1981 ) was a famous Russian ballerina during the early 20th century .
Tommy Gallacher ( 1922 -- 2001 ) was a Scottish footballer in the late 1940s and 1950s .
Ricard Ó Cuairsge Bourke , 7th Mac William Iochtar , died 1473 .
Alfred Septimus Dowling ( 1805 - -1868 ) was a British law reporter .
Jan Walter Susskind ( 1 May 1913 -- 25 March 1980 ) was a Czech - born British conductor , teacher and pianist .
Colonel William Vere Reeve King - Fane OBE , DL ( 29 October 1868 -- 5 November 1943 ) was a member of the Fane family an English landowner , soldier and High Sheriff of Lincolnshire .
Octavien de Saint - Gelais ( 1468 - -1502 ) was a French churchman , poet , and translator .
Francis Baird ( 1802 - -1864 ) was an engineer of Scottish ancestry in St. Petersburg , who took over his father 's flourishing business manufacturing machinery , ships , and metalwork for some of the city 's major structures .
Lois Rodden ( 22 May 1928 - 5 June 2003 ) was an astrologer , astrological data collector and founder of Astrodatabank .
Cyril Davies ( 23 January 1932 -- 7 January 1964 ) was a blues musician and one of the first British blues harmonica players .
Thomas Cundy III ( Thomas de Candie * 17 October 1821 -- + 4 November 1895 ) joined his father 's practice in the 1840s and was also surveyor of the Grosvenor Estate .
Gerhard Thomsen ( 23 June 1899 -- 4 January 1934 ) was a German mathematician , probably best known for his work in various branches of geometry .
Alexandra Elene MacLean Denny ( 6 January 1947 -- 21 April 1978 ) -- known as Sandy Denny -- was an English singer and songwriter , perhaps best known as the lead singer for the folk rock band Fairport Convention .
Rolf Moe ( 24 September 1917 -- 11 December 1999 ) is a Norwegian engineer and civil servant .
Johan Gustaf Renat ( 1682 - -1744 ) was a Swedish soldier and cartographer .
Simone Peterzano ( c. 1540 - c. 1596 ) was an Italian painter of the later Mannerism , native of Bergamo .
Armando Filiput ( 19 December 1923 -- 30 March 1982 ) was an Italian hurdler , European Champion in 1950 .
Ben - Zion Halfon ( Hebrew : בן - ציון חלפון‎ , 1930 -- 21 September 1977 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the Alignment between 1969 and 1977 .
Jerzy Hryniewski ( ˈjɛʐɨ xrɨˈɲɛfski ) ( 29 December 1895 -- 15 March 1978 ) was a Polish politician , who is best known for serving as Prime Minister of the Polish Government in Exile from 18 January to 13 May 1954 .
William Woolls ( 30 March 1814 -- 14 March 1893 ) was an Australian botanist , clergyman and schoolmaster .
Piero Giorgio Bordoni ( Rome , 18 July 1915 -- 19 September 2009 ) was an Italian physicist , who first measured the anelastic relaxation effect ( dissipation of elastic energy and softening of the elastic modulus ) , named after him , due to the stress induced motion of dislocations in metals .
Agenore Incrocci ( 4 July 1919 -- 15 November 2005 ) , best known as Age , was an Italian screenwriter , considered one of the fathers of the commedia all'italiana as one of the two members of the duo Age & Scarpelli , together with Furio Scarpelli .
Henry John Moberly , also known as Harry or Harvey ( 1835 - -1931 ) was a fur trader .
Göran Tunström died in his home in Stockholm 5 February 2000 .
Leo Kirch ( 21 October 1926 -- 14 July 2011 ) was a German media entrepreneur who founded the Kirch Group .
John Kenworthy B.Sc . , F.R.Aes ( 1883 - -1940 ) was an English aviation engineer and aircraft designer .
Jacques de Noyon ( 1668 -- 1745 ) was a French Canadian explorer and coureur des bois .
Kaarlo Toivo Aronen ( 4 June 1886 , Pori - 1 November 1973 ) was a Finnish construction worker and politician .
Arthur Haygarth ( 4 August 1825 -- 1 May 1903 ) was a noted amateur cricketer who became one of cricket 's most significant historians .
Rabin Ghosh ( 1932 - -2010 ) , a 20th - century violin virtuoso of ' Seni - Maihar ' Gharana ( Seni - Maihar School of thoughts ) of North Indian Classical Music , India , was a disciple of Baba Ustad Allauddin Khan Saheb .
Georg Ludwig Maurer , since 1831 Georg Ludwig von Maurer ( 2 November 1790 -- 9 May 1872 ) was a German statesman and legal historian from the Electoral Palatinate .
François Joseph de Choiseul , marquis de Stainville ( 1700 - -1770 ) was a diplomat and courtier in the service of the Dukes of Lorraine .
Baroness Hedwig of Sierstorpff - Driburg ( German : Freiin Sophia Bernardina Luise Friederika Hedwig von Sierstorpf - Driburg ; 22 November 1848 -- 10 January 1900 ) was the maternal grandmother of Prince Bernhard of Lippe - Biesterfeld , Prince consort of Queen Juliana of the Netherlands .
Major general Welbore Ellis Doyle ( 1758 - -1797 ) was the 3rd Military Governor of British Ceylon .
Robert Anthony Welch ( 25 November 1947 -- 3 February 2013 ) was an Irish author and scholar .
Sarah Mulvey ( 13 May 1974 -- 28 January 2010 ) was a British commissioning editor and television producer .
Nicholas Fastolf ( died 1330 ) was an English - born judge who was one of the leading figures of the early Irish judiciary ; according to some sources he was the first judge to hold the office of Lord Chief Justice of Ireland .
Lynsey de Paul ( born Lyndsey Monckton Rubin ; 11 June 1948 -- 1 October 2014 ) was an English singer - songwriter .
Julius Stjernvall ( 26 October 1874 -- 6 May 1939 ) was a Finnish engineer , businessman and vuorineuvos .
Ben Homer ( 27 June 1917 , Meriden , Connecticut -- 12 February 1975 , Los Angeles , California ) was an American songwriter , composer and arranger .
Suleyman Sani Akhundov ( Azeri : Süleyman Sani Axundov ) ( 3 October 1875 -- 29 March 1939 ) was an Azerbaijani playwright , journalist , children 's author , and teacher .
William Erwin Antony ( died 1964 ) was an electrical engineer and pioneer in radio and television transmission .
Henry Anderton ( 1630 -- 1667 ) was an English painter , mainly known for his portraits .
Freeman Harrison Owens died on 9 December 1979 in Pine Bluff , at the age of 89 , and is buried at Bellwood Cemetery in his hometown of Pine Bluff , Arkansas .
Isaac Selby ( 3 November 1859 -- 26 March 1956 ) was an Australian lecturer , historian and anti - Catholic campaigner .
Salomon Schweigger ( also spelled Solomon Schweiger ) ( 30 March 1551 -- 21 June 1622 ) was a German Lutheran theologian , minister , anthropologist and orientalist of the 16th century .
Tilly Kettle ( 1735 - -1786 ) was a portrait painter and the first prominent English portrait painter to operate in India .
Yahballaha II bar Qayyoma was Patriarch of the Church of the East from 1190 to 1222 .
Brigitte Helm ( 17 March 1906 -- 11 June 1996 ) was a German actress , best remembered for her dual role as Maria and her double , the Maschinenmensch , in Fritz Lang 's 1927 silent film Metropolis .
Matthew Henry Phineas Riall Sankey ( 9 November 1853 -- 3 October 1926 ) , CB , CBE , RE was an Irish - born engineer and captain in the Royal Engineers , known as the creator of the Sankey diagram
Nathan Alcock ( September 1707 -- 8 December 1779 ) was an English physician .
Sir Everard Fawkener ( 1694 - -1758 ) was an English merchant and diplomat .
Ioan Maniu ( 1833 - 1895 ) was a Transylvanian Romanian lawyer , politician and journalist .
Carl Gustav Valdemar Ræder ( 16 July 1837 -- 21 December 1887 ) was a Danish farmer and writer .
Wilson Briggs ( 15 July 1942 -- 2005 ) was a Scottish former footballer who played in the Football League for Aston Villa .
Henry Robertson ( 11 June 1816 -- 22 March 1888 ) was a Scottish mining engineer and prolific railway builder , industrialist and Liberal Party politician .
James Annesley , 2nd Earl of Anglesey FRS ( c. 1645 -- 1 April 1690 ) , styled Lord Annesley from 1661 to 1686 , was a British peer .
Juan Escoto ( 1894 - -1975 ) was a Mexican children 's book author and politician .
Sir John Melton ( died 1640 ) was an English merchant , writer and politician .
Frederic Gregory Mather ( born in Cleveland , Ohio , 11 August 1844 ; died in Stamford , Connecticut , 30 August 1925 ) was a United States journalist .
Sir John Russell Reynolds , 1st Baronet ( 22 May 1828 -- 29 May 1896 ) was a British neurologist and physician .
Carl Robert Ehrström ( 1803 - -1881 ) was a Finnish medical doctor , bacteriologist and archaeologist .
Sachin Sengupta ( 1891 - 1961 ) was a prominent Bengali playwright and the producer and director of theatrical plays in Calcutta , India .
Lynton Lamb RDI , FSRA , FSIA ( 15 April 1907 - 4 September 1977 ) was an English artist - designer , Author , lithographer and illustrator who was notable for his book jacket , poster , architectural decoration and postage stamp designs .
Sergey Voychenko ( Belarusian : Сяргей Войчанка , Siarhiej Vojchanka ; Russian : Серге́й Войченко ) ( 15 November 1955 -- 9 December 2004 ) was a Belarusian artist and designer known for his creative posters and photography art work together with his partner Vladimir Tsesler .
Roland Groome ( 1890s in the United Kingdom -- 20 September 1935 ) was a Canadian aviator from Regina , Saskatchewan , Canada .
Thomas Porter McMurray ( 5 December 1887 , Belfast -- 16 November 1949 , London ) was a British orthopaedic surgeon remembered for describing the McMurray test .
Sir Edward Lewis Brockman ( 1865 - 1943 ) was the chief secretary to the Federated Malay States from 1911 - 1920 .
Clive Charles ( 3 October 1951 -- 26 August 2003 ) was an English football player , coach and television announcer .
James Wardrop FRSE FRCSEd FRCS ( 1782 - -1869 ) was a Scottish surgeon and ophthalmologist .
David Gvantseladze ( Georgian : დავით გვანცელაძე ; Russian : Давид Гванцеладзе ; 28 March 1937 -- 1 May 1984 ) was a Georgian wrestler .
Zhao Ziyang ( pronounced ( ʈʂâʊ tsɨ̀jǎŋ ) ; 17 October 1919 -- 17 January 2005 ) was a high - ranking politician in China .
Blessed Irene Stefani ( 22 August 1891 - 31 October 1930 ) , born Aurelia Mercede Stefani , was a Roman Catholic Italian nun and a member of the Consolata Missionary Sisters .
Henry Savery ( 4 August 1791 -- 6 February 1842 ) was a convict transported to Port Arthur , Tasmania and Australia 's first novelist .
Antoni Bolesław Dobrowolski ( 6 June 1872 , in Dworszowice Kościelne -- 27 April 1954 , in Warsaw ) , was a Polish geophysicist , meteorologist and explorer .
Ève Curie died in her sleep on 22 October 2007 in her residence on Sutton Place in Manhattan , aged 102 .
James Howard , 3rd Earl of Suffolk , Earl Marshal ( 10 February 1606/1607 -- 7 January 1688 ) , was grandson of Thomas Howard , 1st Earl of Suffolk , and was himself 3rd Earl of Suffolk and 3rd Baron Howard de Walden .
George Kemp , 1st Baron Rochdale CB ( 9 June 1866 - -24 March 1945 ) was a British politician , soldier , businessman and cricketer .
Bono Benić ( 1708 , Čatići near Kakanj - 27 March 1785 , Kraljeva Sutjeska ) was a Franciscan from Bosnia , provincial of the Franciscan Province of Bosna Srebrena and a historian .
John R. Rathom ( 1868 - -1923 ) was a journalist , editor , and author based in Rhode Island at the height of his career .
Arthur Cartlidge ( 12 June 1880 -- 1940 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Aston Villa and Stoke as well as spending seven years at Bristol Rovers .
Ernest Irving ( 6 November 1878 -- 24 October 1953 ) was an English composer and conductor , primarily remembered for his involvement in film music .
St George Daly ( 1758 -- December 1829 ) was an Irish judge , who had a reputation for ignorance .
Carilef ( French Calais , Latin Calevisus ; died 541 ) was a hermit who founded the monastery of Aniole .
Giacinto de Popoli ( died 1682 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , active near his natal city of Orta di Atella in the Province of Caserta .
Jean - Baptiste Assiginack ( 1768 - 3 Nov. 1866 ) was an Ojibwe leader in the early 19th - century .
Antonio Valverde y Cosío ( 1670 - -1728 ) was a prominent entrepreneur and Spanish soldier who served as interim governor of Santa Fe de Nuevo México in 1716 and from 1718 - -1721 .
Big Walter Price ( 2 August 1914 − 7 March 2012 ) was an American blues singer , songwriter and pianist .
Willem Key ( c. 1515 -- 5 June 1568 ) was a Flemish renaissance painter .
Alexander Andrae ( 27 April 1888 -- 3 April 1979 ) , whose first name is often mistakenly given as Waldemar , was a German military officer from Kösling , Upper Silesia .
George Keith , 5th Earl Marischal ( c.1553 - 1623 ) was a Scottish nobleman and Earl Marischal .
Pieter de Ruelles ( 1630 in Amsterdam -- 1658 in Amsterdam ) , was a Dutch Golden Age landscape painter who died young .
Dimitris Nikolaidis ( Greek : Δημήτρης Νικολαΐδης ; 1922 -- 21 January 1993 ) was a Greek actor .
António Osório Sarmento de Figueiredo , Jr. ( Santa Marta de Penaguião , 13 March 1855 -- Lisbon , 19 May 1935 ) was a Portuguese nobleman , jurist , politician and magistrate .
Geoffrey Faithfull B.S.C. , ( 28 January 1893 - 1 December 1979 ) was a British cinematographer who worked on more than 180 feature films from starting in the industry in the 1910s .
Roundell Palmer , 1st Earl of Selborne PC ( 27 November 1812 -- 4 May 1895 ) , was a British lawyer and politician .
Philip N. Krasne ( born 6 May 1905 in Norfolk , Nebraska , United States , died 18 September 1999 , age 94 , Los Angeles , California , United States ) was an attorney who became a motion picture and television producer .
Nathaniel Butter ( died 22 February 1664 ) was a London publisher of the early 17th century .
William D. Gordon ( 1858 - -1917 ) was a politician and attorney from Michigan who served as United States Attorney for the Eastern District of Michigan from 1898 to 1906 , and who had previously served in the Michigan House of Representatives , and as Speaker of the House during the 38th and 39th Legislatures .
William Dewsbury ( ca . 1621 - -1688 ) was Quaker minister in the early period of the movement .
Paul Lorrain ( died 7 October 1719 ) was , for twenty - two years , the secretary , translator , and copyist for Samuel Pepys , and became well known as the Ordinary ( chaplain ) of Newgate Prison by standardising the publication of the gallows confessions of condemned prisoners .
Michael Scaife ( 24 March 1948 -- 18 December 2001 ) was a British biologist , psychologist , and reader at the University of Sussex , known for his early work in developmental psychology and his later interdisciplinary study in cognitive and computing sciences .
Edward Walford ( 1823 - -1897 ) was a British magazine editor and a compiler of educational , biographical , genealogical and touristic works , perhaps best known for his 6 Volumes of Old and New London ( the first two of which were written by Walter Thornbury ) , 1878 .
Richardson Pack ( 1682 - -1728 ) was an English professional soldier and writer .
Cleng Peerson ( 17 May 1783 -- 16 December 1865 ) was a Norwegian - American pioneer who led the first group of Norwegians to emigrate to the United States , traveling on the Norwegian sloop Restauration .
Johannes Messenius ( 1579 - -1636 ) was a Swedish historian , dramatist and university professor .
Thomas Woodbine Hinchliff ( 5 December 1825 -- 8 May 1882 ) was an English mountaineer , traveller , and author , from 1875 to 1877 the seventh President of the Alpine Club .
Lojze Krakar ( 26 February 1926 -- 24 December 1995 ) was a Slovene poet , translator , editor , literary historian , and essayist .
Thomas Marlay ( c.1680 - -1756 ) was an Irish politician and judge , who ended his career as Lord Chief Justice of Ireland .
Maikash Akbarabadi ( 1902 - -1991 ) was a writer in the Urdu language .
John Victor Emms ( 1912 - -1993 ) was an English landscape painter , who worked chiefly in oils and watercolours .
Mariana Levy ( 22 April 1966 -- 29 April 2005 ) was a Mexican telenovela actress , singer and television show host .
Kh Ghulam Haider Gagroo ( February 1912 -- 11 November 1975 ) , also known as Qaiser Kishtwari , was a Magistrate in Kashmir who composed poetry in the Kashmiri and Urdu languages .
Lieutenant General Sir Lewis Pelly , KCSI ( 14 November 1825 -- 22 April 1892 ) was Conservative Member of Parliament for Hackney North from 1885 to 1892 and an East India Company officer .
Paul V. Roberts ( November 27 , 1938 - February 2006 ) was a prominent environmental engineer .
Hon'inbō Dōchi ( 本因坊道知 , 1690 - -1727 ) was a professional Go player .
Julio Nudler ( 16 December 1941 -- 27 July 2005 ) was an Argentine economic journalist .
Nikolai Nikolayevich Durnovo ( Russian : Никола́й Никола́евич Дурново́ ; 4 November ( O.S. 23 October ) 1876 -- 27 October 1937 ) was a Russian linguist .
Živko Stojsavljević ( 1 October 1900 , Benkovac , Kingdom of Dalmatia -- 19 January 1978 , Belgrade ) was a Serbian painter who received his first painting lessons in Zadar high school , and he continued his education in Italy .
Zhang Yao'er ( 章要兒 ) ( 506 - -570 ) , formally Empress Xuan ( literally `` the responsible empress '' ) , was an empress of the Chinese Chen Dynasty .
Frederik Heidmann ( 27 July 1777 -- 17 October 1850 ) was a Norwegian military officer , civil servant and politician .
Pavlos Tassios ( Greek : Παύλος Τάσσιος ; 1 April 1942 -- 2 October 2011 ) was a Greek film director .
Fincath mac Garrchu ( or Findchad mac Garrchon ) ( died 485 ) was a king of Leinster .
William Hooke ( 1612 - 1652 ) was the governor of New Somersetshire in North America , appointed by Sir Ferdinando Gorges .
Geng Bingwen ( Chinese : 耿炳文 ) ( 1334 - 1403 ) was a Ming dynasty general .
Matthew White Ridley , 4th Viscount Ridley KG GCVO TD DL ( 29 July 1925 -- 22 March 2012 ) , was a British nobleman .
Oliver Sheldon ( 1894 - -1951 ) was a director of the Rowntree Company in York , in the UK .
Xiao Daqi ( 蕭大器 ) ( 524 - -551 ) , courtesy name Renzong ( 仁宗 ) , formally Crown Prince Ai ( 哀太子 , literally `` the lamentable crown prince '' ) , was a crown prince of the Chinese dynasty Liang Dynasty .
Geoffrey I of Villehardouin ( French : Geoffroi Ier de Villehardouin ) ( c. 1169 -- c. 1229 ) was a French knight from the County of Champagne who joined the Fourth Crusade .
John William Stokes , also known as Jack Stokes ( 1 February 1910 -- 3 August 1995 ) was an Australian administrator in the Northern Territory Police , and on the Territories of the Cocos ( Keeling ) Islands and of Christmas Island .
Macarthur Job ( 10 April 1926 in Taree , New South Wales -- 6 August 2014 in Melbourne ) was an Australian aviation writer and air safety consultant .
William Thomas Nugent , 5th Baron Nugent of Riverston , 29 September 1773 - 6 September 1851 .
Piers Butler , 8th Earl of Ormond and 1st Earl of Ossory ( c. 1467 -- 26 August 1539 ) , also known as ( Irish Piers Ruadh ) Red Piers , was from the Polestown branch of the Butler family of Ireland .
Gabrielle Pizzi ( 1940 -- 5 December 2004 ) was an Australian art dealer who promoted Aboriginal art from the Western Desert from the early 1980s .
Tadeusz Żyliński ( 4 November 1904 in Vilnius -- 11 September 1967 in Łódź ) was a Polish technician , textilist and mechanical engineer .
James William Scallion ( 14 February 1842 - 24 April 1926 ) was an Irish - born Canadian teacher , farmer and agrarian activist .
Gillis van Tilborch or Gillis van Tilborgh ( c. 1625 -- c. 1678 ) was a Flemish painter who worked in various genres including portraits , ' low - life ' and elegant genre paintings and paintings of picture galleries .
Alfred Garth Jones died of pneumonia on 6 July 1955 in Queen Mary 's Hospital , Sidcup aged 82 .
John Capon , alias John Salcot ( died 1557 ) was a Benedictine monk who became bishop of Bangor , then bishop of Salisbury under Henry VIII . He is often referred to as John Salcot alias Capon ( variously spelt ) .
Suleiman Arabiyat ( 1938 -- 23 October 2013 ) was a Jordanian academic , politician and writer .
Venmani Achhan Nambudiripad ( 1817 - 1890 ) , also known as Venmani Parameshwaran Nambudiripad was a famous poet of Malayalam .
Michalis Genitsaris ( Greek : Μιχάλης Γενίτσαρης or Γεννήτσαρης ) ( 15 June 1917 -- 11 May 2005 ) was a Greek singer and composer of the rebetiko genre .
James Main Dixon FRSE ( 1856 , Paisley -- 27 September 1933 ) was a Scottish teacher and author , and an important scholar of the Scots language .
Mankada Ravi Varma ( 4 June 1926 -- 22 November 2010 ) was an Indian cinematographer and director who worked in Malayalam cinema .
Dauid mac Tanaide Ó Maolconaire , Ollamh Síol Muireadaigh , died 1419 .
Andrew Roth ( 23 April 1919 , New York City -- 12 August 2010 ) was a biographer and journalist known for his compilation of Parliamentary Profiles , a directory of biographies of British Members of Parliament , a small sample of which is available online in The Guardian .
Robert Dougall , MBE ( 27 November 1913 -- 19 December 1999 ) was an English broadcaster and ornithologist , mainly known as a newsreader and announcer .
Charles Félix Jean - Baptiste Camerata - Passionei di Mazzoleni ( 20 September 1826 -- 4 March 1853 ) was a French - Italian aristocrat born in Ancona , the son of Filippo Camerata - Passionei di Mazzoleni , an Italian count , and Princess Elisa Napoléone Baciocchi , the daughter of Felice Baciocchi Levoy and Elisa Bonaparte .
Frans Francken III ( 1607 - -1667 ) was a Flemish Baroque painter and the best known member of the fourth generation of the Francken family of artists .
Harold Desbrowe - Annear ( 16 August 1865 -- 22 June 1933 ) was an influential Australian architect who was at the forefront of the development of the Arts and Crafts movement in this country .
Louise Shropshire ( 15 February 1913 -- 1993 ) was an African American composer of hymns .
Anna Maria Fox ( 21 February 1816 -- 18 November 1897 ) was a promoter of the Royal Cornwall Polytechnic Society and the artistic and cultural development of Falmouth in Cornwall , UK .
Arthur Rylands Lowe ( 22 June 1873 -- 31 May 1924 ) was a British accountant and also the first full - time professional accountant in Hon Kong .
Chetthathirat ( Thai : เชษฐาธิราช ) or Borommaracha II ( บรมราชาที่ 2 ; c. 1613 -- 1629 ) was the eldest son of King Song Tham and older brother of King Athittayawong , all three of the House of Sukhothai .
Gervaise of Bazoches ( died May 1108 ) , Prince of Galilee and Lord of Tiberias , was a crusader on the First Crusade .
Carl Schotten ( 12 July 1853 -- 9 January 1910 ) was a German chemist who , together with Eugen Baumann , discovered the Schotten - Baumann reaction .
William Borough ( 1536 - -1599 ) was a British naval officer and the younger brother of Stephen Borough .
Susan Fuentes ( 1 November 1954 -- 7 September 2013 ) was a Filipino singer known as the `` Queen of Visayan Songs '' .
George Dryden Wheeler , Sr . ( 6 June 1863 - 21 April 1939 ) , known as Leo Dryden , was an English music hall singer and vocal comic .
The Rt Revd Archibald Rollo Graham Campbell CBE ( 18 February 1903 - 11 April 1978 ) was an Anglican Bishop in the mid 20th century .
George Leigh Cooke ( baptised 1779 -- 1853 ) was a mathematician and priest who held the position of Sedleian Professor of Natural Philosophy at the University of Oxford for over 40 years .
Jeong Mun - bu ( 1565 - -1624 ) was a Korean statesman and patriot .
Ludo Martens ( 12 March 1946 -- 5 June 2011 ) was a Belgian political activist noted for his work on francophone Africa and the Soviet Union .
Isaac ben Meir ( c. 1090 -- c. 1130 ) , also known as the Rivam after his Hebrew acronym , was a French rabbi and one of the Baalei Tosafos .
Marcel Regamey ( 1905 - -1982 ) was a Swiss essayist and journalist from the Canton of Vaud .
Commander Willoughby Shortland RN ( 30 September 1804 -- 7 October 1869 ) was a British naval officer and colonial administrator .
Pietro Respighi S.T.D. JUD ( 22 September 1843 -- 22 March 1913 ) was an Italian Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church and Archpriest of the Basilica of St. John Lateran .
Colonel Sir James William Greig CB , KC , VD ( 31 January 1859 -- 10 June 1934 ) was a British barrister and Liberal Party politician .
Edward Cohen ( 1822 -- 13 April 1877 ) was an Australian merchant and a Victorian colonial politician .
Gregorio Lazzarini ( 1657 -- 10 November 1730 ) was an Italian painter of mythological , religious and historical subjects , as well as portraits .
Don Mosey ( 4 October 1924 -- 11 August 1999 ) was a sports journalist and radio producer , best remembered for his lengthy tenure as a cricket commentator on BBC 's Test Match Special ( TMS ) , which he joined in 1974 and left in 1991 .
Edward Howard , 2nd Earl of Carlisle ( 27 November 1646 -- 23 April 1692 ) , known as Viscount Morpeth from 1661 to 1685 , was an English Whig politician .
John de Derlington ( John of Darlington ) ( died 1284 ) was an English Dominican , Archbishop of Dublin and theologian .
Colonel John Granville , 1st Baron Granville of Potheridge PC ( 12 April 1665 -- 3 December 1707 ) , styled The Honourable John Granville until 1703 , was an English soldier , landowner and politician .
Giovanni Priuli ( or Prioli , ca . 1575 - -1626 ) was an Italian composer and organist of the late Renaissance and early Baroque periods .
Ambrose Caliver ( 1894 - 1962 ) changed the face of black education on a national scale .
Carl Magnus von Hell ( 8 September 1849 -- 11 December 1926 ) was the German chemist who discovered , together with Jacob Volhard and the Russian chemist Nikolay Zelinsky , the Hell--
Conrad Ferdinand Meyer ( 11 October 1825 -- 28 November 1898 ) was a Swiss poet and historical novelist , a master of realism chiefly remembered for stirring narrative ballads like `` Die Füße i m Feuer '' ( The Feet in the Fire ) .
Vincenzo Petagna ( Naples , 17 January 1734 -- 6 October 1810 ) was an Italian biologist and physician , and a director of the Monte Oliveto botanical gardens .
Janet Sobel ( 1894 - -1968 ) was a Ukrainian - American artist whose career started in mid - life and was brief , falling into the shadows of Lee Krasner and Jackson Pollock .
Langdon Warner ( 1881 - -1955 ) was an American archaeologist and art historian specializing in East Asian art . He was a professor at Harvard and the Curator of Oriental Art at Harvard 's Fogg Museum .
Miroslav Zei ( 25 July 1914 -- 2 November 2006 ) was a Slovene biologist , specialist in marine biology , oceanography and ichthyology .
Obaku Dokuryu ( 1596 - -1672 ) was a Japanese calligrapher , scholar , monk and artist .
Charles Alan Fyffe ( 1845 - -1892 ) was an English historian , known also as a journalist and political candidate .
Karl McKay Wiegand ( June 2 , 1873 -- March 12 , 1942 ) was an American botanist who headed the Department of Botany at Cornell University for 28 years .
Jan Elias Kikkert ( 24 June 1843 , Amsterdam - 11 April 1925 , Leiden ) was a Dutch lithographer and watercolorist , best - known for his street scenes of Leiden .
Gholamreza Khan Arkawazi ( Persian : غلامرضاخان ارکوازی‎ ) ( b. 1770 - d. 1839 ) was a famous Kurdish poet who has many verses in the gurani dialect of the Kurdish language .
Richard C. Kerens ( 1842 - -1916 ) was an American contractor and politician .
Alfred Francis James ( 21 April 1918 -- 24 August 1992 ) was an Australian publisher known for being imprisoned in China as a spy .
Friedrich Konrad Beilstein ( 17 February 1838 -- 18 October 1906 ) , Russian name `` Бейльштейн , Фёдор Фёдорович '' , was a chemist and founder of the famous Handbuch der organischen Chemie ( Handbook of Organic Chemistry ) .
Mother Mary Frances Clarke , B.V.M. ( c. 15 December 1802 -- 4 December 1887 ) was an Irish nun who founded the Catholic order of the Sisters of Charity of the Blessed Virgin Mary .
Stephen Allen Vigil ( 14 September 1952 -- 27 May 1997 ) was an American entertainer known as Steve Vigil , who in a brief career in Sweden in 1975 - 1976 broke ground which in new genres started the lengthier careers of other well known artists .
Sidney John Alexander Churchill MVO ( 1 March 1862 -- 11 January 1921 ) -- often referred to as Sidney J. A. Churchill -- was a British diplomat , art connoisseur and author .
Ann Stephens ( 21 May 1931 -- 15 July 1966 ) was a British child actress and singer , popular in the 1940s .
Karomatullo Qurbonov ( Tajik : Кароматулло Қурбонов , Persian : کرامت‌الله قربان‌اف‎ ) ( November 29 , 1961 -- October 17 , 1992 ) was a popular pop singer and composer from Tajikistan .
Fred Billington ( 1 July 1854 -- 2 November 1917 ) was an English singer and actor , best known for his performances in baritone roles of the Savoy Operas with the D'Oyly Carte Opera Company .
Lyudmila Kedrina ( née Reus ; 27 January 1961 -- 10 October 2015 ) was a Russian skier and international alpine skiing champion .
William Merrilees OBE QPM ( 24 September 1898 -- 21 August 1984 ) was Chief Constable of the Lothians and Peebles Constabulary from 1950 to 1968 .
Gertrude Constance Benson ( née Samwell ; 26 February 1864 -- 19 January 1946 ) was a British stage and film actress .
Richard Clarke Sewell ( 1803 -- 7 November 1864 ) was an English lawyer who later moved to Australia .
Saints Theodora and Didymus ( died 304 ) are Christian saints whose legend is based on a 4th - century acta and the word of Saint Ambrose .
Phebe Gibbes ( died 1805 ) was an 18th - century English novelist and early feminist .
Georg von Welling ( 1655 - -1727 ) was a Bavarian alchemical and theosophical writer , known for his 1719 work Opus mago - cabalisticum , published under the pseudonym Gregorius Anglus Sallwigt .
Iván Bassa Slovene Ivan Baša ( 11 April 1875 -- 13 February 1931 ) Slovenian Roman Catholic priest , writer and politic .
Thomas Haller Cooper , ( 29 August 1919 -- 1987 ) , also known as Tom Böttcher , was a member of the German Waffen - SS British Free Corps and former member of the British Union of Fascists .
Sir Ramanbhai Nilkanth , R.B ( Gujarati : રમણભાઈ નીલકંઠ ; 1868 - -1928 ) was a noted author of Gujarati literature .
Jan van der Bruggen ( 1649 -- c. 1699 ) was a Flemish Baroque painter and engraver .
Archelaus Smith ( 23 April 1734 - 3 April 1821 ) , was a tanner , shoemaker and early settler of Barrington , Nova Scotia .
Sir ( Albert ) Henry Self KCB , KBE ( 1890 - 1975 ) was a British civil servant .
Franz Joseph Aumann ( also Auman , Aumon ; 24 February 1728 , Traismauer -- 30 March 1797 , Sankt Florian ) was an Austrian composer .
Raphael Berdugo ( 1747 in Meknes--1821 ) , a son of Rabbi Mordecai Berdugo , was a dayan , a scholar , and one of the greatest rabbis of Morocco .
Columbus Sims ( 1829 - 1869 ) , lawyer , Colonel of California Volunteers in the American Civil War .
Vactor Tousey Chambers ( commonly V.T. Chambers ) ( 6 August 1830 , Burlington , Kentucky -- 7 August 1883 , in Covington , Kentucky ) was an American entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera , specifically , tineina .
Sture Nordin ( 11 November 1933 -- 11 October 2000 ) was a leading Swedish jazz bassist .
Roberto Mauri ( 1924 -- 12 November 2007 ) was an Italian actor , director and screenwriter .
Claire Vanhonnacker ( Waregem , 17 October 1953 -- Buggenhout , 8 November 1992 ) , also known by her artist name Claire , was a Belgian singer .
Jacques Frémin ( 12 March 1628 , Reims -- 2 July 1691 , Quebec ) was a French Jesuit missionary to New France ( Canada ) .
Caro Benigno Massalongo ( 25 March 1852 , Verona -- 18 March 1928 , Verona ) was an Italian botanist who specialized in the field of hepatocology .
Stefano Magno ( around 1499 -- 14 October 1572 ) was a Venetian chronicler .
John Brack ( 10 May 1920 -- 11 February 1999 ) was an Australian painter , and a member of the Antipodeans group .
Maria Hester Park ( née Reynolds ) ( 29 September 1760 -- 7 June 1813 ) was a British composer , pianist , and singer .
Jeanne Vertefeuille ( 23 December 1932 -- 29 December 2012 ) was a CIA officer who participated on a small team that investigated and uncovered the actions of Aldrich Ames , a notorious Cold War spy .
Giovanni Cosimo Villifranchi ( or Villafranchi , 1646 - -1699 ) was , according to Robert Lamar Weaver , `` the most productive and creative Italian comic librettist in the second half of the 17th century . ''
Vittorio Mibelli ( 18 February 1860 -- 26 April 1910 ) was an Italian dermatologist born in Portoferraio , Elba .
Henry Howard , 6th Earl of Suffolk , 1st Earl of Bindon PC ( 1670 -- 19 September 1718 ) was an English nobleman , styled Lord Walden from 1691 to 1706 .
Henri Robert ( 1899 - 1987 ) is a French perfumer and chemist , he is best known for his role as Chief Perfumer at Les Parfums Chanel from 1953 - 1978 .
Sister Christine or Christina Greenstidel ( 17 August 1866 -- 27 March 1930 ) was a school teacher , and close friend and disciple of Swami Vivekananda .
General Juan Antonio Sotillo ( 1790 - 1878 ) was a nineteenth - century military leader from Venezuela .
Mary Blood Mellen ( 1819 - 1886 ) was an American painter who was but one of several individuals ( including William Bradford , Benjamin Champney ( 1817 - -1907 ) , and George Merchant Jr. ) who studied under Fitz Henry Lane ( also called Fitz Hugh Lane ) .
Vincent Martel Deconchy ( 21 January 1768 -- 26 August 1823 ) commanded a French brigade in Spain and Italy during the Napoleonic Wars .
William Foord - Kelcey OBE ( 21 April 1854 -- 3 January 1922 ) was an English barrister , academic and cricketer who played first class cricket for Oxford University from 1874 to 1875 , for Kent from 1874 to 1883 and for MCC in 1878 .
Vasudevan Nair ( 15 June 1944 -- 20 February 2011 ) , known as Malaysia Vasudevan was a Tamil playback singer and actor in the Tamil film industry .
Isaacus Rothovius ( 1572 - -1652 ) was the bishop of Turku ( Sw . Åbo ) from 1627 - -1652 .
Isaac Rand ( 1674 - -1743 ) was an English botanist and apothecary , who was a lecturer and director at the Chelsea Physic Garden .
Grand Duke Dmitry Konstantinovich of Russia ( Russian : Димитрий Константинович ; 13 June 1860 -- 28 January 1919 ) was a son of Grand Duke Konstantin Nikolayevich and a first cousin of Alexander III of Russia .
John Farmer Healy ( 1900−1973 ) was a Jamaican - born Roman Catholic prelate who served as the Bishop of Gibraltar from 1956 to 1973 .
Agamemnon Gratzios or Gratsios ( Greek : Αγαμέμνων Γκράτσιος/Γκράτζιος , 1922 -- 11 August 1993 ) was a Greek Army officer who rose to the rank of full General , and held the posts of Chief of the Hellenic Army General Staff and of the Hellenic National Defence General Staff .
Arthur Groenouw ( 27 March 1862 - 1945 ) was a German ophthalmologist born in Bosatz , a village near Ratibor .
George Soares - Prabhu ( 17 November 1929 -- 22 July 1995 ) was an Indian Jesuit priest , Exegete and Biblical scholar of renown , particularly in the field of Indian Hermeutics of the Christian Scriptures .
Karsten Lund ( 12 November 1943 -- 27 May 2015 ) is a Danish former football ( soccer ) player , who played 310 games and scored 140 goals for Vejle Boldklub .
Walford Dakin Selby ( 1845 - -1889 ) was an English archivist and antiquary .
Amadu Wurie ( 1898 -- 13 June 1977 ) was an early Sierra Leonean educationist and politician .
Saint Sophia the Martyr ( died AD 137 ) is venerated in the Eastern Orthodox Church on September 17 .
Eric Vivian Tullett , known as Tom Tullett ( 1915 -- December 1991 ) was a renowned British Crime Journalist .
Muhammad Ali Jalali ( died 2006 ) was Governor of Paktika from the Taliban 's fall in 2001 to 2005 , when he quit for an unsuccessful run at a parliamentary seat .
Rocco Perri ( born 30 December 1887 , date of death unknown ; last seen alive 23 April 1944 ) was an organized crime figure in Ontario , Canada in the early 20th century .
Francis La Fontaine , or Topeah ( Miami : `` frost on leaves '' ) ( 1810 -- 1847 ) was the last principal chief of the unified Miami tribe , and oversaw the split into the Western and Eastern Miami tribes .
Larry Stanley ( 1896 -- 21 September 1987 ) was an Irish Gaelic footballer who played as a goalkeeper for the Kildare and Dublin senior teams .
Nick Stienstra ( 24 December 1954 - 7 June 1989 in Paramaribo ) was a Dutch - Surinamese footballer and coach .
Martin Fleischmann FRS ( 29 March 1927 -- 3 August 2012 ) was a British chemist noted for his work in electrochemistry .
Karl Brendel is the pseudonym of Karl Genzel ( 21 March 1871 -- 21 August 1925 ) , a schizophrenic outsider artist and one of the `` schizophrenic masters '' profiled by Hans Prinzhorn in his field - defining work Artistry of the Mentally Ill ( 1923 , in German ; English edition 1972 ) .
George Douglas Brown ( 26 January 1869 -- 28 August 1902 ) was a Scottish novelist , best known for his highly influential realist novel The House with the Green Shutters ( 1901 ) , which was published the year before his death at the age of 33 .
Robert Plowden ( born 27 January 1740 ; died at Wappenbury , 27 June 1823 ) was an English Jesuit priest , a firm supporter of Bishop John Milner .
George II , Prince of Waldeck and Pyrmont ( German : Georg Friedrich Heinrich Fürst zu Waldeck und Pyrmont ; 20 September 1789 -- 15 May 1845 ) was Prince of Waldeck and Pyrmont from 1813 to 1845 .
Raymond De Belser ( 17 June 1929 -- 3 October 2014 ) , pseudonym Ward Ruyslinck , was a Belgian writer .
Edmund O'Donovan ( 13 September 1844 -- 1883 ) , Irish war correspondent , was born in Dublin .
Karl Farkas ( 28 October 1893 -- 16 May 1971 ) was an Austrian actor and cabaret performer .
Edward Treacher Collins ( 28 May 1862 -- 13 December 1932 ) was an English surgeon and ophthalmologist .
Anson Dickinson ( 19 April 1779 - 9 March 1852 ) was an American painter of miniature portraits who achieved fame during his lifetime , producing a very large number of works , but who is now largely forgotten .
Dilaver Bey ( 1865 - -1919 ) was the Mayor of Edirne , Turkey from 1898 to 1903 and from 1907 to 1910 .
James Bathe ( c.1500 - -1570 ) was an Irish judge of the Tudor age , who was notable for his service as Chief Baron of the Irish Exchequer for thirty years under four successive monarchs .
Giora Shanan ( 5 May 1908 -- 9 November 2001 ) , Palmach member from 1941 .
Sir James Emerson Tennent , 1st Baronet FRS ( 7 April 1804 -- 6 March 1869 ) , born James Emerson , was a Northern Irish politician and traveller .
Helmut Dantine ( 7 October 1917 -- 2 May 1982 ) was an Austrian - born American actor who often played Nazis in thriller films of the 1940s .
Florence Helena McGillivray ( 1864 - -1938 ) , Associate of the Royal Canadian Academy of Arts , Ontario Society of Artists , was a Canadian painter , known especially for her landscape paintings .
Two years later , in 1447 , Lekë Zaharia was killed in an ambush and Lekë Dukagjini was accused for this murder .
Rodney Hill FRS ( 11 June 1921 -- 2 February 2011 ) was an applied mathematician and a former Professor of Mechanics of Solids at Gonville and Caius College , Cambridge .
Joseph Olita ( March 31 , 1944 -- 1 June 2014 ) was a Kenyan actor who was best known for portraying Idi Amin in Rise and Fall of Idi Amin ( 1981 ) and Mississippi Masala ( 1991 ) .
Edward Smedley ( 1788 - -1836 ) was an English clergyman known as a miscellaneous writer .
Adet Lin ( Chinese : 林鳳如 ; pinyin : Lín Fèngrú ; Wade -- Giles : Lin Feng - ju ; May 6 , 1923 -- 1971 ) was a Chinese - American writer and translator .
Sir Richard Musgrave , 1st Baronet ( 1585 - 6 November 1615 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1604 to 1611 .
Edward Nason West ( 1909 - -1990 ) was an Episcopal priest , author and canon sacrist at the Cathedral of Saint John the Divine in New York .
Lucien Fontenelle ( 1800 - 1840 ) was a prominent fur trader in the Nebraska area in the early-19th century who was born to Francois and Marie Louise Fontenelle on the family plantation south of New Orleans .
Aharon Becker ( Hebrew : אהרן בקר‎ , born 21 December 1905 , died 24 December 1995 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset between 1955 and 1974 .
George Nevill , 1st Earl of Abergavenny ( 24 June 1727 -- 9 September 1785 ) was an English Peer .
Jean d'Orbais ( ca . 1175 - 1231 ) was a French architect from Orbais active in the Reims area .
Edmund Hay ( b. 1540 ? ; d. at Rome , 4 November 1591 ) was a Scottish Jesuit , and envoy to Mary , Queen of Scots .
Nicolai Henrich Jæger ( 28 January 1780 -- 13 July 1846 ) was a Norwegian lawyer and philologist .
Gao Ming ( Chinese : 高 明 ; pinyin : Gāo Míng ; Wade -- Giles : Kao Ming ; c. 1305 -- 1370 ) , also known as Kao Ming , Gao Zecheng , and the Cabbage Root Taoist , was a Chinese poet and playwright during the Yuan Dynasty .
Ettore Felici ( 12 March 1881 - 9 May 1951 ) was the second Apostolic Nuncio to Ireland .
Kimy Pernía Domicó ( 1950 - -2001 ) was an indigenous leader of the Embera Katio in Colombia .
Colonel John Caulfeild ( 1661 - -1707 ) , styled The Honourable from birth , was an Irish soldier and politician .
Bill Crane ( 11 January 1924 -- 2 October 2014 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Andrea Absolonová ( 26 December 1976 -- 9 December 2004 ) , better known by the pseudonym Lea De Mae , was a Czech adult model , pornographic actress and a member of the Czech high diving national team .
Jules Vernon ( 2 April 1867 -- 17 May 1937 ) was born Walter Lester Pope Knyvette , in East India , as the son of an English officer in the army .
Paolo Antonio Foscarini ( c. 1565 -- 10 June 1616 ) was a Carmelite father and scientist , whose book on the mobility of the earth was condemned by the Roman Inquisition in 1616 along with the writings of Copernicus .
Queen Jinseong of Silla ( c.865 - 897 ) ( r. 887 - -897 ) was the fifty - first ruler of the Korean kingdom , Silla .
Andreas Reischek ( 15 September 1845 -- 3 April 1902 ) was an Austrian taxidermist , naturalist , ornithologist and collector notable for his extensive natural history collecting expeditions throughout New Zealand as well as being notorious for acts of grave robbing there .
Jacopo Amigoni ( 1682 - -1752 ) , also named Giacomo Amiconi , was an Italian painter of the late - Baroque or Rococo period , who began his career in Venice , but traveled and was prolific throughout Europe , where his sumptuous portraits were much in demand .
Anto Gvozdenović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Анто Гвозденовић ; 26 January 1853 -- 2 September 1935 ) was a Montenegrin , Russian , and French general , a member of the Imperial Russian Privy Council , and a diplomat and statesman .
Werner Wolfgang Rogosinski FRS ( 24 September 1894 -- 23 July 1964 ) was a German ( later British ) mathematician .
Kurt Landauer ( 28 July 1884 -- 21 December 1961 ) was a German football official .
Sir Henry Foley Knight KCSI CIE ( b. 19 January 1886 - d. 1960 ) was a British administrator and civil servant who served as the Acting Governor of Madras in 1946 .
Alan Philpott ( 8 November 1942 -- 26 May 2009 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Oldham Athletic and Stoke City .
Martin - Paul Samba , born Mebenga m'Ebono ( circa 1875 -- 8 August 1914 ) , was a Bulu military officer during the Imperial German colonial period of Cameroon .
Arslan - Shah of Ghazna ( full name : Sultan ad - Dawlah Abul - Moluk Arslan - Shah ibn Mas'ud ) ( b. ? - d. 1118 ) was the Sultan of the Ghaznavid Empire from 1116 to 1117 C.E.
Walter Van Rensselaer Berry ( July 29 , 1859 -- 1927 ) was an American lawyer , diplomat , Francophile , and friend of several great writers .
Per Almaas ( 8 March 1898 -- 25 July 1991 ) was a Norwegian politician for the Labour Party .
Niels Hanssøn Meng ( 1604 -- August 1676 ) was a Norwegian timber trader and Mayor .
Conall mac Suibni ( died 635 ) , called Conall Guthbinn , was King of Uisnech in Mide of the Clann Cholmáin .
Ahmed Sabry ( 15 September 1933 -- 14 August 1958 ) was an Egyptian fencing champion .
Ole A. Sørli ( 1946 -- 4 August 2009 ) was a Norwegian musician and writer as well as a music industry manager and record producer .
Andrew George Scott ( baptised 5 July 1842 -- 20 January 1880 ) , also known as Captain Moonlite , was an Australian bushranger .
Harold Ian McClure ( 1905 - -9 January 1982 ) , known as Ian McClure , was a surgeon and politician in Northern Ireland .
Pietro Giovanni Guarneri ( 1655 - -1720 ) , also known as Pietro da Mantua or Peter Guarnerius of Mantua was a violin maker of the Guarneri family who also worked as a professional musician .
Frank Knox Morton Pennypacker ( 1872 - -1956 ) was a collector of Long Island , New York historical material and author of several books on Long Island history , including `` George Washington 's Spies , '' the story of the Culper Ring .
Thomas Elisha Hogg ( June 19 , 1842 -- September 1880 ) , born in Cherokee County , Texas , the son of Lucanda ( McMath ) and Joseph Lewis Hogg , was a teacher , lawyer , editor and writer , brother of James Stephen Hogg , Governor of Texas , and uncle of I m a Hogg .
Ellis Wynn ( before 1559 - 1623 ) was an English politician .
Hugh Barker ( died 1632 ) was an English lawyer .
Eugen Hirschfeld ( 22 January 1866 -- 18 June 1946 ) was a medical practitioner , and member of the Queensland Legislative Council .
Dimitar Popgeorgiev Berovski ( 1840 , Berovo , Ottoman Empire -- 1907 , Kyustendil , Kingdom of Bulgaria ) was a Bulgarian revolutionary from Macedonia .
Hugh Goldwin Rivière ( 1869 - -1956 ) was a noted British portraitist .
Mary Pearcey ( 1866 -- 23 December 1890 ) was an English woman who was convicted of murdering her lover 's wife , Mrs. Phoebe Hogg , and child , Phoebe , on 24 October 1890 and executed for the crime on 23 December of the same year .
Benjamin Franklin Grouard ( 1819 - -1894 ) was one of the earliest Latter Day Saint missionaries to the Society Islands , which now constitute French Polynesia .
Arthur Võõbus ( 28 April ( O.S. 15 April ) 1909 -- 25 September 1988 ) was an Estonian scholar of Syriac language .
Jan Mark ( 22 June 1943 -- 16 January 2006 ) was a British writer best known for children 's books .
Béla Sulyok ( 21 November 1904 -- 1 March 1977 ) was a Hungarian economist , who served as Governor of the Hungarian National Bank during the Communist regime from 1 July 1960 to 31 October 1961 .
William Gayley Simpson ( 1892 -- 1991 ) was an activist and author .
Colonel Sir Michael McCorkell KCVO OBE TD JP DL ( 3 May 1925 -- 13 November 2006 ) was an Ulster soldier and British public servant , emulating the high level of British public service of successive generations of the McCorkell family , being Lord Lieutenant of County Londonderry for 25 years .
Elias de Beckingham ( died 1305 ? ) was an English judge .
Stavros Xenidis ( Greek : Σταύρος Ξενίδης , 1924 - 2 November 2008 ) was a Greek actor .
Robert Harley , 1st Earl of Oxford and Earl Mortimer KG ( 5 December 1661 -- 21 May 1724 ) , was a British politician and statesman of the late Stuart and early Georgian periods .
David Atwood Wasson ( 1823 - -1887 ) was an American minister and Transcendentalist author , an essayist and poet .
Annie French Hector ( Dublin , Ireland , 1825 -- London , 10 July 1902 ) was a 19th - century popular novelist who wrote under the pen name `` Mrs Alexander '' .
Florence Annie Conybeare ( 13 September 1872 -- 29 February 1916 ) was a British campaigner for the Women 's Suffrage movement .
José Mariano Serrano ( 8 September 1788 - -1852 ) was a Bolivian - born statesman and jurist .
Axel Otto Mörner ( 8 June 1774 -- 20 October 1852 ) was a Swedish artist and general .
Harris Downey ( born May 12 , 1907 Baton Rouge , Louisiana - 1979 ) was an American short story writer , and novelist .
Jogesh Chandra Chatterjee ( Hindi:योगेश चन्द्र चटर्जी ) ( 1895 - -1969 ) was an Indian freedom fighter , revolutionary and member of Rajya Sabha .
Francis Yaxley ( died 1565 ) was an English politician and conspirator .
Hugh Blythe ( also Hugo Blythe ) B.D. ( d. 1610 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1572 - 1610 and Archdeacon of Leicester from 1589 - 1591 .
Ippolito Fiorini ( c. 1549 - -1621 ) was a composer and lutenist , and the maestro di capella at the court of Alfonso II d'Este in Ferrara during its entire existence ( 1568 - -1597 ) .
Napoléon Aubin ( 9 November 1812 -- 12 June 1890 ) was a Canadian journalist , publisher , playwright , and scientist .
John Macalpine ( Latin : Maccabeus ) ( died 6 December 1557 ) was a Scottish Protestant theologian .
Mary Stachowicz ( née Frank ; born 1951 ) was a Polish American translator , Catholic and mother of four , who on November 13 , 2002 was murdered by her coworker Nicholas Gutierrez in Chicago , Illinois .
Daniel McGilvary ( 1828 - 1911 ) was an American Presbyterian missionary who played an important role in the expansion of Protestantism in Northern Siam .
Frederick de Sola Mendes ( Montego Bay , Jamaica , West Indies , July 8 , 1850 - -1927 ) was a rabbi , author , and editor .
Matthias Steinl ( otherwise Steindel , Staindle , Steindl or Stinle ) ( c. 1644 - -18 April 1727 ) was an Austrian painter , architect and designer , and one of the country 's best known Baroque sculptors .
Sir John Stapley , 1st Baronet of Patcham ( 1628 - -1701 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1654 and 1679 .
Christian Keymann ( also Christian Keimann ; 27 February 1607 -- 13 January 1662 ) was a German hymnwriter .
John George Wood , or Rev J. G. Wood , ( 21 July 1827 -- 3 March 1889 ) , was an English writer who popularised natural history with his writings .
Moses Henry Perley ( 31 December 1804 -- 17 August 1862 ) was a lawyer and entrepreneur in colonial New Brunswick .
John Digby , 3rd Earl of Bristol ( 1634 -- 18 September 1698 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1675 to 1677 when he inherited the peerage as Earl of Bristol .
Pope Adrian V ( Latin : Adrianus V ; c. 1210/1220 -- 18 August 1276 ) , born Ottobuono de ' Fieschi , was Pope from 11 July to his death on August 18th 1276 .
Hildor Lundvik ( Hille , 6 March 1885 -- Stockholm , 24 January 1951 ) first studied law at Uppsala University , then music at the Royal Swedish Academy of Music in Stockholm , graduating as a music teacher in 1912 , as precentor and organist ( Västerås ) in 1919 and singing teacher in 1913 .
Giovanni Girolamo Saccheri ( Italian pronunciation : ( dʒoˈvanni dʒiˈrɔlamo sakˈkɛri ) ; 5 September 1667 -- 25 October 1733 ) was an Italian Jesuit priest , scholastic philosopher , and mathematician .
Ephraim Lockwood ( 4 April 1845 -- 19 December 1921 ) was an English first - class cricketer , and captain of Yorkshire County Cricket Club in the 1876 and 1877 seasons .
John A. Hammond ( April 11 , 1843 -- 1939 ) was a Canadian adventurer , photographer , artist , printmaker and art educator .
Guillaume Pouget ( 14 October 1847 -- 24 February 1933 ) was a Vincentian priest who had great influence on many Christian scholars in the early 20th century .
Colonel Sir Hugh Trefusis Brassey KCVO , OBE , MC , DL , JP ( 5 October 1915 -- 1990 ) was a British soldier and magistrate .
Fr . Abel Periyappuram , C.M.I. , ( 1920 - 26 October 2001 ) was a priest and lyricist , best known as the founding father of Kalabhavan , a centre for learning performance arts in Kochi , India .
Julio Conde ( Villalba de los Alcores , Valladolid , 1915 - Madrid , 1995 ) was a spanish luthier trained by his uncle Domingo Esteso at his workshop in Madrid , where Julio worked with his brothers Faustino y Mariano , establishing Hermanos Conde trademark .
Anthony Petit ( died 1946 ) was an American lighthouse keeper .
Lieutenant - Colonel William Legge , 7th Earl of Dartmouth GCVO TD ( 22 February 1881 -- 28 February 1958 ) , styled Viscount Lewisham between 1891 and 1936 , was a British peer and Conservative politician , who was Acting Lord Great Chamberlain 1928 - 36 .
Edwin Dunkin FRS , ( 19 August 1821 -- 26 November 1898 ) was an astronomer and the president of the Royal Astronomical Society and the Royal Institution of Cornwall .
Francesco Zingales ( Italian pronunciation : ( franˈtʃesko dziŋˈɡaːles ) ; 1884 - 1959 ) was a general in the Royal Italian Army during World War II . Francesco Zingales fought in World War I on the Isonzo Front .
Philip Eustace Stretton ( 1865 - -1919 ) was a British animal and sporting painter working between 1882 until his death .
Sir George Scott Robertson KCSI ( 22 October 1852 -- 1 January 1916 ) was a British soldier , author , and administrator who was best known for his arduous journey to the remote and rugged region of Kafiristan in what is now northeastern Afghanistan .
Bruno Ritter von Hauenschild ( 9 June 1896 -- 10 March 1953 ) , born Bruno Hauenschild , was a general in the German Army .
Lucy Baxter ( 21 January 1837 -- 10 November 1902 ) was an English writer on art , chiefly under the pseudonym of Leader Scott .
Mate Garković ( 12 September 1882 - 26 May 1968 ) was the Roman Catholic archbishop of the Archdiocese of Zadar , Croatia .
Prunella Clough ( 11 November 1919 -- 26 December 1999 ) was a prominent British artist .
Pinchas Cargher AM , known professionally as John Cargher ( 24 January 1919 -- 30 April 2008 ) , was a British - born Australian music and ballet journalist and radio broadcaster .
Horace Rudston ( 22 November 1878 -- 14 April 1962 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played twenty one games for Yorkshire County Cricket Club between 1902 and 1907 , and one match for the North of England in 1905 .
Sir Richard Browne , 2nd Baronet ( before 1634 -- September 1684 ) was a barrister and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1660 .
Henry O'Brien , Lord Ibrackan or Lord O'Brien ( c.1642 -- 1 September 1678 ) , styled Hon . Henry O'Brien until 1657 , was an Irish nobleman and politician .
Andris Andreiko ( 17 October 1942 -- 10 March 1976 ) was a three - time ( 1968 , 1969 , 1972 ) world champion and European champion ( 1974 ) in draughts .
Per Palle Storm ( 1 December 1910 -- 6 January 1994 ) was a Danish - born Norwegian sculptor .
Warda Al - Jazairia ( Arabic : وردة الجزائرية‎ 22 July 1939 -- 17 May 2012 ) was an Algerian singer who was well known for her pan - Arabist songs and music .
Rudolph L. Hanau ( 1881 - 1930 ) was an American dentist who is credited towards developing the Hanau Articulator .
The Rev. Prebendary James Dallaway FSA ( 20 February 1763 -- 6 June 1834 ) was an English antiquary , topographer , and miscellaneous writer .
Reginald Reynolds Amponsah ( 30 December 1919 -- 3 June 2009 ) was a potter and politician in Ghana .
Maria Carta ( 24 June 1934 -- 22 September 1994 ) was an Italian folk music singer - songwriter .
Song Guangsi ( 宋光嗣 ) ( died December 8 , 925 ? ) was a powerful eunuch of the Chinese Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period state Former Shu , serving both of its emperors , Wang Jian ( Emperor Gaozu ) and Wang Yan .
Roger Newman ( 31 August 1940 -- 4 March 2010 ) was a British born - American soap opera actor and writer .
Sverre Lassen - Urdahl ( 17 February 1913 -- 31 December 2005 ) was a Norwegian alpine skier , born in Lake Forest , Illinois , United States .
Robert Weir Schultz ( 26 July 1860 -- 29 April 1951 ) was a Scottish Arts and Crafts architect , artist , landscape designer and furniture designer .
Jean - Baptiste Estoup ( 16 January 1868 in Navenne -- 17 April 1950 in Paris ) was a French stenographer and writer on stenography .
Engineer Francisco Escárcega Márquez ( died 1938 ) was a builder of railroads in Mexico and fought in the Mexican Revolution .
Henry Borwin III , Lord of Rostock ( c. 1220 -- 1 August 1278 ) was a member of the House of Mecklenburg .
Francis Tregian the Elder ( 1548 - -1608 ) was the son of John Tregian of Wolvenden of Probus , Cornwall and Catherine Arundell .
Bendahara Paduka Raja Tun Perak ( died 1498 ) was the fifth and most famous bendahara , a Malay rank similar to a prime minister , of the Sultanate of Malacca .
Philip Basset ( c. 1185 -- 19 October 1271 ) was the Justiciar of England .
John Howe , 1st Baron Chedworth ( died 3 April 1742 ) was a British peer and politician , the son of John Grubham Howe .
Stella Linden ( born Stella M Marsden on 5 June 1919 - 23 January 2005 ) was an actress and writer , best known for mentoring playwright John Osborne and for writing the film Two a Penny .
Dr Avraham Katznelson ( Hebrew : אברהם קצנלסון‎ , also known as Avraham Nissan , born 1888 , died 18 May 1956 ) was a Zionist political figure in Mandate Palestine and a signatory of the Israeli declaration of independence .
Dubhchobhlaigh Bean Ua hEaghra , aka Dubhchobhlaigh Ní Conchobair , Queen of Luighne Connacht , died 1131 .
Sudhindra Thirta ( 31 March 1926 -- 17 January 2016 ) , also referred to as Shri Sudhindra Thirtha Swamiji , was the legal and spiritual head ( mathadipathi ) of the Kashi Math and the twentieth successive person called the swamiji of guru parampara .
Frederic Isherwood ( 13 August 1858 -- 20 February 1927 ) was an English cricketer , who played for Lancashire .
John Dengate ( 1 October 1938 -- 1 August 2013 ) was an Australian folk singer and songwriter .
John Scoble ( January 16 , 1799 -- December 1877 ) was a British abolitionist and political figure in Canada West .
Edigu ( or Edigey ) ( also İdegäy or Edege Mangit ) ( 1352 - -1419 ) was a Mongol Muslim Emir of the White Horde who founded a new political entity , which came to be known as the Nogai Horde .
George Wilkins Kendall ( 1809 - -1867 ) was a journalist , war correspondent , and pioneer Texas sheepman , known as the father of the Texas sheep business .
Paul Pesthy ( 25 March 1938 -- 28 October 2008 ) was an American modern pentathlete and fencer .
Realms of the Haunting is a first - person adventure / shooter game developed by Gremlin Interactive .
Firefighter F.D.18 is an action game created and produced by Konami Computer Entertainment and released in March 2004 for the PlayStation 2 .
Sea Battle is a multiplayer strategy game released by Mattel for its Intellivision video game system in 1980 .
Hero of Sparta is an action - adventure game developed and published by Gameloft for the iOS , Nintendo DS , Android and PlayStation Portable .
The First Templar is an action - adventure video game developed by Haemimont Games and published by Kalypso Media for the Xbox 360 and Microsoft Windows .
Zombies Ate My Neighbors is a run and gun video game developed by LucasArts and originally published by Konami for the Super Nintendo and Sega Genesis consoles in 1993 .
J - League Jikkyō Winning Eleven 2001 is a sports video game developed by Konami for the PlayStation exclusively in Japan on June 2001 .
Worms Armageddon is an artillery strategy game developed by Team17 and part of the Worms series .
Commander Blood is a science fiction adventure game that was developed by Cryo Interactive , a French company that also created Captain Blood ( released in 1988 ) .
Legends of Valour is a role - playing video game developed by Synthetic Dimensions and released by U.S. Gold and SSI in 1992 for the Amiga , Atari ST and PC DOS systems , with the additional FM Towns and PC-98 versions in 1993 - 1994 in Japan only ( as Legends of Valour : Gouyuu no Densetsu ) .
Legend of Grimrock ( LoG ) is a fantasy themed action role - playing game from Finnish indie video game developer `` Almost Human '' .
Championship Manager 2 is a football management computer game in the Sports Interactive 's Championship Manager series .
Peggle Nights is a Windows , Mac OS X and Microsoft Xbox Live Arcade downloadable game from PopCap Games .
Aspyr handles porting Borderlands 2 patches for the Mac and has stated there will be a delay on synchronizng new patches from Gearbox Software .
Theme Hospital is a business simulation game developed by Bullfrog Productions and published by Electronic Arts in 1997 , in which the player designs and operates a hospital .
Lufia & the Fortress of Doom , known as Estpolis Denki ( エストポリス伝記 , officially translated Biography of Estpolis ) in Japan , is a role - playing video game developed by Neverland and published by Taito in 1993 , for the Super Nintendo .
Windows Internet Explorer 8 ( IE8 ) is a web browser developed by Microsoft in the Internet Explorer browser series , released on March 19 , 2009 .
ATA over Ethernet ( AoE ) is a network protocol developed by the Brantley Coile Company , designed for simple , high - performance access of block storage devices over Ethernet networks .
DVD Play is a Digital Video Disc player that comes with most HP and Compaq computers .
Fable II is an action role - playing open world video game in the Fable game series developed by Lionhead Studios and published by Microsoft Game Studios for Xbox 360 .
Entropia Universe is a massively multiplayer online virtual universe designed by the Swedish software company MindArk , based in Gothenburg .
The Invincible Iron Man is an action video game published by Activision and developed by Torus Games for the Game Boy Advance in 2002 .
Mega Man 4 , known in Japan as Rockman 4 Aratanaru Yabō ! ! ( ロックマン4 新たなる野望 ! ! Rokkuman Fō Aratanaru Yabō ! ! , lit . `` Rockman 4 : A New Ambition ! ! '' ) , is a platform game developed by Capcom for the Nintendo Entertainment System .
Visual Test , originally known as MS - Test , was an automated testing tool for Windows applications developed by Microsoft and later sold to Rational Software .
Monty Python 's Complete Waste of Time is a collection of minigames , screen savers , desktop wallpaper and icons for Mac OS System 7 , DOS and Windows released in 1994 by 7th Level , Inc. The content is drawn primarily from the Monty Python 's Flying Circus TV series .
A Game of Concentration ( also known simply as Concentration and Hunt & Score ) is a video game produced by Atari , Inc. and released in 1978 for its Atari 2600 video game system .
Smacker video is a video file format ( with the .SMK file extension ) developed by RAD Game Tools , and primarily used for full - motion video in video games .
A-10 Cuba ! is a flight simulator computer game released by Parsoft Interactive in 1996 for Windows and Mac . The game was a sequel to the Mac - exclusive A-10 Attack!.
Virocop is a run and gun computer game developed by Graftgold and published by Renegade Software in 1995 .
Bit . Trip Flux , marketed as BIT.TRIP FLUX , is an arcade - style rhythm game developed by Gaijin Games and published by Aksys Games as part of the Bit . Trip series .
Zaxxon 's Motherbase 2000 ( known simply as Motherbase in Europe and Parasquad in Japan ) is a shoot 'em up released in 1995 for the Sega 32X.
Ranarama is a top - down Gauntlet - like action game developed by Graftgold in 1987 and published by Hewson Consultants .
The Royal Trap is a visual novel developed and published by Hanako Games on February 23 , 2013 for Windows , Mac OS and Linux .
Mega Turrican is a 16-bit shooter game , developed by Factor 5 in 1993 and marketed by Data East in 1994 .
Herzog Zwei is a Sega Genesis - exclusive game by Technosoft , published in 1989 ( released in North America and Europe in early 1990 ) .
William Wobbler is a 1985 computer game developed by Antony Crowther and released by Wizard Development for the Commodore 64 and Sinclair ZX Spectrum .
AVG AntiVirus ( previously just AVG , abbreviation of Anti - Virus Guard ) is a family of anti - virus and Internet security software for the Windows , OS X , and former Linux and FreeBSD computing platforms , developed by AVG Technologies , a publicly traded Czech company formerly known as Grisoft .
Sunny Garcia Surfing is an extreme sports video game endorsed by veteran surfer Sunny Garcia , developed by Krome Studios , published by Ubisoft , and released exclusively for PlayStation 2 in 2001 .
Empire ( or Classic Empire ) is a turn - based wargame with simple rules , conceived by Walter Bright in 1971 ( released as a computer game in 1977 ) based on various war movies and board games , notably Battle of Britain and Risk .
