Frame Gride is a Japanese mecha fighting game made for the Sega Dreamcast by FromSoftware .
Soul Fighter is a beat 'em up video game developed by Toka for the Sega Dreamcast home console in 1999 .
Battle Tag is a laser tag - shooter hybrid game developed and published by Ubisoft .
DJMax Ray is a music mobile game developed by Pentavision Studio and published by Neowiz Internet in South Korea , and is an adaptation of the earlier DJMax titles Tap Sonic and DJMax Portable .
Pokémate ( ポケメ～ト ) is a Pokémon - themed application for NTT DoCoMo FOMA 900i series mobile phones developed by Square Enix .
In 2012 , Brocade Communications Systems acquired Vyatta and renamed it `` Vyatta , a Brocade Company '' .
Apache HiveMind is an Inversion of Control ( IOC ) software project of the Apache Software Foundation written in Java .
Gunstar Super Heroes ( Japanese : ガンスタースーパーヒーローズ ; Gunstar Future Heroes in Europe ) is a Game Boy Advance title created by Treasure Co. Ltd. It is a sequel to Gunstar Heroes , with the story taking place after the events of the original game and featuring an expanded combat system over its predecessor .

Alex Kidd in Shinobi World is a side - scrolling action game produced by Sega that was originally released for the Master System in 1990 and later re - released for the Wii Virtual Console in 2009 .
It is also the second game to be created by series originator Namco , as Ms. Pac - Man ( the second in the series ) and Pac - Man Plus ( released a few months before Super Pac - Man ) were created without Namco 's involvement .
Neo Bomberman is one of two Bomberman games developed by Hudson Soft that was released for the Neo Geo hardware , the other being Panic Bomber .
Death , Jr. and the Science Fair of Doom is a Nintendo DS platformer game developed by Backbone Entertainment , and is one of the sequels to the PlayStation Portable game Death Jr. released in 2005 .
The Testament of Sherlock Holmes is an adventure video game in the Adventures of Sherlock Holmes series developed by Frogwares and published by Focus Home Interactive .
Street Fighter Alpha 3 , known as Street Fighter Zero 3 ( ストリートファイターZERO 3 ) in Japan and Asia , is a 1998 fighting game by Capcom originally released for the CPS II arcade hardware .

P.N.03 , short for Product Number Zero Three , is a 2003 third - person shooter video game developed and published by Capcom for the Nintendo GameCube .
The Mask of the Sun is an interactive fiction computer game with graphics developed by Ultrasoft and published in North America by Brøderbund and in Europe by Ariolasoft .
Fountain of Dreams is a 1990 role - playing video game developed and published by Electronic Arts for MS - DOS as a successor to 1988 's Wasteland .
Treasure Mountain ! is an educational computer game published by The Learning Company in 1990 for both Windows and Macintosh PCs . It teaches children aged five to nine , reading , basic math , and logic skills .
Castle Wolfenstein is an early stealth - based action - adventure shooter video game developed by Muse Software for the Apple II . It was first released in 1981 and later ported to MS - DOS , the Atari 8-bit family , and the Commodore 64 .

Pinnacle Studio is a video editing program originally developed by Pinnacle Systems as the consumer - level counterpart to Pinnacle 's former professional - level software , Liquid Edition .

A Piano for Mrs. Cimino is a 1982 American television movie produced and directed by George Schaefer .
WTC View is an American film released in 2005 , based on the 2003 play of the same name by Brian Sloan , that traces the search for a roommate in the weeks following 9/11 .
Late Fragment is a Canadian interactive cinema production , written and directed by Daryl Cloran , Anita Doron and Mateo Guez .

The Hooligan Factory is a 2014 Football hooliganism spoof film directed , co - written and starring Nick Nevern .

The Alan Dale Show is an early American television program which ran on the DuMont Television Network in 1948 , and then on CBS Television from 1950 - 1951 .
Pretty Wild is an American reality television series that premiered on E ! on March 14 , 2010 and ran for one season .
La viuda joven ( English : The Young Widow ) , is a Venezuelan telenovela produced by Venevisión .
Neighbours was immediately bought by Seven 's rival Network Ten .
Amores con trampa ( English title : Fooled into Love ) is a Mexican telenovela produced by Emilio Larrosa for Televisa and broadcast in 2015 by Canal de las Estrellas .
Tu Kahe Agar is an Indian television series that aired on Zee TV based on an astrological prediction that can greatly affect human life .
Winning Lines was a National Lottery game show that ran on BBC One in the United Kingdom from 12 June 1999 to 16 October 2004 .
Na Moral ( Portuguese for In Moral ) is a Brazilian talk show broadcast by Rede Globo since July 5 , 2012 and hosted by Pedro Bial .
Almost Royal is a faux - reality television series on the BBC America network .
Just Our Luck is an American sitcom which aired on the American Broadcasting Company in the fall of 1983 .
Lily Live ! is a flamboyant live / scripted comedy show which was produced by LWT and was broadcast for two series on ITV in 2000 and 2001 , presented by Paul O'Grady ( as Lily Savage ) .
Mets Hot Stove is a program airing of SportsNet New York which focuses on the offseason activities of the New York Mets .
The 11 O'Clock Show was a satirical late - night British television comedy series on Channel 4 , which featured topical sketches and commentary on news items .
Ask Aida is an interactive cooking show on the Food Network hosted by Aida Mollenkamp .
Flip Men is an American reality television series starring Mike Baird and Doug Clark that premiered on Spike on October 25 , 2011 , and ran for two seasons .
ITV News Meridian is the regional news programme for the ITV Meridian region and part of the ITV Central region , serving South East England .
From G 's to Gents was an MTV reality television series which features misdirected young men willing to change their lives and become gentlemen .
Ritter 's Cove ( German title Die Küstenpiloten , or `` The Pilots on the Coast '' ) is an adventure television series which aired on CBC Television from 1980 to 1981 , co - produced by Canadian , West German and British companies .
Die Rote Meile is a German television drama that aired on Sat.1 and follows the lives of strippers , prostitutes and their pimps in the district of St. Pauli in Hamburg .
Your World Today is a daily international news - magazine television series that aired on CNN International , a sister channel to CNN -- both being cable - news channels .
Run , Joe , Run was a Saturday - morning television program that aired on NBC from 1974 to 1976 .
Piers Morgan Live ( formerly known as Piers Morgan Tonight ) is a talk show on CNN that was hosted by Piers Morgan .
Guy 's Big Bite is a Food Network show starring Guy Fieri , winner of the second season of The Next Food Network Star .
Stressed Eric is a British cartoon series that was produced by Absolutely Productions for the BBC Two television channel in the United Kingdom and Television New Zealand .
Talent Suomi is the Finnish version of the Got Talent format of the program and airs on Nelonen .
Let 's Rhumba was an American dance instruction program that aired on NBC from November 1946 to January 1947 .
Countdown to the Closing Bell is an American financial program airing on the Fox Business Network from 3 - 4pm ET . Hosted by Liz Claman , this program , which debuted May 12 , 2008 , covers the final hour of trading on Wall Street .
The Reagans is a 180-minute television film about U.S. President Ronald Reagan and his family which CBS had planned to broadcast in November 2003 during fall `` sweeps '' , but was ultimately broadcast on November 30 of that year on cable channel Showtime due to controversy over its portrayal of Reagan .
Science Magazine was a half - hour television show produced by CBC Television from 1975 to 1979 .
Sofía dame tiempo , was a Colombian telenovela produced by RTI for Caracol Televisión and Telemundo in 2003 .
Gimme a Break ! is an American sitcom which aired on NBC for six seasons from October 29 , 1981 until May 12 , 1987 .
The Agenda with Steve Paikin , or The Agenda , is the flagship current affairs program of TVOntario ( TVO ) , Ontario 's public broadcaster .
The Drug Years is a 2006 television documentary series produced by the Sundance Channel and VH1 about illicit drug use in the United States in the second half of the 20th century .
Abe Burrows ' Almanac is an American television series that aired on CBS in 1950 .
You 're Putting Me On ! is an NBC game show in which celebrities tried to communicate the identities of famous people through odd and interesting clues .
What the Deaf Man Heard is a 1997 Hallmark Hall of Fame television movie that aired on CBS television on November 23 , 1997 .
Mary Kay and Johnny initially aired live on the DuMont Television Network before moving to CBS and then NBC .
The Heaven and Earth Show was a BBC television programme that aired on Sunday mornings from 10 am to 11 am on BBC One .
Van der Valk is a British television series that was produced by Thames Television for the ITV network .
Drama at Ten is a Canadian dramatic television miniseries which aired on CBC Television from 1955 to 1956 .
Mighty Moshin ' Emo Rangers is a television Mini Series on MTV UK .
Just Jordan is an American television sitcom that aired on Nickelodeon as a part of the network 's TEENick lineup .
Las Fierbinți is a Romanian sitcom that premiered on Pro TV on March 1 , 2012 , created by Mimi Brănescu , and directed by Dragoș Buliga and Constantin Popescu .
The Secrets of Isis , originally broadcast as Isis , is an American live - action superhero television series produced by Filmation from 1975 to 1977 for CBS 's Saturday morning lineup .
Wednesday Night Hoops appears every Wednesday with the biggest college basketball game in the Atlantic Coast Conference in primetime during the regular season on ESPN As well as the Pac-12 Conference .
The New Adventures of Batman is an animated cartoon that aired on CBS from February 12 to May 28 , 1977 , featuring the DC Comics superheroes Batman and Robin , and Batgirl .
First Years is an American legal drama that aired on NBC from March to April 2001 .
Leave It to Lamas is an American reality series broadcast on the E ! cable television network .
Celebrity Cooking Showdown was a program that aired on NBC from April 17 - -19 and April 22 , 2006 .
Newsfile is a Canadian documentary television series which aired on CBC Television in 1973 .
Cool Million is an American crime drama series that aired on NBC as an element in its `` wheel series '' The NBC Wednesday Mystery Movie during its 1972 - 73 schedule .
DaySide is an American news / talk show on the Fox News Channel , which aired weekdays at 1:00 p.m. ET . Unlike most news channel programs , it had an live audience giving reaction throughout the program , similar to the CNN show TalkBack Live .
Andy Barker , P.I. is an American detective sitcom starring Andy Richter produced and broadcast by NBC , and co - starring Tony Hale , Marshall Manesh , Harve Presnell , and Clea Lewis .
Glebionis coronaria , formerly called Chrysanthemum coronarium , is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
The Defua rat ( Dephomys defua ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Microcybe is a genus of plants in the Rutaceae family , all of which are native to Australia .
The Shelley 's greenbul ( Arizelocichla masukuensis ) is a species of songbird in the Pycnonotidae family .
Tenthredo is a genus of sawflies belonging to the Tenthredinidae family , sub - family Tenthredininae .
The Arizona night lizard ( Xantusia arizonae ) is a small smooth - skinned gray - brown lizard with dark spots that sometimes form partial lines down the back .
Onustus is a genus of large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Xenophoridae , the carrier shells .
Trichosirius is a genus of small sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Capulidae ( previously Trichotropidae ) .
Loricarioidea is a superfamily of catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) .
Hisarai seripierriae is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Hisarai .
Gossypieae is a tribe of the Malvoideae subfamily of flowering plants .
Felis margarita airensis is a subspecies of the sand cat that was described from French Sudan in 1938 .
The Imperial cave salamander or scented cave salamander ( Speleomantes imperialis ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae , endemic to Sardinia .
The Brazilian slender opossum ( Marmosops paulensis ) is an opossum species from South America .
Betula ermanii , or Erman 's birch , is a species of birch tree belonging to the family Betulaceae .
The Carniolan honey bee ( Apis mellifera carnica , Pollmann ) is a subspecies of the western honey bee .
Liangcoris is a recently described monotypic genus of assassin bug family ( Reduviidae ) , in the subfamily Harpactorinae .
The Endocoelantheae was a suborder of sea anemones in the order Actiniaria , This suborder was shown to be part of a larger suborder Anenthemonae in a 2014 study .
Renotus deyrollei is a species of beetle in the family Noteridae , the only species in the genus Renotus .
Pattonomys is a genus of rodent in the family Echimyidae , named after American mammalogist James L. Patton .
Synsepalum is a genus of trees and shrubs in the chicle family , Sapotaceae described as a genus in 1852 .
Aprepodoxa is a genus of moths belonging to Tortricidae family .
The Hessian fly or barley midge , Mayetiola destructor , is a species of fly that is a significant pest of cereal crops including wheat , barley and rye .
Eostriatolamia is an extinct genus of sharks in the family Odontaspididae .
Gastropteridae is a family of sea slugs , gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Philinoidea of the clade Cephalaspidea , the headshield slugs and bubble snails .
The Mexican mole lizard ( Bipes biporus ) , commonly known as the five - toed worm lizard , or simply as Bipes , is a species of amphisbaenian , which is endemic to the Baja California Peninsula .
Tropaeolum majus ( garden nasturtium , Indian cress or monks cress ) is a flowering plant in the family Tropaeolaceae , originating in the Andes from Bolivia north to Colombia .
Cevaeria estebani is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Cevaeria .
Homodontosaurus and most other scalopodontids are now classified as basal members of Baurioidea .
The Javanese shrew ( Crocidura maxi ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The Hokkaidō frog or the Ezo brown frog ( Rana pirica ) is a species in the Ranidae family found in Hokkaidō , Japan , and Sakhalin .
The Greek algyroides ( Algyroides moreoticus ) is a species of lizard in the family Lacertidae .
Hampala is a genus of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family found in South - East Asia .
Sarasinia punctata is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
The Eastern Cape redfin ( Pseudobarbus afer ) is an African freshwater fish species in the family Cyprinidae .
Narcissus latent virus ( NLV ) is a Macluravirus , a plant pathogenic virus of the family Potyviridae , which infects Narcissus .
Homaxinella is a genus of sea sponges , demosponges in the family Suberitidae .
Until recently , Psilocybe was placed taxonomically in the agaric family Strophariaceae based upon its spore and pileipellis morphology .
Pityocona is a small and little - known genus of the twirler moth family ( Gelechiidae ) .
The Mount Nimba screeching frog ( Arthroleptis nimbaensis ) is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family that is endemic to Mount Richard - Molard ( Mount Nimba ) in Guinea , from forests at elevations of 650 to 1,250 m. It is threatened by habitat degradation from mining activities .
The family Cochlonemataceae is a fungus classified in the order Zoopagales .
Ursula 's sunbird ( Cinnyris ursulae ) is a species of bird in the Nectariniidae family .
The Thicklip pupfish ( Cyprinodon labiosus ) is a species of fish in the Cyprinodontidae family .
Anoplogaster cornuta , the common fangtooth , is a species of fangtooth found in temperate and tropical oceans worldwide , but has also been in found in the Western Atlantic and the Pacific .
Arctodiamesa is a genus of non - biting midges in the subfamily Diamesinae of the bloodworm family Chironomidae .
Petrocosmea is a genus of the family Gesneriaceae , the African violet family .
Termitopaediini is a tribe in the rove beetle subfamily Aleocharinae .
Stenoconalia endroedyi is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , the only species in the genus Stenoconalia .
The Stierling 's woodpecker ( Dendropicos stierlingi ) is a species of bird in the Picidae family .
The Bonin thrush , Bonin Islands thrush or Kittlitz 's thrush ( Zoothera terrestris ) is sometimes separated as the only species of the genus Cichlopasser .
The Saint Lucia racer ( Liophis ornatus ) is a species of snake in the Colubridae family .
Watermelon snow , also called snow algae , pink snow , red snow , or blood snow , is Chlamydomonas nivalis , a species of green algae containing a secondary red carotenoid pigment ( astaxanthin ) in addition to chlorophyll .
The European honey buzzard ( Pernis apivorus ) , also known as the pern or common pern , is a bird of prey in the family Accipitridae .
The Zacatecas harvest mouse ( Reithrodontomys zacatecae ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Sinaloa wren ( Thryophilus sinaloa ) is a species of bird in the Troglodytidae family .
Tettigonia is a genus of insect described by Linnaeus in 1758 , belonging to the family Tettigoniidae , subfamily Tettigoniinae .
Proctonotus is a genus of sea slugs , or more accurately nudibranchs , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Proctonotidae .
Dicastria temporalis is a species of beetle in the family Latridiidae , the only species in the genus Dicastria .
The Las Vegas dace ( Rhinichthys deaconi ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Zebra - tailed lizards ( Callisaurus ) are a genus of phrynosomatid lizards endemic to the southwestern United States and northwestern Mexico .
Disanthus is a monospecific genus containing a single species of flowering plant , Disanthus cercidifolius in the family Hamamelidaceae .
The Mongolian gazelle ( Procapra gutturosa ) , or dzeren ( Russian : Дзерэн ) , is a medium - sized antelope native to the semiarid Central Asian steppes of Mongolia , as well as some parts of Siberia and China .
Strasburgeriaceae is a small family of flowering plants in the order Crossosomatales , endemic to New Zealand and New Caledonia .
Orectoloboides is an extinct genus of wobbegong sharks ( family Orectolobidae ) .
It is thought that the Anseriformes originated when the original Galloanserae ( the group to which Anseriformes and Galliformes belong ) split into the two main lineages .
Saxidomus , common name the `` Washington clams '' , is a genus of large edible saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the family Veneridae , the Venus clams .
Psammaechidius spinicollis is a species of beetle in the family Silvanidae , the only species in the genus Psammaechidius .
Pirlot 's big - eared bat ( Micronycteris homezi ) is a species of bat endemic to Venezuela .
The Maharashtra caecilian or Humbarli caecilian , Indotyphlus maharashtraensis , is a species of caecilians described in 2004 by scientists of Bombay Natural History Society and the Natural History Museum , London .
Ascidia is a genus of tunicates in the family Ascidiidae .
Goldringia is an extinct nautilid of the Rutoceratidae family that lived during the Middle Devonian .
The Grévy 's zebra ( Equus grevyi ) , also known as the imperial zebra , is the largest extant wild equid and the largest and most threatened of the three species of zebra , the other two being the plains zebra and the mountain zebra .
Austalis is a genus of Hoverflies , from the family Syrphidae , in the order Diptera .
Ambigolimax valentianus ( previously known as Lehmannia valentiana ) is a species of air - breathing land slug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Limacidae .
Albanotrechus beroni is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Albanotrechus .
The Cape lobster , Homarinus capensis , is a species of small lobster that lives off the coast of South Africa , from Dassen Island to Haga Haga .
Centrotus is a genus of ' treehoppers ' belonging to the family Membracidae .
Mayland 's rainbowfish ( Melanotaenia maylandi ) is a species of fish in the Melanotaeniidae family .
Discoglossus ( common name : painted frogs ) is a genus of frogs in the Discoglossidae family found in southern Europe and northwestern Africa .
The Vieillot 's black weaver ( Ploceus nigerrimus ) is a species of bird in the Ploceidae family .
Dorothy 's slender opossum ( Marmosops dorothea ) is a species of opossum in the family Didelphidae .
Mesocyparis is an extinct genus of uncertain placement within the family Cupressaceae .
The Utah chub ( Gila atraria ) is a cyprinid fish native to western North America , where it is abundant in the upper Snake River and throughout the Lake Bonneville basin .
The Iberian chiffchaff ( Phylloscopus ibericus ) is a species of leaf warbler endemic to Portugal , Spain and North Africa , west of a line stretching roughly from the western Pyrenees via the mountains of central Spain to the Mediterranean .
Trigonopterus is a genus of flightless weevils placed in the Cryptorhynchinae of Curculionidae .
Wutinoceras is a genus of now extinct nautiloid cephalopod of the Wutinoceratidae family .
Kotschya is a genus of legumes in the Fabaceae family , and was recently assigned to the informal monophyletic Dalbergia clade of the Dalbergieae .
The Andean swamp rat ( Neotomys ebriosus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Northern spearnose poacher ( Agonopsis vulsa , also known as the Window - tailed sea - poacher or the Windowtail poacher ) is a fish in the family Agonidae ( poachers ) .
Floridaceras is an extinct genus of Rhinocerotidae ( rhinoceros ) of the Miocene epoch , endemic to North America , living from around ~20.6 - -16.3 Ma , existing for approximately 4.3 million years .
Bilyesta dactylozoides is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Bilyesta .
Oocystis is a planktonic genus of mostly freshwater green algae of the family Oocystaceae .
The Himalayan owl ( Strix nivicolum ) , is an owl of the forests of Himalayas and Taiwan .
Brachythemis is a genus of dragonflies in the family Libellulidae .
The West Caucasian tur ( Capra caucasica syn Capra caucasica caucasica ) is a mountain - dwelling goat - antelope found only in the western half of the Caucasus Mountains range .
Aristogeitonia is a plant genus in the family Picrodendraceae , described as a genus in 1908 .
Antheraea is a moth genus belonging to the family Saturniidae .
Azara 's spinetail ( Synallaxis azarae ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family , named after Spanish naturalist Félix de Azara .
In 2014 , Headden & Campos placed Banguela in the Dsungaripteridae , in a basal position .
A phylogenetic analysis of dissorophids published in 2013 found Scapanops to be one of the most basal members of a clade called Eucacopinae .
The American black bear ( Ursus americanus ) is a medium - sized bear native to North America .
The European cat snake ( Telescopus fallax ) , also known as the Soosan snake , is a venomous colubrid snake endemic to the Mediterranean and Caucasus regions .
Araripemydidae is a family of turtles belonging to the order Testudines .
Microcarbo is a genus of fish - eating birds , known as cormorants , of the family Phalacrocoracidae .
Nocticanacinae , is a subfamily of beach flies in the family of Canacidae .
Rhopiella is a genus of starfish in the family Echinasteridae in the order Spinulosida .
The Rabbitsfoot , scientific name Quadrula cylindrica , is a species of freshwater mussel .
The Northland tusked weta , Anisoura nicobarica , is a rare monotypic weta of the family Anostostomatidae , endemic to the northern half of Northland in New Zealand .
Ardeadoris is a genus of sea slugs , specifically dorid nudibranchs , shell - less marine gastropod mollusks in the family Chromodorididae .
Reichenbachia is a genus of flowering plants belonging to the family Nyctaginaceae , the family that also includes Bougainvillea .
The Guam kingfisher ( Todiramphus cinnamominus ) is a species of kingfisher from the Pacific Islands of Guam .
Polyzoniida is an order of millipedes in the subclass Colobognatha containing three families and at least 74 described species .
Acmispon strigosus ( formerly Lotus strigosus ) , also called stiff - haired lotus or strigose bird's - foot trefoil , is an annual plant in the Pea Family ( Fabaceae ) found from central California to the Baja California Peninsula .
The East Canary gecko or Canary wall gecko ( Tarentola angustimentalis ) is a species of lizard in the Gekkonidae family .
Hemus is a genus of spider crab in the family Majidae .
Samoana is a genus of tropical , air - breathing , land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Partulidae .
Anthocharis is a Holarctic genus of the butterfly tribe Anthocharini , in the Pieridae family .

The American bittern ( Botaurus lentiginosus ) is a species of wading bird of the heron family ( Ardeidae ) .
Macroditassa is a genus of plant in family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1927 .
Neurocalyx is a plant genus in the coffee family Rubiaceae .
The Krabi mouth - brooding betta , Betta simplex , is a species of gourami endemic to Krabi Province , Thailand .
The Society kingfisher or Tahiti kingfisher ( Todiramphus veneratus ) is a species of bird in the family Alcedinidae .
The Saldanha catshark ( Apristurus saldanha ) is a species of catshark , belonging to the family Scyliorhinidae .
Allen 's spotted bat ( Glauconycteris humeralis ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae found in the following countries : the Central African Republic , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Kenya , and Uganda .
The Townsend 's shearwater , Puffinus auricularis , is a rare seabird of the tropics from the family Procellariidae .
Crocus pulchellus , the hairy crocus , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Crocus of the family Iridaceae , found the Northern Balkan Peninsula to Northwestern Turkey .
The Várzea thrush , ( Turdus sanchezorum ) , is a resident breeding bird in the western Amazon .
The Isabel naked - tailed rat ( Solomys sapientis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Guadalcanal honeyeater ( Guadalcanaria inexpectata ) is a species of bird in the Meliphagidae family .
Ustilentylomataceae is a family of Basidiomycota fungi in the order Microbotryales .
The Oki salamander ( Hynobius okiensis ) is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family , endemic to Japan .
Sinentomon is the only genus in the family Sinentomidae , in the hexapod order Protura .
Phyllachne is a genus of four cushion plant species in the family Stylidiaceae .
Lophostemon ( ' lophos ' - crest , ' stemon ' - stamen ) is a genus of 4 species of evergreen tree in the myrtle family Myrtaceae .
Sphaerocodon is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1876 .
Epepeotes is a genus of flat - faced longhorns beetle belonging to the family Cerambycidae , subfamily Lamiinae .
Medinilla is a genus of about 193 species of flowering plants in the family Melastomataceae , native to tropical regions of the Old World from Africa ( two species ) east through Madagascar ( about 70 species ) and southern Asia to the western Pacific Ocean islands .
Latris lineata , the Striped trumpeter , is a species of trumpeter native to the temperate oceans of the southern hemisphere .
Xanthogalum is a botanical genus belonging to the family Apiaceae .
The Prigogine 's double - collared sunbird ( Cinnyris prigoginei ) is a species of bird in the Nectariniidae family .
Laoreicheia bulirschi is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Laoreicheia .
Oxyporhamphus micropterus is a species of halfbeak found in the tropical oceans .
Crassacantha bidens is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Crassacantha .
The Barotse barb ( Barbus barotseensis ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Barbus .
The Papuan babbler or New Guinea babbler or Isidore 's rufous babbler ( Pomatostomus isidorei or Garritornis isidorei ) is a species of bird in the Pomatostomidae family .
Parringtonia is an extinct genus of Triassic archosaur within the family Erpetosuchidae , known from the type species Parringtonia gracilis .
Anisotes is a genus of Afrotropical plants in the family Acanthaceae .
Australian bass ( Macquaria novemaculeata ) are a small to medium sized , primarily freshwater ( but estuarine spawning ) native fish found in coastal rivers and streams along the east coast of Australia .
Pilsbry 's narrow - apertured land snail , scientific name Stenotrema pilsbryi , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Polygyridae .
Petaladenium urceoliferum is a species of flowering plants in the legume family , Fabaceae .
The Sumatran ground cuckoo ( Carpococcyx viridis ) is a large , about 55 cm ( 22 in ) long , long - tailed terrestrial species of cuckoo .
The Barbary sheep ( Ammotragus lervia ) is a species of caprid ( goat - antelope ) native to rocky mountains in North Africa .
Harrison 's tube - nosed bat ( Murina harrisoni ) is a species of vesper bats ( Vespertilionidae ) .
The North African fire salamander ( Salamandra algira ) is a species of salamander in the Salamandridae family found in Algeria , Morocco , Spain , and possibly Tunisia .
Inocutis is a genus of nine species of polypore fungi in the family Hymenochaetaceae .
Hylobius is a genus of true weevils ( family Curculionidae ) .
The Madagascan plover ( Charadrius thoracicus ) is a species of bird in the Charadriidae family .
Plerandra elegantissima ( formerly called Schefflera elegantissima and Dizygotheca elegantissima ) also known as false aralia is a species of flowering plant in the Araliaceae family , native to New Caledonia .
Nassarius , common name nassa mud snails ( USA ) or dog whelks ( UK ) , is a genus of minute to medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Nassariidae .
Alyssopsis is a genus of flowering plants in the mustard family Brassicaceae .
Breadfruit ( Artocarpus altilis ) is a species of flowering tree in the mulberry family ( Moraceae ) originating in the South Pacific and that was eventually spread to the rest of Oceania .
Leucidia is a genus of butterflies in the famlly Pieridae .
Western Bonelli 's warbler is a `` warbler '' in the leaf warbler genus Phylloscopus .
Blue coral ( Heliopora coerulea ) is a species of colonial coral and the only species in the family Helioporidae and the only Octocoral known to produce a massive skeleton .
The Maracas heart - tongued frog , Phyllodytes tuberculosus , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Brazil .
Olenothus uogi is a species of crabs in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Olenothus .
Fargoa is a genus of very small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the tribe Chrysallidini within the family Pyramidellidae .
Soemmerring 's gazelle ( Nanger soemmerringii , formerly Gazella soemmerringii ) is a gazelle found in the Horn of Africa ( Djibouti , Eritrea , Ethiopia , and Somalia ) .
Anaesthetis is a genus of longhorn beetles belonging to the subfamily Lamiinae .
Busbiina is a genus of neotropic butterfly in the family Lycaenidae .
The Burmese narrow - headed softshell turtle ( Chitra vandijki ) is a turtle .
The genus Eurypterus belongs to the family Eurypteridae .
The California ground squirrel ( Otospermophilus beecheyi ) , is a common and easily observed ground squirrel of the western United States and the Baja California Peninsula ; it is common in Oregon and California and its range has relatively recently extended into Washington and northwestern Nevada .
Falsilunatia is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Naticidae , which are known as moon snails or moon shells .
Nipponosynuchus abnormalis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Nipponosynuchus .
Lauterbornia is a genus of midges in the bloodworm family ( Chironomidae ) .
Myroconger seychellensis is an eel in the family Myrocongridae ( thin eels ) described by Emma Stanislavovna Karmovskaya in 2006 .
The Gabon batis or Verreaux 's batis ( Batis minima ) is a species of bird in the Platysteiridae family .
Agassiceras belongs to the psiloceratacean family , Arietitidae , and is characterized by being compressed with a sharp venter and feeble straight ribs that may bifurcate near the umbilical edge .
The European hamster , ( Cricetus cricetus ) , also known as the Eurasian hamster , black - bellied hamster or common hamster , is the only species of the genus Cricetus .
Rhinoclavis is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Cerithiidae , the ceriths .
Marginella is a genus of small tropical and temperate sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Marginellidae , the margin snails .
The Stella hylomyscus or Stella wood mouse ( Hylomyscus stella ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Emmericia is a genus of very small freshwater snails which have an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Amnicolidae , according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda ( Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
The Tsomo River copper or Tsomo River opal ( Chrysoritis lyncurium ) is a species of butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
Subcancilla is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Mitridae .
Chaetocrepis besckii is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Chaetocrepis .
The African arowana , Heterotis niloticus , is a species of bonytongue .
Gmelina is a genus of plants in family Lamiaceae .
Under a cladistic analysis , Oryctodromeus was found to be basal within Euornithopoda and a close relative of the hypsilophodonts Orodromeus and Zephyrosaurus , which are also known from the Cretaceous of Montana .
The Philippine tailless leaf - nosed bat ( Coelops hirsutus ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
Kogania hyleae is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Kogania .
Oldenlandiopsis ( creeping - bluet ) is a genus of flowering plants in the family Rubiaceae .
Xerula is a genus of gilled mushrooms in the Physalacriaceae family .
Roupala is a neotropical genus of woody shrubs and trees in the plant family Proteaceae .
Athamantha , or Athamanta , is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae .
The Italian barbel ( Barbus plebejus ) is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family , nearly related to the common barbel Barbus barbus .
Hector 's lanternfish ( Lampanyctodes hectoris ) is a lanternfish in the family Myctophidae , the only species in the genus Lampanyctodes .
The Amazon river dolphin ( Inia geoffrensis ) , also known as the Boto or pink river dolphin , is a species of toothed whale classified in the family Iniidae .
Anillopsidius atlasicus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Anillopsidius .
Cancriniella is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the aster family , Asteraceae .
Bendire 's thrasher ( Toxostoma bendirei ) a perching bird native to the southwestern United States and northern Mexico , is a medium - sized species of thrasher .
Ornipholidotos is a genus of butterfly , commonly called glasswings or white mimics , in the family Lycaenidae .
The Inaccessible Island rail ( Atlantisia rogersi ) is a small bird of the rail family , Rallidae .
Poikilacanthus oncodes ( syn . Justicia oncodes ( Lindau ) Wassh . & C.Ezcurra ) is a plant native of Cerrado vegetation of Brazil .
Metagonimoides oregonensis is a trematode , or fluke worm , in the family Heterophyidae .
The Bornean ground cuckoo ( Carpococcyx radiceus ) is a large terrestrial species of cuckoo in the Cuculidae family .
Anemone coronaria ( poppy anemone , Spanish marigold , dağ lalesi in Turkish , calanit in Hebrew , shaqa'iq An - Nu'man in Arabic ) is a species of flowering plant in the genus Anemone , native to the Mediterranean region .
Xylocopa bryorum , or Xylocopa ( Koptortosoma ) bryorum , is a species of carpenter bee .
The Oxalobacteraceae are a family of bacteria , included in the order Burkholderiales .
The Sechura lizardfish ( Synodus sechurae ) is a species of lizardfish that lives mainly in the eastern Pacific Ocean .
Orthotrichaceae is the only family of mosses in order Orthotrichales .
The Forrest 's mouse ( Leggadina forresti ) , or desert short - tailed mouse , is a small species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Chestnut - bellied monarch ( Monarcha castaneiventris ) is a species of bird in the Monarchidae family .
Orthonama is a genus of the geometer moth family , Geometridae .
Panorpodes is a genus of scorpionflies in the family Panorpodidae , containing the following species :
The Asian stubtail ( Urosphena squameiceps ) is a species of bird in the Cettiidae family .
Moerckiaceae is a family of liverworts in the order Metzgeriales .
The Thornback skate ( Dentiraja lemprieri ) is a skate of the family Rajidae .
Eunicella is a genus of coral in the family Gorgoniidae family .
Triacanthus is a genus in tripod fish family ( Triacanthidae ) native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
The Malatgan River caecilian ( Caudacaecilia weberi ) is a species of amphibian in the Ichthyophiidae family endemic to the Philippines .
This is the type genus of its family ( Helicinidae ) and subfamily ( Helicinae ) , as well as the superfamily Helicinoidea .
Pachyphloiidae is a family of uniserial Permian Foraminifera included in the fusulinid superfamily Geinitzinacea along with the Geinitzinidae .
Eucerinoda is a genus that belongs to the bee family Apidae , subfamily Apinae .
Tarijactinoides is a genus of trilobite in the order Phacopida , which existed in what is now Bolivia .
Sphaerocylichna is a genus of deepsea snails or bubble snails , marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the family Cylichnidae , the canoe bubbles or chalice bubble snails .
Orionella is a genus of beetle in the family Carabidae , with three known species as of April 2013 .
Scleropyrum is a genus of trees in family Santalaceae first described as a genus in 1838 .
The Caucasian snow vole ( Chionomys gud ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The African keeled mud turtle ( Pelusios carinatus ) is a species of turtle in the Pelomedusidae family .
Notospira phalangioides is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Notospira .
Phytocoris is a genus of plant bugs belonging to the family Miridae .
Kenrick 's starling ( Poeoptera kenricki ) is a species of starling in the family Sturnidae .
The Weyns 's weaver ( Ploceus weynsi ) is a species of bird in the Ploceidae family .
The Sandhills chub ( Semotilus lumbee ) is a North American species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
The Carib grackle ( Quiscalus lugubris ) is a New World tropical blackbird , a resident breeder in the Lesser Antilles and northern South America east of the Andes , from Colombia east to Venezuela and north - eastern Brazil .
The Olympic mudminnow ( Novumbra hubbsi ) is a fish native to the western lowlands of Washington : the Chehalis River basin , Deschutes River basin , and some Olympic Peninsula basins .
The Peruvian skate ( Bathyraja peruana ) is a large skate found in the southeast Pacific Ocean , off the coasts of Peru , Ecuador , and Chile .
Yualikevirus is a genus of viruses in the family Siphoviridae , unassigned to a sub - family .
Mysis is a genus of mysid crustaceans in the family Mysidae , distributed mainly in the coastal zone of the Arctic and high boreal seas .
Balticoceras is a genus in the Orthocerid family , Orthoceratidae , from the Upper Ordovician of Estonia , closely related to Michelinoceras .
Paralaoma is a genus of very small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Punctidae , the dot snails .
The Cook 's swift ( Apus cooki ) , is a small bird , superficially similar to a house martin .
Cumacea is an order of small marine crustaceans of the superorder Peracarida , occasionally called hooded shrimp or comma shrimp .
Gavarilla is a spider genus of the Salticidae family ( jumping spiders ) , found in Brazil .
Paradoxosomatidae , the only family in the suborder Paradoxosomatidea ( also known as Strongylosomatidea ) , is a family of flat - backed millipedes in the order Polydesmida .
Hutterer 's brush - furred mouse or Hutterer 's brush - furred rat ( Lophuromys huttereri ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Chalcididae are a moderate - sized family within the Chalcidoidea , composed mostly of parasitoids and a few hyperparasitoids .
Appert 's tetraka or Appert 's greenbul ( Xanthomixis apperti ) is a small passerine bird endemic to the south - west of Madagascar .
Ansell 's wood mouse ( Hylomyscus anselli ) is a species of rodent in the genus Hylomyscus .
Eurotettix is genus of grasshoppers in the family Acrididae .
Hobbs ' tree frog , Hypsiboas hobbsi , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Colombia , Venezuela , and possibly Brazil .
Aphodius rufipes , the night - flying dung beetle , is a species of scarab beetle , first recorded by the zoologist Carl Linnaeus as Acrossus rufipes in his 10th edition of Systema Naturae .
Gigantocoreabus lumbaris is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Gigantocoreabus .
Streptomyces is the largest genus of Actinobacteria and the type genus of the family Streptomycetaceae .
Halimione is a plant genus from the subfamily Chenopodioideae in the Amaranthaceae family .
Muricoidea is a taxonomic superfamily of predatory sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Neogastropoda .
Bartels 's rat ( Sundamys maxi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Annamit myotis ( Myotis annamiticus ) is a species of mouse - eared bat in the family Vespertilionidae , described in 2001 , and indigenous to the Minh Hóa Districton the northern coast of Vietnam .
Martyniaceae is a family of flowering plants in the Lamiales order that are restricted to the New World .
Per - Ove Persson 1996 has classified Scanisaurus in the Cimoliasauridae , as a mesodiran plesiosaur , with a larger head and relatively shorter neck than in dolichodiran ( long - necked ) plesiosaurs .
Atrina is a cosmopolitan genus of bivalve molluscs belonging to the family Pinnidae .
The Samar cobra ( Naja samarensis ) also called Peters ' cobra , southern Philippine cobra or Visayan cobra , is a highly venomous species of spitting cobra native to Visayas and Mindanao island groups of Philippines .
Ecdyceras is a genus in the Ascocerida doubtfully assigned to the Hebetoceratidae .
Eosyodon is an extinct genus of non - mammalian synapsid .

Pycnodonte is a genus of extinct oysters , fossil marine bivalve mollusks in the family Gryphaeidae , the foam oysters or honeycomb oysters .
The Dayman big - eyed tree frog , Nyctimystes daymani , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family , endemic to Papua New Guinea .
The Baluchistan pygmy jerboa , or the dwarf three - toed jerboa , ( Salpingotulus michaelis ) is a species of rodent in the family Dipodidae .
Stichophthalma is a genus of butterfly in the Nymphalidae family . The members are confined to India , China and Southeast Asia .
The Apo sunbird ( Aethopyga boltoni ) is a species of bird in the sunbird family Nectariniidae .
Phyllomacromia a large genus of dragonflies in the family Macromiidae .
The Ludia 's shrew ( Crocidura ludia ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Silvanidae , `` silvan flat bark beetles , '' is a family of beetles in the superfamily Cucujoidea , consisting of 58 described genera and about 500 described species .
Vernay 's climbing mouse ( Dendromus vernayi ) is a species of rodent in the family Nesomyidae .
The Japanese brown frog ( Rana japonica ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family , endemic to Japan .
Philanthaxoides gallicus is a fossil species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Philanthaxoides .
The Pellegrin 's barb ( Barbus pellegrini ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
The Sikkim keelback ( Amphiesma sieboldii ) is a species of grass snake endemic to South Asia .
The Tatra pine vole , Microtus tatricus , also called the Tatra vole or Tatra ground vole , is a species of vole endemic to the Carpathian mountain range in Slovakia , Poland , Ukraine and Romania .
Hypselorhachis was assigned to the Ctenosauriscidae , a group of sail - backed archosaurs , in 1988 .
The Baoruco burrowing frog or Cabral robber frog ( Eleutherodactylus hypostenor ) is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family .
The Hypostominae are a subfamily of catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Loricariidae .
Cochran 's croaking gecko ( Aristelliger cochranae ) , also commonly known as Cochran 's Caribbean gecko and the Navassa gecko , is a species of lizard which was first described in 1931 by Chapman Grant and named after notable herpetologist and artist Doris Mable Cochran .

Anomostachys is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1951 .
The Laotian langur or white - browed black langur ( Trachypithecus laotum ) is a species of primate in the family Cercopithecidae .
The Atlantic jackknife clam , Ensis directus , also known as the bamboo clam , American jackknife clam or razor clam ( but note that `` razor clam '' sometimes refers to different species ) , is a large species of edible marine bivalve mollusc , found on the North American Atlantic coast , from Canada to South Carolina .
Haastia is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae , native to New Zealand .
Like their relatives in the Elapidae family , the majority of the Hydrophiinae species are highly venomous ; however , when bites occur , venom injection is rare , so envenomation symptoms usually seem nonexistent or trivial .
Cryomonadida is a group of heterotrophic protists , that belong to the Cercozoa .
Kairothamnus is a genus of plants under the family Picrodendraceae described as a genus in 1980 .
Pandinus is a genus of large scorpions belonging to the family Scorpionidae .
Boutiquea is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the family Annonaceae containing the single species Boutiquea platypetala .
Buarremon is a genus of perching birds in the family Emberizidae .
Silver rasbora ( Rasbora argyrotaenia ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Rasbora .
Hispanotherium was a genus of rhinoceros of the tribe Elasmotheriini endemic to Europe and Asia during the Miocene living from 16 - -7.25 mya existing for approximately 8.75 million years .
The Schwartz 's antthrush ( Chamaeza turdina ) , also known as the scalloped antthrush , is a species of bird in the Formicariidae family .
The Jamaican red macaw ( Ara gossei ) may have been a species of parrot in the Psittacidae family that lived on Jamaica , but its existence is hypothetical .
Salvadoraceae is a family in the plant order Brassicales , comprising 3 genera each with a small number of species .
As traditionally circumscribed the Sterculiaceae , Malvaceae , Bombacaceae , and Tiliaceae comprise the `` core Malvales '' of the Cronquist system and the close relationship among these families is generally recognized .
The São Tomé shrew ( Crocidura thomensis ) is a white - toothed shrew approximately three inches long found only on São Tomé Island , São Tomé and Príncipe .
Bryoxiphium is the only genus of moss in family Bryoxiphiaceae , described as a genus in 1869 .
The taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 categorizes Coreospiridae in the superfamilia Scenelloidea within the Paleozoic molluscs of uncertain systematic position .
Stellilabium is a small genus in the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) .
Chromogobius zebratus , Kolombatovic 's goby , is a species of goby found in the Mediterranean and Adriatic Seas where they occur in shallow coastal waters .
The Katanglad shrew mouse ( Crunomys suncoides ) , also known as the Kitanglad shrew - mouse is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Rangeroceratidae is a family of orthoceroid cephalopods known from the late Early Ordovician in eastern North America ( New York and Quebec ) and Great Britain , included in the order Dissidocerida .
Palpibidion minimum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Palpibidion .
The Eurybiini are a small tribe of metalmark butterflies ( family Riodinidae ) .
The Mongolian lark ( Melanocorypha mongolica ) is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family .
Perforatella is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Leptogonum is a genus of plants in the family Polygonaceae with three species on the island of Hispaniola .
Kozlov 's pygmy jerboa ( Salpingotus kozlovi ) is a species of rodent in the family Dipodidae .
Ploceus is a genus of birds in the weaver family Ploceidae .
Atemnora is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family containing one species , Atemnora westermannii .
Rhabdiferoceras is an extinct orthocerid genus belonging to the Baltoceratidae that lived in what would be North America during the Cassinian Stage at the end of the Early Ordovician , existing for approximately two million years from about 474 -472 mya .
Proterpnomyia subandina is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Proterpnomyia of the family Ulidiidae .
The Karthala white - eye ( Zosterops mouroniensis ) , also known as the Mount Karthala white - eye , Grand Comore white - eye , or Comoro white - eye , is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
Onchidium is a genus of air - breathing sea slugs , shell - less marine pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Onchidiidae .
The Maya mouse ( Peromyscus mayensis ' ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Lophanthus is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae family , first described in 1763 .
Chromolaena is a genus of about 165 species of perennials and shrubs in the aster family , Asteraceae .
The Cimidae is a taxonomic family of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the informal group Lower Heterobranchia .
Eocasea is the oldest and most basal member of Caseidae , lacking many of the specialized anatomical features that characterize later members of the group .
Dendrobatinae is the main subfamily of frogs in the Dendrobatidae family , the poison dart frogs from Central and South America , from Nicaragua to the Amazon Basin in Brazil .
Spirostylidae is an extinct family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Caenogastropoda .
The Arctic lamprey ( Lethenteron camtschaticum ) is a species of lamprey , a jawless fish in the order Petromyzontiformes .
The Machilidae are a family of insects belonging to the order Archaeognatha ( the bristletails ) .
Podisma is a genus of ' short - horned grasshoppers ' belonging to the family Acrididae and the subfamily Melanoplinae .

Bischofia is a genus of plants in the Phyllanthaceae first described as a genus in 1827 .

Ramoceros is an extinct genus of the artiodactyl family Antilocapridae endemic to Miocene and Pliocene North America .
The Pemba white - eye ( Zosterops vaughani ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
Hirasea is a genus of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Endodontidae , an endemic family of land snails from the Hawaiian islands .
Andegameryx is an extinct genus belonging to the family Hypertragulidae , within the order Artiodactyla , endemic to Europe during the Miocene , living 22.4 - -20 Ma , existing for approximately 2.4 million years .
The Balearic green toad ( Bufo balearicus , Bufotes balearicus , or Pseudepidalea balearica ) is a toad belonging to the true toad family Bufonidae .
Illicium is a genus of flowering plants treated as part of the family Schisandraceae , or alternately as the sole genus of the Illiciaceae .
Gelsemiaceae is a family of flowering plants , belonging to the order Gentianales .
The Siberian sturgeon ( Acipenser baerii ) is a species of sturgeon in the Acipenseridae family .
The Alabama pigtoe , scientific name Pleurobema johannis , was a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Plesiobalaenoptera is a genus of extinct rorqual which existed in Italy during the late Miocene epoch .
Kondoaceae is a family of fungi in the order Agaricostilbales , part of the Basidiomycota .
Parategeticula is a genus of moths of the family Prodoxidae , one of three genera known as yucca moths ; they are mutualistic pollinators of various Yucca species .
The Agriocnemidinae are a subfamily of the Coenagrionidae family of damselflies .
Salinas chub ( Gila modesta ) is a species of fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Bokermann 's casque - headed tree frog ( Trachycephalus atlas ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Brazil .
The Gila woodpecker ( Melanerpes uropygialis ) is a medium - sized woodpecker of the desert regions of the southwestern United States and western Mexico .
Haliotis pulcherrima is commonly referred to the `` Most Beautiful Abalone '' ( directly translated from Latin ) .
The Sharpe 's rail ( Gallirallus sharpei ) is a species of bird in the family Rallidae .
Mesolimnophila is a genus of crane fly in the family Limoniidae .
The Nicobar treeshrew ( Tupaia nicobarica ) is a treeshrew species in the family Tupaiidae .
Distagnostus is a genus of trilobite in the order Agnostida , which existed in what is now Queensland , Australia .
Hemigraphis is a genus of plants in the family Acanthaceae , consisting of about 30 species native to tropical Asia .
The Eimeria lie within the family Eimeriidae .
Aralazhdarcho was by Averianov assigned to the Azhdarchidae , in view of its lack of teeth and geological age .
Emicocarpus is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1900 .
Orthorrhapha is a circumscriptional name which historically was used for an infraorder of Brachycera , one of the two suborders into which the order Diptera , the flies , are divided .
Yukihikous minobusanus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Yukihikous .
The Alabama red - bellied cooter ( Pseudemys alabamensis ) or Alabama red - bellied turtle , is native to Alabama .
The Philippine frogmouth ( Batrachostomus septimus ) is a nocturnal bird that is found throughout the Philippine archipelago .
Haploblepharus is a genus of catshark , and part of the family Scyliorhinidae , containing four species of shysharks .
Afrosison is a genus of 3 species of plants in the Apiaceae family , all of which are endemic to tropical Africa .
Olpiidae is a family of pseudoscorpions in the superfamily Garypoidea .
The generic name Phreatodrobia is derived from the Greek word `` phreatos '' which means ground water , as in phreatic , and from the suffix -drobia based on family name Hydrobiidae ( where it was originally classified ) , which means `` living in water '' .
Umbetoceras is a genus belonging to the goniatitid superfamily Gastriocerataceae and family Homoceratidae from the Carboniferous of the Russian Federation and Uzbekistan .
Coccolithovirus is a genus of giant double - stranded DNA virus , in the family Phycodnaviridae .
Dinictis is a genus of the Nimravidae , an extinct family of feliform mammalian carnivores , also known as `` false saber - toothed cats '' .
Parnassiaceae Gray are a family of Flowering plants in the eudicot order Celastrales .
