The Australian hornet ( Abispa ephippium ) , actually a type of potter wasp or `` mason wasp '' , is a vespid insect native to the Australian Capital Territory , New South Wales , Northern Territory , Queensland and Western Australia states of Australia .
The Cape Melville tree frog ( Litoria andiirrmalin ) is a species of frog in the family Hylidae .
The Burmese bamboo shark , Chiloscyllium burmensis , is an extremely rare bamboo shark in the family Hemiscylliidae .
Calpus bacchi is a species of beetle in the family Silvanidae , the only species in the genus Calpus .
Pyrolobus is a genus of the Pyrodictiaceae .
Dinosauriformes fall within the clade Dinosauromorpha .
The Geokichla thrushes are medium - sized mostly insectivorous or omnivorous birds in the thrush family , Turdidae .
Bagarius ( Thai : ปลาแค้ ) is an Asian genus of catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Sisoridae .
Verheyen 's multimammate mouse ( Mastomys kollmannspergeri ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae found in Cameroon , Chad , Niger , Nigeria , and Sudan .
The Cape grassbird or Cape grass warbler ( Sphenoeacus afer ) is an African warbler found in southern Africa .
The St. Helena wrasse , Thalassoma sanctahelenae , is a poorly known species of wrasse endemic to the waters around St. Helena .
The Bliss Rapids snail , scientific name Taylorconcha serpenticola , is a species of freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Parasagitta is a genus of arrow worms ( phylum Chaetognatha ) in the family Sagittidae .
The Perez 's frog , also known as Iberian waterfrog , Iberian green frog , or Coruna frog ( Pelophylax perezi ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
Elasmobranchii ( /ɪˌlæzməˈbræŋkiaɪ/ ) is a subclass of Chondrichthyes or cartilaginous fish that includes the sharks ( Selachii ) and the rays , skates , and sawfish ( Batoidea ) .
The Archbold 's newtonia ( Newtonia archboldi ) is a species of bird in the Vangidae family .
Cherry Orange ( Citrus kinokuni ex Tanaka ) is a variety of Mandarin orange , found in Southern China and also grown in Japan where it is known as Mukaku - Kishu .
Pampas deer ( Ozotoceros bezoarticus ) live in the grasslands of South America at low elevations .
Punctabyssia is a genus of small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pseudococculinidae , the false limpets .
Gleboceras is a globular gonititid from the upper Carboniferous of the Urals , named by Ruzhentsev , 1950 , tentatively assigned to the Thalassoceratidae , and placed in the subfamily Gleboceratinae .
Sericicorpus nigrum is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
Blaesodactylus is a small genus of four species of lizards , endemic to Madagascar , commonly known as velvet geckos , and formerly considered part of the genus Homopholis .
The Bibundi bat ( Glauconycteris egeria ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
The Chestnut - bellied spiny rat ( Maxomys ochraceiventer ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Apamea pallifera was originally described in Polia , but listed in Andropolia by Franclemont and Todd ( 1983 ) and Poole ( 1989 ) .
Euphausia is the largest genus of krill , and is placed in the family Euphausiidae .
Coptodipteris is a genus of ferns in the family Dennstaedtiaceae described as a genus in 1937 .
Bisatoceras is a late Paleozoic ( Upper Mississippian - Upper Pennsylvanian ) ammonite ; a member of the goniatitid family Bisatoceratidae .
Arboroharamiya belongs to a group of mammaliaforms called Haramiyida .
The Apache trout , Oncorhynchus apache , is a species of freshwater fish in the salmon family ( family Salmonidae ) of order Salmoniformes .
Daphniphyllum is the sole genus in the flowering plant family Daphniphyllaceae described as a genus in 1826 .
Hodgson 's giant flying squirrel ( Petaurista magnificus ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Yogetor is a spider genus of the Salticidae , or jumping spider family .
Pseudatelus is a genus of shield bugs of the family Pentatomidae and tribe Halyini .
The Poterioceratidae is a family of nautiloid cephalopods included in the Oncocerida that lived during the period from the Early Devonian to the Early Carboniferous ( Mississippian ) .
Perophoridae is a sea squirts family in the suborder Phlebobranchia .
Muscidora tricolor is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Muscidora .
The Hose 's partridge ( Rhizothera dulitensis ) , also known as Dulit partridge , has been considered a distinctive subspecies of the long - billed partridge , a bird in the Phasianidae , or pheasant , family .
Alomya is a genus of the parasitic wasp family Ichneumonidae .
The Australian blackspotted catshark ( Aulohalaelurus labiosus ) is a catshark of the family Scyliorhinidae in the order Carcharhiniformes .
The Jondachi tree frog , Hyloscirtus staufferorum , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Ecuador .
Orthohepevirus is a genus of viruses assigned to the Hepeviridae family .
Urtinotherium was a representative of the large subfamily Indricotheriinae , and almost reached the proportions of Paraceratherium .
Wadeoceras is a nautiloid genus included in the Polyelasmoceratidae , a family of oncocerids living from the Middle Silurian to the Late Devonian .
The Dexiarchia are a suborder of sea slugs , shell - less marine gastropod molluscs in the order Nudibranchia .
Braulidae , or bee lice , is a family of flies ( Diptera ) with eight species in two genera , Braula and Megabraula .
Spatangus is a genus of heart urchins in the Spatangidae family .
The Schwagerinidae comprise a family of large , generally fusiform , foraminiferans included in the Fusulinacea , a superfamily of fusulinids , locally abundant during the later Carboniferous ( Pennsylvanian ) and most of the Permian .
Urbacodon resembles Byronosaurus and Mei but differs from most other Troodontidae in that its teeth lack serrations .
Amphelissoeme viridescens is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Amphelissoeme .
The Guadeloupe big - eyed bat ( Chiroderma improvisum ) is a species of bat in the family Phyllostomidae .
Buccinulum is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Buccinidae , the whelks .
Cagle 's map turtle ( Graptemys caglei ) is a species of turtle in the Emydidae family endemic to the United States .
Kleinia neriifolia also known as Verode or Berode and previously known as Senecio kleinia is one of flowering plant species of the genus Kleinia and in the daisy family ( Asteraceae ) .
Galidictis is a genus in the subfamily Galidiinae of the family Eupleridae : a group of carnivorans that are endemic to Madagascar .
Titiscania is the type genus and also the only genus in the family Titiscaniidae .
The Daurian partridge , Perdix daurica , is a gamebird in the pheasant family Phasianidae of the order Galliformes , gallinaceous birds .
Lagenivaginopseudobenedenia is a genus of monopisthocotylean monogenean , included in the family Capsalidae .
Hirsutella is a genus of asexually reproducing fungi in the Ophiocordycipitaceae family .
Jensenia is a bryophyte plant genus in the liverwort family Pallaviciniaceae .
Chemnitzia is a genus of very small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Blumeodendron is a genus of dioecious trees of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1873 .
Calappula saussurei is a species of crab in the family Calappidae , the only species in the genus Calappula .
Moghradictis is an extinct species of carnivorous cat - like mammals belonging to the superfamily Aeluroidea , endemic to North Africa from the Miocene 23.03 - -15.97 Ma , existing for approximately 7.06 million years .
The Saint Lucia black finch ( Melanospiza richardsoni ) is a species of bird in the family Thraupidae .
Mitopus is a genus of the harvestman family Phalangiidae with nine described species .
Ziegler 's crocodile newt , Tylototriton ziegleri , is a species of newt in the Salamandridae family .
Bitter orange , Seville orange , sour orange , bigarade orange , or marmalade orange refers to a citrus tree ( Citrus × aurantium ) and its fruit .
The Cameroon climbing mouse ( Dendromus oreas ) is a species of rodent in the family Nesomyidae .
Rhaebo haematiticus ( formerly Bufo haematiticus ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Fleischmannia is in the tribe Eupatorieae and as such has flower heads with disc florets and no ray florets .
Harpoceratinae is an extinct subfamily of cephalopods belonging to the family Hildoceratidae .
Creagh 's horseshoe bat ( Rhinolophus creaghi ) is a species of bat in the family Rhinolophidae .
The Apalachicola snapping turtle ( Macrochelys apalachicolae ) is a species that lives in the Apalachicola River , United States .
The Ommatidae are a family of beetles in the suborder Archostemata .
Changiostyrax dolichocarpa , formerly known as Sinojackia dolicocarpa , is a species of flowering plant in the family Styracaceae .
The Indian aurochs ( Bos primigenius namadicus ) is a subspecies of the extinct aurochs .
Aristocapsa is a genus of plants in the family Polygonaceae with a single species , Aristocapsa insignis , restricted to California .
Menetries 's warbler or Ménétries 's warbler ( Sylvia mystacea ) is a small passerine bird of Southwest Asia belonging to the genus Sylvia .
Vinogradov 's jerboa ( Allactaga vinogradovi ) is a species of rodent in the family Dipodidae .
Microdipnodes tshuapanus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Microdipnodes .
The Phyllomedusinae are a subfamily of Hylidae , the tree frogs .
The Yarra pygmy perch , Nannoperca obscura , is a species of temperate perch endemic to Australia .
Weyns 's duiker ( Cephalophus weynsi ) is a tiny antelope found in the Democratic Republic of Congo , Uganda , and western Kenya .
Berula is a cosmopolitan genus of flowering plant in the carrot family , whose species are known as water parsnip , as are some other plants in Apiaceae such as Sium latifolium and Sium suave .
Pseudovadonia is a genus of beetles belonging to the family Cerambycidae , subfamily Lepturinae .
Raorchestes is a genus of frogs in the Rhacophorinae subfamily .
Meristella is placed in the family Meristellidae of the articulate brachiopod order Athyridida .
Munequita pulchra is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
Hovorigenium ecuadorense is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Hovorigenium .
The Crested blenny ( Parablennius laticlavius ) is a species of combtooth blenny found around New South Wales , Australia and New Zealand to depths of between 1 to 3 metres ( 3.3 to 9.8 ft ) .
The Heard Island shag is one of the blue - eyed shags , sometimes placed in the genus Leucocarbo , and a subspecies of the imperial shag .
Lianghusuchus is an extinct genus of crocodylid crocodilian .
Enoplometopus occidentalis , the red reef lobster , Hawaiian reef lobster , or hairy reef lobster , is a reef lobster , native to the Indo - Pacific Ocean .
Tetrorchidium is a genus of flowering plants in the family Euphorbiaceae first described in 1841 .
Couroupita is a genus of flowering plants of Lecythidaceae family first described as a genus in 1775 .
Trichocladus is a genus of plant in family Hamamelidaceae , consisting of shrubs or small trees .
Carlina acaulis ( stemless carline thistle , dwarf carline thistle , silver thistle ) is a perennial dicotyledonous flowering plant in the family Asteraceae , native to alpine regions of central and southern Europe .
The Eastern Atlantic and Mediterranean species of the family Pyramidellidae , here listed under the genus Parthenina Bucquoy , Dautzenberg & Dollfus , 1883 , have been included by most 20th - century European authors in the genus Chrysallida Carpenter , 1856 , following a lead by Winckworth ( 1932 ) .
The Cozumel thrasher ( Toxostoma guttatum ) is a bird from the mockingbird family ( Mimidae ) , which is endemic to the island of Cozumel off the Yucatán Peninsula , Mexico .
The Java mouse - deer ( Tragulus javanicus ) is a species of even - toed ungulate in the family Tragulidae .
Cercozoa are closely related to Foraminifera and Radiolaria , amoeboids that usually have complex shells , and together with them form a supergroup called the Rhizaria .
It is placed in the monotypic family Pseudodalatiidae , and contains the two species Pseudodalatias barnstonensis and Pseudodalatias henarejensis .
Coincya is a genus of flowering plant that belongs to the family Brassicaceae .
Pentila is a genus of butterfly , commonly called pentilas or buffs , in the family Lycaenidae .
Laetia is a genus of plant in family Salicaceae ( formerly placed in Flacourtiaceae ) .
Loricariinae is a subfamily of the family Loricariidae of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) .
The Chaco grass mouse ( Akodon toba ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Cyprus dwarf elephant ( Palaeoloxodon cypriotes ) is an extinct species of elephant related to the living Asian elephant .
Potosi pupfish ( Cyprinodon alvarezi ) is a species of fish in the Cyprinodontidae family .
Rice hoja blanca virus is a member of the genus Tenuivirus .
Aviatyrannis was in 2003 by Rauhut placed in the Tyrannosauroidea , in a basal position .
The spider family Actinopodidae is a family of mygalomorph spiders found in Australia , South America , and Central America .
Liolaemus is by far the largest genus of the liolaemid lizards , which are traditionally treated as subfamily Liolaeminae within the Iguanidae but more recently were proposed for upranking to full family Liolaemidae .
Doliodactyla janatai is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Doliodactyla .
It was traditionally assigned to the tribe Dalbergieae , mainly on the basis of flower morphology ; recent molecular phylogenetic analyses assigned Vatairea into an informal , monophyletic clade called the `` vataireoids '' .
Neoorthogonius orientalis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Neoorthogonius .
Tripora is genus of plants in the Lamiaceae , first described as a genus in 1999 .
The Halmahera boobook ( Ninox hypogramma ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
The Duida woodcreeper ( Lepidocolaptes duidae ) is a species of bird in the Dendrocolaptinae subfamily .
The Llanos long - nosed armadillo ( Dasypus sabanicola ) is a species of armadillo in the family Dasypodidae .
Titanidiops is a spider genus in the family Idiopidae .
Lampropholis , the Indo - Australian ground skinks or sunskinks , are a genus of skinks in the lizard subfamily Lygosominae .
Graptopetalum ( leatherpetal ) is a plant genus of the family Crassulaceae .
The most recent systematic revision of Phorusrhacidae placed Psilopterus within the Psilopterinae subfamily , along with the Procariama and Paleopsilopterus genera , and divided Psilopterus into four species .
Mitotichthys meraculus ( Whitley , 1948 ) ( western crested pipefish ) Mitotichthys mollisoni ( E. O. G. Scott , 1955 ) ( Mollison 's pipefish ) Mitotichthys semistriatus ( Kaup , 1856 ) ( half - banded pipefish ) Mitotichthys tuckeri ( E. O. G. Scott , 1942 ) ( Tucker 's pipefish )
Enneapterygius ventermaculus , known commonly as the Blotched triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Atropa is a genus of flowering plants in the nightshade family , Solanaceae : tall , calcicole , herbaceous perennials ( rhizomatous hemicryptophytes ) , bearing large leaves and glossy berries particularly dangerous to children , due to their combination of an attractive , cherry - like appearance with a high toxicity .
The Asian leaf turtle ( Cyclemys dentata ) is a species of turtle found in Southeast Asia .
Suchomimus was placed in the Spinosauridae , a group of large predators with jaws adapted for hunting fish and with flatter skulls when compared to other similarly - sized theropods , like the Tyrannosauridae .
The Levant sparrowhawk ( Accipiter brevipes ) is a small bird of prey .
Galinthias is a genus in the order Mantodea , in the family Hymenopodidae .
The Chesterfield Island stingaree or Deforge 's stingaree ( Urolophus deforgesi ) is a little - known species of stingray in the family Urolophidae , endemic to the continental slope off the Chesterfield Islands .
The monotypic genus was circumscribed in 2010 to accommodate the species Connopus acervatus , formerly in the genus Gymnopus .
Enneapterygius tutuilae , known commonly as the High - hat triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
The Margarodidae or ground pearls ( cottony cushion scales , giant coccids , giant scale insects ) are a family of scale insects within the superfamily Coccoidea .
The Ja River scrub warbler ( Bradypterus grandis ) is a species of Old World warbler in the Locustellidae family .
The Surinam golden - eyed tree frog , Trachycephalus coriaceus , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Bolivia , Brazil , Ecuador , French Guiana , Peru , Suriname , and possibly Colombia .
The Andaman flowerpecker ( Dicaeum virescens ) is a species of bird in the Dicaeidae family .
Dimeroceratoidea , formerly Dimerocerataceae , is one of six superfamilies in the gonititid suborder Tornoceratina which lived During the Devonian .
Pseudobalistes flavomarginatus Rüppell , 1829 ( Yellowmargin triggerfish ) Pseudobalistes fuscus ( Bloch & J. G. Schneider , 1801 ) ( Yellow - spotted triggerfish ) Pseudobalistes naufragium D. S. Jordan & Starks , 1895 ( Stone triggerfish )
Galegeae is a tribe of the subfamily Faboideae .
Cetotheriophanes is an extinct rorqual from the late Pliocene ( Piacenzian ) of northern Italy .
Raxa is a genus of true bugs in the family Pyrrhocoridae .
The Suwannee bass ( Micropterus notius ) is a species of freshwater fish in the sunfish family ( Centrarchidae ) of order Perciformes .
The Samlakki tree frog ( Litoria capitula ) is a species of frog in the family Hylidae .
Gabbiella is an East African genus of small freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic prosobranch gastropod mollusks in the family Bithyniidae .
The Felinae are a subfamily of the family Felidae , which includes the genera and species listed below .
Sigmoilina is a protist , or proctoctist according to B.K. Sen Gupta , 1999 , included in the miliolid family Hauerinidae ( Loeblich & Tappan , 1988 ) .
The Protorthoptera are an extinct order of Palaeozoic insects , and represent a wastebasket taxon and paraphyletic assemblage of basal neoptera .
Huanansaurus was , within the Oviraptoridae , placed in the Oviraptorinae , as a sister species of Citipati .
Kabeiro is a genus of dendronotid nudibranch in the family Dotidae .
Iridaceae is a family of plants in Order Asparagales , taking its name from the Irises .
The Cahaba pebblesnail , scientific name Clappia cahabensis , is a species of very small freshwater snail , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Lithoglyphidae .
The Halmahera cuckooshrike ( Coracina parvula ) is a species of bird in the Campephagidae family .
Abacetus is a genus of beetles in the family Carabidae , distributed across Africa , Asia and Australia , with a single European species .
The Yucatan deer mouse ( Peromyscus yucatanicus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Sockeye salmon ( Oncorhynchus nerka ) , also called red salmon or blueback salmon , is an anadromous species of salmon found in the Northern Pacific Ocean and rivers discharging into it .
Lampropidae is a family of cold - water crustaceans belonging to the order Cumacea .
Broadley 's dwarf gecko ( Lygodactylus broadleyi ) is a species of gecko native to Tanzania .
The Lake Chad gerbil or Lake Chad tateril , Taterillus lacustris , is a species of gerbil found in Cameroon and Nigeria .
Metalepis is a genus of plant in family Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1866 .
Wied 's marmoset ( Callithrix kuhlii ) , also known as Wied 's black - tufted - ear marmoset , is a New World monkey that lives in tropical and subtropical forests of eastern Brazil .
The Photinini are a large tribe of fireflies in the subfamily Lampyrinae .
Labidodemas is a genus of marine sea cucumbers in the family Holothuriidae .
The Black mountain salamander ( Desmognathus welteri ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Micranthaxia rediviva is a fossil species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Micranthaxia .
Sabine 's puffback ( Dryoscopus sabini ) , also known as the large - billed puffback , is a species of bird in the Malaconotidae family .
Pratt 's vole ( Eothenomys chinensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Clanculus is a genus of sea snail , marine gastropod molluscs of the family Trochidae , the top shells .
The Taiwan partridge ( Arborophila crudigularis ) , also called Taiwan hill partridge , is a species of bird in the Phasianidae family .
Michelia is a genus of flowering plants belonging to the Magnolia family ( Magnoliaceae ) .
Bolitoglossa is a genus of lungless salamanders , also called tropical climbing salamanders or web - footed salamanders , in the family Plethodontidae .
Neodaruma tamanukii is a moth in the Drepanidae family and only species in the Neodaruma genus .
Spotfin croaker ( Roncador stearnsii ) is a species of croaker occurring from Mazatlán , Mexico , to Point Conception , California , including the Gulf of California .
Acanthixalus , commonly known as the African wart frogs , is a small genus of frogs in the Hyperoliidae family .
Sebastonyma is a genus of grass skippers in the family Hesperiidae .
Mitranthes is a genus of plant in family Myrtaceae described as a genus in 1856 .
Zoarces is a genus of eelpouts in the Zoarcidae family .
Dollman 's spiny rat ( Maxomys dollmani ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Pachyceras is a perisphinctoid ammonite genus from the Middle Jurassic , upper Callovian stage , and is the type genus for the family Pachyceratidae .
The Oriental worm - eel ( Lamnostoma orientalis , also known as the Oriental snake eel , the Oriental sand - eel , or the Finny sand - eel ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .
Panorpida or Mecopterida is a superorder of Endopterygota .
The Mindanao Island caecilian , Ichthyophis mindanaoensis , is a species of amphibian in the Ichthyophiidae family endemic to the Philippines .
Zoutpansberg girdled lizard ( Smaug depressus ) is a species of the genus Smaug .
Coniopterygoidea is a lacewing superfamily in the suborder Hemerobiiformia .
Catfish belong to a superorder called the Ostariophysi , which also includes the Cypriniformes , Characiformes , Gonorynchiformes and Gymnotiformes , a superorder characterized by the Weberian apparatus .
Leishmaniavirus ( also known as Leishmania RNA virus or LRV ) is a genus of double - stranded RNA virus , in the family Totiviridae .
The Anzuetoi arboreal alligator lizard ( Abronia anzuetoi ) is a species of lizard endemic to Volcán de Agua in Guatemala .
Fumana ( needle sunrose ) is a small genus of flowering plants in Cistaceae family .
The Bolivian white - crowned tapaculo ( Scytalopus bolivianus ) is a species of bird in the Rhinocryptidae family .
Oxytrichidae is a ciliate protozoan family in the order Sporadotrichida .
Lastreopsis ( shieldfern ) is a genus of ferns in the family Elaphoglossaceae .
The Venerable collared lizard ( Crotaphytus antiquus ) is a species of lizard in the genus Crotaphytus , native to northern Mexico .
Hedyotis ( starviolet ) is a genus of flowering plants in the family Rubiaceae .
Asprocottus herzensteini , the Herzenstein 's rough sculpin , is a deepwater sculpin , a freshwater fish which is endemic to Lake Baikal , Russia .
Euryabax colossus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Euryabax .
Xantolis is a genus of trees and shrubs in the family Sapotaceae described as a genus in 1838 .
Spix 's macaw ( Cyanopsitta spixii ) , also known as the little blue macaw , is a macaw native to Brazil .
The Kermesidae are a family of scale insects belonging to the superfamily Coccoidea .
Pseudovermis is genus of minute sea slugs , specifically aolid nudibranchs , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Pseudovermidae .
Vachellia farnesiana , also known as Acacia farnesiana , and previously Mimosa farnesiana , commonly known as needle bush , is so named because of the numerous thorns distributed along its branches .
Hooglandia ignambiensis is a species of trees in the Cunoniaceae family .
Poecilopyrodes pictus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Poecilopyrodes .
The Bagobo rat ( Bullimus bagobus ) is one of three species of rodent in the genus Bullimus , and in the diverse family Muridae .
Aquilonastra is a genus of small sea stars within the family Asterinidae .
The Transvaal dwarf chameleon ( Bradypodion transvaalense ) is a chameleon native to South Africa , where it is found in forested areas of Mpumalanga and Limpopo provinces .
The Oleacinidae family is classified within the informal group Sigmurethra , itself belonging to the clade Stylommatophora within the clade Eupulmonata ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Ctenochaetus , or bristletooth tangs , is a genus of fish in the Acanthuridae family .
Triglochin is a genus in the family Juncaginaceae described as a genus by Linnaeus in 1753 .
Mexican redhorse ( Moxostoma austrinum ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Moxostoma .
The Perijá metaltail ( Metallura iracunda ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
The Bogotá yellow - shouldered bat ( Sturnira bogotensis ) is a species of bat in the family Phyllostomidae .
Heliciopsis is a genus of about thirteen species of trees , constituting part of the flowering plant family Proteaceae .

The Mees 's nightjar ( Caprimulgus meesi ) is a member of the nightjar family ( Caprimulgidae ) described as new to science in 2004 .

Per - Olof Arvidsson ( 18 December 1864 -- 30 August 1947 ) was a Swedish shooter who competed at the 1908 and 1912 Summer Olympics in eight events in total .

Robert Harbin ( born Ned Williams 14 February 1908 Balfour , South Africa -- 12 January 1978 Westminster , London , UK ) was a British magician and author .

Otto Beckmann ( born 5 May 1908 in Vladivostok , Russia ; died 13 February 1997 in Vienna ) was an Austrian sculptor and pioneer of media and computer art .
Franz Rudolf Bornewasser ( born 12 March 1866 in Radevormwald ; died 20 December 1951 in Trier ) was a Roman Catholic Bishop of Trier , in Germany , during the Nazi era .
Flaminio Ponzio ( 1560 - -1613 ) was an Italian architect during the late - Renaissance or so - called Mannerist period , serving in Rome as the architect for Pope Paul V. Ponzio was born in Viggiù near Varese , and he died in Rome .
Carol Grace was born in New York City 's Lower East Side ; her mother , who was sixteen when she gave birth , was the daughter of Russian Jewish immigrants .
Armando Maugini ( May 1 , 1889 , Messina -- 1975 , Florence ) was an Italian agronomist and tropicalist .
Suzanne Belperron ( 1900 - -1983 ) , born in Saint - Claude , France , was an influential 20th century jewellery designer based in Paris .
John Menzies Macfarlane ( October 11 , 1833 -- June 4 , 1892 ) was a Scottish - born Latter - day Saint hymnwriter , choir director and civic leader who spent most of his life in Utah Territory .
Zdeněk Nejedlý ( February 10 , 1878 in Litomyšl , Bohemia -- March 9 , 1962 in Prague ) was a Czech musicologist , music critic , author , and politician whose ideas dominated the cultural life of what is now the Czech Republic for most of the twentieth century .
August Matthias Hagen ( 23 February 1794 , near Valka , Latvia - 2 December 1878 , Tartu , Estonia ) was a Baltic German painter and graphic artist .

Karl Ludwig Manzel ( 3 June 1858 , Neu Kosenow - 20 June 1936 , Berlin ) was a German sculptor , painter and graphic artist .
Friedrich Hillegeist ( born 21 February 1895 in Vienna , died 3 December 1973 in Vienna ) was an Austrian politician .
René Viguier ( 19 May 1880 in Paris -- 17 January 1931 in Caen ) was a French botanist known for his investigations of plants within the family Araliaceae .
Vasiliy Kulik ( 17 January 1956 -- 26 June 1989 ) was a Soviet serial killer responsible for the murders of 13 people ( children and elderly women ) in Irkutsk between 1984 and 1986 .
Zephaniah Swift died on September 27 , 1823 while visiting his children in Warren , Ohio .

Salvatore Satta ( Nuoro , 9 August 1902 -- Rome 19 April 1975 ) was an Italian jurist and writer .
Alfred Dieck ( 4 April 1906 in Schönebeck -- 7 January 1989 in Bremen ) was a German archaeologist internationally recognised for the scientific studies on bog bodies and bog finds .

William Hendricks ( November 12 , 1782 -- May 16 , 1850 ) was a Democratic - Republican member of the House of Representatives from 1816 to 1822 , the third Governor of Indiana from 1822 to 1825 , and an Anti - Jacksonian member of the U.S. Senate from 1825 to 1837 .
José Celín Discua Elvir ( born 26 August 1950 in Valle de Ángeles ) is a Honduran politician who currently serves as deputy of the National Congress of Honduras representing and leadering the National Party of Honduras for El Paraíso .

Richalmus ( Richalm von Schöntal or Schönthal ) ( died 1219 ) was a German Cistercian abbot , known for his work of monastic life , notorious for its demonology , the Liber Revelationum , printed much later in the sixteenth century .
Francisco Robles García ( May 5 , 1811 -- March 7 , 1893 ) was President of Ecuador from October 16 , 1856 to September 17 , 1859 .
George Edgar West ( October 9 , 1936 -- June 25 , 2008 ) , known as Buddy West , was a Republican member of the Texas House of Representatives from Odessa , Texas , who was known for his staunch support of his hometown University of Texas of the Permian Basin .
Girdhari Lal Bhargava ( 11 November 1936 -- 8 March 2009 ) was a member of the Lok Sabha ( lower house of parliament ) in India .
Olaus Laurentii ( died 25 June 1438 ) was a Swedish ecclesiastic and archbishop of Uppsala .

Dale Mallory is an American politician and former Democratic member of the Ohio House of Representatives , representing the 32nd District from 2007 to 2014 .
Elizabeth Ames Jones ( born October 29 , 1956 ) is a former member of the Texas House of Representatives and the Texas Railroad Commission , the regulatory body over petroleum and natural gas .

Richard Heales ( 1821 -- 19 June 1864 ) , Victorian colonial politician , was the 4th Premier of Victoria .
Steve McManus is a Republican member of the Tennessee House of Representatives for the 10th district , encompassing Cordova and part of Shelby County .
Herman O. Kent ( April 19 , 1884 -- ? ) was a farmhand , typesetter and trade union activist from Milwaukee , Wisconsin who served two terms as a Socialist member of the Wisconsin State Assembly representing Milwaukee County 's 9th Assembly district ( the 9th and 10th wards of the City of Milwaukee ) .

I 'm for the Hippopotamus ( Italian : Io sto con gli ippopotami ) is a 1979 Italian adventure - comedy film directed by Italo Zingarelli and starring Terence Hill and Bud Spencer .

Altered States is a 1980 American science fiction - horror film adaptation of a novel by the same name by playwright and screenwriter Paddy Chayefsky .
Mélo is a 1929 play by Henri Bernstein which premiered in the US in 1931 at the Ethel Barrymore Theatre .

María Candelaria is a 1944 Mexican film directed by Emilio Fernández and starring Dolores del Río and Pedro Armendáriz .
Sackcloth and Scarlet is a 1925 American silnt drama film directed by Henry King and written by Jules Furthman , Thomas J. Geraghty , George Fort Gibbs and Julie Herne .

It consists of only one species , Guarandita bolivariana , which is found in Ecuador ( Bolivar Province ) .

Glochidion sisparense is a species of tree in the Phyllanthaceae family .
Nebria sahlbergi is a species of brown coloured ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Aleutian Islands , Canada , and in the southern part of the United States .
Cnaemidophorus is a genus of plume moth in the Pterophoridae family .
Armillaria heimii is a species of fungus in the Physalacriaceae family of mushrooms .
Endostemon is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae , first described in 1910 .
Heteromyidae is a family of rodents comprised by kangaroo rats , kangaroo mice , and pocket mice .
Stypandra glauca is a species of rhizomatous perennials .
Portulaca pilosa is a species of flowering plant in the purslane family , Portulacaceae , that is native to the Americas .
Adenocarpus is a genus of flowering plants in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Hemicryllis alboguttata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Hemicryllis .
Orthotylus elongatus is a species of bug from the Miridae family that is endemic to Cyprus .
Tiquilia nesiotica , known as gray matplant , is a species of plant in the Boraginaceae family .
Oreumenes is a small Far East genus of large Eumenes - like potter wasps .
Glyptothorax armeniacus is a species of catfish that was first described by Berg , 1918 .
Bematistes is a genus of butterflies in the family Nymphalidae .
Mesogastropoda was for many years a traditional taxonomic group of snails , an order .
Amorphoscelis elegans is a species of praying mantis found in Ethiopia , Somalia , and Tanzania .
Elaphrosaurus ( pron.:ell - AH - fro - SAWR - us ) is a genus of ceratosaurian theropod dinosaur that lived approximately 154 to 150 million years ago during the later part of the Jurassic Period in what is now Tanzania in Africa .
Pseudotmesisternus vestitus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudotmesisternus .
Rhinophis lineatus , or Striped earth snake , is a recently described fossorial species of snake in the Uropeltidae family .
Clitandra is a genus of flowering plants in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1849 .
Gradsteinia torrenticola is a species of moss in the Amblystegiaceae family .
The Apicomplexa ( also called Apicomplexia ) are a large phylum of parasitic protists .
Corynebacterium jeikeium is a rod - shaped , catalase - positive , aerobic species of actinobacteria in the genus Corynebacterium .
Hymenophyton flabellatum is a species of the order Metzgeriales ( liverworts ) , one of perhaps several species in the genus Hymenophyton .
The Ichthyophiidae are the family of Asiatic tailed caecilians or fish caecilians found in South and Southeast Asia as well as southernmost China .
Koeleria vallesiana , Somerset hair grass , is a grass species of the genus Koeleria .
Triadobatrachus ( ' triple - frog ' ) is an extinct genus of frog - like amphibian , including only one known species , Triadobatrachus massinoti .
Grossuana thracica is a species of very small freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae
Nebria dilatata is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Canary Islands .
Chevrotains , also known as mouse - deer , are small ungulates that make up the family Tragulidae , the only members of the infraorder Tragulina .
Cooperoceras is a genus of Tainoceratid nautiloid cephalopod mollusk within the superfamily Tainocerataceae , characterized by and evolute shell with an open , perforate , umbilicus , sinuous ribs at maturity , and recurved hollow spines along the ventro - lateral shoulders .
Horntail or wood wasp is the common name for any of the 150 non - social species of the family Siricidae , of the order Hymenoptera , a type of xylophagous sawfly .
Leptopoma nitidum is a species of land snail with a gill and an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Cyclophoridae .
Actinoseris is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family described as a genus in 1970 .
Hesperomannia ( island - aster ) is a genus of flowering plant in the Asteraceae family .
Thus , the genus contains only a single species , Prophaethon shrubsolei .
Bolma tayloriana , common name Taylor 's star shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
The Tristram 's woodpecker ( kor . : 크낙새 khunak , jap . : Kitataki ) ( Dryocopus javensis richardsi ) is a rare Korean subspecies of the white - bellied woodpecker .
Eupogonesthes xenicus , the Exotic snaggletooth , is a species of barbeled dragonfish found in the eastern Indian Ocean .
Setaria viridis is a species of grass known by many common names , including green foxtail green bristlegrass , and wild foxtail millet .
Schiedea apokremnos is a rare species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common names Kauai schiedea , Na Pali Coast schiedea , and ma`oli`oli .
Mutisia is a genus of flowering plant in the mutisia tribe within the sunflower family .
Lethrinops lethrinus is a species of cichlid native to Lake Malawi and western shore feeder streams , Lake Malombe and the upper reaches of the Shire River .
The Melanotaenium is a genus of smut fungi in the family Melanopsichiaceae .
Collinsium was a genus of lobopodian from the from the early Cambrian .
Typhlachirus caecus is a species of sole native to the coastal waters of Indonesia .
Lametilidae is a family of bivalves .
Synanceia is a genus of fish of the family Synanceiidae , the stonefishes , whose members are venomous , dangerous , and even fatal to humans .
Zea luxurians is a true grass species in the genus Zea and a teosinte , found in Guatemala , Honduras and Nicaragua .
The family of marine fishes Hexagrammidae incorporates the greenlings .
Sedella pumila is a species of flowering plant in the stonecrop family known by the common name Sierra mock stonecrop .
Gamasolaelaps bellingeri is a species of mite belonging to the family Veigaiidae .

Palaeosinopa is an extinct genus of semi - aquatic , non - placental eutherian mammals belonging to the family Pantolestidae .
Spilotragoides griseomaculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Spilotragoides .
Chiton glaucus , common name the green chiton or the Blue Green Chiton ( Boyle , 1970 ) , is a species of chiton , a marine polyplacophoran mollusk in the family Chitonidae , the typical chitons .
Septuaginta is a genus of moth in the Pterophoridae family containing only one species , Septuaginta zagulajevi , which is found in Russia ( the Chita region in Siberia ) .
Elachistocleis panamensis ( common name : Panama humming frog ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Habronattus is a genus in the family Salticidae ( jumping spiders ) .
Gosztonyia antarctica is a species of fish described in early 2009 .
Macropoides crassipes is a species of beetles of the scarab beetle family .
Salix canariensis is a species of willow native to the islands of Madeira and Canaries .
Hakea tephrosperma , commonly known as Hooked Needlewood , is a shrub or small tree species in the family Proteaceae .
Stomatolina rufescens , common name the northern wide - mouthed shell , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
The Kolyma Eighty - eight ( Catacore kolyma ) is the only species in the genus Catacore .
Thyreophagus is a genus of mites in the family Acaridae .
Acer calcaratum is an Asian species of maple found in Yunnan and northern Indochina ( Myanmar , Thailand , Vietnam ) .
The Mordellidae are a family of beetles commonly known as tumbling flower beetles for the typical irregular movements they make when escaping predators , or as pintail beetles due to their abdominal tip which aids them in performing these tumbling movements .
Pseudelephantopus spicatus , the dog's - tongue or false elephant 's foot , is a plant species native to tropical areas in the West Indies , Latin America , Africa and Southeast Asia .
Downingia insignis is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common names harlequin calicoflower and cupped downingia .
Prasophyllum correctum , common name Bairnsdale leek orchid , is a species of orchid species endemic to a small region in the State of Victoria , Australia .
Hemigraphis repanda is a species of plant of family Acanthaceae .
Stegopelta ( meaning `` roofed shield '' ) is a genus of armored dinosaur .
Cyclothyris is an extinct genus of brachiopod from the Cretaceous of Africa , Asia , Europe , and North America .
Epipompilus insularis is a species of spider wasp which is endemic to New Zealand and it is the only species of the genus Epipompilus found in New Zealand .
Nerine masoniorum is a species of flowering plant in the family Amaryllidaceae , subfamily Amaryllidoideae , native to the eastern Cape Province of South Africa .
Streblus smithii ( also known as Smith 's Milkwood and the Three Kings milk tree ) is a species of plant in the family Moraceae .
Epidendrum hololeucum is an epiphytic species of orchid of the genus Epidendrum from Brazil .
Peniagone vitrea is a species of deep - sea swimming sea cucumber in the family Elpidiidae .
Hemidoras morrisi is a species of thorny catfish found in the Amazon basin of Brazil , Ecuador , Colombia and Peru .
Stenopadus is a genus of South American plants in the mutisia tribe within the sunflower family .
Nebria torosa is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Qinghai province of China .
Paphiopedilum insigne is a species of orchid endemic to the Indian states of Assam and Meghalaya .
Schoenoplectus ( club - rush ( Old World species ) , bulrush or tule ( New World species ) ) is a genus of plants in the sedges with a cosmopolitan distribution .
Paramecium bursaria is a species of ciliate protozoan that has a mutualistic endosymbiotic relationship with green algae called Zoochlorella .
The Saffron - faced Blue Dart , ( Pseudagrion rubriceps ) is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Salmo macrostigma is a species of freshwater trout endemic to Northwest Africa , to Algeria in particular .
Melanoides pupiformis is a species of freshwater snail , gastropod in the Thiaridae family .
Ranunculus peltatus ( Pond Water - crowfoot ) is a plant species in the genus Ranunculus , native to Europe , southwestern Asia and northern Africa .
Hemimyzon taitungensis ( common name : Taitung river loach , in Chinese 臺東間爬岩鰍 , 台東間吸鰍 , or 石貼仔 ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the family Balitoridae that is endemic to Taiwan .
Lueddemannia is a genus of orchids found from Venezuela to Peru .
Teiidae is a family of lizards native to the Americas .
Phaeoramularia indica is a species of sac fungus .
Baryonyx ( /ˌbæriˈɒnᵻks/ ) is a genus of theropod dinosaur which lived in the Barremian stage of the early Cretaceous Period , about 130 - -125 million years ago .
Acrocomia crispa ( Cuban belly palm , Corojo Palm ) , a palm species which is endemic to Cuba .
Meta nigra is a long - jawed orb weaver spider species found in Portugal .
The genus Brunnichia , also known as redvine or buckwheat vine , are perennial woody vines native to the United States .
Hyphaene is a genus of palms native to Africa , Madagascar , the Middle East , and the Indian Subcontinent .
Calospatha is an extremely rare , monotypic genus of flowering plant in the palm family found in peninsular Malaysia where it is referred to as rotan demuk .
Triphosa sabaudiata is a species of moth of the Geometridae family that can be found in Albania , Andorra , Austria , Bulgaria , France ( including the islands of Corsica ) , Germany , Greece , Italy , Liechtenstein , Romania , Spain , Switzerland , Ukraine , and in all states of the former Yugoslavia .
Hymenochirus curtipes , also known as Western Dwarf Clawed Frog , is a species of frog in the Pipidae family .
Cyathea decora is a species of tree fern native to Ecuador and possibly other parts of western South America .
Phasmahyla is a genus of tree frogs .
Leptotyphlops filiformis , or the Socotra Island blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
The Dyspnoi are a suborder of harvestmen , with about 32 genera , and about 320 described species .
Oeceoclades peyrotii is a species of terrestrial orchid in the genus Oeceoclades that is endemic to southwestern Madagascar .
Ischnodemus sabuleti , also known as the European Chinch Bug , is a species of swarming true bug from the family Blissidae , which family also includes the American Chinch Bug Blissus leucopterus .
Anogeissus latifolia is a species of small to medium - sized tree native to the India , Nepal , Myanmar , and Sri Lanka .
Iberolacerta is a genus of lizard in the Lacertidae family .
Labyrinthula is a genus of heterokont , comprising ten species .
Odostomia micra , common name the tiny pyramid - shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Hymenocaris is a genus of Cambrian crustaceans .
Centruroides gracilis is a species of scorpion in the family Buthidae , the bark scorpions .
Metarungia is a small Afrotropical genus in the acanthus family of dicotyledonous flowering plants .
Grevillea brevifolia , commonly known as Cobberas grevillea , is a species of the plant genus Grevillea .
Decapodiformes is a superorder of Cephalopoda , which includes all species with ten limbs ; the name derives from the Greek word meaning ten feet .
Pectis papposa is species of flowering plant in the aster family , Asteraceae .
Callosciurus is a genus of squirrels collectively referred to as the `` beautiful squirrels '' .
Micraspis lineola is a species of ladybird .
Parabuthus brevimanus is a species of scorpion from southern Africa , that ranges from southern Angola to Namibia and western South Africa , where its range extends south of the Orange River .
Phellodon niger , commonly known as the black tooth , is a species of tooth fungus in the family Bankeraceae , and the type species of the genus Phellodon .
Fasciolidae is a family of trematodes and includes several veterinary and medical important parasites .
Pseudotephritis approximata is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Pseudotephritis of the family Ulidiidae .
Asiavorator is an extinct genus of carnivorous , cat - like civet endemic to Asia in the Oligocene .
Graphosoma is a genus of the Pentatomidae family known as the striped shield bugs for their distinctive markings .
Ziziphus hutchinsonii is a species of tree in the Rhamnaceae family .
Scyllarides is a genus of slipper lobsters .
Rhynchophorus bilineatus , common name Black Palm Weevil , is a species of beetles belonging to the family Curculionidae .
Georissa laseroni is a species of minute cave snails that have an operculum , gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrocenidae . This species is endemic to Australia .
Cirripectes jenningsi is a species of combtooth blenny found in the Pacific ocean , from the Gilbert Islands to the Tuamoto Islands .
Erigeron lassenianus is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Mount Lassen fleabane .
Archegosauroidea is an extinct superfamily of Permian temnospondyls .
Hexanchus collinsonae ( named after M. E. Collinson ) is a species of prehistoric shark that was found in the Eocene London Clay beds .
Microseris laciniata is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name cutleaf silverpuffs .
Gillichthys is a genus of gobies native to the coasts of Baja California and southern California .
Lycosoidea is a clade or superfamily of araneomorph spiders .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Myriostoma coliforme .
Lobocneme is a genus consisting of 2 species of mantises in the subfamily Stagmatopterinae .
Periclimenes brevicarpalis , the Glass Anemone Shrimp , is a species of shrimp belonging to the family Palaemonidae .
Ostryopsis is a small genus of deciduous shrubs belonging to the birch family Betulaceae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Pseudotryblidium neesii .

Macronematinae is a subfamily level taxon consisting of net - spinning caddisflies whose larvae use webs to catch prey drifting in flowing waterways .
Melanochromis baliodigma is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from the area around Membe Point in areas where sandy bottoms meet up with rocky areas .
Helleborus lividus is a species of flowering plant in the family Ranunculaceae , native to Majorca and possibly nearby Cabrera , Spain .
Tridacna is a genus of large saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the subfamily Tridacninae , the giant clams .
Vaccinium crassifolium , the creeping blueberry , is a species of Vaccinium in the heath family .
Conus vittatus , common name the ribboned cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Thryssa is a genus of anchovies in the Engraulidae family .
Gagea liotardii is a Eurasian and North African species of plants in the lily family .
Stiphodon is a genus of freshwater gobies .
Didelphodon ( meaning `` two womb tooth '' ) is a genus of stagodont metatherians from the Late Cretaceous of North America .
Parathyestes roseolata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parathyestes .
Digitalis purpurea ( foxglove , common foxglove , purple foxglove or lady 's glove ) is a species of flowering plant in the genus Digitalis , in the family Plantaginaceae , native and widespread throughout most of temperate Europe .
Neofusicoccum mangiferae is an anamorphic species of fungus in Ascomycota .
The Samaridae are a family , the crested flounders , of small flatfishes native to the Indo - Pacific .
The subfamily Sminthopsinae includes several genera of small , carnivorous marsupials native to Australia : kultarrs , ningauis , dunnarts , and planigales .
Duvalius doriae , the Doria 's Cave Beetle , is a species of beetle belonging to the family Carabidae .
Boreohesperus is a genus of paradoxosomatid millipedes containing six species native to Western Australia .
Extriplex joaquinana is a species known by the common name San Joaquin saltbush .
Minixi is a small neotropical genus of potter wasps currently containing 4 species .
Uperodon is a small genus of microhylid frogs from South Asia .
Menegazzia neotropica is a species of lichen from the Neotropics .
Lamprologus ocellatus is a species of shell dwelling cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika .
Ningyuansaurus is a basal oviraptorosaurian dinosaur genus .
Brachyamblyopus brachysoma is a species of goby native to fresh and brackish waters of southern and southeastern Asia and possibly occurring in Africa and the Persian Gulf .
Homaledra is a genus of moth , belonging to the family Batrachedridae .
Maiaspondylus is an extinct genus of platypterygiine ophthalmosaurid ichthyosaur known from Northwest Territories of Canada .
Pleurodictyum is an extinct genus of tabulate coral characterized by polygonal corallites ( Pandolfi and Burke , 1989 ) .
It contains only one species , Cervaria xylinella , which is found in India .
Mylesinus is a genus of serrasalmids from South America , where found in the eastern Amazon , Essequibo and Orinoco basins .

Astatumen is a genus of tardigrade in the class Eutardigrada found in Romania .
Sepia plathyconchalis is a species of cuttlefish native to the western Indian Ocean , specifically the Saya - de - Malha Bank , Cargados - Carajos Shoals , and St Brandon Shoals .
Leuroglossus is a genus of deep - sea smelts found in the Pacific Ocean .
Ferdinandea cuprea is a European species of hoverfly notable for its brassy abdomen .
Amphitrias is a genus of moth in the family Depressariidae .
Depressizona is a genus of small to minute sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs or micromolluscs in the superfamily Scissurelloidea .
Haageocereus australis , commonly known as ' Quisco De La Costa De Aric ' , is a species of cactus endemic to southern Peru and northern Chile .
Hygrophorus olivaceoalbus , commonly known as the olive wax cap , is a species of fungus in the genus Hygrophorus .
Choanomphalus aorus is a species of freshwater air - breathing snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails , or planorbids .
Aethia is a genus of four small ( 85 - 300 g ) auklets endemic to the North Pacific Ocean , Bering Sea and Sea of Okhotsk and among some of North America 's most abundant seabirds .
Leptodactylus latinasus ( common name : oven frog , in Spanish urnero ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Polemon acanthias , or Reinhardt 's snake - eater , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Allisonia cockaynei is the only species of liverwort in the genus Allisonia and family Allisoniaceae .
Ophidioceras is an alternate name for the Tarphycerid genus Ophioceras , which is known from the Upper Silurian of Europe and North America .
Aurifilum is a monotypic genus of fungi within the family Cryphonectriaceae containing the sole species Aurifilum marmelostoma .
Chrysoblephus gibbiceps ( red stumpnose ) is a cold water , reef - dwelling species of sea bream , closely related to the red Roman .
Austromegabalanus psittacus , the giant barnacle or picoroco as it is known in Spanish , is a species of large barnacle native to the coasts of Chile and southern Peru .
The Small - spotted Bulbophyllum ( Bulbophyllum guttulatum ) is a species of orchid .
Persea schiedeana , the coyo , is a species of plant in the family Lauraceae .
Amantis malayana is a species of praying mantis native to Indonesia , on the islands of Bacan , Kaisa , and Sulawesi .
Gesomyrmex is a genus of ants in the subfamily Formicinae .
Polistodon is a genus of tritylodont therapsid from the Bajocian or Callovian ( Middle Jurassic ) of China .
Hermosita sangria is a brightly coloured species of sea slug , specifically an aeolid nudibranch .
Lonicera nitida is a species of perennial shrub , a member of the honeysuckle genus Lonicera .
Pterostemonaceae ( Engl . ) Small is a small family of shrubs native to tropical and subtropical Mexico .
Amara communis is a species of beetle of the genus Amara in the Carabidae family that can be found in Ireland , from Siberia to Kamchatka , and Caucasus .
Agave caymanensis is a species of agave that is endemic to Grand Cayman , Little Cayman and Cayman Brac in the Cayman Islands .
Platycepsion is an extinct genus of prehistoric amphibian from the Triassic period in Australia .
Papuascincus is a genus of skinks endemic to New Guinea .
Silene sargentii is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name Sargent 's catchfly .
Lysidice brevicalyx ( 短萼仪花 ) is a tree species in the genus Lysidice endemic to China .
Calamagrostis canadensis is a species of grass , having three or more varieties , in the Poaceae family .
Tetraphis pellucida , the pellucid four - tooth moss , is one of two species of moss in the acrocarpous genus Tetraphis .
Helinus is a genus of flowering plants in the buckthorn family , Rhamnaceae .
A majority of the modern sources treat it as a distinct species Cedrus atlantica , but some sources consider it a subspecies of Lebanon cedar ( C. libani subsp . atlantica ) .
Hemiselmis is a cryptophyte genus , including the species Hemiselmis andersenii .
Phorcus turbinatus , common name the turbinate monodont , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Elysia ornata , commonly known as ornate elysia or ornate leaf slug , is a species of sea slug , a marine gastropod mollusk .
Chorigyne is a genus of plants first described as a genus in 1881 .
Pseudoliotina discoidea , common name the discoid delphinula , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk , in the family Liotiidae .
Ceratocystis corymbiicola is a plant pathogen , affecting Australian Eucalyptus species .
Clinosperma macrocarpa is a species of palm tree known from a single population at around 500 metres ( 1,600 ft ) altitude on Mont Panié , New Caledonia .
Ciliopagurus liui is a species of hermit crab native to the Gulf of Tonkin and waters to the south of Japan .
Renealmia dolichocalyx is a species of plant in the Zingiberaceae family .
Solenopsis daguerrei is a species of parasitic ants native to Argentina and Uruguay .
Altica lythri is a species of flea beetles from the leaf beetle family , that is common in Asia , Europe , and North Africa , including Israel .
Impages cinerea , common name the grey Atlantic auger , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae , the auger snails .
The Rhacophoridae are a family of frog species , which occur in tropical sub - Saharan Africa , South India and Sri Lanka , Japan ; northeastern India to eastern China south through the Philippines and Greater Sundas , and Sulawesi .
Masdevallia striatella is a species of orchid that occurs from Costa Rica to western Panama .
Psorospermium haeckeli ( or Psorospermium haeckelii ) is a parasitic species .
Arctostaphylos gabilanensis is a rare species of manzanita known by the common name Gabilan manzanita .
The San Esteban chuckwalla ( Sauromalus varius ) , also known as the Piebald chuckwalla , Pinto chuckwalla or just chuck for short , is a species of chuckwalla belonging to the Iguanidae family endemic to San Esteban Island in the Gulf of California .
Pleurothallis oxapampae is a species of orchid from Peru first described by Hugo Gunckel Lüer in 1982 .
The Philippine tarsier ( Carlito syrichta ) , known locally as mawmag in Cebuano / Visayans and mamag in Luzon , is a species of tarsier endemic to the Philippines .
Burenoceras is a genus of small , even tiny , Gasconadian cyrtoconic ellesmeroceratids in which the phragmocone -the chambered portion- is shorter that the living chamber .
Zhanghenglong is an extinct genus of herbivorous hadrosauroid iguanodont dinosaur known from the Late Cretaceous ( middle Santonian stage ) Majiacun Formation in Xixia County of Henan Province , China .
Dombeya amaniensis is a flowering plant species found only in Tanzania .
Hoplocharax goethei is a species of characin endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Amazon Basin .
Penicillium ochrochloron is a species of the genus of Penicillium which produces penitrem A.
Etroplus is a small genus of cichlids native to southern India and Sri Lanka , where they are the only native cichlids .
Deinotheriidae ( `` terrible beasts '' ) is a family of prehistoric elephant - like proboscideans that lived during the Cenozoic era , first appearing in Africa , then spreading across southern Asia ( Indo - Pakistan ) and Europe .
Vicia orobus is a species of leguminous plant in the genus Vicia , known as wood bitter - vetch .
Paratilapia is a genus of cichlids generally restricted to Madagascar .
Okenia miramarae is a species of sea slug , specifically a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Goniodorididae .
Dercetoides ( meaning `` resemblant of the throat whale '' ) is a genus of prehistoric fish .
Tremella aurantia is a species of fungi in the family Tremellaceae .
Dyckia brevifolia ( sawblade ) is a species in the genus Dyckia .

Cratoxylum formosum or pink mempat is a species of flowering plant in the Hypericaceae family .
Furcifer verrucosus , also known as the warty chameleon , spiny chameleon or crocodile chameleon , is a species of small reptile endemic to Madagascar .
Apoica is a genus of eusocial paper wasps found throughout the Central and South American tropics .
Dresslerella is a genus of miniature orchids , with about 13 species native to South and Central America .

Heleobia robusta is a species of very small aquatic snail , an operculate gastropod mollusk in the family Truncatelloidea .
Sirex is a genus of wasps in the family Siricidae , the horntails or wood wasps .
Arachis villosulicarpa is a perennial peanut species , which is cultivated by indigenous people in Mato Grosso , a state of Brazil .
Karadzharoceras is a discosorid genus from the Devonian , named by Zhuravleva , 1972 , possibly a member of the Discosoridae .
Scincella melanosticta , also known as black ground skink or black - spotted smooth skink , is a species of skink in the genus of Scincella .
Acropora derawanensis is a species of acroporid coral that was first described by Carden Wallace in 1997 .
Any body of standing water is likely to contain rotifers and Keratella cochlearis is probably the commonest and most widespread species in the world .
Hemibungarus is a monotypic genus of venomous elapid snakes , one of several known commonly as Asian coral snakes or oriental coral snakes .
Somalinautilus is a genus of nautiloid that is found in the Middle to Upper Jurassic of England , France , and Somalialand .
