Serjania brevipes is a species of plant in the Sapindaceae ( soapberry ) family .
Ghatsa pillaii also known as the Silent Valley loach is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Ghatsa .
Aeschynanthus is a genus of about 150 species of evergreen subtropical plants in the family Gesneriaceae .
Pedobacter terricola is a species of Gram - negative , non - motile , pleomorphic bacteria .
Homotherium is an extinct genus of machairodontine saber - toothed cats , often termed scimitar - toothed cats , that ranged from North America , South America , Eurasia , and Africa during the Pliocene and Pleistocene epochs ( 5 mya--11,700 years ago ) , existing for approximately 5 million years .
Folifer brevifilis is a species of cyprinid fish found in China , Vietnam , Laos and Thailand in eastern Asia .
Crocodeilanthe elegans is an orchid species in the genus Crocodeilanthe found from Venezuela to Ecuador .
Trachusa perdita , the California leafcutting bee , is a species of bee in the Megachilidae family .
Graptolithina is a class of hemichordate animal , the members of which are known as graptolites .
Hylocereus megalanthus is a cactus species in the genus Hylocereus that is native to northern South America , where it is known , along with its fruit , by the name of Pitahaya .
Eurotamandua ( ' European tamandua ' ) is an extinct genus of mammal that lived some 49 million years ago , during the early Eocene .
Nicotiana clevelandii is a species of wild tobacco known by the common name Cleveland 's tobacco .
The Nitrosomonadales are a small order of Proteobacteria .
Cirsium drummondii , called Drummond 's thistle or dwarf or short - stemmed thistle , is a North American species of plants in the thistle tribe within the sunflower family .
Mesodesma is a genus of saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the family Mesodesmatidae .
Scopelopsis multipunctatus , the Multispotted Lanternfish , is a species of lanternfish .
Simplepipona is a malagasy genus of potter wasps presently synonymized under the genus Postepipona .
Sidalcea oregana is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common name Oregon checkerbloom .
Potentilla wheeleri is a species of cinquefoil known by the common name Kern cinquefoil or Wheeler 's cinquefoil .
Pavoclinus graminis , the Grass klipfish , is a species of clinid found along the coast of southern Africa from Inhambane , Mozambique to False Bay South Africa .
Synodontis orientalis is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Tanzania , where it occurs in the Ruvu and probably also the Rufiji river basins .
Margaretamys is a genus of rodent in the family Muridae endemic to the island of Sulawesi in Indonesia .
Lewisia congdonii , known by the common name Congdon 's lewisia , is a rare species of flowering plant in the purslane family .
Gymnopentzia is a genus of African plants in the chamomile tribe within the sunflower family .
Actinostephanus haeckeli is a species of sea anemone in the family Actinodendronidae .
Colletteichthys is a genus of toadfishes found in the western Indian Ocean .
Nama stenocarpum is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name mud fiddleleaf .
Blepharizonia laxa is a California species of tarweed known by the common name glandular big tarweed .
Amphimachairodus is an extinct genus of large machairodonts belonging to the clade known as Eumachairodontia ( true saberteeth ) along with relatives like Smilodon and Homotherium .
Brookesia betschi , commonly known as Blanc 's leaf chameleon or the Marojejy leaf chameleon , is a species of chameleon endemic to Madagascar .
Erysipelothrix is a genus of bacteria containing three species .
Vigna is a genus of flowering plants in the legume family , Fabaceae , with a pantropical distribution .
Carabus lineatus salmantitus is a subspecies beetle from Carabidae family , that can is endemic to Spain .
Condylago is a genus of tropical orchid in the Pleurothallidinae subtribe .
Plagiorchiidae is a family of parasitic trematodes ( flukes ) in the order Plagiorchiida .
Thalassoceratoidea , formerly Thalassocerataceae , is a superfamily of Late Paleozoic ammonites characterized by their thick - discoidal to subglobular , involute shells with narrow or closed umbilici and biconvex growth striae with ventral sinuses .
Latridopsis is a genus of trumpeters found in the southwestern Pacific Ocean and the southeastern Indian Ocean .
Dibrachichthys melanurus is a species of four - armed frogfish found in the eastern Indian Ocean and western Pacific Ocean near to Indonesia and Australia where they are found over soft bottoms at depths of 6 to 146 metres ( 20 to 479 ft ) .
Ampelocissus asekii is a species of vine , in the family Vitaceae , from Morobe Province of Papua New Guinea .
Pandalus montagui is a species of cold - water shrimp in the family Pandalidae .
Danthonia decumbens ( formerly Sieglingia decumbens ) is a species of grass commonly known as the heath grass , heath - grass , or staggers grass It is a tussock grass native to Europe and adjacent parts of Asia and North Africa .
Brachistosternus ehrenbergii is a scorpion species and the most cited species in the genus Brachistosternus .
Laetacara curviceps , the Flag acara , is a species of cichlid that lives in slow - moving rivers and streams as well as ponds and lakes of the Amazon Basin and the lower Negro River Basin .
Hulsea californica is a rare species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names San Diego alpinegold and San Diego sunflower .
Stratiomys potamida , the banded general , is a European species of soldier fly .
Cynosurus echinatus is a species of grass known by the common names bristly dogstail grass , rough dog's - tail and hedgehog dogtail .
Fragaria chiloensis , the beach strawberry , Chilean strawberry , or coastal strawberry , is one of two species of strawberry that were hybridized to create the modern garden strawberry ( F. × ananassa ) .
Therioides ( `` beast - like one '' ) is an extinct genus of middle sized carnivorous therocephalian from the Tapinocephalus Assemblage Zone of South Africa .
Carabus rothi is a species of beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in Hungary , Romania , and Ukraine .
Oxyepoecus daguerrei is a species of ant in the genus Oxyepoecus .
Trithemis stictica , the Jaunty Dropwing , is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Eulima lapazana is a species of small , ectoparasitic sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Eulimidae .
Pygopus is a genus belonging to the family of Australian legless lizards .
Supersaurus ( meaning `` super lizard '' ) is a genus of diplodocid sauropod dinosaur first discovered by Vivian Jones of Delta , Colorado , in late Jurassic period rocks of the middle Morrison Formation of Colorado in 1972 , and later in Portugal under the name S. lourinhanensis .
Ficus pellucida , common name the Atlantic fig shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ficidae , the fig shells .
Aspidimorpha deusta is a species of beetles belonging to the Chrysomelidae family .
Zanonia is a monotypic genus in the flowering plant family Cucurbitaceae ( the cucumber , squash , and pumpkin family ) .
Homozeugos conciliatum is a species of grass endemic to Angola .
Combretum glutinosum is a shrub species of the genus Combretum , found in the Sahel belt in parts of Senegal , Burkina Faso , Ghana , Mali , the Gambia , Niger , Nigeria and Cameroon , across to parts of Sudan .
Carychium minimum is a species of very small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Ellobiidae .
Silene marmorensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common names Marble Mountain catchfly , Marble Mountain campion , and Somes Bar campion .
Lethrinops leptodon is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it prefers areas with sandy substrates .
Auchenipterichthys punctatus is a species of driftwood catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the upper Amazon River basin .
There is only one known species , Eupatorina sophiifolia , endemic to the Island of Hispaniola in the West Indies ( Dominican Republic and Republic of Haiti ) .
Speyeria adiaste , the unsilvered fritillary or adiaste fritillary , is a species of butterfly of the Nymphalidae family .
Anguillavus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the upper Cenomanian of Lebanon and the United States .
Arctostaphylos andersonii , the Santa Cruz manzanita , is a species of Arctostaphylos , limited in geography to the Santa Cruz Mountains of California .
Euphorbia amygdaloides ( wood spurge ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Euphorbiaceae , native to woodland locations in Europe , Turkey and the Caucasus .
Piora is a genus of Papuasian plants in the aster tribe within the daisy family .
Galium parisiense is a species of flowering plant in the family Rubiaceae known by the common name wall bedstraw .
Lupinus arboreus , yellow bush lupine ( USA ) or tree lupin ( UK ) , is a species of flowering plant in the legume family Fabaceae .
Reduvius is a large genus of reduviids or assassin bugs .
Taraxacum albidum is a species of dandelion that grows in eastern Eurasia .
Amorphoscelis machadoi is a species of praying mantis found in Angola .
Haplochromis oregosoma is a species of cichlid endemic to Uganda where it occurs in Lake George ( Uganda ) and the Kazinga Channel .
Erigeron eriocalyx is a Eurasian species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Laetesia oceaniae is a species of sheet weaver found in the New Hebrides .
Conus thalassiarchus , common name the bough cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
The Globigerinacea is a superfamily of free - living , calcareous , planktonic foraminiferal protists that have lived in the open ocean since the Eocene .
Leptostylus pygialis is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae , or longhorn beetle , family .
Polydiscia deuterosminthurus is a species of mite recently discovered in the autonomous community of Navarre in Spain .
Herbstosaurus is the name given to a genus of pterosaur that lived during the Jurassic period , in what is now Argentina .
The Limnophorini are a tribe of flies , belonging to the family Muscidae .
Priapulidae is the canonical family of priapulid worm , comprising Priapulus and Priapulosis as well as the Carboniferous genus Priapulites .
Rubus verae - crucis is a Mexican species of brambles in the rose family .
The yellowbelly worm - eating snake ( Trachischium tenuiceps ) is a species of colubrid snake .
Leptotyphlops tesselatus , or Tschudi 's blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Colaspidea grossa is a species of beetle in the Chrysomelidae family , that can be found in North Africa particularly in Morocco and Southern Spain .
Canthocamptus longipes is a species of crustacean in the family Canthocamptidae .
Daphnia galeata is a small species of planktonic crustacean .
Thymus pulegioides ( common names broad - leaved thyme , lemon thyme ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Lamiaceae , native to Europe .
Fulguropsis feldmanni is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Busyconidae , the crown conches and their allies .
Caldicellulosiruptor is a genus of thermophilic , anaerobic , Gram - positive , non - spore forming bacteria .
Sybrodoius tippmanni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Sybrodoius .
Pantoporia is a genus of Asian butterflies sometimes called the lascars .
Oreta extensa is a species of moth of the Drepanidae family .
Poekilopleuron ( meaning `` varied ribs '' ) is an extinct genus of megalosauroid tetanuran theropod dinosaur , which lived during the middle Bathonian of the Jurassic , about 168 to 165 million years ago .
Arielulus is a genus of vesper bats with the following species , sometimes in Pipistrellus :
Yersinia ruckeri is a species of Gram - negative bacteria , known for causing enteric redmouth disease in some species of fish .
Indomyrma dasypyx is a species of ant that belongs to the Indomyrma genus .
Psellogrammus kennedyi is a species of characin that occurs in Argentina , Brazil , and Paraguay .
Udara is a genus of butterflies in the family Lycaenidae . The members ( species ) are found in the Indomalaya ecozone and the Australasian ecozone .
Pseudanhammus keili is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudanhammus .
Heloxycanus patricki is a species of moth of the family Hepialidae , the only member of the genus Heloxycanus .
Dryopteris wallichiana ( alpine wood fern ) is a robust species of deciduous or semi - evergreen fern in the family Dryopteridaceae , native to the Himalayas , Hawaii , Mexico and Jamaica .
Saccharum officinarum , sugarcane , is a large , strong - growing species of grass in the genus Saccharum .
Dolichamphilius is a genus of loach catfishes endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Hylarana luzonensis ( sometimes known as the Luzon frog ) is a species of true frog in the genus Hylarana .
The Salvin 's albatross , white - capped albatross , shy albatross and Chatham albatross were all considered the same species until a 1998 article by Robertson and Nunn .
The parrot subfamily Loriinae consists of three tribes , the lories and lorikeets ( Loriini ) , the budgerigar ( Melopsittacini ) and the fig parrots ( Cyclopsittini ) .
The Streptomycetaceae are a family of Actinobacteria , making up to the monotypic suborder Streptomycineae .
Falsozorispiella albosignata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Falsozorispiella .
The white abalone , scientific name Haliotis sorenseni , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Neolamprologus caudopunctatus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where is occurs along the Zambian shores .
Leaf warblers are small insectivorous birds belonging mainly to the genus Phylloscopus .
Maprounea is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae first named as a genus in 1775 .
Calochortus leichtlinii is a species of flowering plant in the lily family known by the common names Leichtlin 's mariposa , smokey mariposa , and mariposa lily .
Archips semiferanus ( also known as Archips semiferana ) is a species of moth in the family Tortricidae , and one of several species of moth commonly known as Oak leafroller or Oak leaf roller .
Mimononyma flavovariegata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimononyma .
Tubifex tubifex , also called the sludge worm , or sewage worm , is a species of tubificid segmented worm that inhabits the sediments of lakes and rivers on several continents .
Cyathea crassa is a species of tree fern endemic to the Santo Domingo area in the Dominican Republic .
Idionyx is a genus of dragonflies in the family Corduliidae .
Many species of Dicynodon have been named , and the genus is considered a wastebasket taxon .
Ponthieva petiolata is a species of orchid native to Cuba and the Lesser Antilles .
Cyclanthus bipartitus a species of plants in the family Cyclanthaceae , first described as a genus in 1824 .
Liparus dirus is a species of weevils belonging to the family Curculionidae , subfamily Molytinae .
Malacothamnus densiflorus , often known by the common names yellowstem bushmallow and yellow stem bush mallow , is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family .
Zicrona caerulea , common name Blue Shieldbug , is a species of bugs belonging to the Pentatomidae family .
Mimectatina meridiana is a species of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae , and the only species in the genus Mimectatina .
Vicia sepium or bush vetch is a plant species of the genus Vicia .
Chamaecyparis eureka is an extinct species of conifer in the family Cupressaceae .
Labrus is a genus of wrasses native to the eastern Atlantic Ocean into the Mediterranean and Black seas .
The White M Hairstreak , Parrhasius m - album , is a species of butterfly of the Lycaenidae family .
Bothropoma pilula is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Colloniidae .
Cordyline pumilio is the smallest of New Zealand 's five native species of Cordyline .
Pulchrenicodes univittatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pulchrenicodes .
Arnica louiseana is a Canadian species of arnica in the sunflower family , known by the common name Lake Louise arnica or snow arnica .
Pupoidopsis hawaiensis is a species of very small or minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Pupillidae .
Pleurodema is a genus of leptodactylid frogs from South America .
Pseudocaryopteris is a genus of plants first described in 1999 .
Diploastrea heliopora , known commonly as the Diploastrea brain coral or Honeycomb coral among other vernacular names , is a species of hard coral in the family Diploastreidae .
Juniperus przewalskii ( Przewalski 's juniper ) is a species of juniper native to the mountains of western China in Gansu , Qinghai , and northernmost Sichuan , growing at altitudes of 1,000 - 3,300 m. It is an evergreen tree reaching 15 - 20 m tall .
Viviparus georgianus , common name the banded mystery snail , is a species of large freshwater snail with gills and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Viviparidae , the river snails .
Pinus echinata , the shortleaf pine , is a species of pine native to the eastern United States from southern New Jersey , south to northern Florida , west to eastern Oklahoma , and southwest to eastern Texas .
Paracottus knerii , the stone sculpin , is a species of cottoid fish endemic to Russia , where it is found in Lake Baikal and surrounding tributaries as well as the Gramninskie Lakes , Lake Verkhnaya Agata and the Enisei River and various lakes in Tuva .
Anomalomyrma is an Asian genus of ants in the subfamily Leptanillinae .
Aphelops is an extinct genus of rhinoceros endemic to North America during the Miocene through the Pliocene , living from 20.43 - -5.330 mya , existing for approximately 15.1 million years .
Incilius coccifer ( common name : southern round - gland toad or southern roundgland toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Clathrina decipiens is a species of calcareous sponge in the genus Clathrina from the Adriatic sea .
Trichopsomyia is a genus of Hoverflies , from the family Syrphidae ( flower flies ) , in the order Diptera .
Torellella is a genus of problematic tubicolous fossils .
Vaucheria litorea is a species of yellow - green alga ( Xanthophyceae ) .
Chytridiomycetes ( /kᵻˌtrɪdioʊmaɪˈsiːtiːz , -ˈsiːts/ ) is a class of fungi .
Ampelita julii is a species of tropical air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Acavidae .
Pleistodontes addicotti is a species of fig wasp which is native to Australia .
Iurubanga arixi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Iurubanga .
Emeryrhynchium is a monotypical afrotropical genus of potter wasps known from Ecuatorial Africa ( Democratic Republic of Congo , Equatorial Guinea and Sierra Leone ) .
Nodobryoria is a genus of medium to large , reddish - brown lichens that are hair - like to shrubby in shape and grow on conifer trees .
Oedipina taylori ( common name : Taylor 's worm salamander ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Yarravia is a genus of extinct vascular plants mainly known from fossils found in Victoria , Australia .
Echeveria pulidonis is a species of flowering plant in the Crassulaceae family , native to Mexico .
Stanhopea hernandezii is a species of orchid endemic to central and southwestern Mexico .
Rhizomnium punctatum , also called dotted thyme - moss , is a small species in the genus Rhizomnium .
Subanguina wevelli ( Seed - gall nematode ; syn . Afrina wevelli Van den Berg , 1985 ) is a plant pathogenic nematode and an invasive species .
Rhododendron duclouxii is a rhododendron species .
Fargesia murielae , the umbrella bamboo , is a species of flowering plant in the family Poaceae .
Turbo bruneus , common name the brown ( Pacific ) dwarf turban or the little burnt turbo , is a species of sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae .
Hadrurus arizonensis , the giant desert hairy scorpion , giant hairy scorpion , or Arizona Desert hairy scorpion , is the largest scorpion in North America , and one of the 8 - -9 species of Hadrurus in the United States , attaining a length of 14 cm ( 5.5 in ) .
Phytolacca icosandra , sometimes known as button pokeweed or tropical pokeweed , is a species of flowering plant found in the neotropics and introduced into the warmer areas of the western USA .
Orites is a genus of 9 known species , 7 endemic to Australia ( 4 of which occur in Tasmania ) and 2 in South America ; 1 in the Chilean Andes and 1 in Bolivia .
Eunicella singularis , the white gorgonian , is a species of colonial soft coral , a sea fan in the family Gorgoniidae .
Calliurichthys is a genus of dragonets native to the western Pacific Ocean .
Aspasmichthys ciconiae is a species of clingfish found along Pacific coasts from Japan through Taiwan .
It consists of only one species , Sundadoxa multidentata , which is found in Brunei , Indonesia ( Sumatra ) and Malaysia ( Peninsular , Sarawak ) .
Aglyptodactylus is a genus of frogs in the family Mantellidae .
Ribes cynosbati is a North American species of shrubs in the currant family .
Allium trifurcatum is a plant species native to the Sichuan and Yunnan regions in southern China .
Typha varsobica is a plant species native to Republic of Tajikistan .
Quercus oglethorpensis ( also called Oglethorpe oak ) is a species of plant in the beech family .
Plotopteridae is the name of an extinct family of flightless seabirds from the order Suliformes .
Emeopedus solutus is a species of longhorn beetle in the Lamiinae .
Schefflera gleasonii , the yuquilla , is a species of plant in the Araliaceae family .
Deuteragenia ossarium , the Bone - house Wasp , is a species of pompilid wasp discovered in south - east China in 2014 .
Callionymus beniteguri , the White - spotted dragonet , is a species of dragonet native to the water around Japan and the East China Sea .
Quercus gravesii ( also called Chisos red oak or Grave 's oak ) is an uncommon North American species of trees in the beech family .
Rhynchodoras castilloi is a species of thorny catfish endemic to Venezuela where it is found in the middle to lower Apure River .
The Limenitidinae ares a subfamily of butterflies that includes the admirals and relatives .
Sitticus distinguendus , sometimes called the distinguished jumper spider , is species of spider in the Salticidae family .
Atrypanius remissus is a species of longhorn beetle of the subfamily Lamiinae .
Cyprinus pellegrini is one of 22 extant species of ray - finned fish in the genus Cyprinus .
The Uzungwa red colobus ( Procolobus gordonorum ) , also known as the Udzungwa red colobus or Iringa red colobus , is a species of primate in the family Cercopithecidae .
Collemataria is an extinct genus of brachiopod from the Permian .
The parrot subfamily Platycercinae consists of two tribes , the ground parrots and allies ( Pezoporini ) and the many species of broad - tailed parrot ( Platycercini ) .
Ophisaurus ventralis , the eastern glass lizard , is a legless lizard species found in the Southeastern United States .
Grimpoteuthis is a genus of pelagic umbrella octopus that live in the deep sea .
Triplophysa wuweiensis is a species of stone loach endemic to Gansu , China .
Cyclops varius is a species of copepod from the Cyclopidae family .
Panulirus versicolor is a species of spiny lobster that lives in tropical reefs .
Lecanodiaspididae is a family of scale insects commonly known as false pit scales or lecanodiaspidids .
Ephedra sinica ( also known as Chinese ephedra or Ma Huang ) is a plant species native to Mongolia , Russia ( Buryatiya , Chita , Primorye ) , and northeastern China ( Gansu , Hebei , Heilongjiang , Jilin , Liaoning , Nei Mongol , Ningxia , Shaanxi , Shanxi ) .
The flying gurnards are a family , Dactylopteridae , of marine fish notable for their greatly enlarged pectoral fins .
Inocybe cookei , commonly known as the straw fibrecap , is a species of mushroom in the Inocybaceae family .
Bromelia palmeri is a plant species in the genus Bromelia .
Angraecum penzigianum is a species of comet orchid that is endemic to Madagascar , and is recorded from Antsiranana , Fianarantsoa and Toamasina provinces , from elevations of 1,000 - -2,000 m. It is an epiphytic perennial which grows in mossy forests .
Bolivaroscelis werneri is a species of praying mantis in the genus Bolivaroscelis in the order Mantodea .
Hypacanthium is a genus of Asian flowering plants in the thistle tribe within the sunflower family .
Nannostomus espei , commonly known as Espe 's pencilfish or barred pencilfish , is a freshwater species of fish belonging to the Lebiasinidae family of characins .
Ustilago is a genus of approximately 200 smut fungi parasitic on grasses .
Charonia lampas rubicunda , common name the knobbed triton , is a subspecies of very large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Ranellidae , the tritons .
Bombus rupestris is a species of cuckoo bumblebee present in most of Europe except Iceland and the Balkans .
Nebria grumi is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Kyrgyzstan .
Platyarthrus hoffmannseggii is a species of woodlouse which is closely associated with ants ' nests , particularly those of Lasius flavus , Lasius niger and species of Myrmica , where it feeds on ant droppings or mildew .
Pireneitega segestriformis is an araneomorph spider species found in Europe and Russia .
Mesogobius nonultimus , or the Caspian toad goby , is one of the species of gobiid fish endemic to the brackish - waters Caspian Sea ( lake ) .
Temnocinclis is a monotypic genus of sea snails in family Sutilizonidae containing the single species Temnocinclis euripes .
Palaeoloxodon chaniensis is an extinct species of straight - tusked pygmy elephant .
Alexfloydia is an Australian genus of perennial stoloniferous plants panic grass subfamily of the grass family .
Siphonia ( `` Siphon '' ) is a genus of extinct hallirhoid demosponges of the Upper Cretaceous , from about 125 to 66 million years ago .
Sumalia is a genus of butterflies found in Southeast Asia ranging from the Indian Himalayan Region to the Sunda Islands
Diplecogaster is a genus of clingfishes .
Sporormia is a genus of fungi in the family Sporormiaceae .
Polymyxa graminis is a species of plasmodiophorid protist .
Borrelia duttoni is a species of Borrelia .
Rapanea perakensis is a species of broadleaf evergreen plant in the family Primulaceae .
Garypinidae is a family of pseudoscorpions , containing the following genera :
Viverra is a mammalian genus that was first nominated and described by Carl Linnaeus in 1758 as comprising several species including the large Indian civet .
Ceratotherium neumayri is a fossil species of rhinoceros from the eastern Mediterranean , in the Anatolia region in modern Turkey , dating to the late Miocene and is the likely ancestor of both the White Rhinoceros and Black Rhinoceros lineages of Africa .
Sinotubulites is a genus of small , tube - shaped shelly fossils from the Ediacaran period .
Orthoceras ( `` straight horn '' ) is a genus of extinct nautiloid cephalopod .
Artedius fenestralis or the Padded sculpin is a species of sculpin in the family Cottidae .
The genus contains only the species Sapeornis chaoyangensis which is known from fossils found in Jiufotang Formation and Yixian Formation rocks in the People 's Republic of China .
Katibasia insidiosa is a species of loach endemic to Sarawak , Malaysia .
Penstemon spectabilis is a species of penstemon known by the common name showy penstemon .
Jacaratia is a genus of five species of plants formerly included with the papaya in Carica .
Claytonia parviflora is a species of wildflower in the purslane family known by the common name streambank springbeauty .
Volvarina insulana is a species of small to very small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Marginellidae , the margin shells .
Sphodromantis congica , common name Congo mantis is a species of praying mantis found in Angola , Nigeria , and the Congo River region .
Laocypris hispida is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Laos .
Madagascarophis is a genus of small , mildly venomous colubrid snakes native to the island of Madagascar .
Suillus acidus is an edible species of mushroom in the genus Suillus .
Diplospinus multistriatus , the Striped escolar , is a species of snake mackerel of cosmopolitan distribution at depths of from 50 to 1,000 metres ( 160 to 3,280 ft ) .
Juracimbrophlebia is an extinct genus of hangingflies that lived during the Middle Jurassic Period about 165 million years ago .
Marsdenichthys is an extinct genus of Devonian tetrapodomorph .
Psilorhynchus sucatio is a species of Psilorhynchus .
Carassius auratus buergeri ( Japanese : naga - buna , ナガブナ ) is a subspecies of ray - finned fish in the genus Carassius .
Achyranthes bidentata Blume ( English common name : ox knee , Chinese : niu xi ) is a species of flowering plant in the amaranth family , Amaranthaceae .
Calthalotia comtessi , common name the spotted strawberry top shell or the comtesse 's top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Cylindrothorax balteatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cylindrothorax .
The Corsican wildcat ( Felis silvestris reyi ) is a subspecies of the wildcat found on the island of Corsica .
Conus erythraeensis , common name the Red Sea cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Systomus orphoides , the Javaen barb , is a species of cyprinid fish native to Southeast Asia .
Baoris pagana is a species of skipper butterfly found in Asia .
Nosea hainanensis is only species in the butterfly genus Nosea of the Nymphalidae family found in Asia .
Philautus kempii ( not to be confused with Philautus kempiae ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Simochromis babaulti is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika preferring areas with rock - rubble substrates .
Trissexodon constrictus is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Trissexodontidae .
Haploesthes greggii , false broomweed , is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Myriangiales is an order of sac fungi , consisting of mostly plant pathogens .
Aspidichthys ( `` Shield fish '' ) is a genus of large , distinctively tuberculated arthrodire placoderm of uncertain affinities from Upper Devonian marine strata in the Eastern United States and Europe .
Metrioxenini ( metrioxenines ) are a tribe of belids , primitive weevils of the family Belidae , containing about 30 species .
Uracentron is a genus of Tropidurid lizards found in forests in northern South America .
Lecanicillium longisporum is the approved name of an entomopathogenic fungus species , that was previously widely known as Verticillium lecanii ( Zimmerman ) Viegas , but is now understood to be an anamorphic form in the Cordyceps group of genera in the Cordycipitaceae .
Tegula fasciata ( known commonly as the Smooth Atlantic Tegula ) is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tegulidae .
Chtonobdella limbata is a species of blood sucking leech , found in New South Wales , Australia .
Anthonotha is a genus within the subfamily of Caesalpinioideae of the plant family Fabaceae / Leguminosae .
Conasprella eugrammata , common name the eugrammatus cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Runcinidae is a family of medium - sized sea slugs , marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks .
Justicia japonica is a flowering plant species in the genus Justicia .
Xyris panacea , St. Marks yelloweyed grass , is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the yellow - eyed - grass family .
Podolepis is a genus of the pussy's - toes tribe within the daisy family .
Crustaceans ( Crustacea /krʌˈsteɪʃə/ ) form a very large group of arthropods , usually treated as a subphylum , which includes such familiar animals as crabs , lobsters , crayfish , shrimp , krill and barnacles .
Doratomyces ( Dor - ah - toe - mice''-ees ) is a genus of the fungi imperfecti , closely related to Scopulariopsis .
Sinaeschnidia ( meaning `` Chinese Aeschnidium '' ) is a genus of prehistoric dragonfly .
Nesticus is a scaffold web spiders genus in the family Nesticidae found in America and Eurasia .
Penion cuvieranus jeakingsi is a subspecies of very large predatory sea snail , a true whelk , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Calochortus uniflorus is a species of flowering plant in the lily family known by the common names Monterey mariposa lily and large - flowered star - tulip .
Hypsoblennius gilberti , the Rockpool blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the eastern Pacific ocean .
Atopobium vaginae is a species of bacteria in the genus of Actinobacteria , in the family Coriobacteriaceae .
Hemicidaris is an extinct genus of echinoid that lived from the Middle Jurassic to the Early Cretaceous .
Fork - marked lemurs or fork - crowned lemurs are strepsirrhine primates ; the four species comprise the genus Phaner .
The former subfamily Planigalinae contained the planigales and the ningauis : very small marsupial carnivores native to Australia which are , like the quolls , antechinuses , dibblers , Tasmanian devil , and many others , part of the biological order Dasyuromorphia : the carnivorous marsupials .
Angraecum pungens is a species of comet orchid that can be found in Cameroon , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Equatorial Guinea , Gabon and Nigeria .
Burkholderia multivorans is a species in Phylum proteobacteria .
Lycium cooperi is a species of flowering plant in the nightshade family known by the common name peach thorn .
Parvoscincus is a genus of skinks endemic to the Philippines .
Clematis recta , the Erect Clematis or Ground virginsbower , is a species of Clematis unusual in that it is a free - standing shrub rather than a climbing plant .
Sepia thurstoni is a species of cuttlefish native to the Indian Ocean , specifically the waters off Chennai in India and off Negombo and Hambantota in Sri Lanka .
Laiphognathus is a genus of combtooth blennies found in the western Pacific and Indian Oceans .
Pyrrhulina rachoviana is a small species of tropical fish from the family Lebiasinidae named in honor of the German aquarist Arthur Rachow .
Exaeretodon is a genus of traversodontid cynodont ; several species are known , from various formations .
Inonotus dryadeus , commonly known as oak bracket , warted oak polypore , weeping polypore or weeping conk , is an inedible species of fungus belonging to the genus Inonotus , which consists of bracket fungi with fibrous flesh .
Gecarcoidea lalandii is a large species of terrestrial crab .
Hamlyn 's monkey ( Cercopithecus hamlyni ) , also known as the owl - faced monkey , is a species of Old World monkey that inhabits the bamboo and primary rainforests of the Congo .
Afrotheria as a clade has usually been discussed without a Linnaean rank , but has been assigned the rank of cohort , magnorder , and superorder .
Sepiella is a genus of cuttlefish encompassing around seven species .
The Metastrongylidae are a family of nematodes .
The Korean hare ( Lepus coreanus ) is a species of hare found in the Korean Peninsula and adjoining parts of northeastern China .
Sclerocarpus is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower tribe within the daisy family .
Anapistula is a genus of araneomorph spider .
Allium fasciculatum is a species of onions known from the Himalayas of Bhutan , Sikkim , Nepal , and the Chinese provinces of Qinghai , Sichuan and Tibet .
Cecidipta major is a species of snout moth in the genus Cecidipta .
Apsopelix is an extinct genus of bony fish that existed about 95 - 80 million years ago in the shallow waters of the Western Interior Seaway , Hudson Seaway , and Japan .
The Gabon bushbaby ( Sciurocheirus gabonensis ) is a species of primate in the family Galagidae found in Cameroon , Gabon , and the Congo Republic .
Bollmannia is a genus of gobies native to the Atlantic and Pacific coasts of the Americas .
Eristalinus seychellarum is a species of hoverfly found in the Seychelles .
Danfoss ' mouse lemur ( Microcebus danfossi ) , or the Ambarijeby mouse lemur , is a species of mouse lemur endemic to Madagascar .
Oncidium sphacelatum is a species of orchid ranging from Mexico to Central America , southeastern Venezuela .
Belonesox belizanus , the pike topminnow , is a species of poeciliid found from Mexico to Costa Rica .
Fluviopupa gracilis is a species of very small freshwater snails that have an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Tateidae .
Sabatia campestris ( Texas star ; also prairie rose - gentian , prairie sabatia , meadow pink ) is a species of Sabatia , native to the south - central United States , from Texas east to Mississippi and north to Iowa and Illinois .
Synodontis ornatissimus is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it is found in the Ubangi River drainage .
Ancylosis velessa is a species of snout moth in the genus Ancylosis .
Rubus macraei , commonly known as ʻĀkalakala , is a species of Rubus that is endemic to Hawaii .
Atriplex phyllostegia is a species of saltbush known by the common names arrowscale , leafcover saltweed , and Truckee orach .
Graphistylis is a genus of Brazilian flowering plants in the daisy family .
Gobitrichinotus arnoulti is a species of sand darter endemic to Madagascar where it occurs in fresh waters .
Plectostoma laidlawi is a species of air - breathing land snail with an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Diplommatinidae .
Biziura is a genus of stiff - tailed ducks endemic to Australasia and containing one living and one fossil species .
Sepia incerta is a species of cuttlefish native to the southwestern Indian Ocean , specifically south and east Africa , from Port Elizabeth to Mozambique ( north to 18ºS ) .
Artedidraco is a genus of barbeled plunderfishes native to the Southern Ocean .
Adenanthos ileticos is a species of shrub in the family Proteaceae .
Arctotraversodon is a genus of traversodontid cynodont from the Late Triassic of Canada .
Histopona egonpretneri is a funnel - web spider species found in Croatia .
Lachnospermum , common name Rooiblombos , is a genus of South African flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Otophryne is a small genus of microhylid frogs from northern South America .
Tristramella intermedia is an extinct species of fish in the Cichlidae family .
Commelineae is a tribe of monocotyledonous flowering plants in the dayflower family ( Commelinaceae ) .
Nebria changbaiensis is a species of metallic green coloured ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Jilin province of China .
Calathus gomerensis is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that is endemic to Canary Islands .
Ideopsis is a genus of nymphalid butterflies in the subfamily Danainae found in South - east Asia .
Aeshna rileyi , the Riley 's hawker , is a species of dragonfly in the family Aeshnidae .
Anchusa arvensis is a plant species of the genus Anchusa .
Emblemaria hudsoni is a species of chaenopsid blenny found around Peru , in the southeast Pacific ocean .
Sphodromantis aethiopica , common name Ethiopian mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in Ethiopia .
Crenicichla johanna is a species of cichlid native to South America .
Lamprologus is a genus of fishes from the cichlid family .
Salarias sibogai is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western central Pacific ocean .
Anolbanolis is an extinct genus of iguanian lizards that lived in the Bighorn Basin of what is now Wyoming during the earliest Eocene .
Ancistrocladus letestui is a species of liana of the plant family of the Ancistrocladaceae occurring in the subtropical or tropical dry forests of Cameroon , Congo - Brazzaville , Zaire , and Gabon .
Buddleja longiflora is a rare species endemic to one small area of Brazil , growing in fields high on the Serra do Caparaó at an altitude of 2400 m. The species was first described and named by Brade in 1957 .
Olivancillaria orbignyi , common name Ureta 's olive , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olividae , the olives .
Atelerix is a genus of mammal in the family Erinaceidae .
Acrolophidae ( Burrowing webworm moths ) is a family of moths in the Lepidoptera order .
Stelgidopteryx ( Baird , 1858 ) is a small genus of swallows .
Rhadinocentrus ornatus , commonly known as the ornate rainbowfish , is a species of rainbowfish endemic to eastern Australia .
Gaylussacia ursina , the bear huckleberry , is a plant species native to the coastal plains of the southeastern United States , in the southern Appalachians of ( Georgia , Tennessee , and the Carolinas ) .
Tropidia polystachya , the young palm orchid , is a species of orchid native to Mexico , Central America , Greater Antilles , Bahamas , Cayman Islands , Florida , Colombia , Venezuela , and Ecuador ( including Galápagos ) .
Tesakoviaspis concentrica is an extinct species of primitive jawless fish from the Middle Ordovician .
Baeolidia moebii is a species of sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Aeolidiidae .
Oxytropis lambertii is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by several common names , including purple locoweed , woolly locoweed , and Lambert crazyweed .
Plegma caelatura is a species of minute , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Euconulidae .
Rhododendron ponticum , called common rhododendron or pontic rhododendron , is a species of Rhododendron native to southern Europe and southwest Asia .
Lesueurina platycephala , the Flathead pygmy - stargazer , is a species of southern sandfish endemic to the coastal waters of southern Australia .
Helicopelta rostricola is a species of deep water sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Addisoniidae , the true limpets .
Brissopsis jarlii is a species of sea urchins of the Family Brissidae .
Clavaria amoena , sometimes called the Yellow Coral Fungus is a species of coral fungus in the family Clavariaceae .
Oligonicella scudderi , common name Scudder 's mantis or slender prairie mantid , is a species of praying mantis native to the Southern United States .
Asplenium ruta - muraria is a species of fern commonly known as wall - rue .
Pseudotothyris janeirensis is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil , where it is found in Rio de Janeiro .
Cyphocleonus is a genus of true weevil .
Clematis occidentalis is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family known by the common name western blue virginsbower .
The Yucatan small - eared shrew ( Cryptotis mayensis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Caliris elegans is a mantis species in the genus Caliris found in Malaysia , Sumatra and Borneo .
Joycea is a genus of 3 grass species , endemic to Australia .
Grindelia scabra , the rough gumweed , is a rare North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Chironeura chrysocyma is a moth in the Xyloryctidae family , and the only species in the genus Chironeura .
Profilicollis is a genus of acanthocephalan parasites of crustaceans .
Calla ( Bog Arum , Marsh Calla , Wild Calla , and Water - arum ) is a genus of flowering plant in the family Araceae , containing the single species Calla palustris .
The family and CDC Filoviridae ( members are called Filovirus ) is the taxonomic home of several related viruses that form filamentous infectious viral particles ( virions ) , and encode their genome in the form of single - stranded negative - sense RNA .
Recurvidris browni is a species of ant of the subfamily Myrmicinae , which can be found from Indonesia ( Kalimantan ) , Malaysia ( Sarawak and W. Malaysia ) and Thailand .
Pogonomyrmex rugosus , or rough harvester ant , is a species of ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae which is endemic to the southwestern United States .
Lethrinops parvidens , known as the Lethrinops red flush in the aquarium fish trade , is a species of cichlid fish endemic to Lake Malawi where it is found over sandy substrates in the southern portion of the lake .
Tuberostylis is a genus of Mesoamerican and South American plants in the boneset tribe within the sunflower family .
Trichastylopsis albidus is a species of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae , and the only species in the genus Trichastylopsis .
Helianthus carnosus is a rare North American species of sunflower known by the common name lakeside sunflower .
Mimiphiastus vivesi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimiphiastus .
The Blanford 's rosefinch or crimson rosefinch ( Agraphospiza rubescens ) is a species of finch in the Fringillidae family .
Anelpistina is a genus of insects .
Limnochromis abeelei is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it occurs in deeper waters in the southern portion of the lake .
Alkanindiges is a genus of Gram - negative alkane degrading bacteria which belong to the class of Gammaproteobacteria and which occurs in activated sludge systems .
Clusiella elegans is a plant species in the genus Clusiella .
Erebia is a Holarctic genus of brush - footed butterflies , family Nymphalidae .
The Finnish forest reindeer ( Rangifer tarandus fennicus ) ( Finnish : metsäpeura , Russian : лесной северный олень ) is a rare and threatened subspecies of reindeer native to Finland and northwestern Russia .
The black hairy thick - tailed scorpion , Parabuthus villosus , is a species of scorpion from southern Africa , where it ranges from the Northern Cape to Namibia .
Duopalatinus is a small genus of long - whiskered catfishes native to South America .
Borophagus diversidens ( `` devouring glutton '' ) is an extinct species of the genus Borophagus of the subfamily Borophaginae , a group of canids endemic to North America from the early Miocene epoch through the Pliocene epoch 4.9 - -1.8 Ma .
Pterocarpus dalbergioides , the Andaman padauk , Andaman redwood or East Indian mahogany , is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family .
Tillandsia extensa is a species of the genus Tillandsia .
Dorstenia lindeniana is a species of herb in the plant family Moraceae which is native to Mexico , Guatemala and Belize .
Apioplagiostoma is a genus of fungi within the Valsaceae family .
Thryptomene calycina , commonly known as Grampians Thryptomene , is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae .
Najas graminea , also known as ricefield water - nymph is a species of aquatic plant found in freshwater habitats , especially still or slow - moving waters , like ponds and rice fields .
Helina is a very large genus from the fly family Muscidae .
Nemacladus calcaratus is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name Chimney Creek nemacladus .
Clypidina notata , common name the black - ribbed false limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Liolaemus hellmichi , commonly known as Hellmich 's tree iguana , is a species of lizard in the family Iguanidae .
Patiria pectinifera , the blue bat star , is a species of starfish in the family Asterinidae .
Hymenoxys grandiflora is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names graylocks four - nerve daisy or graylocks rubberweed .
Diademichthys lineatus , known commonly as the long - snout clingfish or urchin clingfish , is a species of marine fish in the family Gobiesocidae .
Oligodon woodmasoni is a species of snake found in the Nicobar Islands of India .
Phasianotrochus rutilus , common name the pink - tipped kelp shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
The Siberian zokor ( Myospalax myospalax ) is a species of rodents in the family Spalacidae .
There are two species of cat 's claw commonly used in North America and Europe , Uncaria tomentosa and Uncaria guianensis , each having different properties and uses .
Essexella is a genus of scyphozoan jellyfish known from Late Carboniferous fossils containing the species Essexella asherae .
Acrochordonichthys gyrinus , the Falcate chameleon catfish , is a species of catfish of the family Akysidae .
Antennaria suffrutescens is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names evergreen pussytoes and evergreen everlasting .
Megacephala bocandei is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Guerin - Meneville in 1848 .
Aspergillus ochraceus is a mold species in the genus Aspergillus known to produce the toxin ochratoxin A , one of the most abundant food - contaminating mycotoxins , and citrinin .
Sternotherus odoratus is a species of small turtle native to southeastern Canada and much of the Eastern United States .
Odontoglossum gloriosum , the Glorious Odontoglossum , is a species of orchid endemic to Colombia .
Balantidium coli is a parasitic species of ciliate protozoan that causes the disease Balantidiasis .
Entocolax ludwigii is a species of parasitic sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Eulimidae .
Paleohemilophus dominicanus is an extinct species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paleohemilophus .
Allium chamaemoly , called dwarf garlic , is a species of garlic native to the Mediterranean region and cultivated elsewhere for its pretty flowers and potently aromatic bulbs .
The deep - water flatheads are a family , the Bembridae , of bottom - dwelling fish .
Qinglongopterus is a genus of rhamphorhynchine rhamphorhynchid pterosaur from the Middle / Upper Jurassic of Mutoudeng , Qinglong County , Hebei Province , China .
Moenchia erecta , erect chickweed or upright chickweed ( though the latter name may refer to any species of Moenchia ) , is a small annual plant in the family Caryophyllaceae .
Basiptera castaneipennis is a species of longhorn beetle in the Cerambycinae subfamily , and the only species in the genus Basiptera .
Aplidium solidum is a species of colonial sea squirts , a tunicate in the family Polyclinidae .
Glossodoris hikuerensis , is a species of sea slug , a colorful nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Chromodorididae .
Paragus is a genus of hoverfies .
Sardinella fimbriata ( fringescale sardinella ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Sardinella .
Parachartergus apicalis is a species of wasp in the Polistinae subfamily , found in the Neotropics .
Spinostropheus is a genus of small carnivorous ceratosaurian theropod dinosaur that lived in the Middle Jurassic period of Niger .
Bryaninops ( commonly known as sea whip gobies ) is a tropical Indo - Pacific genus of gobies .
It contains only one species , Erysimaga chlororrhabda , which is found in Papua New Guinea .
Lessingia lemmonii is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Lemmon 's lessingia .
Hydrobioides nassa is a species of a freshwater snail with an operculum , aquatic prosobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Bithyniidae .
Eleginus is a genus of cods with these recognized species :
Laelia furfuracea is a species of orchid endemic to Mexico ( Oaxaca ) .
Bidens triplinervia is a Latin American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Chaetorellia australis is a species of tephritid fruit fly known as the yellow starthistle peacock fly .
Pleurolidia juliae is a species of sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Pleurolidiidae .
Oonopidae is a family of spiders commonly known as goblin spiders , consisting of over 1,600 described species in about 110 genera worldwide , with total species diversity estimated at 2000 to 2500 species .
Johnwyattiidae is an extinct taxonomic family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks .
Lampropeltis getula nitida , or the Baja cape kingsnake , is a subspecies of the common kingsnake , originating from Baja California , in Mexico .
Neoptychites is an extinct ammonoid cephalopod genus from the Turonian stage of the Upper Cretaceous , with a world wide distribution .
Anacropora spinosa is a species of briar coral that can be found in the central Indo - Pacific , Southeast Asia , the Solomon Islands , Japan , the East China Sea and the oceanic west Pacific Ocean .
Brachycaudus cardui is a species of aphid , commonly known as the thistle aphid or the plum - thistle aphid .
Dorylus molestus is a species of African army ant .
Acer tataricum ( Tatar Maple or Tatarian Maple ) is a species of maple widespread across central and southeastern Europe and temperate Asia , from Austria and Turkey east as far as Japan and the Russian Far East .
Amphipteryx longicaudata is a species of damselfly in family Amphipterygidae .
Siphonaria pectinata , common name the striped false limpet , is a species of air - breathing sea snail or false limpet , a marine heterobranch gastropod mollusc in the family Siphonariidae , the false limpets .
The Tocantins vesper mouse , Calomys tocantinsi , is a South American rodent species of the family Cricetidae .
Melinaea ludovica is a species of butterfly of the Nymphalidae family found in South America .
Anubias is a genus of aquatic and semi - aquatic flowering plants in the family Araceae , native to tropical central and western Africa .
Buergeria oxycephala ( Hainan stream treefrog or red - headed flying frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
The type species Sulcusuchus erraini was named in 1990 by Zulma Brandoni de Gasparini and Luis Spalletti .
Absolmsia is a genus of flowering plants of the family Apocynaceae of two species , native to Southwest of China and Borneo .
Anisopodus subarmatus is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that was described by Melzer in 1931 .
Brachylophus bulabula is a species of iguanid lizard endemic to some of the larger central and northwestern islands of Fiji ( Ovalau , Gau , Kadavu and Viti Levu ) , where it occurs in Fijian wet forest .
Ameiva exsul ( English vernacular : Puerto Rican ground lizard or common Puerto Rican ameiva ; Spanish vernacular : iguana ) is a species of lizard in the whiptail family .
The Rich Mountain salamander ( Plethodon ouachitae ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
The Strigeoidea are a superfamily of flatworms , belonging to the large group Digenea .
Buthus ibericus is a scorpion species found in western Spain and Portugal .
Epistylis is a genus of peritrichous ciliate with a short oral disc and collar , and a rigid stalk , often branching to form a colony .
Hortonella is a genus of alga that has been placed deep in the coralline stem group on the basis of its scarcely differentiated thallus .
Myrsine ceylanica is plant species in the Primulaceae family .
Taraxacum ( /təˈræksəkᵿm/ ) is a large genus of flowering plants in the family Asteraceae and consists of species commonly known as dandelion .
The tree species Aesculus glabra is commonly known as Ohio buckeye , American buckeye , or fetid buckeye .
Diastrophosternus bruchi is a species of longhorn beetle in the Cerambycinae subfamily , and the only species in the genus Diastrophosternus .
Juncus phaeocephalus is a variable species in which several subspecific varieties have been characterized mainly on its branching patterns of the inflorescences .
Bunium persicum is a plant species in the family Apiaceae that was previously included in genus Carum .
Teleogryllus is a genus of crickets in the family Gryllidae .
Stomatepia mongo , the Mongo , is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Barombi Mbo in western Cameroon .
Thamnocephalidae is a family of crustaceans with wide distribution including Western Australia and Southern Africa .
In contrast with other rangeomorphs , which have wide distributions , Avalofractus seems to have been an endemic species , being known only from the Spaniard 's Bay deposits .
Chara elegans is a green alga species in the genus Chara .
Lavandula pedunculata , commonly called French Lavender , is a species of flowering plant in the Lamiaceae family .
Psychotria dolichantha is a flora species in the Rubiaceae family .
Crossocheilus elegans is a fish species in the genus Crossocheilus from northern Borneo , Indonesia .
Arnica porsildiorum is an Arctic species of arnica in the sunflower family .
Polyalthia laddiana is a species of plant in the genus Polyalthia .
Telescopium telescopium , or `` Horn snail , '' is a species of marine gastropod mollusk in the family Potamididae .
Psilocarphus tenellus is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names slender woollyheads and slender woolly marbles .
The Cymatoceratidae is a family of Mesozoic and early Cenozoic nautiloid cephalopods and the most abundant of this kind in the Cretaceous .
Cyathea ascendens is a species of tree fern native to northeastern New Guinea , where it grows in rain forest at an altitude of 800 - -1000 m. The erect trunk is slim and 1 - -2 m tall .
Limnonectes microtympanum ( common name : Sulawesi wart frog ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Diadiaphorus is an extinct genus of litoptern mammal from the Miocene of South America .
Microhadrosaurus ( meaning `` small sturdy lizard '' in Greek ) is a genus of duckbill dinosaur from the Campanian or Maastrichtian - age Upper Cretaceous Yuanpu Formation ( also known as the Nanxiong Formation ) of Guangdong , China .
Podochilus is a genus of about 60 - 80 species of small , moss - like epiphytic orchids , distributed across China , the Indian Subcontinent , Southeast Asia ( Indochina , Indonesia , Philippines , etc , ) New Guinea , Australia and the Solomon Islands .
Buettnerella is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Urocyclidae .
Gilia scopulorum is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common names rock gilia and Rocky Mountain gilia .
Chelidonichthys ischyrus , is a species of sea robin that is endemic to Sagami Bay , Japan .
Selaginella substipitata , the stalked spikemoss , is a species of plant in the Selaginellaceae family , endemic to Caribbean islands , Colombia , and Venezuela .
Oreohelix subrudis is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Oreohelicidae .
Asconiscus is a genus in the Asconiscidae family of marine isopod crustaceans in the suborder Cymothoida , containing a single genus and a single species , Asconiscus simplex .
The Cameroonian forest shrew ( Sylvisorex camerunensis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Thiorhodovibrio winogradskyi is a purple sulfur bacteria , the type species of its genus .
Ceraeochrysa elegans is a green lacewing species in the genus Ceraeochrysa .
Carabus jankowskii jankowskii is a subspecies of black coloured beetle from Carabidae family .
Oreomunnea pterocarpa , known locally as gavilán or gavilán blanco is a species of Oreomunnea in the family Juglandaceae .
Pterostichus is a very large genus of ground beetles with a Holarctic distribution in the subfamily Harpalinae .
Thayeria boehlkei is a species of characin fish endemic to the Amazon river basin and Araguaia river , in Peru and Brazil respectively .
Peranema is a genus of free - living flagellate protists , with more than 20 accepted species , varying in size between 8 and 200 micrometers .
Hydroides is a genus of tube - forming serpulid worm found on submerged saltwater rocks , shells , and boats in many coastal areas around the world .
Biplex perca is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ranellidae , the tritons .
Patella ulyssiponensis , common name the rough limpet , or China limpet is a species of sea snail , a true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Patellidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Coelotrochus chathamensis is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Trochidae , the top snails or top shells .
Peithona prionoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Peithona .
Melica rectiflora is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that can be found in Southeastern Europe .
Campanula californica is a species of bellflower known by the common names swamp bellflower and swamp harebell .
Lactophrys is a genus of boxfishes native to the western Atlantic Ocean .
Leptotyphlops joshuai , or the Joshua 's blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Moringa ovalifolia is an endemic species of central Namibia and southwestern Angola .
Charisma carinata , common name the carinate charisma , is a species of extremely small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
The Sulawesi hornbill is a social species that lives in groups of up to 20 individuals .
Caecum johnsoni , common name the Johnson 's caecum , is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Caecidae .
Huernia hallii is a species of plant in the Asclepiadaceae family .
Trichosphaeria is a genus of fungi in the family Trichosphaeriaceae .
Zanthoxylum fagara or wild lime , is a species of flowering plant that , despite its name , is not actually in the citrus genus with real limes and other fruit , but is a close cousin in the larger citrus family , Rutaceae .
Anaphes nipponicus is a species of fairyfly from Eastern Asia .
Heliophanus hastatus is a spider species in the genus Heliophanus found in South Africa .
Ophrys argolica , Late Spider Orchid , or Argolian Bee - orchid , is a terrestrial species of orchid native to Greece , Italy , Croatia , Cyprus , Turkey , Lebanon and Syria .
The Cladochytriaceae are a family of fungi in the order Cladochytriales .
Ptyas korros , commonly known as the Chinese ratsnake or Indo - Chinese rat snake , is a species of colubrid snake endemic to Southeast Asia .
Byrrhodes grandis is a species of beetles in the genus Byrrhodes of the family Anobiidae .
Tonyosynthemis is a genus of slender black and yellow dragonflies found in eastern Australia .
Moniezia a genus of tapeworms that are parasitic in mammals , including sheep , goat and cattle .
Conus wittigi , common name Wittig 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Triporthidae is a family of characiform fishes , including about 23 species .
Stenochlaena palustris ( Tagalog : diliman ) is an edible medicinal fern species .
Sagittaria filiformis , the threadleaf arrowhead , is an aquatic plant species native to the eastern United States , from Maine south to Florida and Alabama .
Agaricus pattersoniae is an edible species of mushroom .
Gobiomorus is a genus of sleeper gobies native to marine , fresh and brackish waters along the Pacific and Atlantic coasts of the Americas .
Appasus is a genus of giant water bugs ( family Belostomatidae ) .
The Microcerberidae are a family of isopod crustaceans .
Dioryctria merkeli , the loblolly pine coneworm moth , is a species of snout moth in the genus Dioryctria .
The Muisk vole ( Microtus mujanensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Acodontaster conspicuus is a species of starfish in the family Odontasteridae .
Micranthes howellii ( formerly Saxifraga howellii ) is a species of saxifrage known by the common name Howell 's saxifrage .
Cyllecoris histrionius is a species of bug in Miridae family that can be found in the United Kingdom , Iceland , Western , Eastern , and Central Europe .
Cyprinus longipectoralis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Cyprinus .
Streptogyna is a widespread genus of tropical plants in the grass family .
Septocyta ruborum is a species of fungus in the Ascomycota .
Redlichiidae is a family of redlichiid trilobites which lived from the Botomian to the Middle Cambrian period .
Ceanothus griseus is a species of flowering shrub known by the common names Yankee Point , Carmel ceanothus and Carmel creeper .
Cyclostrema huesonicum , common name the Key West cyclostreme , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Liotiidae .
Gaillardia parryi , Parry 's blanketflower , is a North American species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Acanthops centralis is a species of praying mantis in the subfamily Acanthopinae of the family Acanthopidae and is one of many mantis from various genera that resembles a dead leaf .
Sideroxylon foetidissimum , commonly known as false mastic or yellow mastic , is a species of flowering plant in the chicle family , Sapotaceae .
The black kauri or blue kauri ( Agathis atropurpurea ) is a species of conifer in the Araucariaceae family .
Cymothoida is the name of a suborder of isopod crustaceans with a mostly carnivorous or parasitic lifestyle .
Uegitglanis zammaranoi is the only species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) in the genus Uegitglanis of the family Clariidae .
Nephilidae is a spider family with 75 described species in four genera .
Retropinna is a genus of New Zealand smelts containing one species native to Australia , one native to Tasmania and one native to New Zealand .
The Ceylon breadfruit , ( Artocarpus nobilis ) , is a tree species in the family Moraceae .
Coreopsis palmata is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family It is native to the central United States and central Canada , mostly the Mississippi Valley and adjacent areas from Louisiana north to Manitoba and east into southwestern Michigan .
Populus wilsonii ( Wilson 's poplar ) is a species of deciduous poplar tree found in China 's Gansu , Hubei , Shaanxi , Sichuan , Xizang and Yunnan provinces .
Pyganodon grandis ( giant floater ) is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Spartina maritima , the small cordgrass , is a species of cordgrass native to the coasts of western and southern Europe and western Africa , from the Netherlands west across southern England to southern Ireland , and south along the Atlantic coast to Morocco and also on the Mediterranean Sea coasts .
Bactris cubensis is a species of palm endemic to the Nipe - Baracoa Massif and eastern Sierra Maestra in eastern Cuba at elevations between 40 and 700 metres above sea level .
Anatemnus is a genus of pseudoscorpions .
Malacoptila is a genus of puffbird in the Bucconidae family , one of ten genera .
Erketu is the name given to a genus of dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous .
Yeosuana aromativorans is a species of non - motile aerobic marine bacterium that can degrade benzopyrene .
The division between Natantia and Reptantia was replaced in 1963 , when Martin Burkenroad erected the suborder Pleocyemata for those animals that brood their eggs on the pleopods , leaving Dendrobranchiata for the prawns .
Tirathaba mundella , the oil palm bunch moth , is a species of snout moth .
Penstemon cyaneus is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common names blue penstemon and dark - blue beardtongue .
Festuca viridula is a species of grass known by several common names , including green fescue , greenleaf fescue , and mountain bunchgrass .
Youngina is an extinct genus of diapsid reptile from the Late Permian Beaufort Group ( Tropidostoma - Dicynodon zones ) of the Karoo Red Beds of South Africa .
Champsochromis is a small genus of cichlid fishes endemic to Lake Malawi in east Africa .
Parvilucifera is a genus of marine parasitic protozoa that parasitise dinoflagellates .
Nesolycaena is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The members ( species ) are found in the Australasian ecozone .

Penicillium maximae is a species of the genus of Penicillium which is named after Queen Máxima of the Netherlands .
Atriplex ( /ˈætrᵻplɛks/ ) is a plant genus of 250 - -300 species , known by the common names of saltbush and orache ( or orach ) .
Brodiaea orcuttii is a species of flowering plant in the cluster - lily genus known by the common name Orcutt 's brodiaea .
Solidago wrightii , commonly known as Wright 's goldenrod , is a North American species of goldenrod in the sunflower family .
Gerrinae is a subfamily of Water Strider .
Catonephele is a nymphalid butterfly genus found in Mexico , Central America , South America , and the West Indies .
Calliostoma pellucidum , common name the pellucid top shell , is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Calliostomatidae , the calliostoma top snails .
Mesopsocus immunis is a species of Psocoptera from Mesopsocidae family that can be found throughout Western Europe ( except for Denmark and Iceland ) , and Hungary .
Geikiidae is a family of Late Permian dicynodonts .
Oedogonium is a genus of filamentous green algae , with unbranched filaments that are one cell thick .
Ambassis fontoynonti , commonly known as the dusky glass perch , is a species of fish in the family Ambassidae .
Fluviphylax is a genus of poeciliids native to the Amazon Basin , Orinoco Basin and Oyapock Basin in South America .
Galaxias is a genus of small , highly successful freshwater fish in the Galaxiidae family .
The cod icefishes or nothothens are the family Nototheniidae of acanthopterygian fishes .
Pommerhelix monacha is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Camaenidae .
Sphaerichthys is a genus of gouramies native to Southeast Asia .
Ouranopithecus is an extinct genus of Eurasian great ape represented by two species , Ouranopithecus macedoniensis , a late Miocene ( 9.6mya-8.7mya ) hominoid from Greece and Bulgaria , and Ouranopithecus turkae , also from the late Miocene ( 8.7mya-7.4mya ) of Turkey .
Holochlamys beccarii is the only species in the genus Holochlamys .
Nothocestrum latifolium , commonly known as broadleaf ʻaiea , is a species of flowering plant in the nightshade family , Solanaceae , that is endemic to Hawaiʻi .
It was named by T. Shikama and H. Ozaki in 1966 and the type species is Brazilosaurus sanpauloensis .
Streptomyces amakusaensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from the Amakusa Island in Japan .
Yoldiidae is a taxonomic family of small saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the order Nuculanoida .
Thevenotia is a genus of Asian plants in the thistle tribe within the daisy family .
Penkimia is a genus of terrestrial orchid native to high elevations ( 1,600 - -2,000 metres or 5,200 - -6,600 feet ) in the Himalayas of Yunnan and Nagaland .
Anopheles claviger is a mosquito species found in Palearctic ecozone covering Europe , North Africa , northern Arabian Peninsula , and northern Asia .
The Brachyceran family Kovalevisargidae is an extinct group of flies known from the Jurassic Daohugou biota of China .
Bergtrollus dzimbowski is a species of tardigrades .
Caroliniella aenescens is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Caroliniella .
Andriashevicottus megacephalus , Andriyashev largeheaded sculpin , is a species of sculpin native to the northwestern Pacific Ocean .
Halymenia a genus of a macroscopic red algae that grows in oceans worldwide .
Sepia tuberculata is a species of cuttlefish native to South African waters from Melkbosstrand ( 33 ° 43′S 18 ° 26′E ) to Knysna ( 34 ° 03′S 23 ° 03′E ) .
Phaius fragilis is a species of orchid in the genus Phaius endemic to the Philippines .
Tuctoria greenei is a species of grass endemic to California .
Darcythompsoniidae is a family of copepods , containing four genera .
Aphthona abdominalis is a species of leaf beetle known as the minute spurge flea beetle .
Planitrochidae is an extinct family of fossil sea snails , Paleozoic gastropod mollusks .
Euxesta stigmatias is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Euxesta of the family Ulidiidae .
The rotifers ( Rotifera , commonly called wheel animals ) make up a phylum of microscopic and near - microscopic pseudocoelomate animals .
Microstomus is a genus of righteye flounders native to the North Pacific and Northeast Atlantic oceans .
Rhynchospora knieskernii is a rare species of sedge known by the common name Knieskern 's beaksedge .
Pheidole decepticon ( named after the Decepticons from the toy line Transformers ) is a species of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
It is monotypic , with only a single described species Crocodilurus amazonicus , the crocodile tegu .

Agyneta iranica is a species of sheet weaver found in Iran .

Ricordea florida is a species of coral of the family Ricordeidae and the order Corallimorpharia , whose members are also called false corals .
The Yellow - tailed parrot ( Pionites xanthurus ) is one of the four species in the genus Pionites of the Psittacidae family .
Petchia is a genus of plant in the Apocynaceae family , first described as a genus in 1926 .
Leptochirus is a genus of beetles in the family Staphylinidae , the rove beetles .
Duriavenator is a genus of theropod dinosaur described in 2008 by Roger Benson ; its finds were excavated in England .
Thalaina clara , the Clara 's satin moth , is a species of moth of the family Geometridae .
Lepisma is a genus of primitive insects belonging to the family Lepismatidae .
Opacuincola is a genus of New Zealand freshwater snails in the family Tateidae .
Notadusta hungerfordi , common name Hungerford 's Cowry , is a species of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Cryptovenator ( Crypto , from Greek kryptos ( hidden , secret ) ; venator , from Latin ( hunter ) ) is an extinct genus of sphenacodontid pelycosaur which existed in Germany during the latest Carboniferous ( late Gzhelian age , 300 Ma ± 2.4 Ma ) .
Solidago macrophylla , the largeleaf goldenrod or large - leaved goldenrod , is North American species of herbaceous perennial plants of the sunflower family .
Moggridgea terrestris is a spider species in the genus Moggridgea .

Manticora tuberculata is a species of tiger beetle native to Angola ( Kajambo ) , Namibia , South Africa ( western Cape Colony ) .
Phesatiodes fuscosignatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Phesatiodes .
Dipterocarpus retusus is a large tree and perhaps the best known species in the genus Dipterocarpus .
Astragalus coarctatus is a species of milkvetch that is endemic to northeastern Turkey , and is only known from its type specimen , collected in 1871 in Kars Province .
Melica yajiangensis , is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that is endemic to China .
Ulidia splendida is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Ulidia of the family Ulidiidae .

Homalopoma rotella is a species of minute sea snail with a calcareous operculum , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Colloniidae .
Lerheimia wulfi is a species of chironomid midge found in the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Odontobutis haifengensis is a species of freshwater sleeper endemic to China where it is only found in fresh and brackish waters of Guangdong Province .
Microgoes oculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Microgoes .
Myersina is a genus of gobies found from the Atlantic coast of South Africa through the Indian Ocean to the western Pacific Ocean .
Ogasawarana nitida is a species of land snail with an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Helicinidae , the helicinids .

Rorippa curvisiliqua is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name curvepod yellowcress .
The Asian short - toed lark ( Alaudala cheleensis ) is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family .
Paxistima canbyi is a species of small broadleaf evergreen shrub or groundcover that is usually about one foot high , but can get up to almost three feet high .

Scaphella worki is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the votules .
The Antilles monkeys ( Xenotrichini ) are a tribe of extinct primates , which lived on the Greater Antilles as recently as the 16th century .
Pyrus boissieriana , the `` Boissier Pear '' , is a species of Pyrus - pear native to the Kopet Dag region on the Turkmenistan and Iranian border .
Trogontherium is an extinct genus of giant beavers .
Ammopelmatus muwu is a species of insect in family Stenopelmatidae .
Patagonotothen is a genus of cod icefishes native to the southern oceans .
Geisonocerina is an extinct genus from the carnivorous nautiloid cephalopod order Orthocerida that lived in what would be North America , Europe , and Asia during the Ordovician through Permian from 449 - -290 mya , existing for approximately 159 million years .
Furcifer nicosiai is a large species of chameleon that is endemic to western Madagascar .
The Tripartellidae are an extinct family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Disporum viridescens is a species of flowering plant in the genus Disporum .
Himantarium gabrielis is a species of centipede in the family Himantariidae .
Neoniphon is a genus of squirrelfishes .
Hexarthrius parryi , the Fighting Giant Stag Beetle , is a species of large stag beetles .
The Rhyacichthyidae or loach gobies are a small family of perciform fish in two genera and three species .
Sorghastrum is a genus of grasses in the grass family , native to Africa and the Americas .
Doodia media , also known as rasp fern ( or pukupuku in Māori ) , is a fern species in the Blechnaceae family .
Brachyglottis stewartiae is a species of flowering plant , often referred to as a tree daisy , in the Asteraceae family .
Serapias cordigera is a species of orchid found from the Azores , south - central Europe to the Mediterranean .
Scarus ghobban , also known as the blue - barred parrotfish , blue - barred parrotfish , blue trim parrotfish , cream parrotfish , globe - headed parrotfish , green blotched parrotfish , yellow scale parrotfish , and bluechin parrotfish , is a species of marine fish in the Scaridae family .
