Furcacauda is a genus of thelodontid agnathan from the Lower Devonian of Canada , and is the type genus of the order Furcacaudiformes .
Gnathophyllum americanum , commonly known as the `` striped bumblebee shrimp , '' is a species of shrimp that is common throughout tropical lagoons , bays , and reefs .
Monardella australis is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name southern monardella .
Arnica longifolia is a North American species of arnica in the sunflower family , known by the common names seep - spring arnica , longleaf arnica and spearleaf arnica .
Solidago pulchra , the Carolina goldenrod , is a rare North American plant species in the sunflower family .
Hardmanoceras is a Tarphycerid genus belonging to the Trochilidae from the upper Lower Ordovician to possibly the lower Middle Ordovician , found in Western Australia .

Cheilotoma is a genus of beetles in the subfamily Cryptocephalinae of the leaf beetles family .

Cycnorhamphus ( meaning `` swan beak '' ) is a genus of ctenchasmatoid pterodactyloid pterosaur from the Late Jurassic of France and Germany .
The Cupedidae are a small family of beetles , notable for the square pattern of `` windows '' on their elytra ( hard forewings ) , which give the family their common name of reticulated beetles .
Nanotyrannus ( `` dwarf tyrant '' ) is a potentially dubious genus of tyrannosaurid dinosaur .

Contarinia is a genus of midges , small flies in the family Cecidomyiidae .

The mottled water hyacinth weevil , Neochetina eichhorniae , is a beetle that has been introduced as a biological pest control herbivore agent to waterways and lakes in countries worldwide to control the spread of the invasive noxious weed species Eichhornia crassipes , the water hyacinth , an aquatic plant native to the Amazon basin .
The western nominate group is now treated as separate species ; the Orange River white - eye ( Z. pallidus ) and the Cape white - eye ( Z. virens ) .

Carex interior is a species of sedge known by the common name inland sedge .
Pseudamnicola artanensis is a species of very small brackish water snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .

Colombellinidae is an extinct family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .

Tetradymia glabrata is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name littleleaf horsebrush .
Dicata odhneri is a species of sea slug , specifically an aeolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Facelinidae .
Papilio erskinei is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found on Ugi Island .
Labrisomus cricota , the Mock blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the western Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea where it occurs on rocky bottoms with plentiful algal growth at depths down to 4 metres ( 13 ft ) .
It consists of only one species , Zenenata zenena , which is found in Ecuador ( Loja Province ) .
Atlantea is a genus of butterflies from the Caribbean in the family Nymphalidae .
Mongolicosa is a genus of wolf spiders containing six species found in central Asia from the Altai Mountains east to western Buryatia and south to Xinjiang and the Gobi Desert .
Crambe maritima ( common name sea kale , seakale or crambe ) is a species of halophytic flowering plant in the genus Crambe of the family Brassicaceae ( Cruciferae ) , that grows wild along the coasts of Europe , from the North Atlantic to the Black Sea .
Miconia calvescens , the velvet tree , miconia , or bush currant , is a species of flowering plant in the family Melastomataceae .
Tanyptera is a genus of true crane flies ; its species are lustrous and black and yellow or red in color .
Acanthomysis is a genus of mysids , containing 28 species .
Conus aureus , common name the aureus cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Phyllodactylus is a genus of geckos distributed in South America and Central America , and as far north as the southern United States .
Amphibolurus is a genus of lizards native to Australia .
Cephaloleia splendida is a species of rolled - leaf beetle in the family Chrysomelidae , first found in Costa Rica and Panama .
Calyptronoma occidentalis is a pinnately compound leaved palm species which is endemic to Jamaica .
Geigeria is a genus of African flowering plants in the daisy family .
Olenellus is an extinct genus of redlichiid trilobites , with species of average size ( about 5 centimetres or 2.0 inches long ) .
Araucaria hunsteinii ( Klinki or Klinkii ) is a species of Araucaria native to the mountains of Papua New Guinea .
Aloe purpurea ( previously Lomatophyllum purpureum / borbonicum / aloiflorum . Locally known as `` Mazambron '' ) is a species of Aloe endemic to the island of Mauritius , in the Indian Ocean .
Picea crassifolia or Qinghai spruce is a species of conifer in the Pinaceae family .
The type species , Embasaurus minax , was described by the Soviet paleontologist Anatoly Riabinin in 1931 .
Rhododendron crassifolium is a species of tropical rhododendron , a perennial flowering plant belonging to the Ericaceae family .
Juncus cooperi is a species of rush known by the common name Cooper 's rush .
The single species that comprises the genus is Pothoidium lobbianum .
Artemisia serrata is a North American species in the sunflower family , with the common mame Serrate - leaved sage or Saw - tooth Wormwood .
Agamodon anguliceps is a species of reptile in the Trogonophidae family .
Stenocercus fimbriatus , the Western leaf lizard , is a species of lizard in the Tropiduridae family within the genus Stenocercus .
Calliostoma scalenum , common name the Gulfstream top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Auerodendron northropianum is a plant species of the family Rhamnaceae that is native to the Caribbean and is found in the Bahamas .
The Arvicolinae are a subfamily of rodents that includes the voles , lemmings , and muskrats .
Prostoma jenningsi is a species of ribbon worm known only from one site near Croston , Lancashire .
Mairia is a genus of South African flowering plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Araeopaschia demotis is a species of snout moth in the genus Araeopaschia .
Banksia tenuis var . tenuis is a variety of Banksia tenuis .
Dioryctria ebeli , the south coastal coneworm moth , is a species of moth of the Pyralidae family .
Choanozoa ( Greek : χόανος ( choanos ) = `` funnel '' + ζῶον ( zōon ) = `` animal '' ) is the name of a phylum of protists that belongs to the line of opisthokonts .
Lefteye flounders are a family , Bothidae , of flounders .
Tringa is a genus of waders , containing the shanks and tattlers .
Phlyctenactis tuberculosa , common name the wandering sea anemone or swimming anemone , is a species of sea anemone in the family Actiniidae .
Billbergia cylindrostachya is a species in the genus Billbergia .
Thinornis is a genus of plovers which consists of two extant and threatened species .
Imperata cylindrica , commonly known as blady grass , cogon grass /koʊˈɡoʊn/ , kunai grass /ˈkuːnaɪ/ , or Japanese bloodgrass , is a species of grass in the genus Imperata .
Acanthocepola is a genus of bandfishes native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Carabus albrechti freyi is a subspecies of ground beetle from Carabidae family , that is endemic to Sado Island of Japan .
Langaha madagascariensis ( formerly Langaha nasuta , commonly known as the Madagascar or Malagasy leaf - nosed snake ) is a medium - sized highly cryptic arboreal species .
Lophothoracia orthozona is a species of snout moth in the genus Lophothoracia .
Sternotherus is a genus of aquatic turtles known commonly as musk turtles , which are endemic to North America .
Nemastoma lugubre is an harvestmen species found in the whole of Europe from the Arctic to the Mediterranean .
Termatosaurus ( `` end lizard '' , because it came from the end of the Upper Triassic ) is a genus of phytosaur , an extinct crocodile - like aquatic animal .
Cyathea kermadecensis is a species of tree fern endemic to Raoul Island in the Kermadec Islands , where it is locally common in damp , and sometimes drier , forest and scrub .
Luciosoma bleekeri ( Chinese : 布氏梭大口魚 , Thai : ปลาซิวอ้าว ) is a species of small cyprinid fish found in Southeast Asia from the Mae Klong River to the Mekong .
Sternidius variegatus is a species of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae , and the only species in the genus Sternidius .
Nebria paradisi is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in the northern part US state of Oregon .
Chalcopteroides is a genus of darkling beetle , defined by Embrik Strand in 1935 , and replacing the older name Chalcopterus which was preoccupied .
Salix lasiolepis ( arroyo willow ) is a species of willow native to western North America .
Conus araneosus , common name the cobweb cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
Leptosiphon septentrionalis is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name northern linanthus .
Guzmania hedychioides is a species of Bromeliaceae ( flowering plants ) of the genus Guzmania .
The true soles are a family , Soleidae , of flatfishes .
Paphiopedilum lowii is a species of orchid endemic to western and central Malaysia .
Cyrtopodion kachhensis , commonly known as the Kutch gecko , is a species of gecko which is endemic to South Asia .
Buddleja lanata is a species endemic to Ecuador where it grows on dry , windy plateaux amid grasses and bracken at elevations of 1,150 -- 2,700 m. The species , first named and described by Bentham in 1845 is now threatened by habitat loss .
Pireneitega ovtchinnikovi is an araneomorph spider species found in Russia , Abkhazia and Georgia .
Morelia spilota variegata is a subspecies of python found in New Guinea and Australia , smaller than the nominate subspecies Morelia spilota spilota and has a more restricted geographic range .
Istigobius is a genus of gobies found in fresh , brackish and marine waters of the regions along the coasts of the Indian and western Pacific oceans .
Lecithocera indigens is a species of moth of the Lecithoceridae family .
Neopetrosia subtriangularis is a species of marine petrosiid sponges native to the waters off Florida and the Caribbean Sea .
Tetramolopium filiforme is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name ridgetop tetramolopium .
Isaria sinclairii is a species of entomopathogenic fungus .
Corydiidae , previously known as Polyphagidae , is a family of the order Blattodea ( cockroaches ) .
Crenadactylus ocellatus is the smallest species of nocturnal Gekkonidae ( gecko ) found in Australia .
Longneck eels or neck eels are a family , Derichthyidae , of eels .
Bromus is a large genus of grasses , classified in its own tribe Bromeae .
Amantis nawai is a small species of praying mantis native to Eastern Asia .
Chesnonia verrucosa , the Warty Poacher , is a species of poacher native to the northeastern Pacific Ocean where it is found at depths of from 18 to 425 metres ( 59 to 1,394 ft ) .
Choia is a genus of extinct demosponge ranging from the Cambrian until the Lower Ordovician periods .
Pethia macrogramma is a species of cyprinid fish native to Myanmar where it is only known from streams in the Myitkyina area .
Correa backhouseana is a species of flowering plant in the family Rutaceae .
Aromobates leopardalis ( common name : leopard rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Pholistoma auritum is a species of flowering plant in the borage family which is known by the common name blue fiestaflower .
Hedysarum ( sweetvetch ) is a genus of the botanical family Fabaceae , consisting of about 309 species of annual or perennial herbs in Asia , Europe , North Africa , and North America .
Aonyx is a genus of otters , containing two species , the African clawless otter and the Cameroon clawless otter .
The Hooded Bulbophyllum ( Bulbophyllum calyptratum ) is a species of orchid .
Adelophthalmus is a genus of prehistoric eurypterid of the family Adelophthalmidae .
Minyichthys is a circumtropical genus of pipefishes consisting of species from the Indo - Pacific and eastern and western Atlantic regions .
It contains only one species , Nyctocyrmata crotalopis , which is found in South Africa .
Navarretia viscidula is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name sticky pincushionplant .
Camissonia pusilla is a species of evening primrose known by the common name little wiry suncup .
Papuasyntaxis is a genus of moths in the Arctiidae family , containing only one species , Papuasyntaxis metallescens , which is known only from central Papua Indonesia .
It consists of only one species , Yanachagana polyperla , which is found in Peru .
Krigia occidentalis , known as western dwarfdandelion , is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
The spider genus Cabello consists of only one species , Cabello eugeni .
Ameiva atrigularis , known as giant ameiva and Amazon racerunner , is a species of teiid lizard found on Trinidad and Tobago and in Venezuela .
Rorippa columbiae is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names Columbian yellowcress and Columbia yellow cress .
The Miridae are large and diverse insect family at one time known by the taxonomic synonym Capsidae .
Mimodystasia mjoebergi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimodystasia .
Euchromia schoutedeni is a species of moth in the Arctiidae family .
Saxonipollis saxonicus is an extinct plant species .
Clematis viticella , the Italian leather flower , purple clematis , or `` Virgin 's bower '' , is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family ; it is native to Europe .
Aerangis citrata is an epiphytic species of orchid indigenous to Madagascar .
Lankanectes corrugatus ( common names : Sri Lanka wart frog , corrugated water frog ) is a species of frog in the Nyctibatrachidae family .
Wangisuchus is an extinct genus of archosauriform reptile from the Middle Triassic of China that is known from fragmentary fossil jaw bones .
Geotrupidae ( from Greek geos , earth , and trypetes , borer ) is a family of beetles in the order Coleoptera .
Gibbula umbilicalis , common name the flat top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Cystoseira is a genus of brown algae in the order Fucales .
The Guinean gerbil , Gerbilliscus guineae , is a species of gerbil found in Burkina Faso , Côte d'Ivoire , Gambia , Ghana , Guinea , Guinea - Bissau , Mali , Senegal , Sierra Leone , and possibly Liberia .
Bifidobacterium animalis and Bifidobacterium lactis were previously described as two distinct species .
Coronilla valentina , the shrubby scorpion - vetch or scorpion vetch , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Coronilla of the legume family Fabaceae , native to Portugal , Spain , Malta and Croatia ( Dalmatia ) .
Bursa davidboschi is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Bursidae , the frog shells .
Chamidae , common name the jewel boxes or jewel box clams , is a taxonomic family of saltwater clams , the marine bivalve mollusks in the order Veneroida .
Allium yongdengense is a plant species native to the Gansu and Qinghai regions in China .
Oenothera elata is a species of Oenothera known by the common name Hooker 's evening primrose .
Bronchocela is a genus of Asian agamid lizards .
Diochus electrus is an extinct species of rove beetle in genus Diochus , the only definitive fossil species in subfamily Staphylininae .
Titanoecidae is a spider family with five genera and more than 50 species worldwide .
Pirimela is a genus of crab containing a single species , Pirimela denticulata .
Metarhizium brunneum , is the re - instated name of a group of reassigned Metarhizium isolates , previously grouped in the species `` Metarhizium anisopliae var . anisopliae '' : based on a multigene phylogenetic approach using near - complete sequences from nuclear DNA .
Leptotes bicolor is a species of orchid native to Paraguay and southern Brazil .
The Rhodogorgonales are an order of red algae , a sister group to the corallines .
Melanastia bicolor is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Melanastia .
Pseudapriona flavoantennata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudapriona .
Sydowiella is a genus of fungi within the Sydowiellaceae family .
Isoetes tuckermanii ( Tuckerman 's quillwort ) is a tetraploid species of quillwort in the Isoetaceae family .
Rhynchium is an Australian , Afrotropical , Indomalayan and Palearctic genus of potter wasps .
Spongipellis unicolor is a species of polypore fungus in the family Polyporaceae .
Eschrichtioides is an extinct genus of eschrichtiid known from the early Pliocene of northern Italy .
Myosorex is a mammal genus in the Soricidae ( shrew ) family .
Iberochondrostoma almacai is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to southern Portugal , where it is only found in the drainages of the Mira , Arade and Bensafrim rivers .
Calotomus zonarchus , commonly known as yellowbar parrotfish , is a species of parrotfish native to the waters of the Hawaiian Islands and Midway Atoll .
The Little Colorado spinedace ( Lepidomeda vittata ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
The Bonnacord caecilian , Uraeotyphlus oommeni , is a new species of Uraeotyphlus , described on the basis of a single , distinctive specimen from the Western Ghats of southern Kerala , India .
Eumetula macquariensis is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Newtoniellidae .
Villosa taeniata , common name the Painted creekshell , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae .
Libinia emarginata , the portly spider crab , common spider crab or nine - spined spider crab , is a species of stenohaline crab that lives on the Atlantic coast of North America .
Hadopyrgus rawhiti is a critically endangered species of freshwater snail native to New Zealand .
Tauredophidium hextii is a species of cusk - eel found in the Indian and western Pacific Oceans .
Hylarana tytleri is a frog species in the family Ranidae .
The Valerianaceae Batsch , the valerian family , was a family of flowering plants that is now considered part of the Caprifoliaceae .
Heliopsis buphthalmoides is a New World species of flowering plant in the family sunflower family .
Ceanothus incanus is a species of shrub in the buckthorn family Rhamnaceae known by the common name coast whitethorn .
Streptococcus is a genus of coccus ( spherical ) gram - positive bacteria belonging to the phylum Firmicutes and the order Lactobacillales ( lactic acid bacteria ) .

Achoania is an extinct genus of primitive lobe - finned fish which lived during the Early Devonian period .

Horkelia wilderae is a rare species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name Barton Flats horkelia .
Nehalennia pallidula is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Erythrotrichia is a red algae genus in the family Erythrotrichiaceae .
Cetopsidium ferreirai is a species of whale catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Trombetas River , a tributary of the lower Amazon River .
Cycas arenicola is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas , native to Australia , in the far north of Northern Territory in the basin of the upper East Alligator River in Arnhem Land .
Heterotheca marginata , Sonora false goldenaster , is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the aster family .
Pheidole epiphyta is a species of ant that was discovered and described by Longino , J. T. in 2009 .
Leptosiphon ciliatus ( syn . Linanthus ciliatus ) is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name whiskerbrush .
Janassa is an extinct genus of petalodont cartilaginous fish that lived in marine environments in what is now central United States of America and Europe during the Carboniferous and Permian .
Limnonectes timorensis ( common name : Timor river frog and Timor wart frog ) is a species of frog in the family Dicroglossidae .
Conus emaciatus , common name the false virgin cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Ascoclavulina sakaii .
Asiatosaurus ( meaning `` Asian lizard '' ) was a genus of herbivorous sauropod dinosaur which lived during the early Cretaceous .
Mormodes aromatica is a species of orchid occurring from Mexico ( Guerrero , Oaxaca , Chiapas ) to Honduras .
Orophia sordidella is a species of univoltine , xerothermic moth in the family Oecophoridae .
Quercus chapmanii , commonly referred to as the Chapman oak , is a species of oak that grows in the Southeastern United States .
Priolepis semidoliata , the half - barred goby , is a species of goby native to the Indo - Pacific region .
Solanum evolvuloides is a species of Solanum , which was first described in 2011 by Giacomin & Stehmann .
Entemnotrochus rumphii , common name the Rumphius ' slit shell , is a species of large sea snail with gills and an operculum , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pleurotomariidae , the slit snails .
Pseudohadena is a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family .
Mugilogobius latifrons is a species of goby endemic to the Malili Lake system ( consisting of Matano , Towuti and smaller lakes ) in central Sulawesi , Indonesia generally being found in extremely shallow waters .
Clarkia dudleyana is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name Dudley 's clarkia .
Nealeodus is a genus of conodonts which existed in what is now Canada during the middle Ordovician .
Juncus edgariae , is a species of rush commonly called Edgar 's rush , or wiwi that is native to New Zealand .
Bothriembryon glauerti is a species of tropical air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Bothriembryontidae .
Cymo melanodactylus , the furry coral crab , is a species of small decapod crustacean in the family Xanthidae .
Elekmania barahonensis is a species of the genus Elekmania .
Phlox douglasii , common name tufted phlox or Columbia phlox , is a species of perennial herb belonging to the family Polemoniaceae .
Siphonium is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the familyVermetidae , the worm snails or worm shells .
Lithodoras dorsalis , the Rock - bacu , is the only species in the genus Lithodoras of the catfish ( order Siluriformes ) family Doradidae .
Agaricus pilatianus is a rare species of poisonous mushroom found in Europe .
Nimbaphrynoides is a small genus of true toads from highlands in the Mount Nimba region of the West African countries of Guinea , Liberia and Côte d'Ivoire .
Conradina brevifolia is a rare species of shrub in the mint family known by the common name short - leaved false rosemary .
Tachina tricolor is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to Himachal Pradesh , a province of India .
The Lecithoceridae ( long - horned moths ) are a family of small moths .
Notothenia microlepidota , the black cod or smallscaled cod , is a species of cod icefish native to the Pacific waters around New Zealand and Macquarie Island .
Banksia ser . Cyrtostylis is a taxonomic series within the plant genus Banksia .
Nephropoidea is a superfamily of decapod crustaceans .
The Scolopendridae are a family of large centipedes ( class Chilopoda ) .
Polemonium pulcherrimum is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by several common names , including beautiful Jacob's - ladder , showy Jacob's - ladder , and skunk - leaved polemonium .
Acrolepia autumnitella is a species of moth of the family Acrolepiidae .

Ficus pseudopalma is a species of fig known by the common names Philippine fig , dracaena fig , and palm - leaf fig . In nature it is endemic to the Philippines , especially the island of Luzon .
Basisperma is a genus of flowering plants in the myrtle family , Myrtaceae first described as a genus in 1942 .
Cylindrecamptus lineatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cylindrecamptus .
Urophora sogdiana is a species of tephritid , or fruit flies , in the genus Urophora of the family Tephritidae .
Cariamiformes ( or Cariamae ) is an order of primarily flightless birds that has existed for over 60 million years .
Zeyheria tuberculosa is a species of tree in the Bignoniaceae family .
Evarcha falcata is a species of jumping spider with Palaearctic distribution .
Conjunctio is an extinct genus of dissorophid temnospondyl amphibian from the Early Permian of New Mexico .
Toxomerus occidentalis , is a species of flower fly found in western North America from British Columbia south to California , Colorado and Texas .
Lilium hansonii , called the Japanese turk's - cap lily , is an East Asian species of plants in the lily family .
Jatropha curcas is a species of flowering plant in the spurge family , Euphorbiaceae , that is native to the American tropics , most likely Mexico and Central America .
Liobagrus somjinensis is a species of catfish in the Amblycipitidae family ( the torrent catfishes ) .
The Anaimalai spiny lizard or Anaimalais salea ( Salea anamallayana ) is a species of agamid lizard endemic to the southern Western Ghats , India .
Setaria pumila is a species of grass known by many common names , including yellow foxtail , yellow bristle - grass , pigeon grass , and cattail grass .
Olorotitan was a genus of lambeosaurine duckbilled dinosaur from the middle or latest Maastrichtian - age Late Cretaceous , whose remains were found in the Tsagayan Formation beds of Kundur , Amur Region , Far Eastern Russia .
Mittonia hampsoni is a species of snout moth in the genus Mittonia .
Callichirus kraussi ( Stebbing , 1900 ) , commonly named the Common Sandprawn or Pink Prawn , is a species of ghost shrimp , an African crustacean in the family Callianassidae .
Pholidolepis is an extinct prehistoric genus of prehistoric bony fish .
Mimetauge napeogenalis is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Mimetauge .
Heteromera is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family described as a genus in 1874 .
Dolichupis virgo is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Triviidae , the false cowries or trivias .
Anisopodus varius is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that was described by Melzer in 1935 .
Pterasteridae is a family of sea stars in the order Velatida , consisting of eight genera .
Rhododendron araiophyllum ( 窄叶杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to northeast Myanmar and northeastern and western Yunnan , China , where it grows at altitudes of 1900 - -3400 meters .
Primula suffrutescens is a species of primrose known by the common name Sierra primrose .
Trimorphodon is a genus of mildly venomous , rear - fanged , colubrid snakes .
The Speckled blue grouper ( Epinephelus cyanopodus ) also known as the Purple Rockcod is a species of fish in the Serranidae family .
Astragalus coccineus is a species of milkvetch known by the common name scarlet locoweed or scarlet milkvetch .
Boschniakia hookeri is a species of parasitic plant in the broomrape family known by the common names Vancouver groundcone and small groundcone .
Goodman 's mouse lemur ( Microcebus lehilahytsara ) is a species of mouse lemur from the region near Andasibe in eastern Madagascar .
Ptychatractus occidentalis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ptychatractidae .
Geoscincus is a monotypic genus of skinks : the only accepted species is Geoscincus haraldmeieri ( Meier 's skink ) .
Peganum nigellastrum ( Chinese : 骆驼蒿 , luo tuo hao ) is a plant species in the genus Peganum found in China .
Schizosaccharomyces pombe , also called `` fission yeast '' , is a species of yeast used in traditional brewing and as a model organism in molecular and cell biology .
Cottontail rabbits are among the 17 lagomorph species in the genus Sylvilagus , found in the Americas .
Zanthoxylum thomasianum , also known as the St. Thomas prickly - ash , is a species of plant in the Rutaceae family .
Nepenthes sanguinea ( /nɨˈpɛnθiːz sæŋˈɡwɪniə/ ; from Latin sanguineus `` blood red '' ) is a large and vigorous Nepenthes pitcher plant species , native to Peninsular Malaysia and southernmost Thailand , where it grows at 300 - -1800 m altitude .
Hoheria glabrata ( mountain lacebark or ribbonwood ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Malvaceae , endemic to New Zealand .
Gigantoproductus giganteus is an extinct species of brachiopod in the family Monticuliferidae , known only from its fossil remains .
Boyeria vinosa , the fawn darner , is a species of dragonfly in the family Aeshnidae .
Cantoria violacea , commonly known as Cantor 's Water Snake , is a species of snake found in tropical Asia .
Pachycheilosuchus ( meaning `` thick lipped crocodile '' ) is an extinct genus of mesoeucrocodylian from the Early Cretaceous of Texas , United States .
Icublabia multispinosa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Icublabia .
Haliplus carinatus is a species of Adephagan beetle in the genus Haliplus .
It contains the single species Ephestris melaxantha .
Catharsius molossus is a species of dung beetle belonging to the Scarabaeidae family .
Paramphilius firestonei is a species of loach catfish endemic to Liberia where it is found in the St. Paul , Du and Borlor Rivers .
Ribes tularense is a rare species of currant known as the Sequoia gooseberry or Tulare gooseberry .
Luteimonas aquatica is a species of yellow - pigmented bacteria .
Syngnathus carinatus is a species of the pipefishes , which is endemic of the northern part of the Gulf of California .
Chinshakiangosaurus ( meaning `` Chinshakian lizard '' ) is a genus of dinosaur and probably one of the most basal sauropods known .
Thyrocopa kikaelekea , a species of flightless moth from Hawaii in genus Thyrocopa , was recently discovered by entomologists at University of California , Berkeley and described in a 2008 paper .
Paroncheilus affinis also known as the Bigtooth cardinalfish is a species of marine fish in the Apogonidae family and the only member of its genus .
Pusula radians , the `` radiant button shell''or `` radiating trivia '' , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Triviidae , the false cowries or trivias .
The New Pod Borer ( Adisura marginalis ) is a species of moth of the Noctuidae family .
Xenita keniensis is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Xenita .
Archaeornithoides is a genus of maniraptoriform theropod dinosaur of the Late Cretaceous of Mongolia .
Acampe , abbreviated as Acp in horticultural trade , is a genus of monopodial , epiphytic vandaceous species of orchids , distributed from tropical Asia from India , eastwards to China and southwards to Malaysia , and the Philippines as well as from tropical Africa , Madagascar and islands of the Indian Ocean .
Inermaegocidnus elongatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Inermaegocidnus .
Cayratia acris is a species of plant native to Australia and Papua New Guinea .
Gualosuchus is an extinct genus of proterochampsian archosauriform from the Middle Triassic of Argentina .
Persea nudigemma is a species of plant in the Lauraceae family , commonly known as laurel .
Cercopithecini is a tribe of Old World monkey that includes several monkey species , including the vervet monkeys , talapoins and the guenons , all in Africa .
Amorphoscelis nigriventer is a species of praying mantis found in Côte d'Ivoire , Ghana , and Guinea .
Thaumastochloa is a genus of Australian , Papuasian , and Indonesian plants in the grass family .
Dallia is a genus of mudminnows native to Russia and Alaska .
Dasyvesica nepomuca is a species of snout moth in the genus Dasyvesica .
Trichoaspis julus is a species of mite placed in its own family , Trichoaspididae , in the order Mesostigmata .
Oedopa elegans is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Oedopa of the family Tephritidae .
Pouteria sandwicensis is a species of flowering tree in the sapodilla family , Sapotaceae , that is endemic to the main islands of Hawaii .
Elachistosuchus is an extinct genus of neodiapsid reptile , most likely basal archosauromorph , known from the Late Triassic Arnstadt Formation of Saxony - Anhalt , central Germany .
Microphrys weddelli is a species of crab in the family Majidae .
Parargina is a subtribe of butterflies of the subfamily Satyrinae .
Odontoglossum praestans is a species of orchid native to western South America .
Calystegia affinis is a critically endangered species of climbing or creeping vine in the plant Convolvulaceae family .
Incilius epioticus ( common name : Cerro Utyum toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Periegops is a genus of spiders , the only genus in the family Periegopidae , with three described species .
The family Procellariidae is a group of seabirds that comprises the fulmarine petrels , the gadfly petrels , the prions , and the shearwaters .
Asteraceae or Compositae ( commonly referred to as the aster , daisy , composite , or sunflower family ) is an exceedingly large and widespread family of flowering plants ( Angiospermae ) .
Bdellodes is a genus of mites , including the species Bdellodes lapidaria .
Morchella galilaea is a species of fungus in the family Morchellaceae that was described as new to science in 2012 .
It is possible that the Queensland populations currently included as Endiandra virens between Caboolture and Kin Kin represent a distinct species once named Endiandra lowiana by F. M. Bailey in 1892 .
Lilianae ( Liliiflorae ) is a botanical name , for a superorder ( that is , a rank higher than that of order ) of angiosperms ( flowering plants ) .
Dacryoscyphus is a genus of anamorphic fungi in the Dacrymycetales order .
Canna flaccida is a species of the Canna genus , a member of the family Cannaceae .
Rhynchosia volubilis is a plant species in the genus Rhynchosia .
Channallabes is a genus of airbreathing catfishes found in Africa .
Zea perennis , the perennial teosinte , is a true grass species in the genus Zea and a teosinte .
Laternula elliptica is a species of saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Laternulidae , the lantern shells .
Brachylaimidae is a family of parasitic flukes in the sub - class Digenea .
Vokesimurex mindanaoensis , common name the Mindanao murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
The Balkan Loach ( Cobitis elongata ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cobitidae family .
Hydropsalis is a genus of nightjar in the Caprimulgidae family .
Cyathodes is a genus of shrubs within the heath family .
Orthotylus stratensis is a species of bug from a family of Miridae that is endemic to Greece .
Thaumatodryinus tuukkaraski is a wasp species found in the Teita Hills of Kenya .
Pyrrhocoridae is a family of insects with more than 300 species world - wide .
Pandanus gabonensis is a species of plant in the Pandanaceae family .
Odontophrynus lavillai ( Spanish name : escuericito ) is a species of frog in the Odontophrynidae family .
Carex umbrosa is a species of sedge native to Europe and Asia as far east as Japan .
Plourdosteus is an extinct genus of placoderm , which was relatively widespread in Euramerica during the Givetian to Frasnian ages of the Devonian .
Paracercomonas is a genus of rhizaria .
Rhyssoplax chathamensis is a species of chiton in the family Chitonidae .
The gunnels are a family , Pholidae , of marine fishes in the order Perciformes .
Polystira albida , common name White Giant Turris , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turridae , the turrids .
Macrotylus quadrilineatus is a species of plant bug belonging to the family Miridae , subfamily Phylinae .
Trucheosaurus is an extinct genus of rhytidosteid temnospondyl from the late Permian period of Sydney Basin , New South Wales , Australia .
Micromys erythrotis is a species of rodent in the genus Micromys that is native to Asia .
The ground sharks , order Carcharhiniformes , are the largest order of sharks .
Euryades corethrus is a species of butterfly from the family Papilionidae that is found in Brazil , Paraguay , Uruguay , and Argentina .
Serpulina innocens , formerly known as Serpula innocens ( this is a fungal genus ) and formerly as Treponema innocens is a species of bacteria .
Clepticus is a genus of wrasses native to the Atlantic Ocean .
Conus capitaneus , common name the captain cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Myrmica vandeli is an ant species is found sporadically in across several European countries ( Austria , Bulgaria , the Czech Republic , France , Germany , Great Britain , Poland , Romania , Spain , Sweden , Switzerland , Slovakia , western Ukraine , and the former Yugoslavia ) .
Pleurostylia is a small genus of shrubs in the bittersweet family containing 13 species .
Retusa obtusa , common name the `` Arctic barrel - bubble '' , is a species of very small head - shield sea snail or bubble shell , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Retusidae .
Albertosaurines , or dinosaurs of the subfamily Albertosaurinae , lived in the Late Cretaceous of USA and Canada .
Ancylanthos was a genus of flowering plants in the Rubiaceae family but is no longer recognized .
Beris fuscipes , the short - horned black legionnaire , is a European species of soldier fly .
Chalcides levitoni , commonly called Leviton 's cylindrical skink , is a species of lizard endemic to Saudi Arabia ( Jizan Province ) .
Iridomyrmex alpinus is a species of ant of the genus Iridomyrmex .
Calyptrogenia is a genus of flowering plants in the family Myrtaceae first described as a genus in 1941 .
It contains the single species Aethosia ectrocta , which is found in Haiti .
Trochoidea picardi is or was a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Triplophysa xiangxiensis is a species of stone loach endemic to Yuan River in Hunan , China .
Hemimarginula pumila , the pygmy ermarginula , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Asclepias californica is a species of milkweed known by the common name California milkweed .
Eucalyptus mannifera , commonly known as the Brittle Gum or Broad leaved Manna Gum , is a species of eucalypt native to eastern Australia .
Anabarilius andersoni is a species of cyprinid fish that is endemic to China .
Dichanthelium clandestinum is a species of grass known by the common name deertongue .
Myosurus cupulatus is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family known by the common name Arizona mousetail .
Pelvicachromis is a genus of small ( 5.5 - -12.5 cm or 2.2 - -4.9 in ) , brightly coloured cichlids from tropical West Africa and Central Africa .
Trigonochlamydidae is a family of air - breathing land slugs , terrestrial gastropod molluscs in the clade Eupulmonata ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Syncaris pasadenae was a species of shrimp in the family Atyidae , which is believed to be extinct .
Nannocharax is a genus of distichodontid fishes found in Africa .
Amanita parvipantherina , also known as the Asian Small Panther Amanita , is a species of agaric restricted to Yunnan province in China .
Empicoris seorsus is a species of thread - legged bug endemic to New Zealand .
Cupaniopsis anacardioides , with common names tuckeroo , carrotwood , beach tamarind and green - leaved tamarind , is a species of flowering tree in the soapberry family , Sapindaceae , that is native to eastern and northern Australia .
Rhacophorus prasinatus ( common names : tributary flying frog , green treefrog , emerald green treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family endemic to northern Taiwan .
The genus Coricladus of conifers was originally defined by André Jasper , Fresia Ricardi - Branco , and Margot Guerra - Sommer in 2005 .
Eleutherodactylus abbotti , sometimes known as the Abbott 's robber frog , is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to Hispaniola and found in the Dominican Republic and Haiti .
There are two accepted sub species Alangium salviifolium ( L. f. ) Wangerin which is a tree which has acute or rounded leaves without domatia Alangium salviifolium subsp .
Caecidotea nickajackensis is a species of isopod crustacean in the family Asellidae .
Farlowella knerii is a species of armored catfish endemic to Ecuador where it occurs in the Napo and Pastaza River basins .
Cornutia obovata is a rare species of tree in the mint family , and formerly considered a member of the verbena family .
Alexiidae is a family of beetles , in the suborder Polyphaga .
†Partula turgida was a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Stilbopeziza yerbae .
Merrilliobryum fabronioides is a species of moss in the family Myriniaceae .
Sipha flava is a species of aphid in the family Aphididae .
Crematogaster scutellaris is a species of ants belonging to the family Formicidae subfamily Myrmicinae .
Sarcoscypha occidentalis , commonly known as the stalked scarlet cup or the western scarlet cup , is a species of fungus in the family Sarcoscyphaceae of the Pezizales order .
Barklya is a genus of Australian trees in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Crataegus crus - galli is a species of hawthorn known by the common names cockspur hawthorn and cockspur thorn .
Zhuchengtyrannus ( meaning `` Zhucheng tyrant '' ) is an extinct genus of large carnivorous theropod dinosaur known from the Late Cretaceous period of Shandong Province , China .
Latirus polygonus , common name : short - tailed latirus , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fasciolariidae , the spindle snails , the tulip snails and their allies .
Tomocichla tuba is a species of cichlid found in fast - moving waters on the Atlantic slope of Central America in Nicaragua , Costa Rica and Panama .
Turcutheca is a Tommotian ( Early Cambrian ) genus of mollusc , whose affinities are uncertain , although it bears a certain resemblance to both the hyolithids and the ellesmeroceratids ( early cephalopods ) .
Ivesia baileyi is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name Bailey 's ivesia .
Drimia namibensis ( syn . Rhadamanthus namibensis ) is a species of plant that is endemic to Namibia .
Spathopsis is a genus of fresh - water mussel ; it is a bivalve or clam which is in the Mutelidae family .
Calamagrostis nardifolia is a species of grass native to the southern Andes .
Dakeoceras is a simple cyrtoconic ellesmeroceratid genus of cephalopods in the fossil record .
Arctostaphylos montaraensis is a species of manzanita known by the common name Montara manzanita .
Romagnesiella is an agaric fungal genus that colonizes mineral , calcareous or sandy soils in Europe and North Africa .
The Rhodospirillaceae are a family of Proteobacteria .
Brachyderes lusitanicus , the pine weevil , is a species in the weevil family ( Curculionidae ) .
Marstonia castor , common name the beaver pond marstonia , is a species of very small freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic operculate gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Mirbelieae , commonly known as the bush , golden or egg - and - bacon peas are a legume tribe endemic to Australia .
Trypanosoma congolense is a species of trypanosomes and is the major pathogen responsible for the disease nagana in cattle and other animals including sheep , pigs , goats , horses and camels , dogs , as well as laboratory mice .
Coelognathus flavolineatus , the black copper rat snake or yellow striped snake , is a species of Colubrid snake found in Southeast Asia .
Mahonia incerta is a shrub described as a species in 1901 .
Micrurus fulvius ( Eastern coral snake , common coral snake , American cobra , more ) is a species of venomous elapid snake endemic to the southeastern United States .
Pila occidentalis is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Ampullariidae , the applesnails .
Osornophryne ( plump toads ) is a genus of true toads endemic to the Cordillera Central in Colombia and central Andes in Ecuador .
Paracantha cultaris is a species of tephritid fruit fly found in western North America , as far south as Costa Rica .
Plesiocidaris durandi is an extinct species of sea urchin .
Megadytes giganteus is a species in the genus Megadytes of large diving beetles found in the Caribbean and in South America .
Magilus antiquus , common name the Magilus coral snail , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Bistolida erythraeensis , common name : the Red Sea cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Macrobrachium rosenbergii , also known as the giant river prawn , giant freshwater prawn , Malaysian prawn , freshwater scampi ( especially in India : in West Bengal it is called golda chingdi ) , or cherabin , is a species of freshwater shrimp native to the Indo - Pacific region , northern Australia and Southeast Asia .
Saichania ( Mongolian meaning `` beautiful one '' ) is a genus of herbivorous ankylosaurid dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous period of Mongolia and China .
Drosera praefolia is a perennial tuberous species in the genus Drosera that is endemic to South Australia .
Neoboletus pseudosulphureus is a species of bolete fungus in the family Boletaceae .
Escovopsis is a genus of five formally acknowledged parasitic microfungus species that rely on other fungi to be their hosts .
Cranocephalites is a Middle Jurassic ammonitid genus named by Spath in 1932 and included in the family Cranoceratidae , superfamily Stephanoceratacea .
Durio acutifolius is a species of durian tree in the Bombacaceae family .
Mastotermes electromexicus is an extinct species of termite in the family Mastotermitidae known from a group of Late Oligocene to Early Miocene fossils found in Mexico .
Harttia guianensis is a species of armored catfish endemic to French Guiana where it is found in the Sinnamary and Approuague River basins .
Midongya mirabilis is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Midongya .
Blastoids ( class Blastoidea ) are an extinct type of stemmed echinoderm .
Traquairaspidiformes is an order of extinct heterostracan agnathan fish known from the Silurian and Early Devonian periods .
Scotopteryx luridata , the July belle , is a species of moth in the Geometridae family .
Xenophrys major is a species of toad found in northeastern India , Burma , Thailand , Cambodia , Laos , Vietnam , and southern China .
Tropisternus lateralis is a species of hydrophilid beetle that ranges across much of the Americas .
Aciagrion hisopa , is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Oxymeris crenulata , common name crenulate auger , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae , the auger snails .
Spirostreptidae is a family of millipedes in the order Spirostreptida .
Notogibbula bicarinata , common name `` Cox 's top shell '' , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Trochidae , the top shells .

Theodoxus altenai is a species of freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Neritidae , the nerites .
The Microlophus heterolepis is a species of lava lizard endemic to Chile and Peru .
Scorzoneroides or hawkbits is a genus of plants of dandelion tribe within the daisy family .
Taonius pavo is a species of glass squid found in the Atlantic Ocean .
Callionymus superbus , the proud dragonet or superb dragonet , is a species of dragonet native to the western Pacific Ocean where it occurs down to depths of 25 metres ( 82 ft ) .
Bromus vulgaris is a species of brome grass known by the common name Columbia brome .
Asplenium vespertinum is a species of fern known by the common name western spleenwort .

Cryptocephalus samniticus is a species of cylindrical leaf beetle belonging to the family Chrysomelidae , which is a subfamily Cryptocephalinae .

Pseudoblepharispermum is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , native to East Africa .
The Leafless Dendrobium ( Dendrobium aphyllum ) is a species of orchid .
Calathus bosnicus is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that is can be found in Albania and Bosnia and Herzegovina .
Eucraera magna is a species of Lasiocampidae moth , it is known from Sierra Leone and Eritrea .
Graphium meyeri is a species of butterfly of the family Papilionidae , that is found in Sulawesi .

Chiloglanis lufirae is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it is found in the Lufira River drainage .
Echites is a genus of flowering plants in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1756 .
Karwinskia humboldtiana , commonly known as coyotillo or Humboldt coyotillo , is a species of flowering shrub or small tree in the buckthorn family , Rhamnaceae .

Pisanosaurus ( pron.:``PIE - san - uh - SAWR - us '' ) is an extinct genus of primitive ornithischian dinosaur that lived approximately 228 to 216 million years ago during the latter part of the Triassic Period in what is now South America .

Platyosphys is a genus of basilosaurine basilosaurid from Middle Eocene ( Bartonian ) of the eastern United States , Western Sahara , and Ukraine .
Acarozumia is an Australasian genus of potter wasps .
Monardella crispa is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name crisp monardella .
It is a monotypic genus , containing only Clavomphalia yunnanensis , a Chinese species first described by German mycologist Egon Horak in 1987 .

Kosmoceras jason is an ammonite species from the Callovian ( Middle Jurassic ) , lasting between 154 and 160 Ma .
Yunnanilus nigromaculatus is a species of stone loach endemic to the Dianchi Lake basin ( which includes the small Yangling Lake ) in China , but has apparently been extirpated from Dianchi Lake itself due to heavy pollution .
Arion owenii is a species of small air - breathing land slug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Arionidae , the roundback slugs .

Calamagrostis epigejos , common names wood small - reed or bushgrass , is a species of grass in the Poaceae family which is native to Eurasia and Africa .
