Penicillium gladioli is a species of the genus of Penicillium which occurs on Corm of the plant gladiolus debtis .
The Lecanorales are an order of mostly lichen - forming fungi belonging to the class Lecanoromycetes in the division Ascomycota .
Euspira fusca , common name the dark necklace shell , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Naticidae , the moon snails .
Anabas testudineus , the climbing perch , is a species of fish in the family Anabantidae , the climbing gouramis .
Necrosuchus is an extinct genus of caiman from the Paleocene epoch ( Selandian age , about 60 million years ago ) .
Pectocarya platycarpa is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names broadfruit combseed and wide - toothed pectocarya .
Fritillaria camschatcensis is a species of fritillary native to northeastern Asia and northwestern North America , including northern Oregon , Washington , British Columbia , Alaska , northern Japan , and the Russian Far East ( Amur , Kamchatka , Khabarovsk , Magadan , Primorye , Sakhalin and the Kuril Islands ) .
Pyracantha crenulata , the Nepalese firethorn , Nepal firethorn or Himalayan firethorn , is a species of firethorn .
The Texas horned lizard ( Phrynosoma cornutum ) is one of about 14 North American species of spikey - bodied reptiles called horned lizards .
Xenobolus carnifex is a species of spirobolidan millipede found in South India and Sri Lanka .
Tricarpelema is a genus of monocotyledonous flowering plants in the dayflower family consisting of 8 species .
Haworthia bayeri is a species of the genus Haworthia in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , endemic to the southern Cape Provinces in South Africa .
It was first named by Téo Veiga De Oliveira , Cesar Leandro Schultz , Marina Bento Soares and Carlos Nunes Rodrigues in 2011 and the type species is Candelariodon barberenai .
Tibioploides arcuatus is a spider species found in Scandinavia , Russia and Estonia .
Santanaclupea is an extinct genus of clupeiform fish .
Tricholophia ceylonica is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Tricholophia .
Loricariichthys melanocheilus is a species of catfishes found in the Uruguay River basin .
Oestocephalidae is an extinct family of Late Carboniferous aïstopod lepospondyls .
Manakins of the genus Chiroxiphia have an unusual mating system , based on female mate choice .
Meloe violaceus , the violet oil beetle , is a species of oil beetle belonging to the family Meloidae subfamily Meloinae .
Dendrobranchiata is a suborder of decapod crustaceans , variously called shrimp or prawns .
Clavicoccus erinaceus is an extinct species of mealybug in the family Pseudococcidae .
Clavelinidae is a family of tunicates in the order Enterogona .
Macrochirichthys macrochirus , the long pectoral - fin minnow or giant sword minnow , is a species of cyprinid fish found in rivers and lakes in Southeast Asia ( Vietnam and Thailand to the Greater Sundas ) where it is used as a food fish .
Mordacia is the sole genus of the family Mordaciidae , also known as the Southern Topeyed Lampreys .
Phthinosaurus is an extinct genus of therapsid from the Middle Permian of Russia .
Madagaster is a genus of Madagascan plants in the aster tribe within the daisy family .
Diospyros hillebrandii , is a species of flowering tree in the ebony family , Ebenaceae , that is endemic to the islands of Oʻahu and Kauaʻi in Hawaii .
Ausktribosphenos is an extinct genus of Australosphenida from Early Cretaceous of Australia .
Crenuchus spilurus , the sailfin tetra , is a species belonging to the South American darter family , Crenuchidae .
Pandanus kaida is a monocot species of plant in the Pandanaceae family , known only in cultivation .
Dracorex is a dinosaur genus of the family Pachycephalosauridae , from the Late Cretaceous of North America .
The Scaphiopodidae are a family of endangered American spadefoot toads .
Opisthodon is a small genus of Limnodynastine frogs with only two species .
Cladonia stellaris is an ecologically important species of lichen that forms continuous mats over large areas of the ground in boreal and arctic regions around the circumpolar north .
Euthystira brachyptera , the Small Gold Grasshopper , is a species of grasshopper belonging to the family Acrididae .
Lixus angustatus is a species of weevil found in Europe ( including the Iberian Peninsula ) and the Mediterranean Basin .
Lathyrus sylvestris , the flat pea or narrow - leaved everlasting - pea , is a plant species of the genus Lathyrus .
Coreopsis integrifolia ( fringleaf tickseed or mouse - ear tickseed ) is a North American plant species of the sunflower family .
Hypoctonus formosus is a species of arachnids belonging to the family Thelyphonidae .
Prostyliferidae is an extinct family of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Sorbeoconcha .
Chiococceae is a tribe of flowering plants in the Rubiaceae family and contains about 233 species in 27 genera .
Conus amphiurgus , common name the amphiurgus cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Heraldia nocturna , the Upside - down pipefish , is a species of pipefish endemic to the coast of southern Australia where it is found in rocky reefs at depths of from 2 to 15 metres ( 6.6 to 49.2 ft ) .
Pseudomyagrus waterhousei is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudomyagrus .
The Abyssinian longclaw ( Macronyx flavicollis ) is a species of bird in the Motacillidae family .
In 1824 Henri Marie Ducrotay de Blainville named these two groups Gymnosomata and Thecosomata and named the combining order Aporobranchia instead of Pteropoda .
Melica longiflora is a grass species in the Poaceae family that is endemic to Chile where it can be found from Coquimbo to Talca .
Lockhartia acuta is a species of orchid native to Costa Rica , Panama , Venezuela , Colombia and Trinidad .
Deschampsia flexuosa , commonly known as wavy Hair - grass , is a species of bunchgrass in the grass family widely distributed in Eurasia , Africa , South America , and North America .
Micavibrio aeruginosavorus is a species of epibiotic predatory bacteria .
Mimulus purpureus is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name little purple monkeyflower .
Centaurea virgata is a species of Centaurea .
Cloacaspis is an extinct genus of Olenid Ptychopariid trilobite .
Hoplobatrachus crassus , also called Jerdon 's bullfrog , Jerdon 's bull frog is a species of frog found widely distributed on the plains of India , Bangladesh , Nepal and Sri Lanka .
Sophora raivavaeensis is a species of flowering plant in the pea family , Fabaceae , that is endemic to French Polynesia .
Microrca bistrialis is a species of snout moth in the genus Microrca .
The genus is monotypic , consisting of the species Paucidentomys vermidax .
The Eudendriidae are a taxonomic family of hydroids ( Hydrozoa ) .
Sium latifolium is a species of flowering plant in the family Apiaceae known by the common names great water - parsnip , greater water - parsnip , and wideleaf waterparsnip .
Spirostachys is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1850 .
Labyrinthodontia ( Greek , `` maze - toothed '' ) is an extinct amphibian subclass , which constituted some of the dominant animals of late Paleozoic and early Mesozoic eras ( about 390 to 150 million years ago ) .
Daceton boltoni is a Neotropical species of arboreal ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Clathrina cylindractina is a species of sponge in the genus Clathrina from Brazil .
Taveirosaurus ( tah - VAY - roo - SAWR - us ) ( meaning `` Taveiro lizard '' ) is a genus of ornithischian dinosaur that lived in Europe during the Late Cretaceous .
Dianopachysaurus is an extinct genus of pachypleurosaur known from the lower Middle Triassic ( Anisian age ) of Yunnan Province , southwestern China .
The Bixaceae are a family of dicotyledonous plants commonly called the achiote family .
Neacomys guianae , also known as the Guianan neacomys or Guiana bristly mouse , is a nocturnal rodent species from South America .
Collinsia bartsiifolia is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name white blue - eyed Mary .
Herichthys carpintis , the lowland cichlid , pearlscale cichlid or green Texas cichlid , is a species of cichlid endemic to Mexico where it occurs in the Pánuco River drainage and the Soto La Marina River .
Euceraphis punctipennis , the downy birch aphid or European birch aphid , is a species of aphid in the order Hemiptera .
Hebeloma vinosophyllum is a toxic species of agaric fungus in the family Hymenogastraceae .
Cephalopholis urodeta , known commonly as the Flagtail Grouper or also V - tail Grouper , is a species of marine fish in the family Serranidae .
Heliamphora folliculata ( Latin : folliculatus = having follicles ) is a species of Marsh Pitcher Plant endemic to the Aparaman group of tepuis in Venezuela .
Moorea producens is a species of filamentous cyanobacteria in the genus Moorea , including tropical marine strains formerly classified as Lyngbya majuscula due to morphological resemblance but separated based on genetic evidence .
Apaturina erminea , common name Turquoise Emperor , is a species of butterflies in the family Nymphalidae , subfamily Apaturinae .
The Raffia palms ( Raphia ) are a genus of about twenty species of palms native to tropical regions of Africa , and especially Madagascar , with one species ( R. taedigera ) also occurring in Central and South America .
Ecnomiohyla tuberculosa ( common name : Canelos treefrog ) is a species of frog in the family Hylidae .
Duplicaria duplicata , common name the duplicate auger , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae , the auger snails .
Syncordulia serendipator , the rustic presba , is a species of dragonfly in the family Corduliidae .
Cavaticovelia is a monotypic genus of insects in the order Hemiptera , the true bugs , containing the single species Cavaticovelia aaa .
Clavus canalicularis , common name the ear turrid , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Drilliidae .
Troidini is a tribe of swallowtail butterflies that consists of some 135 species in 12 genera .
Picea maximowiczii , the Japanese bush spruce , is a species of conifer in the pine family .
Bystrowiella is an extinct genus of bystrowianid reptiliomorph from upper Middle Triassic ( Ladinian age ) deposits of Kupferzell and Vellberg , northern Baden - Württemberg , Germany .
Streptomyces atratus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in Shimoneda in Japan .
Trimetopon barbouri ( Barbour 's tropical ground snake ) is a species of snake from the Colubridae family .
Erythropodium caribaeorum ( commonly known as the encrusting gorgonian or encrusting polyps ) is a species of sessile marine animal in the Erythropodium genus .
Pectocarya penicillata is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names sleeping combseed , shortleaf combseed , winged combseed and northern pectocarya .
Oxymeris maculata , common name the Crenulate Auger , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae , the auger snails .
Tremella fuciformis is a species of fungus ; it produces white , frond - like , gelatinous basidiocarps ( fruiting bodies ) .
Cicadetta montana ( also New Forest Cicada ) is a species of Cicadetta found throughout Europe and in parts of Asia .
Opuntia monacantha , commonly known as drooping prickly pear , cochineal prickly pear , or Barbary fig , is a species of plant in the Cactaceae family .
Rhododendron fastigiatum is a dwarf lepidote rhododendron species with purple flowers native to Yunnan , China .
The Neogoveidae are a family of harvestmen with twelve described species in five genera .
Hieracium lactucella ( also called European hawkweed ) is a species of perennial plant from Asteraceae family that can be found in Europe , New York ( United States ) and Nova Scotia ( Canada ) .
The Common Eupselia Moth , Eupselia carpocapsella , is a species of moth of the Oecophoridae family .
Phegopteris is a genus of ferns known collectively as the beech ferns .
Osmorhiza occidentalis is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name western sweet cicely or western sweetroot .
Allium nigrum , common name black garlic , broad - leaved leek , or broadleaf garlic , is a Middle Eastern species of wild onion .
Pseudagrion sublacteum or cherry - eye sprite is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Picea mariana ( black spruce ) is a North American species of spruce tree in the pine family .
Schistomerus is an extinct genus of predaceous diving beetle that is known from one species , Schistomerus californense , which inhabited Lake Barstow during the middle Miocene .
Scutellaria alpina , common name Alpine skullcap , is a species of flowering plant in the mint family , Lamiaceae .
Mamenchisaurus ( /mɑːˈmʌntʃiˈsɔːrəs/ mah - MUN - chi - SAWR - əs , or spelling pronunciation /məˌmɛntʃiˈsɔːrəs/ ) is a sauropod dinosaur genus including several species , known for their remarkably long necks which made up half the total body length .
Leptolaena delphinensis is a species of flowering plant in the Sarcolaenaceae family .
Modulatrix is a genus of bird endemic to the mountains of south eastern Africa .
Zygoballus is a genus of jumping spiders found in North and South America .
The Congo golden mole ( Calcochloris leucorhinus ) is a species of mammal in the family Chrysochloridae .
Geranium psilostemon , commonly called Armenian cranesbill , is a species of hardy flowering herbaceous perennial plant in the genus Geranium , Geraniaceae family .
Csiromedusa medeopolis is a species of jellyfish described in 2010 .
Siphonorhis is a genus of nightjars , known as the Caribbean pauraques , in the family Caprimulgidae .
Dicranum is a genus of mosses , also called Wind - Blown Mosses or Fork Mosses .
Callitrichales Dumort ( 1829 ) is an order of flowering plants .
Cearadactylus is a genus of large Early Cretaceous ( Albian ) pterosaurs from South America .
Pseudalsophis is a genus of snakes in the Colubridae family .
Sepidium is a genus of beetles of the family Tenebrionidae .
Sericostomatoidea is a superfamily in the order Trichoptera , the caddisflies .
Slow lorises are a group of several species of nocturnal strepsirrhine primates which make up the genus Nycticebus .
Striatura milium , common name the fine - ribbed striate snail , is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Gastrodontidae .
The yellow latan palm ( Latania verschaffeltii ) is a species of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family .
The family Pomatiidae is a taxonomic family of small operculate land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusks that can be found over the warmer parts of the Old World .
Drosera lanata was first formally described by Katsuhiko Kondo in 1984 when he authored three new species of the D. petiolaris complex .
Eucamerotus ( meaning `` well - chambered '' in reference to the hollows of the vertebrae ) was a genus of sauropod dinosaur from the Barremian - age Lower Cretaceous Wessex Formation ( Wealden ) of the Isle of Wight , England .
Mesopsocus duboscqui is a species of Psocoptera from Mesopsocidae family that can be found in Cyprus , France , Greece , Italy , and Spain .
Hoplocorypha distinguenda is a species of praying mantis found in Nigeria .
Neoperla darlingi is a species of insect in the family Perlidae .
Lucihormetica verrucosa is a species of giant cockroach in the family Blaberidae , commonly known as the warty glowspot cockroach .
Mitrastemon is a genus of two widely disjunct species of parasitic plants .
Musa basjoo , known variously as Japanese Banana , Japanese Fibre Banana or Hardy Banana , is a species belonging to the genus Musa .
Ceroglossus chilensis , the Chilean Magnificent Beetle , is a species of beetles of the Carabidae family .
Systomus clavatus , the Stedman barb , is a species of cyprinid fish native to India and Bangladesh in the Ganges River basin where it occurs in foothill streams and rivers .
Styrax obassia is a species of flowering plant in the Styracaceae family .
Chelonistele is a genus of the orchid family consisting of 13 currently accepted species .
The Sonora mud turtle ( Kinosternon sonoriense ) is a species of turtle in the Kinosternidae family .
Allium tribracteatum , known by the common name Threebract onion , is a California species of wild onion .
The Chinese grey shrike ( Lanius sphenocercus ) is a species of bird in the Laniidae family .
Hedychium gardnerianum is the most widely cultivated Hedychium species as an ornamental plant in gardens and parks .
Pardachirus is a genus of soles mainly native to coastal water in the Indo - Pacific .
Sagittiferidae is a family of acoelomorph worms .
Bulbothrix cinerea is a species of lichenized fungi within the family Parmeliaceae .
Cochlespira is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Cochlespiridae .
Ananas erectifolius is a species of plant closely related to the pineapple .
Limonium is a genus of 120 flower species .
Lobaunia danubialis is a species of minute freshwater spring snails , aquatic gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
Toxotes kimberleyensis is a species of archerfish found in the Kimberley region of Western Australia .
Latrodectus pallidus is a species of spider commonly found throughout North Africa , the Middle East , and central Asia .
Drimia indica is a species of flowering plant found from South Asia to South Africa .
Chenops is an extinct genus of notostracan which existed in the Yixian Formation , Inner Mongolia , and the Jehol fauna of China during the early Cretaceous period ( Barremian age ) .
Polyrhachis is a genus of formicine ants found in the Old World with a large number of species ( over 600 ) .
Psychrobacter luti is a species of bacterium first isolated from Antarctic environments .
Tomopterna ( common names : sand frogs , burrowing frogs , Old World bullfrogs ) is a genus of frogs from sub - Saharan Africa .
Cidaris cidaris is a species of sea urchin commonly known as the long - spine slate pen sea urchin .
Leptacanthichthys gracilispinis , the Plainchin dreamarm , is a species of dreamer found in the northern oceans at depths of around 1,000 metres ( 3,300 ft ) occasionally as deep as 2,000 metres ( 6,600 ft ) .
Senna gaudichaudii , known as Gaudichaud 's senna and as heuhiuhi in Hawaiian , is a species of flowering plant in the legume family , Fabaceae , that is endemic to Queensland , Australia and the Pacific Islands .
Coryphantha ( from Greek , `` flowering on the top '' ) , or beehive cactus , is a genus of small to middle - sized , globose or columnar cacti .
Rhododendron strigillosum ( 芒刺杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to Sichuan and Yunnan in China , where it grows at altitudes of 1600 - -3800 meters .
Riodina lysippus is a species of Neotropical metalmark butterfly .
Lispocephala is a very large genus of true flies of the family Muscidae .
Acanthemblemaria crockeri , the Browncheek blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in coral reefs in the Gulf of California , in the eastern central Pacific ocean .
Centrolene daidaleum ( common name : Alban Cochran frog ) is a species of frog in the Centrolenidae family .
Verbascum speciosum is a species of flowering plant in the figwort family known by the common name Hungarian mullein or showy mullein .
Cycas chamaoensis is named after the only known habitat of this species , on and near Khao Chamao mountain in Khao Chamao District , Thailand .
Cyathea albidosquamata is a species of tree fern native to the Maluku Islands and New Guinea , where it grows in rain forest and montane forest at an altitude of 1200 - -1500 m. The trunk is erect and about 2 m tall .
Chaptalia texana , common name Silverpuff , is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Anarnatula subflavida is a species of snout moth in the genus Anarnatula .
Epixanthops casellatoi is a species of crabs in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Epixanthops .
Brasiliorchis schunkeana ( syn . Maxillaria schunkeana ) is a species of orchid .
Horsfield 's tarsier ( Cephalopachus bancanus ) , also known as the western tarsier , is the only species of tarsier in the genus Cephalopachus .
Euaugaptilus hyperboreus is a species of deep - water copepod .
Diaea evanida ( also called the Pink Flower Spider ) is a species of arachnid in the Thomisidae family .
Azorella fuegiana is a species of Azorella flowering plant , found in Chile .
Polypodium hydriforme is a species of parasite attacking the eggs of sturgeon and similar fishes ( Acipenseridae and Polyodontidae ) .
Zungaro is a genus of long - whiskered catfishes native to South America , with two currently recognized species :
Ambrosia cordifolia , called the Tucson bur ragweed , is a North American species of plant in the sunflower family .
The Pyrenean brook salamander or Pyrenean newt ( Catalan : tritó pirinenc ; Basque : uhandre piriniarra ; Spanish : tritón pirenaico ) , Calotriton asper , is a largely aquatic species of salamander in the family Salamandridae .
Lewisia kelloggii is a species of flowering plant in the purslane family known by the common name Kellogg 's lewisia .
Iris ludwigii , with the common name Ludwig Iris , is a species in the genus Iris .
Neosabellaria cementarium is a species of marine tube worm in the family Sabellariidae , perhaps better known by its previous name , Sabellaria cementarium .
Alexeyisaurus is an extinct genus of elasmosaurid plesiosaur known from the upper Triassic ( lower - middle Norian age ) of Wilczek Formation , Wilczek Land , of Franz Josef Land , Russia .
Symphysanodon , also known as the slopefishes is a genus of small marine fishes .
Coincya richeri is a plant species in the Brassicaceae ( mustard family ) .
Phalaenopsis stuartiana is a species of orchid endemic to the island of Mindanao , in the Philippines .
Euryops pectinatus is a species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae , native to South Africa .
Clusia major , the autograph tree , copey , balsam apple , pitch - apple , and Scotch attorney , is a tropical and sub - tropical plant species in the genus Clusia .
Luciobarbus xanthopterus is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to the Tigris - Euphrates River System .
Palacanthilhiopsis vervierii is a species of very small or minute freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Moitessieriidae .
Drymaplaneta heydeniana is a species of cockroach .
Lestes viridulus is a damselfly species in the family Lestidae , the spreadwings .
Cavipalpia argentilavella is a species of snout moth in the genus Cavipalpia .
It consists of only one species Plexiphleps stellifera , which is found in Asia , from India to Taiwan .
Atriplex halimus ( known also by its common names : Mediterranean saltbush , Sea orache , Shrubby orache , Silvery orache ) is a species of fodder shrub in the Amaranthaceae family , which is native to Europe and Northern Africa , including the Sahara in Morocco .
Cistus crispus is a shrubby species of flowering plant in the family Cistaceae , with pink to purple flowers , native to south - western Europe and western north Africa .
Flagellaria is the sole genus in the flowering plant family Flagellariaceae .
It contains the single species Abnormipterus abnormis .
It was first named by Marco Aurélio G. França , Jorge Ferigolo and Max C. Langer in 2011 and the type species is Decuriasuchus quartacolonia .
Megalodoras guayoensis is a species of thorny catfish endemic to Venezuela where it occurs in the Orinoco River basin .
Lupinus mutabilis is a species of lupin grown in the Andes , mainly for its edible bean .
Synchlora aerata , the wavy - lined emerald moth or camouflaged looper , is a species of moth of the Geometridae family .
Achatina albopicta , common name the African land snail , is a species of large air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Achatinidae .
Guaibasaurus is an extinct genus of basal dinosaur known from the Triassic of Rio Grande do Sul , southern Brazil .
Actinella effugiens is a species of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Hygromiidae , the hariy snails and their allies .
Dorcus parallelipipedus , the lesser stag beetle , is a species of stag beetle found in Europe .
Juncus rugulosus is a species of rush known by the common name wrinkled rush .
Melastoma polyanthum is a species of shrubs , of the plant family Melastomataceae .
Blenniella periophthalmus is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian oceans .
Carphodactylus laevis is a species , in a monotypic genus , of Australian gecko , also known as the Chameleon Gecko .
The Processidae are a family of shrimp , comprising 65 species in five genera , and the only family in the superfamily Processoidea .
Belostomatidae is a family of freshwater hemipteran insects known as giant water bugs or colloquially as toe - biters , Indian toe - biters , electric - light bugs , alligator ticks , or fleas ( in Florida ) .
Cavalcantia is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae , endemic to the State of Pará in Brazil .
Depressipoma is a genus of small sea snails with calcareous opercula , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Colloniidae .
Microcorys is a genus of flowering plants in the family Lamiaceae , first described in 1810 .
The Phasmatodea ( also known as Phasmida or Phasmatoptera ) are an order of insects , whose members are variously known as stick insects ( in Europe and Australasia ) , stick - bugs or walking sticks ( in the United States and Canada ) , phasmids , ghost insects and leaf insects ( generally the family Phylliidae ) .
Titanoptera is an extinct order of insects from the Triassic period .
Callotillus is a beetle genus in the family Cleridae , the checkered beetles .
Planocephalosaurus is an extinct genus of diapsid reptile belonging to the Order Sphenodontia .
Tridacninae , common name , the giant clams , is a taxonomic subfamily of very large saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the family Cardiidae , the cockles .
Phreatia is a genus of about 150 species of orchids , distributed in India , Southeast Asia , Indonesia , New Guinea , Australia , and the Pacific islands .
Boykinia aconitifolia , also known as Brook Saxifrage and Allegheny brookfoam , is a species of vascular plant in the genus Boykinia .
Jadera haematoloma , the red - shouldered bug , goldenrain - tree bug or soapberry bug is a species of true bug that lives throughout the United States and south to northern South America .
Walker 's tree iguana , Liolaemus walkeri , is a species of lizard in the Iguanidae family .
Mahonia fordii is a species of shrub in the Berberidaceae described as a species in 1913 .
Hoplocorypha lacualis is a species of praying mantis found in Somalia , Tanzania and the Congo River region .
Potentilla norvegica is a species of cinquefoil known by the common names rough cinquefoil , ternate - leaved cinquefoil , and Norwegian cinquefoil .
Calamagrostis koelerioides , fire reedgrass , is a bunch grass species in the Poaceae family .
Sturisoma festivum is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela where it is found in the Lake Maracaibo basin .
Cyclocheilichthys furcatus is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Cyclocheilichthys found in Mekong .
Protungulatum donnae is the type species for the Protungulatum genus , an extinct early form of eutherian mammal .
Melaka virus ( MELV ) is a novel bat - borne virus of the Pteropine orthoreovirus species .
Iris chrysographes , commonly known as the Black Iris , is a plant species that belongs to the genus Iris .
Panthea is a genus of the owlet moth family , Noctuidae .
Psammagrostis is a genus of plants in the grass family .
Polemon gracilis , or the graceful snake - eater , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the family Atractaspididae .
Camptotheca ( happy tree , cancer tree , or tree of life ) is a genus of medium - sized deciduous trees growing to 20 metres ( 66 ft ) tall , native to southern China and Tibet .
Veronica triphyllos is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name finger speedwell , or fingered speedwell .
Lycopus virginicus is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by many common names , including Virginia water horehound , American water hoarhound , sweet bugleweed , water bugle , carpenter 's herb , green archangel , purple archangel , Paul 's betony , woodbetony , wolf foot , and Egyptian 's herb .
Neurosymploca ? oligocenica is an extinct species of moth in the family Zygaenidae , and possibly in the modern genus Neurosymploca .
Jujubinus exasperatus , the Rough Top Shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Pseudaneitea aspera is a species of air - breathing land slug , a terrestrial gastropod mollusc in the family Athoracophoridae , the leaf - veined slugs .
Dorymyrmex amazonicus is a Neotropical species of ant in the subfamily Dolichoderinae .
Vexillum cancellarioides , common name the Cancellaria Mitre , is a species of small sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Costellariidae , the ribbed miters .
Ribes menziesii , the canyon gooseberry , is a species of currant found only in California and Oregon .
Eriogonum lobbii is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Lobb 's buckwheat .
Argania is a genus of flowering plants containing the sole species Argania spinosa , known as argan , a tree endemic to the calcareous semidesert Sous valley of southwestern Morocco and to the Algerian region of Tindouf in the western Mediterranean region .
Aphrissa is a genus of butterflies in the family Pieridae found in Central America and South America .
The Hypoptychidae , the sand - eels , are a small family of gasterosteiform fishes native to the northwestern Pacific Ocean .
Pneumophionyssus aristoterisi is a species of mite placed in its own family , Pneumophionyssidae , in the order Mesostigmata .
Crocus nudiflorus is a species of flowering plant in the genus Crocus of the family Iridaceae , found from southwestern France to Spain .
Gnamptogenys triangularis is a Neotropical species of ants in the subfamily Ectatomminae .
Ophioglossaceae , the adder's - tongue family , is a family of ferns , currently thought to be most closely related to Psilotaceae , the two together comprising the class Psilotopsida as the sibling group to the rest of the ferns .
Striatheca lineata is a species of beetles in the genus Striatheca of the family Anobiidae .
Franciscodoras marmoratus is the only species in the genus Franciscodoras of the catfish ( order Siluriformes ) family Doradidae .
Rhaphidura lowii is a species of plant in the Rubiaceae family , the sole species in the monotypic genus Rhaphidura .
Australonycteris is an extinct and monotypic genus of microchiropteran bat with the single species Australonycteris clarkae .
Stagmomantis gracilipes , common name Arizona tan mantis , is a species of praying mantis in genus Stagmomantis .
Triglops is a genus of sculpins .
Afroneta longipalpis is a species of sheet weaver found in Reunion .
Thalassiosira weissflogii is a species of centric diatom , a unicellular microalga .
Arthroleptis xenodactylus ( common names : Amani screeching frog , eastern squeaker ) is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family .
Cryptocentrus also known as Watchman gobies , and one of the genera known as shrimp gobies or prawn gobies , is a genus of gobies native to tropical marine waters of the Indian and Pacific oceans .
Helix lutescens is species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicidae , the true snails .
Asperula cynanchica ( squinancywort or squincywort ) is a species of flowering plant in the Rubiaceae family .
Lupinus angustifolius is a species of lupin known by many common names , including narrowleaf lupin , narrow - leaved lupin and blue lupin .
Enhydrocyon is an extinct genus of bone crushing dog which inhabited North America exclusively during the Oligocene living from around 28.7 - -22.0 Ma ( AEO ) and existed for approximately 6.7 million years .
Lichenostomus is a genus of honeyeaters endemic to Australia .
Rhabdosargus holubi is a species of fish in the seabream family , Sparidae .
Conus tiaratus , common name the tiara cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Astrangia solitaria , the dwarf cup coral or southern cup coral , is a species of stony coral in the family Rhizangiidae .
Mycena olida , commonly known as the rancid bonnet , is a species of mushroom in the Mycenaceae family .
Proteopsis is a genus of flowering plants in the evil tribe within the sunflower family .
Allium desertorum is a species of onion found in Israel , Jordan , Palestine , and Egypt ( including Sinai ) .
Nebria lituyae is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to the US state of Alaska .
Migorybia miranda is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Migorybia .
Harpesaurus is a genus of agamid lizard from forests in Java , Sumatra , Borneo and nearby smaller islands .
Bergiaria platana is a species of long - whiskered catfish endemic to Argentina where it occurs in the Paraná River basin .
The Coiba Island howler ( Alouatta coibensis ) is a species of howler monkey , a type of New World monkey , endemic to Panama .
Stewartia ovata , sometimes spelled Stuartia ovata , known commonly as mountain camellia , is a species of Stewartia native to low to mid - elevations in the southern Appalachian Mountains and nearby regions from Mississippi to Virginia .
Ixodes neuquenensis is a species of tick that lives on the monito del monte ( Dromiciops gliroides ) , a nocturnal mammal that lives in the northern temperate forests of southern South America .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Asterodothis solaris .
Ficus ficus or the paper fig shell is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ficidae , the fig shells .
Melica eligulata is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that is endemic to western part of Asia .
Valvata sincera , common name the mossy valvata is a species of small freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Valvatidae , the valve snails .
Mystus gulio , the Long Whiskers Catfish , is a species of catfish of the family Bagridae .
Brassica oleracea is the species of plant that includes many common foods as cultivars , including cabbage , broccoli , cauliflower , kale , Brussels sprouts , collard greens , savoy , kohlrabi and kai - lan .
Falcataria moluccana , commonly known as the Moluccan albizia , is a species of fast - growing tree in the legume family , Fabaceae .
The Crocodylidae family of crocodylians includes the true crocodiles which are the members of the subfamily Crocodylinae and the Tomistoma genus .
Tribonyx is a small genus , containing two species of birds in the rail family , that is sometimes lumped with the moorhens in Gallinula .
Amblydoras nauticus is a species of thorny catfish endemic to Peru where it is found in the upper Amazon basin .
This species was originally described in 1819 , and named Capillaria plica .
Nudiantennarius subteres , the Deep - water frogfish , is a species of frogfish found in the Pacific Ocean around the Philippines and Indonesia .
Synodontis centralis is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it occurs in the middle Congo Basin .
Morchella pragensis , commonly known as the Prague morel , is a species of ascomycete fungus in the family Morchellaceae .
Polypedates cruciger ( commonly known as the Sri Lanka whipping frog or common hour - glass tree - frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family endemic to Sri Lanka .
Grindelia camporum is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names Great Valley gumplant and Great Valley gumweed .
The Congo logsucker ( Garra congoensis ) is a small species of ray - finned fish in the genus Garra .
The cat gecko , Aeluroscalabotes felinus , is a species of gecko found in Indonesia , Malaysia , Singapore , Cambodia and Thailand .
Doto affinis is a species of sea slug , a Dendronotid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Dotidae .
Cattleya mossiae ( literally `` Moss ' Cattley 's '' ) , commonly known as easter orchid , is a species of labiate Cattleya orchid .
Orfelia fultoni is the only bioluminescent species of fly found in North America .
Huechys sanguinea , commonly known as the black and scarlet cicada , is a species of cicada belonging to the family Cicadidae .
The genus Soldanella , commonly known in English as snowbell , includes about 15 species of flowering plants native to European mountains , from the Pyrenees , the Apennines , the Alps , the Carpathians and the Balkans .
Colubrina californica is a species of shrub in the buckthorn family known by the common name Las Animas Nakedwood .
Agrostis thurberiana is a species of grass that is native to northwest and southwest United States and Canada .
Pimephales , commonly known as the bluntnose minnows ( a term used locally to refer to Pimephales notatus specifically ) , is a genus of cyprinid fish found in North America .
Numidotheriidae is an extinct family of primitive proboscidean that lived from the late Paleocene to the early Eocene periods of North Africa .
The Choristidae are a small ( only eight species in three genera ) family of scorpionflies known only from Australia .
The family Calcitronidae is an extinct group of arachnids .
Antennaria racemosa is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name racemose pussytoes .
Labidochromis heterodon is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known to occur around Boadzulu Island .
Hemandradenia chevalieri is a species of plant in the Connaraceae family .
Roystonea maisiana is a species of palm which is endemic to the Maisí region of Guantánamo Province in eastern Cuba .
Lindmania aurea is a plant species in the genus Lindmania .
Sclerocactus ( `` hard cactus '' , from Greek ; refers to the hard , dry fruit ) is a genus of cacti .
Dehalobacter restrictus is a species of bacteria in the phylum Firmicutes .
Turraeanthus africana is a species of plant in the Meliaceae ( Mahogany ) family .
Pediomelum castoreum is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common names beaver Indian breadroot and beaver dam breadroot .
Corylopsis pauciflora ( buttercup witch hazel , winter hazel ) is a species of flowering plant in the genus Corylopsis of the family Hamamelidaceae , native to Taiwan and Japan .
Carabus lineatus lateralis is a subspecies of green - coloured beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in Portugal and Spain .
Amaranthus graecizans , the Mediterranean amaranth or short - tepalled pigweed , is an African species in the botanical family Amaranthaceae .
Kingdonia uniflora is a species of perennial herbs native to China .
Herpesviridae is a large family of DNA viruses that cause diseases in animals , including humans .
Gastromyzon farragus is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Gastromyzon .
Virgibacillus soli is a species of Gram - positive bacteria .
Rhamnus crocea , the spiny redberry , is a species of buckthorn .
The Romaleidae or lubber grasshoppers are a family of grasshoppers .
Attenborosaurus is an extinct genus of pliosaurid from the Early Jurassic of Dorset , England .
Oleria is a genus of clearwing ( ithomiine ) butterflies , named by Hübner in 1816 .
Cordia alliodora is a species of flowering tree in the borage family , Boraginaceae , that is native to the American tropics .
Cuniculus hernandezi is a species of paca that is endemic to the Central Andes in Colombia .
Lycaste , abbreviated as Lyc in horticultural trade , is a genus of orchids that contains about 30 species with egg - shaped pseudobulbs and thin , plicate ( pleated ) leaves .
Megacephala spenceri is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Sloane in 1897 , and is native to Australia .
Litokoala is an extinct genus of marsupials , and along with Nimiokoala , is closely related to the modern koala .
Chaenopsis resh is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in coral reefs around Venezuela and Colombia , in the western central Atlantic Ocean .
Hypolimnas anomala , the Malayan Eggfly or Crow Eggfly ( Chinese : 畸紋紫斑蛺蝶 ) is a species of eggfly .
Menegazzia aeneofusca is a species of lichen from South America , New Zealand , and Australia .
Macromphalina is a genus of very small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Vanikoridae .
Myrcianthes oreophila is a species of tree in the Myrtaceae family .
Falsamblymora tidorensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Falsamblymora .
Trichovelleda rufula is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichovelleda .
Procambarus morrisi ( the `` Putnam County cave crayfish '' ) is a species of crayfish in the family Cambaridae .
Pleiospilos bolusii ( mimicry plant ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Aizoaceae , native to the Eastern Cape of South Africa , where it grows at an altitude of 750 - -1,100 m ( 2,461 - -3,609 ft ) .
Tapinella atrotomentosa , commonly known as the velvet roll - rim or velvet - footed pax , is a species of fungus in the family Tapinellaceae .
Orthotylus calichi is a species of bug from a family of Miridae that is endemic to Sardinia .
Helminthosphaeria is a genus of fungi in the family Helminthosphaeriaceae ( Ascomycota ) .
Neothauma tanganyicense is a species of freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusc in the family Viviparidae .
Sinopoda is a genus of huntsman spiders found in Asia .
Lithoxus jantjae is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela where it occurs in the Ventuari River above the Tencua Falls .
Hymenoxys bigelovii is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Bigelow 's rubberweed .
Heriades parvula is a species of leaf - cutting bee in the genus Heriades , of the family Megachilidae .
Acanthostigma septoconstrictum is a species of fungus in the Tubeufiaceae family of fungi .
Triuridaceae is a family of tropical and subtropical flowering plants , including members which lack chlorophyll and are mycotrophic ( obtain food by digesting intracellular fungi ) .
The Peruvian vesper mouse ( Calomys sorellus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Ameles kervillei is a species of praying mantis that lives in Syria .
Osmeroides is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish from the Cretaceous .
Sphenodesme is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae family , first described in 1820 .
Colchicum cupani is a widespread species , known as the Mediterranean Meadow Saffron , which grows around much of the central Mediterranean Basin , reported from France , Sardinia , Italy , Albania , Greece , Montenegro , Croatia , Sicily , Algeria , Malta and Tunisia .
Senilia is a genus of edible saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the family Arcidae , the ark shells .
Morchella septentrionalis species of fungus in the Morchellaceae family native North America .
Aetheliparis rossi is a species of snailfish only known from the mesopelagic zone in the North Atlantic off Cape Hatteras , North Carolina .
Eryngium aquaticum is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name rattlesnakemaster , marsh rattlesnake master , corn - snakeroot , bitter snakeroot , and marsh eryngo .
The Lecythidaceae comprise a family of about 20 genera and 250 - 300 species of woody plants native to tropical South America and Madagascar .
Catocala cara , the darling underwing , is an Erebidae species .
Scolymia , commonly called Scoly coral , is a genus of large polyp stony corals .
Dinophyceae is a class of dinoflagellates .
Silene grayi is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name Gray 's catchfly .
Neduba extincta , commonly known as the Antioch Dunes shieldback katydid , is an extinct species of katydid ( family Tettigoniidae ) that was endemic to California , United States .
It is a highland plant growing at elevations of 1100 - -1635 m. Nepenthes micramphora is closely allied to N. abgracilis and N. cid , both also from Mindanao , and together these species comprise the informal `` N. micramphora group '' .
Cochlostoma achaicum is a species of small land snail with an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusc in the family Cochlostomatidae .
Ornithocephalus ciliatus is a species of orchid found from Trinidad , the Guianas , Venezuela , Ecuador , Peru and Brazil .
Fromia ghardaqana , common name Ghardaqa sea star , is a species of marine starfish in the family Goniasteridae .
Mauritia scurra , common name the Jester Cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Moodnopsis inornatella is a species of snout moth in the genus Moodnopsis .
Menegazzia subbullata is a species of lichen found in Australia and South America .
Prodeinodon ( meaning `` Before Deinodon '' ) is a dubious genus of theropod dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous ( Barremian to Aptian stages ) of China and Mongolia .
Largidae is a family of insects within the order Hemiptera .
Senecio scorzonella , known by the common name Sierra ragwort , is a species of the genus Senecio and family Asteraceae which is native to California and Nevada .
Cerapachys typhlus is a species of reddish brown army ant found in the Sinharaja Rain Forest , Sri Lanka .
The Darien harvest mouse ( Reithrodontomys darienensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Pliopholygidae is an extinct family of operculate freshwater snails , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the informal group Architaenioglossa .
Widdringtonia wallichii previously Widdringtonia cedarbergensis ( Clanwilliam Cedar or Clanwilliam Cypress ) is a species of Widdringtonia native to South Africa , where it is endemic to the Cederberg Mountains northeast of Cape Town in Western Cape Province .
Vernonia nonoensis is a species of flowering plant in the Asteraceae family that is endemic to Ecuador .
Tetranychus urticae ( common names include red spider mite and two - spotted spider mite ) is a species of plant - feeding mite that is generally considered a pest .
Octomeria rodeiensis is a species of orchid endemic to southeastern Brazil and Ecuador .
The common sanddragon ( Progomphus obscurus ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Gomphidae , found in eastern United States and southern Ontario .
Fossil remains of the species Chulsanbaatar vulgaris have been found in strata dating to the Campanian ( Upper Cretaceous ) in the Red Beds of Hermiin Tsav ( also known as Khermeen Tsav , part of the Barun Goyot Formation ) in Mongolia .
Gagata pakistanica is a species of sisorid catfish which is probably endemic to Pakistan .
Erigeron aureus ( Alpine yellow fleabane ) is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family , native to the Cascades and Rocky Mountains of northwestern North America ( Alberta , British Columbia , Washington ) .
Gnaphosa occidentalis is a ground spider species found in Western Europe .
Goniobranchus galactos is a species of colourful sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Chromodorididae .
Astele ciliaris , common name the keeled Australian top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Battarrea phalloides is an inedible species of mushroom in the family Agaricaceae , and the type species of the genus Battarrea .
Africallagma sapphirinum , the sapphire bluet is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Semljicola caliginosus is a spider species found in England , Scotland and Russia .
Cynoglossus puncticeps , commonly known as the Speckled tonguesole is a species of tonguefish .
Aphyllorchis , commonly pauper orchids , is a genus of 30 species of terrestrial leafless orchidnative to a region extending from India east to China and Japan , south to Indonesia , New Guinea and Queensland .

Galeomma is a genus of African flowering plants in the sunflower family .
The Parazenidae , the parazens , are a family of zeiform fishes found in the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans .
Galium rotundifolium is a plant species of the Rubiaceae .
The Philopteridae are a family of Ischnocera , chewing lice mostly parasitic on birds .
Aepycamelus is an extinct genus of camelid , formerly called Alticamelus , which lived during the Miocene 20.6 - -4.9 million years ago , existing for about 15.7 million years .
The New Zealand owlet - nightjar ( Aegotheles novazelandiae ) was a large species of owlet - nightjar ( family Aegothelidae ) formerly endemic to the islands of New Zealand .
Homotherini is an extinct tribe of carnivoran mammals of the family Felidae ( true cats ) .
Raiamas kheeli is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Raiamas .

Trichopeza is a genus of empidoid flies .

Penicillium corylophilum is a species of the genus of Penicillium which occurs in damp buildings in USA , Canada and western Europe but it can also be found in a variety of foods and mosquitoes .
Stichorkis is a genus of orchids native to the Indian Subcontinent , Southeast Asia , New Guinea , and various islands of the Pacific and Indian Oceans .
Baccharis plummerae is a California species of Baccharis known by the common name Plummer 's baccharis .
Streptomyces albidoflavus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from Poland .
Geum geniculatum is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name bent avens .
Stethacanthidae is an extinct family of prehistoric sharks .
Viola cryana , the Cry violet , also known as Cry pansy , is an extinct plant species from the violet genus Viola which was endemic to the French Department Yonne .
Papaver radicatum is a species of poppy known by the common names Arctic poppy , rooted poppy , and yellow poppy .
Paregaploa conviva is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Paregaploa .
Euowenia is an extinct genus of Diprotodontia from the Pliocene .
Eledone gaucha is a species of octopus from the southern Atlantic Ocean .
Eutetramorium is a small genus of ants within the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Plaxhaplous was a genus of glyptodont , an extinct relative of the modern armadillo .
Changchengornis is an extinct basal bird genus from the Early Cretaceous .
Tacheocampylaea tacheoides is a species of air - breathing , land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicidae , the typical snails .
Leersia oryzoides is a species of grass known by the common name rice cutgrass or just cut - grass .
Hapalogaster cavicauda is a species of king crab that lives on the Pacific coast of North America .

Phaeoceros is a genus of hornworts in the family Notothyladaceae .

Dasiosoma testaceum is a species of brown coloured ground beetle in the Lebiinae subfamily that is endemic to Zimbabwe .
Amaranthus retroflexus is a species of flowering plant in the Amaranthaceae family with several common names , including red - root amaranth , redroot pigweed , red - rooted pigweed , common amaranth , pigweed amaranth , and common tumbleweed .
Spermodea lamellata is a species of minute European land snail , a terrestrial gastropod mollusc , or micromollusc , in the family Valloniidae .
Exidiopsis macroacantha is a species of fungus in the family Auriculariaceae .
Chromidotilapia is a genus of cichlid fishes .

Thecophora atra is a species of small fly in the family Conopidae subfamily Myopinae .
Chrysoblephus laticeps ( ' golden - eyed broad head ' ) , also known as the Red Roman or Roman seabream , is a species of sea bream from southern African , ranging from Namibia to the Eastern Cape .
Macrodipteryx was a genus of African nightjars consisting of two species : the pennant - winged nightjar and the standard - winged nightjar .

Retispatha is a rare , monotypic genus of flowering plant in the palm family endemic to Borneo , where the sole species , Retispatha dumetosa , is known as wi tebu bruang ( dialectial : wi tebi bagadap ) or `` the bear 's sugar cane '' .
Ratsirakia legendrei is a species of sleeper goby endemic to fresh waters of Madagascar .

Ptericoptomimus truncatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Ptericoptomimus .
Geosesarma is genus of small freshwater or terrestrial crabs , typically less than 10 millimetres ( 0.4 in ) across the carapace .
Isognomon radiatus , Lister 's tree oyster or the radial purse oyster , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Pteriidae .
Semperdon uncatus is a species of small , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Charopidae .
Gagea dubia is a Mediterranean species of plants in the lily family .
McCord 's box turtle ( Cuora mccordi ) is a species of the southeast Asian genus Cuora ( family Geoemydidae ) .
Biseridens is the most basal genus of anomodont therapsid .
Neolamprologus falcicula is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is only known from the waters off of Burundi .
Buccochromis is a genus of haplochromine cichlids endemic to East Africa .
Alepidomus evermanni is a species of silverside endemic to western Cuba .
Calliclinus is a genus of labrisomid blennies native to the Pacific and Atlantic coasts of southern South America .
Hedleyella falconeri , the giant panda snail , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Caryodidae .
Nanorana blanfordii ( common names : Blanford 's paa frog , Blanford 's frog , Blanford 's spiny frog ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Sphaeromatidea is a suborder of isopod crustaceans , comprising the following superfamilies and families :
Tetanola polita is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Tetanola .
Phylloporus veluticeps is a species of fungus in the Boletaceae family .
Mescalerolemur ( meaning `` Mescalero Apache 's lemur '' ) is an extinct genus of adapiform strepsirrhine from late Middle Eocene ( Uintan age ) deposits of Brewster County , Texas .
Litargosuchus ( `` fast running crocodile '' ) is an extinct genus of sphenosuchian crocodylomorph from the Early Jurassic of South Africa .
Elysia clarki is a species of sacoglossan sea slug , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Plakobranchidae .
Samaipaticereus corroanus is a species of cactus and the sole species of the genus Samaipaticereus .
Acmispon americanus , known by the common names American bird's - foot trefoil and Spanish clover , is a species of legume native to most habitats of California , the Western United States , Western Canada , and northern Mexico .
Posidonia oceanica ( commonly known as Neptune Grass or Mediterranean tapeweed ) is a seagrass species that is endemic to the Mediterranean Sea .
Eua zebrina is a species of tropical air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Partulidae .
Ipomopsis sancti - spiritus is a rare species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name Holy Ghost ipomopsis .
Lupinus constancei is a species of lupine known by the common name The Lassics lupine , or lassicus lupine .
Mauisaurus ( `` Maui reptile '' ) is a genus of plesiosaur that lived during the Late Cretaceous period around 80 to 69 million years ago in what is now New Zealand .
Emblemaria culmenis , the Ridge blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny known from a single specimen collected in Venezuela , in the western central Atlantic ocean .
Neotropical bellbird ( or simply bellbird ) is the common name given to passerine birds of the genus Procnias , found in the Neotropics .
Cypraeovula iutsui is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Amblyodipsas polylepis , or the common purple - glossed snake , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Drosera peltata , commonly called the shield sundew or pale sundew , is a climbing or scrambling perennial tuberous species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera .
Dendrobium senile , commonly known as the White - haired Dendrobium or Old Man Orchid , is a species of flowering plant in the Orchidaceae family .
Brachyurophis is a genus of elapid snakes known as shovel - nosed snakes , so named because of their shovel - nosed snout which is used to burrow .
Ceramida malacensis is a species of beetle in the Melolonthinae subfamily .
Parvicursor ( meaning `` small runner '' ) is a genus of tiny maniraptoran dinosaur with long slender legs for fast running .
Betta channoides is a species of gourami endemic to the island of Borneo , where it is only found in the province of Kalimantan Timur .
The Cylindrotominae or long - bodied craneflies are a subfamily of crane flies .
After extensive musical education , Karel Berman started his career as a bass singer of opera in Opava .
Benedikt Schack ( Czech : Benedikt Žák ) ( 7 February 1758 -- 10 December 1826 ) was a composer and tenor of the Classical era , a close friend of Mozart and the first performer ( 30.10.1791 ) of the role of Tamino in Mozart 's opera The Magic Flute .
Maria Vitale ( 1924 - 1984 ) was an Italian operatic soprano , particularly associated with the Italian repertory .
Lucine Amara ( born March 1 , 1924 ) is an American soprano who was largely based at the Metropolitan Opera in New York .
Luis Ernesto Alva y Talledo , better known as Luigi Alva ( born 10 April 1927 ) is a Peruvian operatic tenor , active in the second half of the 20th century .
Simone Kermes ( born 17 May 1970 ) is a German coloratura soprano , especially known for her virtuoso voice , suited to the opera seria genre of the Baroque and early Classical period .
Els Bongers is a Dutch soprano singer active in concert , opera and musical theatre .
Berlian Hutauruk ( born Jakarta , 11 October 1957 ) is an Indonesian soprano of Batak descent .
Cornell MacNeil ( September 24 , 1922 -- July 15 , 2011 ) was an American operatic baritone known for his exceptional voice and long career with the Metropolitan Opera , which spanned 642 performances in twenty - six roles .
Kristinn Sigmundsson ( born 1 March 1951 ) is an Icelandic bass who for the past 20 years has been one of Iceland 's best known international opera singers .
Art Lund ( April 1 , 1915 in Salt Lake City , Utah -- May 31 , 1990 in Holladay , Utah ) was an American baritone singer , initially with bandleaders Benny Goodman and Harry James , and was also a television and stage actor .
Joni Henson ( born May 31 , 1977 ) is a Canadian operatic soprano who was born and raised in Sault Ste . Marie , Ontario .
Fanie de Jager ( born 8 April 1949 ) is a South African operatic tenor and singer of light classical music .
Henriette Méric - Lalande ( 1798 -- 7 September 1867 ) was a French operatic soprano , one of the leading sopranos of the early 19th century .
Elena D'Angri ( also known as Elena Angri ) ( May 1821 or 1824 in Corfu -- 1886 in Barcelona ) was a Greek - born operatic contralto of Italian origin who was active in the mid-19th century in European opera houses and in the United States .
Ayşe Leyla Gencer ( Turkish pronunciation : ( lejˈla ɟenˈdʒeɾ ) ) née Çeyrekgil ( 10 October 1928 -- 10 May 2008 ) was a Turkish operatic soprano .
Paul Esswood ( born 6 June 1942 ) is an English countertenor and conductor .
Marcella Craft ( 1874 - -1959 ) was an American operatic soprano who performed internationally in the late 19th century and early 20th century .
La Julia Rhea ( March 16 , 1898 -- July 5 , 1992 ) was an African American operatic soprano , and a pioneering figure in the world of music in the United States .
Giorgio Ronconi ( 6 August 1810 - 8 January 1890 ) was an Italian operatic baritone celebrated for his brilliant acting and compelling stage presence .
Maryann Mootos is an American operatic soprano from Boston , Massachusetts .
Klaus Mertens ( born 25 March 1949 in Kleve ) is a German bass and bass - baritone singer who is known especially for his interpretation of the complete works of Johann Sebastian Bach for bass voice .
Sylvia Stahlman ( March 5 , 1929 -- August 19 , 1998 ) was an American soprano , particularly associated with light , coloratura roles .
Marcel Merkès ( July 7 , 1920 -- March 30 , 2007 ) , was a French tenor operetta singer .
Anna Kaufmann was a German operatic soprano who was a principal artist at the Bavarian State Opera in Munich from 1869 to 1872 .
Matthew Polenzani ( born 1968 ) is an American lyric tenor .
Dawn Kotoski ( born 1966 ) is an American operatic soprano who has a substantial international opera career .
Kurt Böhme ( 5 May 1908 -- 20 December 1989 ) was a German bass .
Theodore Ritch ( 1894 in Odessa -- 1943 ) was a Russian tenor .
Léon Rothier ( December 26 , 1874 -- December 6 , 1951 ) was a French operatic bass who enjoyed a long association with New York 's Metropolitan Opera .
Maurício ( Moisés ) Bensaúde ( also known professionally as Maurizio Bensaude ) ( 13 February 1863 in Ponta Delgada -- 22 December 1912 in Lisbon ) , was a Portuguese operatic baritone .
Burak Bilgili is a Turkish operatic bass - baritone who was born in Akşehir , a town in the Konya Province of Turkey .
Lizzie Graham ( 1844 - 1927 ) was a late nineteenth - century Puerto Rican soprano singer from Ponce , Puerto Rico .
Marcella Detroit ( born Marcella Levy , June 21 , 1952 ) is an American soprano vocalist ( perhaps best known for her backup singing on many Top 20 Billboard hits ) , guitarist , and songwriter .
Lisa Vroman ( born 1956 ) is an American lyric soprano and stage actress .
Michael Schopper ( born 28 May 1942 ) is a German bass - baritone in opera and concert , and an academic teacher .
Grete Stückgold ( 1895 - -1977 ) was a soprano opera singer .
Salvatore Papaccio ( June 23 , 1890 -- December 24 , 1977 ) was a tenor and an exponent of Canzone Napoletana .
Philip Kraus ( born November 17 , 1950 ) is an American operatic baritone and stage director known for his performances with the Lyric Opera of Chicago , starting in 1991 , and for his co - founding of Light Opera Works , a professional light opera company in Chicago , in 1980 .
Marta Cunningham CBE ( December 1869 - June 25 , 1937 ) , was an American - born European - based soprano - singer and philanthropist .
Maria Cebotari ( 10 February 1910 -- 9 June 1949 ) was a celebrated Romanian soprano and actress , one of Europe 's greatest opera stars in the 1930s and 1940s .
Don Seabolt ( born July 30 , 1944 ) is an American singer and songwriter best known for singing tenor with the famed Blue Ridge Quartet from Spartanburg , South Carolina from 1971 - 1978 .
Jaroslava Maxová ( born 6 April 1957 ; Jaroslava Horská , Jaroslava Horská - Maxová ) is a Czech mezzo - soprano opera singer and vocal coach .
Patricia Petibon ( born 27 February 1970 ) is a French Ligera coloratura soprano acclaimed for her interpretations of French Baroque music .
Johannes Mannov ( born 1960 , Copenhagen , Denmark ) , a Danish baritone .
Richard Bruno Heydrich ( 23 February 1865 -- 24 August 1938 ) was a German opera singer ( tenor ) , and composer .
John Abell ( 1653 -- after 1724 ) was a Scottish countertenor , composer and lutenist .
Greta Williams was a celebrated English operatic soprano and contralto , and occasional pianist of the Victorian era .
Marjana Lipovšek ( mezzo soprano ) is an opera and concert singer .
Diamante Maria Scarabelli was an Italian soprano singer of the later 17th century and the early 18th century .
Teddy Tahu Rhodes ( born 30 August 1966 ) is a New Zealand operatic baritone .
Konstantinos Paliatsaras is a Greek operatic tenor .
Gerald English ( born 6 November 1925 ) is an English tenor .
Lella Cuberli ( September 29 , 1945 ) is an American soprano , particularly associated with the Belcanto repertory .
Marta Beňačková ( 29 August 1953 , Bratislava ) is a Slovak mezzo - soprano who has had an active performing career since the 1970s in concerts , operas , and recitals .
Anja Kampe is a German - Italian operatic soprano , born 1968 in the GDR .
Elena Gerhardt ( 11 November 1883 -- 11 January 1961 ) was a German mezzo - soprano singer associated with the singing of German classical lieder , of which she was considered one of the great interpreters .
Frederick Dalberg ( 7 January 1907 -- 9 May 1988 ) was an English born South African opera bass .
Joyce DiDonato ( born February 13 , 1969 ) is an American operatic lyric - coloratura mezzo - soprano notable for her interpretations of the works of Handel , Mozart , and Rossini .
Mario Sereni ( March 25 , 1928 -- July 24 , 2015 ) was an Italian baritone , who sang leading roles at the New York Metropolitan Opera for many years .
Giuseppe Cremonini ( 25 November 1866 -- 9 May 1903 ) was an Italian operatic tenor who had a prominent opera career in Europe and the United States during the last decade of the nineteenth century .
Raymonde Delaunois ( 12 October 1885 - 30 June 1984 ) was a Belgian mezzo - soprano opera singer .
Nadezhda Petrenko is a Ukrainian soprano singer , working mostly in Prague .
Lori Lewis is an American opera singer and soprano currently residing in Salem , Oregon graduate in the University of Kansas , she was a vocalist and official member of the Swedish symphonic metal band Therion .
József Simándy ( born Kistarcsa , September 18 , 1916 -- died Budapest March 4 , 1997 ) was a Hungarian tenor with German origins .
Stephen Dickson ( 16 February 1951 -- 18 October 1991 ) was an American baritone who had an active career in operas and concerts from 1972 through 1990 .
Aaltje Noordewier - Reddingius ( born Aaltje Reddingius ; 1 September 1868 , Deurne -- 6 April 1949 , Hilversum ) was a noted Dutch classical soprano who had an active performance career in the concert repertoire from 1888 through the 1930s .
Arnold van Mill ( March 26 , 1921 in Schiedam -- October 5 , 1996 in Hamburg ) was a Dutch opera singer who specialised in bass .
Alessandro Polonini ( 1844 , Crema -- 1920 , Crema ) was an Italian bass - baritone .
Ailyn Pérez ( born 1979 ) is an American operatic soprano and the winner of the 2012 Richard Tucker Award .
Diana Montague ( born 8 April 1953 ) is a British mezzo - soprano known for her performances in opera and as a concert singer .
D'Anna Fortunato ( born in Pittsburgh , Pennsylvania , on February 21 , 1945 ) is a noted American mezzo - soprano .
Chalía Herrera , born Rosalía Gertrudis de la Concepción Díaz de Herrera y de Fonseca ( 17 November 1864 , in Havana -- 16 November 1948 ) , was a Cuban soprano .
Damien Top ( born 13 July 1963 in Rouen ) is a French tenor , musicologist and conductor , and is artistic director of the International Albert Roussel Festival .
David Devriès ( born February 14 , 1881 in Bagnères - de - Luchon , France , died July 17 , 1936 in Neuilly - sur - Seine , France ) was a French operatic lyric tenor noted for his light , heady tone , and polished phrasing .
Dai Yuqiang ( 戴玉强 ; Langfang , 1963 ) is a Chinese operatic tenor .
Leone Giraldoni ( born circa 1824 , Paris ; died 19 September 1897 , Moscow ) was a celebrated Italian operatic baritone .
Robert Dean Smith ( born 2 May 1956 in Kansas ) is an American operatic tenor .
Francesco Maria Bonini ( 1865 -- 11 January 1930 ) was an Italian baritone who had a major international opera career from 1896 through 1927 .
Carlo Colombara ( born 1964 in Bologna , Italy ) is an Italian operatic bass .
Claudia Eder ( born 7 February 1948 ) is a German mezzo - soprano in opera and concert , and an academic in Mainz .
Karel Kalaš ( 9 October 1910 -- 3 May 2001 ) was a Czech operatic bass and film and television actor .
Natalie Coyle is a London - based , classically trained soprano .
Édouard de Reszke , originally Edward , ( 22 December 1853 -- 25 May 1917 ) was a Polish bass from Warsaw .
Růžena Maturová ( 2 September 1869 -- 25 February 1938 ) was a Czech operatic soprano whose international career began in the late 1880s and continued through the first decade of the 20th century .
